WEBVTT

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:19.260
Scholastic audio presents Wings of Fire.

00:00:19.320 --> 00:00:23.579
Book 12, The Hive Queen, by 2ET

00:00:23.579 --> 00:00:24.179
Sutherland.

00:00:24.239 --> 00:00:27.000
Read by Shannon McManus.

00:00:51.060 --> 00:00:53.520
The Lost Continent Prophecy.

00:00:53.640 --> 00:00:59.219
Turn your eyes, your wings, your fire, to

00:00:59.219 --> 00:01:00.420
the land across the sea.

00:01:00.539 --> 00:01:04.500
Where dragons are poisoned, and dragons

00:01:04.500 --> 00:01:07.560
are dying, and no one can ever be free.

00:01:07.620 --> 00:01:11.280
A secret lurks inside their eggs.

00:01:11.340 --> 00:01:13.980
A secret hides within their book.

00:01:14.040 --> 00:01:18.900
A secret buried far below May save those

00:01:18.900 --> 00:01:20.700
brave enough to look.

00:01:20.760 --> 00:01:24.719
Open your hearts, your mind, your wings

00:01:24.719 --> 00:01:26.879
to the dragons who flee from the hive.

00:01:26.939 --> 00:01:32.280
Face a great evil with talent united, or

00:01:32.280 --> 00:01:33.840
none of the tribes will survive.

00:01:45.959 --> 00:01:52.200
Prologue.

00:01:52.319 --> 00:01:57.000
The ocean swept across Moon's claws, as

00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:59.159
dark and speckled with stars as our own

00:01:59.159 --> 00:01:59.519
scales.

00:01:59.579 --> 00:02:02.579
She'd always thought of the sea as the

00:02:02.579 --> 00:02:03.239
edge of the world.

00:02:03.359 --> 00:02:06.000
Once you got there, that was it.

00:02:06.060 --> 00:02:07.799
You couldn't go any farther.

00:02:07.920 --> 00:02:10.740
But now she knew that wasn't true.

00:02:10.800 --> 00:02:13.740
A dragon had been blown ashore.

00:02:13.800 --> 00:02:15.900
All the way from across the ocean.

00:02:15.960 --> 00:02:19.680
A dragon from a tribe nobody in Pyria had

00:02:19.680 --> 00:02:20.219
ever seen before.

00:02:20.280 --> 00:02:24.000
A dragon with 4 wings instead of two.

00:02:24.060 --> 00:02:27.659
A dragon with long furling antennae, and

00:02:27.659 --> 00:02:30.659
scales like sliced gems, and the ability

00:02:30.659 --> 00:02:32.520
to spin silk that burned.

00:02:32.639 --> 00:02:36.360
Luna was proof that there was a continent

00:02:36.360 --> 00:02:39.120
far on the other side of the sea, filled

00:02:39.120 --> 00:02:40.259
with strange dragons.

00:02:40.319 --> 00:02:43.860
Dragons who need my help, she says.

00:02:43.919 --> 00:02:45.960
Moon shivered.

00:02:46.080 --> 00:02:47.460
That couldn't be right.

00:02:47.520 --> 00:02:50.280
They didn't need her of all dragons.

00:02:50.400 --> 00:02:54.000
It was Moon's fault. that Dark Stalker

00:02:54.000 --> 00:02:55.919
had nearly taken over all of Pyria.

00:02:56.039 --> 00:02:59.280
Her fault that he'd killed so many ice

00:02:59.280 --> 00:03:01.379
wings, including their queen.

00:03:01.439 --> 00:03:05.159
She'd seen too much good in him, and not

00:03:05.159 --> 00:03:05.819
enough of the bad.

00:03:05.879 --> 00:03:08.879
It was too soon for her to trust another

00:03:08.879 --> 00:03:10.740
dragon with a story of persecution.

00:03:10.860 --> 00:03:13.800
She wanted to use her visions to help the

00:03:13.800 --> 00:03:14.099
world.

00:03:14.159 --> 00:03:17.280
But she was not ready to have the fate of

00:03:17.280 --> 00:03:19.080
any more tribes in her talons.

00:03:19.139 --> 00:03:22.919
But Luna wanted moon to save all the silk

00:03:22.919 --> 00:03:23.460
wings.

00:03:23.580 --> 00:03:25.979
Luna thought Moon was the 2nd coming of

00:03:25.979 --> 00:03:28.439
Clearsight, who was apparently the number

00:03:28.439 --> 00:03:31.139
one beloved ancient goddess of Pentala.

00:03:31.259 --> 00:03:33.300
So, no pressure there.

00:03:33.360 --> 00:03:36.000
She can tell us what's going to happen

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:39.659
next, Luna's brain saying, she can see

00:03:39.659 --> 00:03:41.039
everything the hive wings will do.

00:03:41.099 --> 00:03:44.039
She can predict Queen Wasp's next move

00:03:44.039 --> 00:03:45.900
and then the chrysalis will know how to

00:03:45.900 --> 00:03:46.620
stop her.

00:03:46.680 --> 00:03:48.659
It was like that all day long.

00:03:48.719 --> 00:03:52.439
Luna had extremely grand ideas of Moon's

00:03:52.439 --> 00:03:54.900
abilities, and shining dreams of how they

00:03:54.900 --> 00:03:55.680
would change everything.

00:03:55.740 --> 00:03:59.639
She was so wound up, in fact, about

00:03:59.639 --> 00:04:02.099
Moon's ability to see the future, that

00:04:02.099 --> 00:04:03.840
Moon hadn't quite found the courage yet

00:04:03.840 --> 00:04:06.000
to tell her she could also read minds.

00:04:06.060 --> 00:04:09.240
It was really awkward, hearing all of

00:04:09.240 --> 00:04:11.819
Luna's thoughts about her and Kibli and

00:04:11.819 --> 00:04:12.360
Jerboa.

00:04:12.419 --> 00:04:15.240
And honestly, it was getting more awkward

00:04:15.240 --> 00:04:17.459
every moment that Moon didn't tell her.

00:04:17.519 --> 00:04:21.239
If she'd had any extra Skyfire, she would

00:04:21.239 --> 00:04:23.219
have slipped it to Luna somehow to

00:04:23.219 --> 00:04:25.439
silence the pile up of expectations.

00:04:25.500 --> 00:04:27.420
But she didn't have any.

00:04:27.540 --> 00:04:29.639
So telling her wouldn't help much

00:04:29.639 --> 00:04:30.000
anyway.

00:04:30.060 --> 00:04:31.980
I should, though.

00:04:32.040 --> 00:04:33.420
It's wrong not to.

00:04:33.540 --> 00:04:35.639
Moonside.

00:04:35.759 --> 00:04:40.079
She sang the future right now, came a

00:04:40.079 --> 00:04:42.360
thought, loud and clear from right behind

00:04:42.360 --> 00:04:42.660
her.

00:04:42.779 --> 00:04:46.019
Moon winced, and turned around to find

00:04:46.019 --> 00:04:49.139
Luna bounding over the sand, well, trying

00:04:49.139 --> 00:04:50.279
to bound over the sand.

00:04:50.339 --> 00:04:52.740
The sand had a way of sinking out

00:04:52.740 --> 00:04:55.439
suddenly from under one's talons, so it

00:04:55.439 --> 00:04:56.759
was impossible to get any sort of

00:04:56.759 --> 00:04:57.660
bounding rhythm.

00:04:57.720 --> 00:05:00.720
Those were partly Luna's thoughts.

00:05:00.779 --> 00:05:03.480
Moon sometimes got tangled up with them

00:05:03.480 --> 00:05:04.800
when they were too close to her own.

00:05:04.860 --> 00:05:08.160
She wasn't sure why, but there was

00:05:08.160 --> 00:05:10.199
something more entangling about Luna's

00:05:10.199 --> 00:05:11.399
mind than other dragons.

00:05:11.519 --> 00:05:13.500
Why are you out here by yourself?

00:05:13.560 --> 00:05:16.740
Una asked, settling next to moon in a

00:05:16.740 --> 00:05:17.459
spray of sand.

00:05:17.519 --> 00:05:20.579
I like to look at the moons sometimes

00:05:20.579 --> 00:05:23.100
Moon answered, and then laughed.

00:05:23.160 --> 00:05:25.139
That's my whole name, actually.

00:05:25.199 --> 00:05:27.120
Moon watcher.

00:05:27.240 --> 00:05:30.120
My name means moon in the old language.

00:05:30.180 --> 00:05:30.899
Did you know that?

00:05:30.959 --> 00:05:32.040
Luna asked.

00:05:32.100 --> 00:05:34.379
Now it's a kind of moth.

00:05:34.439 --> 00:05:37.259
She dug a tiny hole in the sand in front

00:05:37.259 --> 00:05:39.300
of her. and dropped a thread of flame

00:05:39.300 --> 00:05:39.959
silk into it.

00:05:40.019 --> 00:05:42.660
The glow warmed moon's talons.

00:05:42.720 --> 00:05:44.639
I didn't know that.

00:05:44.699 --> 00:05:47.579
Moon said, but she liked hearing it.

00:05:47.639 --> 00:05:50.339
It made her feel a little closer to Luna

00:05:50.339 --> 00:05:52.740
who could be a bit intense sometimes

00:05:52.740 --> 00:05:55.259
What's the old language?

00:05:55.379 --> 00:05:57.540
Luna shrugged.

00:05:57.600 --> 00:05:58.680
I don't know.

00:05:58.740 --> 00:06:01.319
The language everyone spoke in Pantala

00:06:01.319 --> 00:06:02.579
before Claire's side arrived.

00:06:02.639 --> 00:06:05.699
Clearsight, changed your language?

00:06:05.819 --> 00:06:07.860
Moon said, surprised.

00:06:07.980 --> 00:06:09.540
I think so.

00:06:09.600 --> 00:06:12.540
I heard a story once anyway, that we all

00:06:12.540 --> 00:06:13.620
speak dragon because of her.

00:06:13.680 --> 00:06:17.100
That explained why the Pentalons and

00:06:17.100 --> 00:06:18.959
Pyreans could understand each other.

00:06:19.019 --> 00:06:21.180
But Moon was still puzzled.

00:06:21.240 --> 00:06:24.060
Why didn't Clearsight learn their

00:06:24.060 --> 00:06:24.660
language instead?

00:06:24.779 --> 00:06:28.319
Maybe she foresaw that we'd need to

00:06:28.319 --> 00:06:29.699
communicate with each other one day.

00:06:29.759 --> 00:06:32.639
Or maybe she just hoped for it.

00:06:32.699 --> 00:06:35.100
Are you having a vision?

00:06:35.160 --> 00:06:37.019
Luna asked hopefully.

00:06:37.079 --> 00:06:39.720
No, Moon said.

00:06:39.779 --> 00:06:40.620
Sorry.

00:06:40.680 --> 00:06:42.600
No, nothing yet.

00:06:42.660 --> 00:06:46.740
Luna's wings slid down into the sand, and

00:06:46.740 --> 00:06:49.019
she picked up a seashell, fiddling with

00:06:49.019 --> 00:06:50.519
it as though focusing on it would keep

00:06:50.519 --> 00:06:51.120
her from crying.

00:06:51.240 --> 00:06:54.540
I am really sorry, Luna.

00:06:54.600 --> 00:06:55.680
Moon said.

00:06:55.740 --> 00:06:57.600
I don't know how to get you back to

00:06:57.600 --> 00:06:58.439
Pantala.

00:06:58.500 --> 00:07:00.540
Nothing in my visions has shown me that.

00:07:00.600 --> 00:07:04.079
I'm worried about my little brother, Luna

00:07:04.079 --> 00:07:06.360
said, throwing the seashell into the

00:07:06.360 --> 00:07:06.600
ocean.

00:07:06.720 --> 00:07:08.579
And sore tail.

00:07:08.639 --> 00:07:10.620
He must be losing his mind.

00:07:10.680 --> 00:07:13.379
Kibley will think of something.

00:07:13.439 --> 00:07:14.639
Moon said.

00:07:14.699 --> 00:07:15.959
He usually does.

00:07:16.079 --> 00:07:18.060
She hesitated.

00:07:18.120 --> 00:07:19.560
Luna.

00:07:19.620 --> 00:07:21.660
I don't know if it's a good idea to tell

00:07:21.660 --> 00:07:23.759
you this, but I've been hearing a

00:07:23.759 --> 00:07:24.779
prophecy in my head.

00:07:24.839 --> 00:07:27.480
A prophecy?

00:07:27.540 --> 00:07:28.800
Luna echoed.

00:07:28.920 --> 00:07:32.040
It started with my vision of you, in

00:07:32.040 --> 00:07:33.060
Jerboa's hut.

00:07:33.180 --> 00:07:36.060
I could hear a few words, and now

00:07:36.060 --> 00:07:38.459
whenever I'm with you, it gets clearer

00:07:38.459 --> 00:07:40.620
and clearer, I don't completely

00:07:40.620 --> 00:07:43.379
understand it, and I'm afraid it might

00:07:43.379 --> 00:07:43.980
scare you.

00:07:44.040 --> 00:07:47.939
I'm not easily scared, Luna said.

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:49.259
Please tell me.

00:07:49.379 --> 00:07:53.279
Moon sensed movement behind her, and then

00:07:53.279 --> 00:07:55.379
a few stray grumbling thoughts in a voice

00:07:55.379 --> 00:07:56.279
she recognized.

00:07:56.399 --> 00:07:58.860
Kibley had returned successful then.

00:07:58.920 --> 00:08:02.399
Well, he could hear this, and so could

00:08:02.399 --> 00:08:03.420
the 2 dragons with him.

00:08:03.480 --> 00:08:06.480
She took Luna's talents between her own

00:08:06.480 --> 00:08:09.420
closed her eyes, and let her mind clear

00:08:09.420 --> 00:08:11.879
so the words of the prophecy could flow

00:08:11.879 --> 00:08:12.180
through her.

00:08:12.240 --> 00:08:14.699
She did not love this bit.

00:08:14.759 --> 00:08:18.060
Cryptic rhyming prophecies were not as

00:08:18.060 --> 00:08:20.579
useful as visions, in her opinion, and

00:08:20.579 --> 00:08:21.959
the last one had gone to a pretty

00:08:21.959 --> 00:08:23.220
terrifying place.

00:08:23.279 --> 00:08:26.339
But the last one had also saved her and

00:08:26.339 --> 00:08:28.379
her friends, so she couldn't ignore

00:08:28.379 --> 00:08:28.560
them.

00:08:28.620 --> 00:08:33.480
Turn your eyes, your wings, your fire, she

00:08:33.480 --> 00:08:33.960
whispered.

00:08:34.019 --> 00:08:36.000
To the land across the sea.

00:08:36.120 --> 00:08:39.240
She felt Loon as it shiver all through

00:08:39.240 --> 00:08:40.019
her own scales.

00:08:40.080 --> 00:08:43.980
Where dragons are poisoned, and dragons

00:08:43.980 --> 00:08:46.559
are dying, and no one can ever be free.

00:08:46.679 --> 00:08:49.860
A secret lurks inside their eggs.

00:08:49.980 --> 00:08:52.919
A secret hides within their book, a

00:08:52.919 --> 00:08:56.100
secret buried far below, may save those

00:08:56.100 --> 00:08:57.360
brave enough to look.

00:08:57.360 --> 00:09:01.500
Open your hearts, your minds, your wings

00:09:01.500 --> 00:09:03.480
to the dragons who flee from the hive

00:09:03.480 --> 00:09:07.500
face a great evil with talent united, or

00:09:07.500 --> 00:09:09.240
none of the tribes will survive.

00:09:09.299 --> 00:09:11.100
Silence fell.

00:09:11.159 --> 00:09:13.860
Moon took a few deep breaths.

00:09:13.919 --> 00:09:18.059
I know this secret in the book, Luna said

00:09:18.059 --> 00:09:18.539
thoughtfully.

00:09:18.600 --> 00:09:21.000
But what's the secret in the eggs?

00:09:21.120 --> 00:09:23.039
And the buried one?

00:09:23.159 --> 00:09:25.919
Maybe that's the flame silks.

00:09:26.039 --> 00:09:28.080
No one can ever be free.

00:09:28.139 --> 00:09:29.279
That's definitely true.

00:09:29.340 --> 00:09:31.559
A great evil.

00:09:31.620 --> 00:09:32.820
Hmm.

00:09:32.940 --> 00:09:36.179
Maybe the hive wings are the great evil?

00:09:36.299 --> 00:09:41.159
Yeesh, Kidley said. coming up and nudging

00:09:41.159 --> 00:09:42.480
one of Moon's wings with his.

00:09:42.539 --> 00:09:45.659
Didn't we just face a great evil?

00:09:45.720 --> 00:09:48.179
That should count, I say. if anyone asks

00:09:48.179 --> 00:09:48.419
me.

00:09:48.480 --> 00:09:51.000
Great evil, faced, done.

00:09:51.059 --> 00:09:52.440
Take it off the to-do list.

00:09:52.559 --> 00:09:55.379
She opened her eyes and smiled at him.

00:09:55.500 --> 00:09:58.080
Sounds like a new great evil.

00:09:58.200 --> 00:10:00.779
Their friend Turtles said nervously from

00:10:00.779 --> 00:10:01.320
beside him.

00:10:01.379 --> 00:10:04.379
Can I vote no on any more great evils in

00:10:04.379 --> 00:10:04.980
our lifetime?

00:10:05.100 --> 00:10:07.679
Hey, turtle, Moon said.

00:10:07.740 --> 00:10:09.059
Hey, tsunami.

00:10:09.120 --> 00:10:12.240
The tall blue sea wing founder of Jade

00:10:12.240 --> 00:10:14.460
Mountain Academy gave her an exasperated

00:10:14.460 --> 00:10:14.700
face.

00:10:14.820 --> 00:10:17.039
Moon, she said.

00:10:17.100 --> 00:10:19.620
I feel like I was really clear about not

00:10:19.620 --> 00:10:21.299
having anything to do with any more

00:10:21.299 --> 00:10:22.139
prophecies.

00:10:22.200 --> 00:10:25.259
They just happened to me, Moon

00:10:25.259 --> 00:10:25.980
protested.

00:10:26.039 --> 00:10:26.879
I'm sorry.

00:10:26.940 --> 00:10:28.919
Moon?

00:10:28.980 --> 00:10:31.259
Luna whispered, poking her

00:10:31.259 --> 00:10:32.460
surreptitiously with her tail.

00:10:32.580 --> 00:10:35.340
Who are these dragons?

00:10:35.460 --> 00:10:39.059
Oh, sorry, of course, Moon said.

00:10:39.120 --> 00:10:41.879
Luna, this is our friend Hurtle and his

00:10:41.879 --> 00:10:42.840
sister Tsunami.

00:10:42.899 --> 00:10:44.399
They're from the Sea Wing tribe.

00:10:44.460 --> 00:10:46.620
Thank you for going to get them, Kibli.

00:10:46.679 --> 00:10:51.539
Well, I thought that maybe turtle here

00:10:51.539 --> 00:10:55.620
could make us something, Kibley said

00:10:55.620 --> 00:10:59.100
carefully, which would perhaps take us

00:10:59.100 --> 00:11:02.159
across the ocean so that Luna can get

00:11:02.159 --> 00:11:02.340
home.

00:11:02.399 --> 00:11:07.259
Oh, Luna said, squinting at turtle.

00:11:07.379 --> 00:11:09.419
Like my silk sail?

00:11:09.539 --> 00:11:14.279
But one we can steer, or something like

00:11:14.279 --> 00:11:15.899
that, Moon said.

00:11:15.960 --> 00:11:18.779
She and Kibley had agreed that they

00:11:18.779 --> 00:11:20.820
should wait to tell Luna about animus

00:11:20.820 --> 00:11:21.179
magic.

00:11:21.240 --> 00:11:24.600
If she got this excited and full of

00:11:24.600 --> 00:11:27.120
glorious vengeful plans over Moon's

00:11:27.120 --> 00:11:29.460
future seeing, Goodness knows how she

00:11:29.460 --> 00:11:31.740
would feel about real magic. and all the

00:11:31.740 --> 00:11:33.360
things it could do to her enemy tribe.

00:11:33.419 --> 00:11:36.240
Things we can't let her do.

00:11:36.299 --> 00:11:38.460
Kibli and Moon agreed.

00:11:38.519 --> 00:11:41.399
Animus magic was too dangerous.

00:11:41.519 --> 00:11:45.179
But something made by animus magic that

00:11:45.179 --> 00:11:46.620
could get her home.

00:11:46.679 --> 00:11:47.700
That wouldn't hurt anyone.

00:11:47.759 --> 00:11:51.000
Kimberley had offered to ask Turtle if

00:11:51.000 --> 00:11:51.840
he'd be willing to do that.

00:11:51.899 --> 00:11:54.960
Right, Turtle said.

00:11:55.080 --> 00:11:55.919
Make something.

00:11:55.980 --> 00:11:58.139
So here's the thing.

00:11:58.200 --> 00:11:59.039
I can't.

00:11:59.100 --> 00:12:02.039
Oh, Moon said.

00:12:02.100 --> 00:12:03.779
That's all right, Turtle.

00:12:03.840 --> 00:12:04.919
We understand.

00:12:04.980 --> 00:12:06.179
Your soul?

00:12:06.240 --> 00:12:09.419
No, no, Turtle said, looking worried.

00:12:09.480 --> 00:12:10.679
That's not it.

00:12:10.740 --> 00:12:14.639
I mean, I actually tried and I can't.

00:12:14.759 --> 00:12:18.480
Kibling made a face at Moon like, It's

00:12:18.480 --> 00:12:18.720
true.

00:12:18.779 --> 00:12:20.100
I have no idea why.

00:12:20.159 --> 00:12:22.620
Luna, Moon said.

00:12:22.679 --> 00:12:24.000
Can you give us a moment?

00:12:24.059 --> 00:12:25.440
Sure.

00:12:25.500 --> 00:12:28.980
The 4 winged dragon turned and trudged

00:12:28.980 --> 00:12:31.919
slowly back to Jaboa's hut, limping on

00:12:31.919 --> 00:12:32.879
her injured ankle.

00:12:32.940 --> 00:12:35.580
I knew I shouldn't have gotten my hopes

00:12:35.580 --> 00:12:35.759
up.

00:12:35.879 --> 00:12:39.779
Her mind thought sadly, and Moon felt

00:12:39.779 --> 00:12:40.679
awful for her.

00:12:40.740 --> 00:12:44.519
Poor lost dragon, tsunami said.

00:12:44.580 --> 00:12:46.799
It must be so weird for her to be here

00:12:46.799 --> 00:12:49.679
surrounded by strangers, with no way to

00:12:49.679 --> 00:12:50.039
get home.

00:12:50.100 --> 00:12:53.039
So, what's wrong, turtle?

00:12:53.159 --> 00:12:56.100
Moon asked, as soon as Luna was out of

00:12:56.100 --> 00:12:56.460
earshot.

00:12:56.519 --> 00:13:00.419
I don't know, Turtles said, flinging up

00:13:00.419 --> 00:13:03.539
his wings, I can't do any animus spells

00:13:03.539 --> 00:13:03.960
all of a sudden.

00:13:04.080 --> 00:13:06.179
I've tried all kinds of little things and

00:13:06.179 --> 00:13:07.379
nothing works.

00:13:07.500 --> 00:13:11.700
Three moons, she said. blinking in

00:13:11.700 --> 00:13:12.600
confusion and alarm.

00:13:12.659 --> 00:13:15.600
Here's the really weird part.

00:13:15.659 --> 00:13:17.879
I don't think anemone can either.

00:13:17.940 --> 00:13:18.960
He said.

00:13:19.019 --> 00:13:21.480
Right before Kibley came to get us.

00:13:21.539 --> 00:13:23.639
She was telling me about a spell she

00:13:23.639 --> 00:13:26.460
tried to restore Tamarin's site.

00:13:26.519 --> 00:13:28.440
I'd been thinking of trying one for

00:13:28.440 --> 00:13:30.960
Starflights, so we were comparing notes.

00:13:31.080 --> 00:13:34.320
But she said, it didn't work, and she

00:13:34.320 --> 00:13:35.100
couldn't figure out why.

00:13:35.159 --> 00:13:38.519
Turtle turned to give Kibli a severe

00:13:38.519 --> 00:13:38.700
look.

00:13:38.759 --> 00:13:43.379
I suspect, he said, that Kibley broke

00:13:43.379 --> 00:13:44.580
animus magic.

00:13:44.639 --> 00:13:46.440
Me?

00:13:46.559 --> 00:13:47.580
Kibley cried.

00:13:47.639 --> 00:13:48.659
What did I do?

00:13:48.779 --> 00:13:52.019
The soul spells, Turtle said.

00:13:52.080 --> 00:13:54.779
Remember how you carefully planned them

00:13:54.779 --> 00:13:57.720
out with us to protect our souls and make

00:13:57.720 --> 00:13:59.700
sure we can only do magic that doesn't

00:13:59.700 --> 00:14:01.500
affect another dragon's free will?

00:14:01.559 --> 00:14:05.399
And no magic that's selfishly motivated

00:14:05.399 --> 00:14:06.419
Kibley said.

00:14:06.539 --> 00:14:07.320
Right.

00:14:07.379 --> 00:14:09.539
We all agreed safeguards would be

00:14:09.539 --> 00:14:09.899
helpful.

00:14:09.960 --> 00:14:13.860
Except I think it ruled out everything

00:14:13.860 --> 00:14:15.240
Turtle said.

00:14:15.299 --> 00:14:18.240
Maybe everything we do could be

00:14:18.240 --> 00:14:21.360
considered selfishly motivated or affect

00:14:21.360 --> 00:14:23.460
someone's free will in some way.

00:14:23.460 --> 00:14:26.460
So now, none of our spells work.

00:14:26.519 --> 00:14:29.700
Oh my goodness, said Moon.

00:14:29.759 --> 00:14:34.259
That is, no, that's, that's ridiculous.

00:14:34.320 --> 00:14:35.940
Kibli protested.

00:14:36.000 --> 00:14:38.340
I did not break animus magic.

00:14:38.399 --> 00:14:42.600
I do not think I broke animus magic.

00:14:42.659 --> 00:14:43.980
That makes no.

00:14:44.820 --> 00:14:45.539
Let me think about this.

00:14:45.600 --> 00:14:48.600
Did you try taking off your soul spell

00:14:48.600 --> 00:14:50.639
objects to see if it would work without

00:14:50.639 --> 00:14:51.059
them?

00:14:51.120 --> 00:14:52.139
Moon asked.

00:14:52.200 --> 00:14:54.539
Anemone didn't want to.

00:14:54.659 --> 00:14:55.740
Turtle said.

00:14:55.799 --> 00:15:00.059
But I did, just to try a small spell, and

00:15:00.059 --> 00:15:01.019
it still didn't work.

00:15:01.080 --> 00:15:03.600
He pointed at Kibley.

00:15:03.659 --> 00:15:05.039
Broken.

00:15:05.100 --> 00:15:08.220
If it still didn't work without the sole

00:15:08.220 --> 00:15:11.519
spell, then it's not the sole spell

00:15:11.519 --> 00:15:15.240
Kibley said, and therefore, not me, who

00:15:15.240 --> 00:15:16.320
broke animus magic.

00:15:16.440 --> 00:15:20.159
It really feels like it is you, though

00:15:20.159 --> 00:15:21.240
Turtle said.

00:15:21.299 --> 00:15:24.779
Maybe something else is going on, Moon

00:15:24.779 --> 00:15:26.279
said. worried.

00:15:26.340 --> 00:15:29.460
Dark Stalker flashed through her mind

00:15:29.460 --> 00:15:32.580
making plans, tinkering with dragon's

00:15:32.580 --> 00:15:33.120
powers.

00:15:33.240 --> 00:15:34.799
She knew he was gone now.

00:15:34.860 --> 00:15:37.799
He'd been turned into a dragonette, with

00:15:37.799 --> 00:15:41.340
no powers, and no memory of his past, but

00:15:41.340 --> 00:15:42.899
sometimes, in her nightmares.

00:15:43.019 --> 00:15:45.179
He still managed to mess with her

00:15:45.179 --> 00:15:45.480
friends.

00:15:45.539 --> 00:15:48.960
What if someone else did this to you?

00:15:49.080 --> 00:15:53.220
Or left something behind that did this to

00:15:53.220 --> 00:15:53.460
you.

00:15:53.519 --> 00:15:55.500
Some kind of safeguard?

00:15:55.559 --> 00:15:58.019
He could have done that, couldn't he?

00:15:58.080 --> 00:16:01.379
So if he ever lost his powers, so would

00:16:01.379 --> 00:16:01.919
everyone else.

00:16:01.980 --> 00:16:05.100
There isn't anyone who could do that

00:16:05.100 --> 00:16:07.139
Kibley said gently.

00:16:07.200 --> 00:16:09.899
He'd had to wake her up from some of

00:16:09.899 --> 00:16:10.799
those nightmares.

00:16:10.860 --> 00:16:13.320
So he knew what she was thinking, as

00:16:13.320 --> 00:16:15.240
clearly as though he had mind reading

00:16:15.240 --> 00:16:15.899
abilities too.

00:16:15.960 --> 00:16:19.679
This is just a glitch, not a sinister

00:16:19.679 --> 00:16:19.980
plan.

00:16:20.039 --> 00:16:21.179
We'll fix it.

00:16:21.240 --> 00:16:23.580
What about Jerboa?

00:16:23.639 --> 00:16:24.840
Tsunami asked.

00:16:24.899 --> 00:16:26.159
Is her magic working?

00:16:26.220 --> 00:16:28.259
She's an animus dragon too, right?

00:16:28.320 --> 00:16:30.419
Sort of.

00:16:30.480 --> 00:16:32.940
But she's an animus dragon who won't

00:16:32.940 --> 00:16:33.659
touch her magic.

00:16:33.720 --> 00:16:34.980
Moon said.

00:16:35.039 --> 00:16:37.139
We can't ask her for help with this.

00:16:37.200 --> 00:16:41.100
Well, all right, then let's not.

00:16:41.159 --> 00:16:42.419
Tsunami said.

00:16:42.480 --> 00:16:45.299
You guys, we don't need animus magic.

00:16:45.360 --> 00:16:47.220
We don't?

00:16:47.340 --> 00:16:49.620
Turtle tipped his head up to look at our

00:16:49.620 --> 00:16:52.019
tsunami grin with all her teeth.

00:16:52.139 --> 00:16:55.080
My friends and I solved plenty of

00:16:55.080 --> 00:16:56.639
problems without animus magic.

00:16:56.700 --> 00:16:58.019
Thank you very much.

00:16:58.080 --> 00:17:02.340
It's called being resourceful, and smart

00:17:02.340 --> 00:17:05.579
and totally heroic, no prophecies

00:17:05.579 --> 00:17:05.940
required.

00:17:06.000 --> 00:17:08.759
All right, smarty McSquid.

00:17:08.880 --> 00:17:09.900
Turtle said.

00:17:09.960 --> 00:17:12.359
So how would you endure resourceful

00:17:12.359 --> 00:17:14.160
heroic friends solve this problem?

00:17:14.220 --> 00:17:18.059
Well, step one is, we need more

00:17:18.059 --> 00:17:18.779
information, right?

00:17:18.839 --> 00:17:22.199
Tsunami said, we want to go over there to

00:17:22.199 --> 00:17:24.599
see if Luna's stories are all true, to

00:17:24.599 --> 00:17:26.159
find out what's really going on, and

00:17:26.159 --> 00:17:27.179
whether we should get involved.

00:17:27.240 --> 00:17:30.480
I think she's telling the truth, from

00:17:30.480 --> 00:17:32.819
what I can see in her mind, Moon said.

00:17:32.880 --> 00:17:35.400
But it is hard to get a full picture of

00:17:35.400 --> 00:17:36.059
the situation.

00:17:36.119 --> 00:17:39.359
I wish we could go scout it out and see

00:17:39.359 --> 00:17:40.859
if there is a way we can help her.

00:17:40.920 --> 00:17:45.779
Maybe also what the great evil is, Kibley

00:17:45.779 --> 00:17:46.200
suggested.

00:17:46.259 --> 00:17:48.839
A heads up about that would be super.

00:17:48.900 --> 00:17:52.619
So, we need to get to the other continent

00:17:52.619 --> 00:17:53.880
tsunami said.

00:17:53.940 --> 00:17:56.339
We don't need a magic flying sail thing

00:17:56.339 --> 00:17:56.759
to do that.

00:17:56.819 --> 00:18:00.119
Oh, uh, Kibley said.

00:18:00.180 --> 00:18:02.940
Well, I mean, I did think of this.

00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:05.039
It's why I got you too specifically.

00:18:05.160 --> 00:18:07.440
Just so we're clear that I thought of

00:18:07.440 --> 00:18:07.799
this first.

00:18:07.859 --> 00:18:10.019
Thought of what?

00:18:10.140 --> 00:18:11.400
Turtle asked.

00:18:11.460 --> 00:18:14.460
To get to the lost continent turtle?

00:18:14.519 --> 00:18:16.920
Tsunami said, sweeping one wing out

00:18:16.920 --> 00:18:17.640
toward the ocean.

00:18:17.759 --> 00:18:21.119
All you and I have to do is swim there.

00:18:21.180 --> 00:18:25.319
Part one.

00:18:25.440 --> 00:18:27.180
The glittering hive.

00:18:27.240 --> 00:18:29.880
Chapter one.

00:18:29.940 --> 00:18:33.839
For most of her life, Crickets best

00:18:33.839 --> 00:18:34.740
friends were books.

00:18:34.799 --> 00:18:38.339
Books accepted you the way you were, and

00:18:38.339 --> 00:18:40.140
shared all their secrets with you.

00:18:40.200 --> 00:18:43.019
Books never told you to stop asking

00:18:43.019 --> 00:18:45.720
questions or accused you of being nosy

00:18:45.720 --> 00:18:46.319
and annoying.

00:18:46.380 --> 00:18:49.019
Books never said cricket.

00:18:49.079 --> 00:18:49.920
You don't need to know that.

00:18:49.980 --> 00:18:51.299
Mind your own business.

00:18:51.359 --> 00:18:55.380
In books, everything had an explanation.

00:18:55.440 --> 00:18:57.960
She especially liked nonfiction.

00:18:58.019 --> 00:19:00.420
Lots of facts and things had to make

00:19:00.420 --> 00:19:00.720
sense.

00:19:00.779 --> 00:19:03.779
If a question came up, eventually you got

00:19:03.779 --> 00:19:04.380
the answer.

00:19:04.440 --> 00:19:08.279
Every mystery was solved by the end. facts

00:19:08.279 --> 00:19:08.700
fit together.

00:19:08.759 --> 00:19:11.339
When you wanted something explained, there

00:19:11.339 --> 00:19:15.119
it was, with no whispering or cold stares

00:19:15.119 --> 00:19:16.680
or slammed doors.

00:19:16.740 --> 00:19:20.160
Another thing she liked about books was

00:19:20.160 --> 00:19:21.539
the fact that one of them had probably

00:19:21.539 --> 00:19:22.500
saved her life.

00:19:22.559 --> 00:19:26.039
It was a giant book called The

00:19:26.039 --> 00:19:28.259
Architecture of the Hives, expanded

00:19:28.259 --> 00:19:28.680
edition.

00:19:28.740 --> 00:19:31.740
Now, with sections on hydroponics and

00:19:31.740 --> 00:19:34.859
silk bridges, which technically belonged

00:19:34.859 --> 00:19:37.680
to her mother, and therefore, technically

00:19:37.680 --> 00:19:41.339
was off limits to tiny grubby dragonette

00:19:41.339 --> 00:19:42.000
talons.

00:19:42.059 --> 00:19:44.700
Which was why two-year-old cricket was

00:19:44.700 --> 00:19:46.019
hiding in a cupboard with it.

00:19:46.079 --> 00:19:48.539
The 1st time everyone lost their minds.

00:19:48.599 --> 00:19:52.740
Why is this book so in love with itself?

00:19:52.799 --> 00:19:54.660
Little cricket muttered.

00:19:54.720 --> 00:19:57.240
All she'd wanted to know is how to get

00:19:57.240 --> 00:19:59.579
from her home in Cicada hives to the

00:19:59.579 --> 00:20:01.980
Temple of Clearsight in wasp hives

00:20:01.980 --> 00:20:04.380
preferably in some clever, really fast

00:20:04.380 --> 00:20:06.539
way, where she could be home that same

00:20:06.539 --> 00:20:08.819
night, and nobody would notice she'd been

00:20:08.819 --> 00:20:09.059
gone.

00:20:09.119 --> 00:20:12.599
She just wanted to see it again, even if

00:20:12.599 --> 00:20:13.619
only for a moment.

00:20:13.680 --> 00:20:17.400
But every sentence in this book was miles

00:20:17.400 --> 00:20:18.000
too long.

00:20:18.059 --> 00:20:20.400
And the author kept repeating himself

00:20:20.400 --> 00:20:21.480
over and over.

00:20:21.539 --> 00:20:24.720
Not to mention the never ending rapturous

00:20:24.720 --> 00:20:27.720
paragraphs about every tiny curve and

00:20:27.720 --> 00:20:31.859
window and detail that exemplified Queen

00:20:31.859 --> 00:20:35.640
Wasps' exquisite mental quality, and I

00:20:35.640 --> 00:20:38.099
for visual balance, or some such

00:20:38.099 --> 00:20:38.579
nonsense.

00:20:38.640 --> 00:20:42.000
This is not a book of answers.

00:20:42.059 --> 00:20:44.519
Cricket grumbled, flipping ahead.

00:20:44.579 --> 00:20:46.619
This is a book of groveling.

00:20:46.680 --> 00:20:50.220
She paused on a full page drawing of wasp

00:20:50.220 --> 00:20:50.700
pives.

00:20:50.759 --> 00:20:54.119
The book was nearly as big as she was, so

00:20:54.119 --> 00:20:56.099
the artist had lots of space to draw the

00:20:56.099 --> 00:20:57.359
temple at the heart of the hive.

00:20:57.420 --> 00:21:01.079
She rested her chin on her talons, and

00:21:01.079 --> 00:21:03.779
stared dreamily at the perfect columns

00:21:03.779 --> 00:21:07.019
the perfect dome on the roof, the perfect

00:21:07.019 --> 00:21:10.380
library, and quiet pools all around the

00:21:10.380 --> 00:21:11.519
temple of Clearsight.

00:21:11.579 --> 00:21:15.180
She'd visited it for the 1st time only a

00:21:15.180 --> 00:21:17.880
few days earlier, when her sister, Katie

00:21:17.880 --> 00:21:20.160
did, took her as a treat for her 2nd

00:21:20.160 --> 00:21:20.519
birthday.

00:21:20.579 --> 00:21:23.640
It was the most beautiful place cricket

00:21:23.640 --> 00:21:24.480
had ever seen.

00:21:24.539 --> 00:21:28.140
Imagine being the librarian and living

00:21:28.140 --> 00:21:28.859
there forever.

00:21:28.920 --> 00:21:32.099
Imagine being in charge of the book of

00:21:32.099 --> 00:21:34.619
Clear Sight, the most important book in

00:21:34.619 --> 00:21:37.140
the world, and being one of the only 2

00:21:37.140 --> 00:21:39.180
dragons who ever got to read it.

00:21:39.240 --> 00:21:42.660
Now that was a book with answers.

00:21:42.720 --> 00:21:46.319
Hundreds of years ago, Clearsight had

00:21:46.319 --> 00:21:47.880
written down her prophecies of every

00:21:47.880 --> 00:21:49.680
important thing that would happen after

00:21:49.680 --> 00:21:52.680
her death, starting in her time and

00:21:52.680 --> 00:21:54.059
reaching far into the future.

00:21:54.119 --> 00:21:57.480
If cricket read it, she'd really know

00:21:57.480 --> 00:21:57.779
everything.

00:21:57.839 --> 00:22:00.720
Maybe her brain would finally stop

00:22:00.720 --> 00:22:02.759
buzzing with questions all the time.

00:22:02.880 --> 00:22:05.640
Maybe she'd finally feel like everything

00:22:05.640 --> 00:22:06.299
made sense.

00:22:06.420 --> 00:22:09.539
Cricket wanted the world to feel more

00:22:09.539 --> 00:22:10.140
like a book.

00:22:10.200 --> 00:22:13.079
Here is a question, so here is an

00:22:13.079 --> 00:22:13.380
answer.

00:22:13.440 --> 00:22:15.539
Here are other mysteries of the

00:22:15.539 --> 00:22:16.200
universe.

00:22:16.259 --> 00:22:18.299
Now here is everything you want to know

00:22:18.299 --> 00:22:18.660
about them.

00:22:18.720 --> 00:22:22.140
If her life were a book, she could check

00:22:22.140 --> 00:22:24.420
the index and go straight to the page

00:22:24.420 --> 00:22:26.460
that would tell her why her parents were

00:22:26.460 --> 00:22:29.279
always fighting, or why her mother didn't

00:22:29.279 --> 00:22:29.579
love her.

00:22:29.640 --> 00:22:33.119
She would read the chapter about how Katy

00:22:33.119 --> 00:22:36.240
did was always sad, and then she could

00:22:36.240 --> 00:22:38.220
read about how to fix it to make her

00:22:38.220 --> 00:22:39.240
sister happy.

00:22:39.420 --> 00:22:42.599
Those were the big mysteries of 2 year

00:22:42.599 --> 00:22:43.740
old cricket's life.

00:22:43.799 --> 00:22:46.799
She had no idea that there was an even

00:22:46.799 --> 00:22:49.380
bigger one, hiding below the surface of

00:22:49.380 --> 00:22:52.319
her entire tribe, or that she might be

00:22:52.319 --> 00:22:53.279
the key to solving it.

00:22:53.339 --> 00:22:56.519
A shriek from outside tore through the

00:22:56.519 --> 00:22:59.099
hum of cricket's thoughts, startling her

00:22:59.099 --> 00:23:01.140
so much, she banged her head on the top

00:23:01.140 --> 00:23:03.359
of the cupboard, and nearly knocked over

00:23:03.359 --> 00:23:05.880
the little flame silk lamp she'd smuggled

00:23:05.880 --> 00:23:06.299
in.

00:23:06.359 --> 00:23:09.119
She caught it with a flare of panic and

00:23:09.119 --> 00:23:09.660
relief.

00:23:09.720 --> 00:23:13.259
If she set her mother's book on fire, she

00:23:13.259 --> 00:23:15.180
might as well go ahead and burn the whole

00:23:15.180 --> 00:23:16.680
house down to hide the evidence.

00:23:16.740 --> 00:23:19.380
She'd be in just as much trouble either

00:23:19.380 --> 00:23:19.680
way.

00:23:19.740 --> 00:23:24.119
The scream came again, and Cricket nearly

00:23:24.119 --> 00:23:25.980
leaped out of the cabinet to investigate

00:23:25.980 --> 00:23:27.900
but before she could.

00:23:27.960 --> 00:23:31.500
Heavy talons entered the kitchen, and she

00:23:31.500 --> 00:23:33.299
covered the lamp quickly with her wings.

00:23:33.420 --> 00:23:37.619
There is a traitor in this hive. said her

00:23:37.619 --> 00:23:39.839
mother's voice, but not her mother's

00:23:39.839 --> 00:23:40.559
voice at all.

00:23:40.559 --> 00:23:42.420
Do not let him escape.

00:23:42.480 --> 00:23:46.680
Cricket held her breath, more terrified

00:23:46.680 --> 00:23:48.180
than she even understood.

00:23:48.240 --> 00:23:50.279
Who was her mother talking to?

00:23:50.339 --> 00:23:53.700
Why did she sound all wrong?

00:23:53.759 --> 00:23:56.819
More talon steps entered the room.

00:23:56.880 --> 00:23:59.099
This had to be Katy did.

00:23:59.160 --> 00:24:00.900
The only other dragon at home.

00:24:00.960 --> 00:24:03.779
But without any further conversation.

00:24:03.960 --> 00:24:05.579
The 2 of them ran out the front door.

00:24:05.640 --> 00:24:08.759
Cricket pushed the cupboard door open a

00:24:08.759 --> 00:24:10.079
crack and peeked out.

00:24:10.140 --> 00:24:13.319
The kitchen was deserted, although she

00:24:13.319 --> 00:24:14.700
could hear a lot of commotion on the

00:24:14.700 --> 00:24:15.480
street outside.

00:24:15.539 --> 00:24:19.319
Curiosity and fear went to war within

00:24:19.319 --> 00:24:19.559
her.

00:24:19.619 --> 00:24:22.740
And as often happened in cricket's life

00:24:22.740 --> 00:24:23.880
curiosity won.

00:24:23.940 --> 00:24:27.420
She left the book hidden, took the lamp

00:24:27.420 --> 00:24:30.180
with her, and slipped out of the cabinet

00:24:30.180 --> 00:24:32.819
hurrying upstairs to her mother's office

00:24:32.819 --> 00:24:34.859
which had a window with a view of the

00:24:34.859 --> 00:24:34.980
street.

00:24:35.039 --> 00:24:38.460
It was the same street she flew down

00:24:38.460 --> 00:24:38.819
every day.

00:24:38.880 --> 00:24:42.539
Houses built of tree stuff, turquoise

00:24:42.539 --> 00:24:44.700
mosaic tiles glittering in the light of

00:24:44.700 --> 00:24:47.339
the flame silk lamps, neatly tended

00:24:47.339 --> 00:24:50.039
gardens here and there, a line of black

00:24:50.039 --> 00:24:52.380
stones inlaid in the ground, to show

00:24:52.380 --> 00:24:54.059
young dragonettes the way to school.

00:24:54.119 --> 00:24:57.119
But instead of her polite, peaceful

00:24:57.119 --> 00:24:59.220
neighbors, and the usual strolling

00:24:59.220 --> 00:24:59.759
dragons.

00:24:59.819 --> 00:25:02.220
The street was now bristling with

00:25:02.220 --> 00:25:04.200
marching rows of teeth and claws.

00:25:04.259 --> 00:25:09.180
Cricket had never heard the word mob, but

00:25:09.180 --> 00:25:12.000
when she did, years later, she thought it

00:25:12.000 --> 00:25:13.799
was almost right for what she'd seen.

00:25:13.859 --> 00:25:15.660
But not quite.

00:25:15.720 --> 00:25:19.680
The dragons below her weren't enraged or

00:25:19.680 --> 00:25:20.579
in chaos.

00:25:20.700 --> 00:25:24.000
They moved in eerie unison, and near

00:25:24.000 --> 00:25:27.059
complete silence, as they surrounded the

00:25:27.059 --> 00:25:29.160
one dragon who was out of sync with the

00:25:29.160 --> 00:25:32.220
rest, cutting off all his possible escape

00:25:32.220 --> 00:25:32.519
routes.

00:25:32.579 --> 00:25:35.400
He cowered in the center of the glaring

00:25:35.400 --> 00:25:36.000
circle.

00:25:36.119 --> 00:25:39.180
His red and black striped wings folded in

00:25:39.180 --> 00:25:41.519
tightly, He looked quite old.

00:25:41.579 --> 00:25:44.640
Bolder than most dragons cricket knew

00:25:44.640 --> 00:25:47.579
maybe 60 or 100?

00:25:47.640 --> 00:25:49.740
She didn't really know how to guess the

00:25:49.740 --> 00:25:51.420
ages of grown up dragons.

00:25:51.480 --> 00:25:54.480
But he was quite big, and his scales were

00:25:54.480 --> 00:25:57.539
a little dull, and he moved in a tired

00:25:57.539 --> 00:25:59.160
aching bones kind of way.

00:25:59.220 --> 00:26:02.279
Please, just let me go.

00:26:02.339 --> 00:26:04.440
He shouted at the crowd.

00:26:04.500 --> 00:26:08.039
His eyes flickered white for a moment, and

00:26:08.039 --> 00:26:08.640
then dark again.

00:26:08.759 --> 00:26:11.640
I promise I'm not a threat to you.

00:26:11.759 --> 00:26:13.559
I don't want to be like them.

00:26:13.619 --> 00:26:15.960
That is not an option.

00:26:16.019 --> 00:26:19.380
The surrounding dragon said, in one

00:26:19.380 --> 00:26:19.680
voice.

00:26:19.740 --> 00:26:23.099
It wasn't just the voice that was wrong.

00:26:23.220 --> 00:26:24.779
Their eyes.

00:26:24.839 --> 00:26:26.700
Their eyes were all wrong too.

00:26:26.759 --> 00:26:29.940
Cricket felt a spasm of fear.

00:26:30.000 --> 00:26:31.619
Throughout the crowd.

00:26:31.680 --> 00:26:34.920
The dragon's eyes were all white, like

00:26:34.920 --> 00:26:36.779
pure, glassy marbles.

00:26:36.839 --> 00:26:40.920
Like empty snakeskins, like dead blood

00:26:40.920 --> 00:26:42.000
sucked grubs.

00:26:42.119 --> 00:26:45.480
Three of them stepped forward, with their

00:26:45.480 --> 00:26:48.599
claws or tails raised, to point menacing

00:26:48.599 --> 00:26:49.740
stingers of their prey.

00:26:49.799 --> 00:26:51.960
Their faces were blank.

00:26:52.019 --> 00:26:54.839
Cold, and merciless.

00:26:54.900 --> 00:26:57.839
They looked ready to kill without a

00:26:57.839 --> 00:26:58.680
flicker of emotion.

00:26:58.740 --> 00:27:02.460
And one of them was Katy did.

00:27:02.519 --> 00:27:05.819
Cricket ducked below the window frame, her

00:27:05.819 --> 00:27:06.960
heart beating frantically.

00:27:07.019 --> 00:27:09.000
What is happening?

00:27:09.059 --> 00:27:10.740
What is wrong with my sister?

00:27:10.859 --> 00:27:13.019
What's wrong with all of them?

00:27:13.140 --> 00:27:16.920
She heard another scream from below, and

00:27:16.920 --> 00:27:18.240
forced herself to peek out again.

00:27:18.299 --> 00:27:21.720
The old dragon was being marched away

00:27:21.720 --> 00:27:23.940
down the street, struggling weakly

00:27:23.940 --> 00:27:27.180
surrounded by a phalanx of dragons, who

00:27:27.180 --> 00:27:29.160
were almost all crickets, friends and

00:27:29.160 --> 00:27:29.579
neighbors.

00:27:29.640 --> 00:27:32.940
Except now, they had been transformed

00:27:32.940 --> 00:27:36.059
into something else, something dark, and

00:27:36.059 --> 00:27:37.200
no longer dragon.

00:27:37.259 --> 00:27:40.079
And cricket wasn't sure she'd ever be

00:27:40.079 --> 00:27:41.759
able to look at them the same way again.

00:27:41.819 --> 00:27:45.240
Her eyes caught on a flutter of blue near

00:27:45.240 --> 00:27:48.480
a doorway, and she realized that his silk

00:27:48.480 --> 00:27:50.700
wing was there, pressing herself back

00:27:50.700 --> 00:27:52.500
into the shadows to stay out of the way.

00:27:52.559 --> 00:27:56.039
The silkwings' eyes were normal, but her

00:27:56.039 --> 00:27:58.140
expression was fearful and puzzled.

00:27:58.200 --> 00:28:00.960
Cricket's gaze flicked across the houses

00:28:00.960 --> 00:28:01.440
quickly.

00:28:01.500 --> 00:28:04.619
And she spotted 5 more silk wings

00:28:04.619 --> 00:28:06.660
watching from doorways and windows.

00:28:06.720 --> 00:28:09.720
None of them had the snake skin eyes.

00:28:09.779 --> 00:28:13.200
A couple wore resigned expressions, as

00:28:13.200 --> 00:28:15.539
though they'd seen this before, but at

00:28:15.539 --> 00:28:17.700
least all of them had some emotion on

00:28:17.700 --> 00:28:18.180
their faces.

00:28:18.240 --> 00:28:21.720
None of them were empty, like the hive

00:28:21.720 --> 00:28:22.500
wings down below.

00:28:22.559 --> 00:28:26.039
So whatever's happening, it's only

00:28:26.039 --> 00:28:28.200
happening to hive wings, it's not

00:28:28.200 --> 00:28:29.460
affecting the silk wings.

00:28:29.519 --> 00:28:31.319
Or me.

00:28:31.380 --> 00:28:34.559
Her mind leaped onto this puzzle.

00:28:34.619 --> 00:28:37.140
Preferring it enormously to the other

00:28:37.140 --> 00:28:39.059
option of contemplating the horror of

00:28:39.059 --> 00:28:40.440
what she'd just seen.

00:28:40.500 --> 00:28:42.720
Is it because I'm too young?

00:28:42.779 --> 00:28:45.000
But that couldn't be it.

00:28:45.059 --> 00:28:47.279
There were little dragonettes everywhere

00:28:47.279 --> 00:28:50.099
in the crowd, intoning the same words as

00:28:50.099 --> 00:28:51.119
the other hive wings.

00:28:51.119 --> 00:28:54.839
Bombardier, the most annoying dragonette

00:28:54.839 --> 00:28:57.180
in her class, was among the ones who'd

00:28:57.180 --> 00:28:58.440
marched the old dragon away.

00:28:58.500 --> 00:29:02.400
Even Midge, the tiniest dragonette on the

00:29:02.400 --> 00:29:04.859
block, who had hatched a month ago, was

00:29:04.859 --> 00:29:07.380
down there, with her eyes blank, and

00:29:07.380 --> 00:29:08.160
teeth bared.

00:29:08.220 --> 00:29:11.400
Maybe this was something parents taught

00:29:11.400 --> 00:29:12.059
their kids to do.

00:29:12.119 --> 00:29:14.940
But because cricket's parent didn't like

00:29:14.940 --> 00:29:18.240
her, they'd forgotten or neglected to do

00:29:18.240 --> 00:29:18.779
it.

00:29:18.839 --> 00:29:21.539
Maybe the other high wings had learned it

00:29:21.539 --> 00:29:21.900
in school.

00:29:21.960 --> 00:29:24.480
Sometime when cricket was reading under

00:29:24.480 --> 00:29:26.519
her desk and not paying attention.

00:29:26.579 --> 00:29:29.519
Maybe there were secret meetings for all

00:29:29.519 --> 00:29:31.200
the other hive wings except her.

00:29:31.259 --> 00:29:34.259
And she wasn't invited, because she asked

00:29:34.259 --> 00:29:35.220
too many questions.

00:29:35.279 --> 00:29:37.859
But Katie did.

00:29:37.920 --> 00:29:40.680
Katydid would have told her of all the

00:29:40.680 --> 00:29:42.599
hive wings did something together that

00:29:42.599 --> 00:29:43.619
cricket should know about.

00:29:43.680 --> 00:29:46.079
She would have taught her how to blank

00:29:46.079 --> 00:29:48.420
out her eyes, and march with the others

00:29:48.420 --> 00:29:50.940
and threaten old dragons and look totally

00:29:50.940 --> 00:29:51.420
scary.

00:29:51.480 --> 00:29:55.319
More important, Katy did would never

00:29:55.319 --> 00:29:57.180
actually do any of those things.

00:29:57.240 --> 00:29:58.920
Except she did.

00:29:58.980 --> 00:30:01.019
I just saw her.

00:30:01.079 --> 00:30:03.599
A door slammed downstairs.

00:30:03.720 --> 00:30:07.380
Cricket glanced outside and saw the hive

00:30:07.380 --> 00:30:08.519
wings dispersing.

00:30:08.579 --> 00:30:10.980
The ones who had marched the old dragon

00:30:10.980 --> 00:30:12.779
away were still visible in the distance

00:30:12.779 --> 00:30:15.299
but everyone else was blinking and

00:30:15.299 --> 00:30:16.980
yawning and heading back indoors.

00:30:17.099 --> 00:30:18.720
Uh-oh.

00:30:18.779 --> 00:30:21.480
If Katy did was one of the ones marching

00:30:21.480 --> 00:30:24.539
off, that meant the dragon who'd just

00:30:24.539 --> 00:30:26.640
come into the house would be mother.

00:30:26.700 --> 00:30:29.519
Cricket ran out of her mother's office

00:30:29.519 --> 00:30:32.400
and dove into the nearest closet just in

00:30:32.400 --> 00:30:32.700
time.

00:30:32.759 --> 00:30:35.400
Through the crack in the door, she saw

00:30:35.400 --> 00:30:38.220
her mother stomp past the closet and into

00:30:38.220 --> 00:30:40.740
her office in a blur of orange and black

00:30:40.740 --> 00:30:44.400
scales, her wings buzzing slightly, the

00:30:44.400 --> 00:30:45.599
way they did when she was annoyed.

00:30:45.660 --> 00:30:47.519
Usually at cricket.

00:30:47.579 --> 00:30:50.940
Come to think of it, it was really

00:30:50.940 --> 00:30:52.740
strange for Cricket's mother to leave her

00:30:52.740 --> 00:30:54.779
office during her morning work hours.

00:30:54.839 --> 00:30:57.720
Cricket and Katy did weren't allowed to

00:30:57.720 --> 00:31:00.000
make even the slightest noise before noon

00:31:00.000 --> 00:31:01.440
in case they disturbed her.

00:31:01.500 --> 00:31:05.279
The office door slid shut, and Cricket

00:31:05.279 --> 00:31:06.839
let out the breath she'd been holding.

00:31:06.900 --> 00:31:10.319
A part of her desperately wanted to burst

00:31:10.319 --> 00:31:12.660
in and ask her mother all the questions

00:31:12.660 --> 00:31:16.680
swarming in her head, starting with, would

00:31:16.680 --> 00:31:17.819
Katy did come back?

00:31:17.880 --> 00:31:18.900
How soon?

00:31:18.960 --> 00:31:22.559
And of course, things like, so what in

00:31:22.559 --> 00:31:23.640
the hive was that?

00:31:23.759 --> 00:31:27.299
But some deeper instinct protected her.

00:31:27.359 --> 00:31:31.200
This once, she didn't let her curiosity

00:31:31.200 --> 00:31:31.500
win.

00:31:31.559 --> 00:31:35.640
Instead, she crept up to Katy Did's room

00:31:35.640 --> 00:31:38.099
on the top floor and curled herself under

00:31:38.099 --> 00:31:40.859
her sister's dark blue silk blankets.

00:31:40.920 --> 00:31:44.339
She closed her eyes, and tried not to cry

00:31:44.400 --> 00:31:45.299
and waited.

00:31:45.359 --> 00:31:48.420
It was late that night when Katie did

00:31:48.420 --> 00:31:51.000
finally returned, exhausted and wind

00:31:51.000 --> 00:31:51.480
blown.

00:31:51.539 --> 00:31:54.480
Cricket's father had come home earlier

00:31:54.480 --> 00:31:56.640
and Cricket had listened to both her

00:31:56.640 --> 00:31:58.980
parents eating dinner and hissing at each

00:31:58.980 --> 00:31:59.220
other.

00:31:59.279 --> 00:32:02.880
Neither one had looked for her, or called

00:32:02.880 --> 00:32:04.200
to ask her to join them.

00:32:04.259 --> 00:32:05.819
But that was normal.

00:32:05.880 --> 00:32:08.640
Katie did was the only one in the house

00:32:08.640 --> 00:32:10.799
who tried to organize family meals.

00:32:10.859 --> 00:32:13.740
She was the one who made sure cricket was

00:32:13.740 --> 00:32:16.619
fed and got to school on time in a year.

00:32:16.680 --> 00:32:19.019
She'd be the one who finally took cricket

00:32:19.019 --> 00:32:20.700
to an eye doctor to get her glasses.

00:32:20.759 --> 00:32:24.240
She was the only dragon cricket loved.

00:32:24.299 --> 00:32:27.599
Her heart lit up as Katydid came through

00:32:27.599 --> 00:32:27.960
the door.

00:32:28.019 --> 00:32:30.539
Cricket bounded out of the blankets

00:32:30.539 --> 00:32:32.940
grabbed her sister's shoulders, and

00:32:32.940 --> 00:32:34.619
stared into her face.

00:32:34.680 --> 00:32:35.940
Her eyes were back to normal.

00:32:36.000 --> 00:32:37.980
Wow.

00:32:38.039 --> 00:32:41.880
Gentle, Katie did scolded, but kindly.

00:32:41.880 --> 00:32:45.240
She removed Cricket's claws, and rolled

00:32:45.240 --> 00:32:46.799
her shoulders as though they were sore.

00:32:46.859 --> 00:32:50.519
I had to fly to wasp high than back today

00:32:50.519 --> 00:32:51.839
so take it easy on me.

00:32:51.900 --> 00:32:53.640
Why?

00:32:53.700 --> 00:32:54.960
Cricket demanded.

00:32:55.019 --> 00:32:56.279
Why did you have to?

00:32:56.339 --> 00:32:58.680
What did you do to that old dragon?

00:32:58.799 --> 00:33:00.900
What happened to your eyes this morning?

00:33:00.960 --> 00:33:03.480
Why was everyone acting so awful and

00:33:03.480 --> 00:33:03.839
weird?

00:33:03.900 --> 00:33:07.680
All the questions she'd been bottling up

00:33:07.680 --> 00:33:10.500
all day spilled out of her, along with

00:33:10.500 --> 00:33:12.180
the tears she thought she'd beaten.

00:33:12.240 --> 00:33:14.099
What was that voice?

00:33:14.160 --> 00:33:15.660
Why did you look so mean?

00:33:15.720 --> 00:33:17.819
Katie did, what happened to you?

00:33:17.880 --> 00:33:21.059
Katie did, was opposed to say something

00:33:21.059 --> 00:33:21.839
reassuring.

00:33:21.900 --> 00:33:24.839
She was supposed to shrug and laugh, and

00:33:24.839 --> 00:33:27.299
explain how it was a hive wing game, and

00:33:27.299 --> 00:33:28.619
cricket would learn it next week.

00:33:28.680 --> 00:33:30.779
Not to worry, nothing important.

00:33:30.839 --> 00:33:34.259
But instead, Katy did stared at her.

00:33:34.319 --> 00:33:37.140
With the least reassuring expression

00:33:37.140 --> 00:33:38.279
possible on her face.

00:33:38.339 --> 00:33:41.880
What happened to me, she said.

00:33:41.940 --> 00:33:43.920
Didn't it happen to you too?

00:33:43.980 --> 00:33:46.559
No, Cricket cried.

00:33:46.619 --> 00:33:50.099
I mean, I don't know what it was, but I

00:33:50.099 --> 00:33:52.019
sure didn't get all super possessed and

00:33:52.019 --> 00:33:53.940
freaky looking and mean like everyone

00:33:53.940 --> 00:33:55.019
else I could see.

00:33:55.019 --> 00:33:58.440
Your eyes were totally white, Katie did.

00:33:58.500 --> 00:34:00.480
And you were growling at that old

00:34:00.480 --> 00:34:00.960
dragon.

00:34:01.019 --> 00:34:03.359
Couldn't you see how scared he was?

00:34:03.420 --> 00:34:06.779
But that was a whole hive of command?

00:34:06.839 --> 00:34:08.099
Katy did said.

00:34:08.159 --> 00:34:10.019
All talons out.

00:34:10.079 --> 00:34:12.719
Every dragon in the hive was included.

00:34:12.780 --> 00:34:14.940
There's no way you could have been left

00:34:14.940 --> 00:34:15.179
out.

00:34:15.239 --> 00:34:18.899
Her kind orange yellow face was all

00:34:18.899 --> 00:34:19.259
worry.

00:34:19.380 --> 00:34:22.260
Cricket had never seen her sister look so

00:34:22.260 --> 00:34:22.679
anxious.

00:34:22.739 --> 00:34:25.259
Left out of what?

00:34:25.320 --> 00:34:27.300
Cricket asked nervously.

00:34:27.360 --> 00:34:31.139
Katy did rubbed her forehead, and sidled

00:34:31.139 --> 00:34:32.099
over to close the door.

00:34:32.159 --> 00:34:35.039
Although their parents were probably both

00:34:35.039 --> 00:34:37.619
asleep already, and usually never came up

00:34:37.619 --> 00:34:38.879
to the sisters rooms anyway.

00:34:38.940 --> 00:34:43.019
It doesn't happen often, she said softly

00:34:43.019 --> 00:34:47.760
but sometimes, Queen Wasp controls

00:34:47.760 --> 00:34:49.019
dragons.

00:34:49.079 --> 00:34:51.960
I mean, not just with orders and soldiers

00:34:51.960 --> 00:34:54.900
I mean, she gets into your brain and

00:34:54.900 --> 00:34:59.099
makes you do, um, anything she wants you

00:34:59.099 --> 00:34:59.400
to.

00:34:59.460 --> 00:35:00.780
What?

00:35:00.900 --> 00:35:01.980
Cricket said.

00:35:02.039 --> 00:35:03.119
How?

00:35:03.179 --> 00:35:05.820
That's, What?

00:35:05.880 --> 00:35:09.719
It's very efficient, Katy did pointed

00:35:09.719 --> 00:35:09.900
out.

00:35:09.960 --> 00:35:13.139
Like today, when there was a trader who'd

00:35:13.139 --> 00:35:15.000
run away from her and was trying to hide

00:35:15.000 --> 00:35:18.239
out in our hive, Queen Wasp can take over

00:35:18.239 --> 00:35:20.639
all the dragons in the hive at once and

00:35:20.639 --> 00:35:21.719
find him immediately.

00:35:21.780 --> 00:35:25.139
Then we catch him, and she releases most

00:35:25.139 --> 00:35:27.300
everybody while a few of us escort him

00:35:27.300 --> 00:35:27.719
back to her.

00:35:27.780 --> 00:35:31.260
But, do you want to?

00:35:31.320 --> 00:35:32.219
Cricket asked.

00:35:32.340 --> 00:35:35.639
Can she do it anytime she wants from

00:35:35.639 --> 00:35:36.059
anywhere?

00:35:36.119 --> 00:35:37.920
What if you're busy?

00:35:37.980 --> 00:35:40.559
Or what if you don't want to do what she

00:35:40.559 --> 00:35:40.920
says?

00:35:41.039 --> 00:35:43.260
Her sister shook her head.

00:35:43.320 --> 00:35:46.139
You do want to.

00:35:46.199 --> 00:35:47.219
She said.

00:35:47.280 --> 00:35:49.739
She is the queen cricket.

00:35:49.860 --> 00:35:51.840
If she were standing next to you giving

00:35:51.840 --> 00:35:54.360
an order, you'd do it no matter what.

00:35:54.420 --> 00:35:55.199
Of course.

00:35:55.320 --> 00:35:58.800
This is basically the same, except she

00:35:58.800 --> 00:36:00.059
doesn't have to be everywhere at once.

00:36:00.119 --> 00:36:04.500
It's not the same at all, Cricket thought

00:36:04.500 --> 00:36:05.219
rebelliously.

00:36:05.280 --> 00:36:09.420
So, your talons move, and your voice

00:36:09.420 --> 00:36:12.719
speaks, and your wings fly, and there's

00:36:12.719 --> 00:36:13.980
nothing you can do to stop it?

00:36:14.039 --> 00:36:14.880
she asked.

00:36:14.940 --> 00:36:18.900
You can't even say, no thank you, not

00:36:18.900 --> 00:36:19.320
today?

00:36:19.380 --> 00:36:21.840
Katie did threw out her wings.

00:36:21.900 --> 00:36:23.579
Of course not.

00:36:23.639 --> 00:36:26.039
Cricket, you wouldn't really ever say

00:36:26.039 --> 00:36:27.599
that to the queen, surely.

00:36:27.659 --> 00:36:28.860
Be serious.

00:36:28.920 --> 00:36:32.219
If she ordered me to stab someone, I

00:36:32.219 --> 00:36:33.780
would, Cricket thought.

00:36:33.840 --> 00:36:37.320
If she asked me to drag away an elderly

00:36:37.320 --> 00:36:40.500
dragon who was crying, I would say no.

00:36:40.559 --> 00:36:42.179
She thought.

00:36:42.239 --> 00:36:44.219
She hoped.

00:36:44.280 --> 00:36:45.539
She wasn't sure.

00:36:45.599 --> 00:36:48.239
There was a difference between being

00:36:48.239 --> 00:36:51.000
brave in a book, and brave in real life.

00:36:51.059 --> 00:36:53.400
So there certainly might be a difference

00:36:53.400 --> 00:36:56.099
between the cricket in her head, and a

00:36:56.099 --> 00:36:58.440
real cricket, standing in front of the

00:36:58.440 --> 00:37:00.000
actual terrifying queen.

00:37:00.119 --> 00:37:02.340
But how does it work?

00:37:02.400 --> 00:37:03.900
Cricket asked.

00:37:03.960 --> 00:37:06.300
I've never seen anything like that in any

00:37:06.300 --> 00:37:07.199
science book.

00:37:07.260 --> 00:37:08.820
I have no idea.

00:37:08.940 --> 00:37:13.019
Katy did said tiredly, which was how a

00:37:13.019 --> 00:37:15.059
lot of conversations between the sisters

00:37:15.059 --> 00:37:15.300
ended.

00:37:15.360 --> 00:37:17.940
Cricket wasn't ready to let this one go

00:37:17.940 --> 00:37:18.900
yet, though.

00:37:18.960 --> 00:37:21.360
And why doesn't it work on me?

00:37:21.420 --> 00:37:22.800
She pressed.

00:37:22.860 --> 00:37:24.179
Is mother right?

00:37:24.239 --> 00:37:26.460
There's something wrong with me?

00:37:26.519 --> 00:37:27.900
No.

00:37:28.019 --> 00:37:29.760
Katy did protested.

00:37:29.880 --> 00:37:31.019
Of course not.

00:37:31.079 --> 00:37:32.340
I don't know why.

00:37:32.460 --> 00:37:34.199
But why doesn't matter?

00:37:34.320 --> 00:37:37.079
What matters is how to protect you so no

00:37:37.079 --> 00:37:38.760
one realizes it doesn't work on you.

00:37:38.820 --> 00:37:41.400
You'll have to stay alert for when it

00:37:41.400 --> 00:37:41.880
happens.

00:37:41.940 --> 00:37:44.219
We'll find places for you to hide.

00:37:44.280 --> 00:37:46.739
The good news is she doesn't do it very

00:37:46.739 --> 00:37:47.039
often.

00:37:47.099 --> 00:37:50.340
I'll keep you safe, cricket, I promise.

00:37:50.400 --> 00:37:53.760
You think I'll be in trouble if Queen

00:37:53.760 --> 00:37:54.840
Wasp finds out?

00:37:54.960 --> 00:37:57.719
Cricket said, in a small voice.

00:37:57.840 --> 00:38:02.820
I'm afraid maybe, Katy did admitted.

00:38:02.880 --> 00:38:05.820
She put her wings around cricket, and

00:38:05.820 --> 00:38:06.840
they leaned into each other.

00:38:06.900 --> 00:38:12.360
But, if she takes over your brain, won't

00:38:12.360 --> 00:38:12.900
she know about me?

00:38:12.960 --> 00:38:14.699
Now that you know?

00:38:14.760 --> 00:38:16.139
Cricket asked.

00:38:16.199 --> 00:38:18.780
No, it doesn't work like that.

00:38:18.840 --> 00:38:20.460
Katie did said.

00:38:20.519 --> 00:38:22.980
She doesn't get into our thoughts and

00:38:22.980 --> 00:38:24.420
secrets and everything we know.

00:38:24.480 --> 00:38:27.300
She just controls what our bodies are

00:38:27.300 --> 00:38:28.199
doing for a little while.

00:38:28.260 --> 00:38:30.360
Cricket shuddered.

00:38:30.420 --> 00:38:33.300
That sounded completely horrible.

00:38:33.360 --> 00:38:37.739
Plus, also, it was extremely weird and

00:38:37.739 --> 00:38:40.980
unsettling that Katy did didn't think it

00:38:40.980 --> 00:38:42.119
sounded completely horrible.

00:38:42.179 --> 00:38:45.000
But Katy did kept her promise.

00:38:45.059 --> 00:38:48.420
For the next 4 years, Katie did covered

00:38:48.420 --> 00:38:50.400
for her, and Cricket learned to be

00:38:50.400 --> 00:38:52.800
careful in how to hide quickly until the

00:38:52.800 --> 00:38:53.699
commands passed.

00:38:53.760 --> 00:38:58.619
The question of why did matter to her, and

00:38:58.619 --> 00:39:01.079
she did all the research she could, but

00:39:01.079 --> 00:39:01.619
with no luck.

00:39:01.679 --> 00:39:05.699
Still, she kept the secret, and she was

00:39:05.699 --> 00:39:09.480
clever, and safe, and as cautious, as an

00:39:09.480 --> 00:39:11.400
impulsive, curious little dragonette

00:39:11.400 --> 00:39:11.760
could be.

00:39:11.820 --> 00:39:15.239
Until the most beautiful dragon cricket

00:39:15.239 --> 00:39:18.659
had ever seen, fell over a wall into her

00:39:18.659 --> 00:39:21.179
school courtyard, and all her caution

00:39:21.179 --> 00:39:22.260
through itself out the window.

00:39:22.320 --> 00:39:25.800
She couldn't exactly say why she'd helped

00:39:25.800 --> 00:39:28.679
Blue hide or why she'd told him her

00:39:28.679 --> 00:39:29.340
secret.

00:39:29.400 --> 00:39:32.639
Or why she'd left the safety of her hive

00:39:32.639 --> 00:39:35.460
to fly across the savannah with him on a

00:39:35.460 --> 00:39:37.019
hazardous rescue mission.

00:39:37.079 --> 00:39:39.960
Maybe those were all answers she'd find

00:39:39.960 --> 00:39:41.099
at the end of her own book.

00:39:41.159 --> 00:39:42.840
For now.

00:39:42.900 --> 00:39:45.119
All she had were consequences.

00:39:45.179 --> 00:39:48.480
She was a fugitive, wanted for stealing

00:39:48.480 --> 00:39:50.820
the book of Clearsight, and helping flame

00:39:50.820 --> 00:39:52.380
silks escape the queen.

00:39:52.440 --> 00:39:55.920
The book of Clearsight had not, contained

00:39:55.920 --> 00:39:57.599
all the answers to the universe after

00:39:57.599 --> 00:39:57.840
all.

00:39:57.900 --> 00:40:01.559
Worse, cricket's secret hive mind

00:40:01.559 --> 00:40:04.079
immunity had been exposed in the temple.

00:40:04.139 --> 00:40:06.179
And now the queen knew that she was

00:40:06.179 --> 00:40:08.760
different, that the mind control didn't

00:40:08.760 --> 00:40:09.179
work on her.

00:40:09.239 --> 00:40:12.420
Cricket would never be able to go home

00:40:12.420 --> 00:40:12.659
again.

00:40:12.719 --> 00:40:17.280
But on the other talon, now she had blue

00:40:17.280 --> 00:40:20.579
in her life, and as she sat by his softly

00:40:20.579 --> 00:40:23.400
glowing cocoon in an underground cave

00:40:23.400 --> 00:40:26.519
deep below Pantala, she decided she had

00:40:26.519 --> 00:40:28.019
no regrets about what she'd done.

00:40:28.139 --> 00:40:31.139
Except maybe one.

00:40:31.199 --> 00:40:33.059
She really?

00:40:33.119 --> 00:40:34.320
Really?

00:40:34.380 --> 00:40:37.679
Really wished she'd brought a book with

00:40:37.679 --> 00:40:37.860
her.

00:40:37.920 --> 00:40:40.860
Cricket sighed and stretched out her

00:40:40.860 --> 00:40:45.179
wings. 4 more days of sitting in a cave

00:40:45.179 --> 00:40:46.260
with nothing to read?

00:40:46.320 --> 00:40:48.480
She was seriously going to lose her

00:40:48.480 --> 00:40:48.780
mind.

00:40:48.840 --> 00:40:53.820
It had been very dramatic and romantic.

00:40:53.880 --> 00:40:55.980
When Blue's golden flame silk had begun

00:40:55.980 --> 00:40:58.380
spiraling from his wrists, and they'd

00:40:58.380 --> 00:41:00.659
come running down into this secret cave

00:41:00.659 --> 00:41:03.900
and she'd knelt beside him, and pledged

00:41:03.900 --> 00:41:06.360
to be there when he woke up, and to stay

00:41:06.360 --> 00:41:07.440
beside him always.

00:41:07.500 --> 00:41:11.880
But now, he was peacefully snoozing away

00:41:11.880 --> 00:41:16.139
growing his wings, and she was so bored.

00:41:16.199 --> 00:41:19.199
She stood up and circled his cocoon.

00:41:19.260 --> 00:41:23.579
It was a beautiful silvery gold color, but

00:41:23.579 --> 00:41:25.380
she missed the blue and purple of blues

00:41:25.380 --> 00:41:25.920
scales.

00:41:26.039 --> 00:41:29.039
She wished she could see even a hint of

00:41:29.039 --> 00:41:29.699
them through the silk.

00:41:29.820 --> 00:41:32.940
She knew that when she did, that would be

00:41:32.940 --> 00:41:35.039
a sign he was almost ready to come out.

00:41:35.099 --> 00:41:38.039
She hoped his friends would be back by

00:41:38.039 --> 00:41:38.280
then.

00:41:38.400 --> 00:41:42.239
She hoped Luna and Swordtail and Sundew

00:41:42.239 --> 00:41:42.659
were safe.

00:41:42.780 --> 00:41:45.239
How long had she been down here?

00:41:45.300 --> 00:41:48.539
Her sense of time seemed muffled by the

00:41:48.539 --> 00:41:51.059
caves, but she thought a whole day might

00:41:51.059 --> 00:41:51.599
have passed.

00:41:51.659 --> 00:41:55.260
Had Luna been blown out to sea, or

00:41:55.260 --> 00:41:56.699
recaptured by the hive wings.

00:41:56.760 --> 00:41:59.099
Had Swordtell followed her?

00:41:59.159 --> 00:42:00.900
Was Sundew all right?

00:42:00.960 --> 00:42:03.719
It felt a little odd to worry about

00:42:03.719 --> 00:42:06.420
Sundew, who had been her captor only a

00:42:06.420 --> 00:42:07.139
few days earlier.

00:42:07.199 --> 00:42:08.820
Sundew.

00:42:08.880 --> 00:42:12.300
Well, really, Sundu's parents, had forced

00:42:12.300 --> 00:42:13.920
Cricket to help steal the book of

00:42:13.920 --> 00:42:16.019
Clearsight, which led to this whole

00:42:16.019 --> 00:42:16.320
mess.

00:42:16.380 --> 00:42:19.559
But then Sundu had helped her rescue Blue

00:42:19.559 --> 00:42:22.679
and Luna, so that more than balanced the

00:42:22.679 --> 00:42:24.059
scales in cricket's opinion.

00:42:24.119 --> 00:42:27.599
And the truth was, she kind of liked the

00:42:27.599 --> 00:42:28.619
fierce leaf wing.

00:42:28.679 --> 00:42:32.219
Sundu let herself be mad, and always said

00:42:32.219 --> 00:42:34.380
what she really thought. and made all her

00:42:34.380 --> 00:42:36.539
own decisions, even when her parents

00:42:36.539 --> 00:42:39.119
didn't like it, and Cricket didn't know

00:42:39.119 --> 00:42:40.199
any high wings like that.

00:42:40.260 --> 00:42:43.380
Prickly opinions that stuck out in the

00:42:43.380 --> 00:42:46.199
hives tended to get smashed down fairly

00:42:46.199 --> 00:42:46.500
quickly.

00:42:46.559 --> 00:42:49.380
Are all leaf wings like that?

00:42:49.440 --> 00:42:52.019
Brave enough to do their own thing, no

00:42:52.019 --> 00:42:53.280
matter what anyone else thinks?

00:42:53.400 --> 00:42:57.840
Sundu's parents, Belladonna and Hemlock

00:42:57.840 --> 00:42:59.880
would have preferred to keep cricket and

00:42:59.880 --> 00:43:02.400
swordtail under their wings until they

00:43:02.400 --> 00:43:03.539
found another use for them.

00:43:03.599 --> 00:43:07.019
It was Sundoo who had insisted on helping

00:43:07.019 --> 00:43:08.760
them free the flame silks instead.

00:43:08.820 --> 00:43:12.179
And she'd kept the book of Clear Sight

00:43:12.179 --> 00:43:13.559
instead of giving it to them.

00:43:13.619 --> 00:43:17.400
Cricket's parents would never have agreed

00:43:17.400 --> 00:43:20.159
to that, or trusted her with something so

00:43:20.159 --> 00:43:20.579
important.

00:43:20.639 --> 00:43:24.360
Belladonna and Hemlock had grumbled, but

00:43:24.360 --> 00:43:26.639
when Sundew put her talons down, they

00:43:26.639 --> 00:43:27.420
accepted it.

00:43:27.480 --> 00:43:30.000
She didn't have to help fight the hive

00:43:30.000 --> 00:43:32.460
wings who spotted Luna and Sortell either

00:43:32.460 --> 00:43:33.599
Cricket thought.

00:43:33.659 --> 00:43:35.460
But she didn't even hesitate.

00:43:35.519 --> 00:43:38.460
Cricket wished she could ever be that

00:43:38.460 --> 00:43:39.239
sure of herself.

00:43:39.300 --> 00:43:42.900
Sundoom moved like a dragon who'd already

00:43:42.900 --> 00:43:44.699
found all the answers to her questions.

00:43:44.820 --> 00:43:48.840
It was really quiet in the caves this far

00:43:48.840 --> 00:43:49.500
under the earth.

00:43:49.559 --> 00:43:53.219
If she sat still and concentrated, she

00:43:53.219 --> 00:43:54.659
could hear water trickling in the

00:43:54.659 --> 00:43:54.900
distance.

00:43:54.960 --> 00:43:57.960
And every once in a while, she heard

00:43:57.960 --> 00:44:01.019
weird little squeaky echoes, which she

00:44:01.019 --> 00:44:03.900
suspected, all right, she hoped.

00:44:03.960 --> 00:44:05.820
Where more of those little reading

00:44:05.820 --> 00:44:08.219
monkeys, like the ones she in blue had

00:44:08.219 --> 00:44:09.960
seen at the bottom of a stinkhole on the

00:44:09.960 --> 00:44:10.320
savannah?

00:44:10.380 --> 00:44:12.360
If I could find them?

00:44:12.420 --> 00:44:14.880
Maybe I could borrow one of their books

00:44:14.880 --> 00:44:17.880
she thought wistfully, which made her

00:44:17.880 --> 00:44:18.480
laugh at herself.

00:44:18.539 --> 00:44:20.460
Of course she wouldn't be able to

00:44:20.460 --> 00:44:22.019
understand a little reading monkey

00:44:22.019 --> 00:44:24.179
language, if that's what it was.

00:44:24.239 --> 00:44:27.239
Plus, her claws would be too big for

00:44:27.239 --> 00:44:28.019
their tiny books.

00:44:28.079 --> 00:44:31.619
But imagine holding a book by another

00:44:31.619 --> 00:44:33.480
species in her talons.

00:44:33.539 --> 00:44:35.820
What if she could translate it?

00:44:35.880 --> 00:44:37.260
What would it say?

00:44:37.320 --> 00:44:39.420
What did monkeys think about?

00:44:39.480 --> 00:44:41.340
What were their stories about?

00:44:41.400 --> 00:44:44.460
What did they know that dragons didn't?

00:44:44.519 --> 00:44:47.400
It felt as if her head might explode?

00:44:47.460 --> 00:44:49.380
thinking about everything she might

00:44:49.380 --> 00:44:49.800
discover?

00:44:49.860 --> 00:44:54.000
In another life, where studying them

00:44:54.000 --> 00:44:55.739
could have been my destiny.

00:44:55.800 --> 00:44:58.739
A noise sounded from the stone passages

00:44:58.739 --> 00:44:59.760
beyond the cave.

00:44:59.820 --> 00:45:03.659
Cricket froze, all senses on alert.

00:45:03.719 --> 00:45:05.219
It came again.

00:45:05.280 --> 00:45:09.300
The scratch of claws on rock, the sound

00:45:09.300 --> 00:45:11.280
of a tail slithering along the floor.

00:45:11.340 --> 00:45:14.940
Someone else was in the caves.

00:45:15.000 --> 00:45:18.900
Chapter 2.

00:45:19.139 --> 00:45:21.960
Cricket held her breath.

00:45:22.019 --> 00:45:24.300
Her mind frantically darting through her

00:45:24.300 --> 00:45:24.659
options.

00:45:24.719 --> 00:45:27.239
Could she pretend she was guarding the

00:45:27.239 --> 00:45:27.659
cocoon?

00:45:27.719 --> 00:45:30.360
That maybe Queen Wasp had given her a

00:45:30.360 --> 00:45:30.900
secret mission?

00:45:30.960 --> 00:45:34.199
Not if the dragon who is coming had white

00:45:34.199 --> 00:45:34.440
eyes.

00:45:34.559 --> 00:45:38.219
If Queen Wasp was inside this dragon's

00:45:38.219 --> 00:45:40.380
brain, she'd recognize cricket as the

00:45:40.380 --> 00:45:41.880
dragon who'd stolen the book of

00:45:41.880 --> 00:45:44.519
Clearsight, and 2 of her flame silks.

00:45:44.579 --> 00:45:46.739
She'd be able to raise the entire

00:45:46.739 --> 00:45:49.559
continent to descend on this cave in a

00:45:49.559 --> 00:45:49.920
heartbeat.

00:45:49.980 --> 00:45:52.500
And there was no way cricket could hide

00:45:52.500 --> 00:45:53.699
blue before they arrived.

00:45:53.760 --> 00:45:57.239
She stepped in front of his cocoon anyway

00:45:57.239 --> 00:45:58.920
and tried to make her face look

00:45:58.920 --> 00:45:59.579
menacing.

00:45:59.639 --> 00:46:02.219
But the dragon who appeared in the

00:46:02.219 --> 00:46:04.559
doorway was the green and gold of summer

00:46:04.559 --> 00:46:07.320
leaves, with 2 wings instead of four.

00:46:07.380 --> 00:46:10.739
Cricket had never been so relieved to see

00:46:10.739 --> 00:46:12.119
a scowl that fierce.

00:46:12.179 --> 00:46:16.260
Sundew, she cried, leaping toward her.

00:46:16.320 --> 00:46:17.280
You're all right.

00:46:17.340 --> 00:46:20.699
No thanks to any of you, Sundew

00:46:20.699 --> 00:46:21.119
grumbled.

00:46:21.179 --> 00:46:23.880
She winced as she stepped into the cave.

00:46:23.940 --> 00:46:25.980
And cricket spotted a trickle of blood

00:46:25.980 --> 00:46:27.119
running down her shoulder.

00:46:27.179 --> 00:46:28.860
What happened?

00:46:28.920 --> 00:46:31.920
Cricket asked, catching sundew's pouches

00:46:31.920 --> 00:46:33.840
as the leaf wing threw them off and

00:46:33.840 --> 00:46:34.920
setting them against the wall.

00:46:34.980 --> 00:46:37.500
Have you seen Sortell and Luna?

00:46:37.559 --> 00:46:39.780
I'm so sorry I couldn't fly up and help

00:46:39.780 --> 00:46:39.960
you.

00:46:40.019 --> 00:46:42.420
Not that I'm much use in a fight anyway

00:46:42.420 --> 00:46:45.000
but Blue's metamorphosis started and I

00:46:45.000 --> 00:46:46.079
had to get him somewhere safe.

00:46:46.139 --> 00:46:49.079
She waved her wings at the glowing lump

00:46:49.079 --> 00:46:49.500
behind her.

00:46:49.559 --> 00:46:52.079
What did you do to the hive wings?

00:46:52.139 --> 00:46:53.460
Do they know where we are?

00:46:53.519 --> 00:46:56.219
She felt the shape of the book of

00:46:56.219 --> 00:46:58.860
Clearsight in the last pouch, and laid it

00:46:58.860 --> 00:47:01.019
carefully, reverently, on the stone

00:47:01.019 --> 00:47:01.559
floor.

00:47:01.619 --> 00:47:04.199
The queen had lied to everyone about the

00:47:04.199 --> 00:47:07.380
book, but it was still very old, and

00:47:07.380 --> 00:47:10.860
pretty sacred, and most important, a book

00:47:10.860 --> 00:47:13.920
something to read, at last.

00:47:13.980 --> 00:47:17.699
I led them away, sundew said, shaking

00:47:17.699 --> 00:47:18.960
raindrops off her wings.

00:47:19.019 --> 00:47:22.320
I flew south, though smug, moss brained

00:47:22.320 --> 00:47:24.300
monsters chased me all the way to Lake

00:47:24.300 --> 00:47:26.880
Scorpion, and then I lost them and came

00:47:26.880 --> 00:47:29.940
back the very annoyingly long way around

00:47:29.940 --> 00:47:31.019
Dragonfly Bay.

00:47:31.079 --> 00:47:32.639
It's pouring outside.

00:47:32.699 --> 00:47:34.800
Easy to lose a dragon in a storm.

00:47:34.860 --> 00:47:36.599
She shook her head.

00:47:36.659 --> 00:47:38.699
Didn't see Luna anywhere.

00:47:38.760 --> 00:47:41.820
But I did find this bedraggled, unhelpful

00:47:41.820 --> 00:47:42.119
mess.

00:47:42.179 --> 00:47:45.480
Sundew ducked out into the passageway and

00:47:45.480 --> 00:47:46.260
cricket followed her.

00:47:46.320 --> 00:47:49.980
Swordtail lay sprawled on the cave floor

00:47:49.980 --> 00:47:50.820
unconscious.

00:47:50.880 --> 00:47:54.360
He seemed much wetter than sundew, as

00:47:54.360 --> 00:47:56.280
though she had just dredged him up from

00:47:56.280 --> 00:47:57.059
the bottom of the ocean.

00:47:57.119 --> 00:48:00.239
Long strands of seaweed were tangled

00:48:00.239 --> 00:48:02.340
through his horns and his talons, and

00:48:02.340 --> 00:48:04.139
wrapped around his dark blue wings.

00:48:04.199 --> 00:48:06.179
By the book.

00:48:06.239 --> 00:48:07.860
Where has he been?

00:48:07.920 --> 00:48:10.619
Cricket asked, crouching beside him to

00:48:10.619 --> 00:48:11.460
study his face.

00:48:11.639 --> 00:48:12.719
Is he all right?

00:48:12.780 --> 00:48:15.780
Sundew shrugged, disinterestedly.

00:48:15.840 --> 00:48:17.340
He's alive.

00:48:17.400 --> 00:48:19.500
I found him like this on a rock in the

00:48:19.500 --> 00:48:19.679
bay.

00:48:19.800 --> 00:48:22.139
He's lucky I found him instead of a hive

00:48:22.139 --> 00:48:22.500
wing.

00:48:22.559 --> 00:48:24.840
Although I was pretty tempted to leave

00:48:24.840 --> 00:48:25.260
him there.

00:48:25.320 --> 00:48:28.800
She grabbed one of his back talons and

00:48:28.800 --> 00:48:30.960
started dragging him into Blue's cave.

00:48:31.019 --> 00:48:33.300
Cricket followed, trying to hold

00:48:33.300 --> 00:48:35.400
Swordtail's head above the bumpy rocks.

00:48:35.460 --> 00:48:37.739
That he was alone?

00:48:37.800 --> 00:48:39.000
She asked.

00:48:39.059 --> 00:48:42.059
A sundew dropped the silk wing in a heap

00:48:42.059 --> 00:48:43.619
beside the flame silk cocoon.

00:48:43.739 --> 00:48:47.880
My guess is Luna got blown out to sea, and

00:48:47.880 --> 00:48:48.780
he tried to follow her.

00:48:48.840 --> 00:48:50.340
Sundoo said.

00:48:50.400 --> 00:48:52.980
She stretched her wings again, and shook

00:48:52.980 --> 00:48:54.539
out her talons as though her shoulder

00:48:54.539 --> 00:48:54.780
hurt.

00:48:54.900 --> 00:48:57.659
But the storm chucked him into a boulder

00:48:57.659 --> 00:49:00.059
instead, which he deserved, if you ask

00:49:00.059 --> 00:49:00.239
me.

00:49:00.360 --> 00:49:03.239
Did you see him fly off and leave me

00:49:03.239 --> 00:49:05.340
fighting 2 hive wings alone?

00:49:05.400 --> 00:49:06.480
I mean, sure.

00:49:06.539 --> 00:49:09.119
Luna is great, and I know he just got her

00:49:09.119 --> 00:49:10.380
back and all, and I get it.

00:49:10.440 --> 00:49:12.179
I have a one true love too.

00:49:12.239 --> 00:49:13.920
You do?

00:49:13.980 --> 00:49:15.480
Cricket said.

00:49:15.539 --> 00:49:16.860
Fascinated.

00:49:16.920 --> 00:49:17.639
Who?

00:49:17.699 --> 00:49:20.039
But on the other talent?

00:49:20.099 --> 00:49:21.360
Hive wings?

00:49:21.420 --> 00:49:23.760
Sundew went on, ignoring her.

00:49:23.820 --> 00:49:26.099
With pointy stabby bits.

00:49:26.159 --> 00:49:29.159
Plus, he left you guys in danger too

00:49:29.159 --> 00:49:31.139
which he apparently didn't even think

00:49:31.139 --> 00:49:32.219
about.

00:49:32.280 --> 00:49:34.500
He probably thinks you could take on 9

00:49:34.500 --> 00:49:36.360
times that many high wings by yourself

00:49:36.360 --> 00:49:38.880
and be all right, Cricket admitted.

00:49:38.940 --> 00:49:41.039
I mean, that's what I think.

00:49:41.099 --> 00:49:44.039
She was still wrapping her mind around

00:49:44.039 --> 00:49:44.880
the last revelation.

00:49:44.940 --> 00:49:47.940
Sundew has a one true love?

00:49:48.059 --> 00:49:50.039
Another leaf wing, I guess.

00:49:50.099 --> 00:49:52.980
What kind of dragon would Sundoo fall in

00:49:52.980 --> 00:49:53.280
love with?

00:49:53.340 --> 00:49:56.340
Is it someone equally terrifying?

00:49:56.400 --> 00:50:00.360
Hmm, Sundew said, looking a little

00:50:00.360 --> 00:50:01.019
mollified.

00:50:01.079 --> 00:50:03.599
Well, that would be the 1st sign of life

00:50:03.599 --> 00:50:05.159
from his brain, that's for sure.

00:50:05.219 --> 00:50:08.039
I guess he never found Luna.

00:50:08.099 --> 00:50:10.019
And you didn't see where she went?

00:50:10.079 --> 00:50:12.900
Cricket glanced worriedly a blues

00:50:12.900 --> 00:50:13.500
cocoon.

00:50:13.559 --> 00:50:15.840
Could he hear anything through the layers

00:50:15.840 --> 00:50:16.320
of silk?

00:50:16.380 --> 00:50:17.760
Probably not.

00:50:17.820 --> 00:50:21.119
She was pretty sure metamorphosis was

00:50:21.119 --> 00:50:22.980
kind of a long, dreamless sleep.

00:50:23.039 --> 00:50:25.980
But how would he react when he came out

00:50:25.980 --> 00:50:27.960
and discovered that the sister he'd

00:50:27.960 --> 00:50:31.019
worked so hard to rescue was gone.

00:50:31.079 --> 00:50:34.679
No, but I got a survivor vibe from her.

00:50:34.739 --> 00:50:37.019
That one can take care of herself, I

00:50:37.019 --> 00:50:37.199
think.

00:50:37.260 --> 00:50:41.340
Sundew picked up one of Sordell's wings

00:50:41.340 --> 00:50:43.440
and dropped it, with a wet, wapping

00:50:43.440 --> 00:50:43.739
sound.

00:50:43.800 --> 00:50:47.760
Moon faced, self aggrandizing opinions to

00:50:47.760 --> 00:50:48.719
the contrary.

00:50:48.719 --> 00:50:51.840
But wait, how did you get him back here?

00:50:51.900 --> 00:50:54.179
Cricket asked wonderingly.

00:50:54.300 --> 00:50:57.000
Sundew was about the same size as

00:50:57.000 --> 00:50:59.159
swordtail, maybe a little smaller.

00:50:59.219 --> 00:51:01.980
There was no way the leaf wing could have

00:51:01.980 --> 00:51:04.079
carried him across the bay and into the

00:51:04.079 --> 00:51:06.840
cave, especially in the storm, and

00:51:06.840 --> 00:51:08.400
especially if she was trying not to be

00:51:08.400 --> 00:51:08.639
noticed.

00:51:08.699 --> 00:51:12.599
Has anyone ever told you that you ask a

00:51:12.599 --> 00:51:13.800
lot of questions?

00:51:13.860 --> 00:51:15.599
Sundew snapped.

00:51:15.659 --> 00:51:19.739
Oh yes, Cricket said, all the time.

00:51:19.800 --> 00:51:22.679
Sundew crinkled her nose, which cricket

00:51:22.679 --> 00:51:24.780
hoped was her trying not to laugh

00:51:24.780 --> 00:51:25.380
expression.

00:51:25.500 --> 00:51:29.219
Well, stop for a few heartbeats while I

00:51:29.219 --> 00:51:29.820
catch my breath.

00:51:29.940 --> 00:51:32.760
All right, cricket said.

00:51:32.820 --> 00:51:35.400
Although wanting to know so many things

00:51:35.400 --> 00:51:37.980
and not being able to find them out, felt

00:51:37.980 --> 00:51:40.079
like small creatures buzzing under her

00:51:40.079 --> 00:51:40.440
scales.

00:51:40.500 --> 00:51:43.260
Can I get you some water for that?

00:51:43.380 --> 00:51:45.840
She pointed to sundew's injury?

00:51:45.900 --> 00:51:48.599
If you stay with Blue, I can go find the

00:51:48.599 --> 00:51:49.320
underground river.

00:51:49.380 --> 00:51:51.719
It can't be far if we can hear it so well

00:51:51.719 --> 00:51:52.079
from here.

00:51:52.139 --> 00:51:55.500
Maybe, she'd have a better chance of

00:51:55.500 --> 00:51:57.300
getting answers if she did something

00:51:57.300 --> 00:51:58.199
helpful first.

00:51:58.320 --> 00:52:00.960
Yes, all right.

00:52:01.019 --> 00:52:02.219
Sundew said.

00:52:02.280 --> 00:52:04.199
At least it'll be quiet while you're

00:52:04.199 --> 00:52:04.440
gone.

00:52:04.500 --> 00:52:07.079
She pointed to one of her pouches.

00:52:07.139 --> 00:52:10.139
There's a moss in there that can absorb

00:52:10.139 --> 00:52:11.099
nearly a whole pond.

00:52:11.159 --> 00:52:12.480
Take some of that with you.

00:52:12.539 --> 00:52:15.960
Cricket dug out a talon full of moss and

00:52:15.960 --> 00:52:17.519
bounded off into the caves.

00:52:17.579 --> 00:52:20.219
It wasn't hard to make a mental map in

00:52:20.219 --> 00:52:22.260
her head as she followed the sound of

00:52:22.260 --> 00:52:23.219
water through the tunnels.

00:52:23.280 --> 00:52:26.460
The river she found was more of a stream

00:52:26.460 --> 00:52:28.380
although she guessed it would get

00:52:28.380 --> 00:52:29.880
stronger if she kept walking down it

00:52:29.880 --> 00:52:31.679
toward the sound of rapids.

00:52:31.739 --> 00:52:34.139
But a little bit of water was all she

00:52:34.139 --> 00:52:36.599
needed, so she dipped the clump of moss

00:52:36.599 --> 00:52:39.000
in until it was well soaked, then headed

00:52:39.000 --> 00:52:40.380
back to Blue's cave.

00:52:40.440 --> 00:52:43.139
Sundew muttered, thank you.

00:52:43.199 --> 00:52:45.599
As she took the moss and pressed it to

00:52:45.599 --> 00:52:46.500
the cut on her shoulder.

00:52:46.559 --> 00:52:49.679
Cricket hovered for a moment, wondering

00:52:49.679 --> 00:52:52.019
if she could help more, but the green

00:52:52.019 --> 00:52:54.719
dragon looked extra scowly and prone to

00:52:54.719 --> 00:52:57.059
biting, so Cricket decided it would be

00:52:57.059 --> 00:52:58.739
safer to back away for a little while.

00:52:58.800 --> 00:53:02.400
I hope Luna's all right, she said

00:53:02.400 --> 00:53:04.019
circling sword tail.

00:53:04.079 --> 00:53:05.760
I wonder if she can swim.

00:53:05.820 --> 00:53:09.599
At least Sortell was unconscious, and

00:53:09.599 --> 00:53:11.400
therefore unlikely to snap at her.

00:53:11.460 --> 00:53:14.340
Cricket started untangling the seaweed

00:53:14.340 --> 00:53:17.519
from his wings, piling it up nearby, there

00:53:17.519 --> 00:53:19.019
was a lot of it.

00:53:19.079 --> 00:53:20.699
Was it edible?

00:53:20.760 --> 00:53:22.619
She hadn't eaten in.

00:53:22.679 --> 00:53:23.760
Hmm.

00:53:23.820 --> 00:53:26.460
She wasn't sure, but it seemed like a

00:53:26.460 --> 00:53:27.000
very long time.

00:53:27.119 --> 00:53:30.000
She'd probably have to starve for another

00:53:30.000 --> 00:53:33.059
day or 2 before she'd find gloppy, wet

00:53:33.059 --> 00:53:35.039
seaweed at all appetizing, though.

00:53:35.099 --> 00:53:37.679
How long ago did you find him?

00:53:37.739 --> 00:53:38.579
she asked.

00:53:38.639 --> 00:53:42.719
The pile of seaweed oozed and squished as

00:53:42.719 --> 00:53:43.619
she added more to it.

00:53:43.679 --> 00:53:46.739
Squelp, the work splaff.

00:53:46.800 --> 00:53:48.840
Do you think he'll wake up soon?

00:53:48.900 --> 00:53:51.239
I wonder if he'll stay to watch Blue come

00:53:51.239 --> 00:53:53.639
out, or go off looking for Luna again.

00:53:53.699 --> 00:53:56.219
Maybe she's stranded on another island in

00:53:56.219 --> 00:53:58.440
the bay, so maybe she'll come back and

00:53:58.440 --> 00:53:58.860
find us?

00:53:58.920 --> 00:54:01.559
Should we leave a message in the beach

00:54:01.559 --> 00:54:02.880
cave so she'll come down here?

00:54:02.940 --> 00:54:07.079
But no, then Queen Wasps Scouts might see

00:54:07.079 --> 00:54:07.260
it.

00:54:07.380 --> 00:54:09.239
We sure don't want them finding us.

00:54:09.300 --> 00:54:11.460
Hey, how did you find me?

00:54:11.519 --> 00:54:14.880
Sundu growled.

00:54:14.940 --> 00:54:16.679
You don't even know that you're doing

00:54:16.679 --> 00:54:16.920
it.

00:54:16.980 --> 00:54:19.440
Here, wake him up so you can bother

00:54:19.440 --> 00:54:20.219
someone else.

00:54:20.280 --> 00:54:22.800
She grabbed one of her pouches and threw

00:54:22.800 --> 00:54:23.460
it to cricket.

00:54:23.519 --> 00:54:25.260
Oh, sorry.

00:54:25.320 --> 00:54:27.659
Sorry, cricket said.

00:54:27.719 --> 00:54:30.059
She had, in fact, forgotten about not

00:54:30.059 --> 00:54:32.219
asking Sundo any more questions during

00:54:32.219 --> 00:54:33.840
her trip back and forth to the river.

00:54:33.900 --> 00:54:35.940
What's in here?

00:54:36.000 --> 00:54:38.460
I mean, um, I'll figure it out.

00:54:38.519 --> 00:54:41.519
She flipped open the pouch, which was

00:54:41.519 --> 00:54:43.860
woven out of large, shiny waterproof

00:54:43.860 --> 00:54:46.679
leaves, and found 3 neat compartments

00:54:46.679 --> 00:54:48.360
with different bundles in each.

00:54:48.420 --> 00:54:51.480
She hoped none of them contained alarming

00:54:51.480 --> 00:54:54.480
insects, like the ones she'd seen sundew

00:54:54.480 --> 00:54:55.500
fight dragons with.

00:54:55.559 --> 00:54:58.440
Middle section, sundew said.

00:54:58.500 --> 00:55:00.000
Crush one under his nose.

00:55:00.059 --> 00:55:03.119
She threw a few berries in her mouth, and

00:55:03.119 --> 00:55:05.219
lay down with her back to cricket, sword

00:55:05.219 --> 00:55:06.000
tail, and blew.

00:55:06.000 --> 00:55:08.699
Inside the middle compartment of the

00:55:08.699 --> 00:55:11.159
pouch, wrapped in a soft covering of

00:55:11.159 --> 00:55:13.980
cobwebs, cricket found a trio of weird

00:55:13.980 --> 00:55:16.800
looking plants, each with shiny red

00:55:16.800 --> 00:55:19.500
modeled with yellow streaks, and curved

00:55:19.500 --> 00:55:20.340
in around itself.

00:55:20.460 --> 00:55:22.920
So there was a hollow in the middle and a

00:55:22.920 --> 00:55:23.940
point at one end.

00:55:24.000 --> 00:55:27.360
Cricket carefully took one out, held it

00:55:27.360 --> 00:55:30.119
under SwordTail's snout, and squished it

00:55:30.119 --> 00:55:30.840
between our claws.

00:55:30.900 --> 00:55:34.260
The scent that came out was unexpectedly

00:55:34.260 --> 00:55:36.300
horrible, and strong enough to make her

00:55:36.300 --> 00:55:37.199
own eyes water.

00:55:37.260 --> 00:55:40.199
Sortail grunted, his face twitching in

00:55:40.199 --> 00:55:40.860
distress.

00:55:40.920 --> 00:55:43.559
Cricket held the plant in place as long

00:55:43.559 --> 00:55:46.019
as she could, then ran across the cave to

00:55:46.019 --> 00:55:47.460
throw it out into the passageway.

00:55:47.519 --> 00:55:51.360
When she came back, Sortell was blinking

00:55:51.360 --> 00:55:53.340
and trying to sit up, rubbing his eyes.

00:55:53.400 --> 00:55:56.699
He unraveled a long strand of seaweed

00:55:56.699 --> 00:55:58.860
from his legs, and managed to roll

00:55:58.860 --> 00:55:59.579
upright.

00:55:59.579 --> 00:56:02.460
His bewildered gaze took in the flame

00:56:02.460 --> 00:56:04.500
silk cocoon, and then cricket.

00:56:04.559 --> 00:56:07.920
Cricket wanted to help, but the truth was

00:56:07.920 --> 00:56:09.780
Sortell made her a little nervous.

00:56:09.840 --> 00:56:13.320
She knew he was Blue's best friend, and

00:56:13.320 --> 00:56:15.840
Blue trusted him, but he was kind of loud

00:56:15.840 --> 00:56:18.659
and mad, and she got the feeling he

00:56:18.659 --> 00:56:19.559
didn't like her very much.

00:56:19.619 --> 00:56:22.619
There had always been dragons in her

00:56:22.619 --> 00:56:24.840
classes who didn't like her, because she

00:56:24.840 --> 00:56:27.000
got the right answer, or made the class

00:56:27.000 --> 00:56:29.639
run long with her questions, or because

00:56:29.639 --> 00:56:31.619
she'd rather be reading a book than

00:56:31.619 --> 00:56:33.119
playing one of their recess games.

00:56:33.179 --> 00:56:35.880
Or because she understood equations

00:56:35.880 --> 00:56:38.280
better than she understood other dragons

00:56:38.280 --> 00:56:41.280
and sometimes she was just awkward and

00:56:41.280 --> 00:56:42.659
out of step with everyone else.

00:56:42.719 --> 00:56:44.280
And you know what?

00:56:44.400 --> 00:56:46.440
Normal conversations were hard.

00:56:46.500 --> 00:56:48.780
Didn't anyone else find them hard?

00:56:48.840 --> 00:56:52.860
But Sortell disliked her entirely because

00:56:52.860 --> 00:56:54.059
she was a hive wing.

00:56:54.119 --> 00:56:55.920
She couldn't argue with that.

00:56:55.980 --> 00:56:59.039
She couldn't help being a hive wing, and

00:56:59.039 --> 00:57:00.719
she couldn't defend anything her tribe

00:57:00.719 --> 00:57:03.239
had done, and it wasn't useful to keep

00:57:03.239 --> 00:57:06.420
saying, but I'm not like them over and

00:57:06.420 --> 00:57:06.719
over.

00:57:06.780 --> 00:57:09.420
She just had to hope that eventually

00:57:09.420 --> 00:57:11.639
she'd do enough to prove she could be

00:57:11.639 --> 00:57:12.000
trusted.

00:57:12.059 --> 00:57:15.300
Cricket glanced over at the resting leaf

00:57:15.300 --> 00:57:17.159
wing, wishing she could talk to her

00:57:17.159 --> 00:57:17.579
instead.

00:57:17.639 --> 00:57:20.880
Sundew hated hive wings even more than

00:57:20.880 --> 00:57:21.719
Swordtail did.

00:57:21.780 --> 00:57:25.079
But she seemed okay with cricket, in her

00:57:25.079 --> 00:57:26.099
own ferocious way.

00:57:26.159 --> 00:57:28.679
Cricket suspected there was someone

00:57:28.679 --> 00:57:31.739
almost as kind as blue under all sundew's

00:57:31.739 --> 00:57:34.980
layers of thorns, although so far, she'd

00:57:34.980 --> 00:57:36.179
only caught glimpses of her.

00:57:36.239 --> 00:57:40.019
The leaf wing was also really smart, and

00:57:40.019 --> 00:57:41.760
knew a 1000000 things about plants and

00:57:41.760 --> 00:57:43.920
insects, that cricket had never learned

00:57:43.920 --> 00:57:44.219
in school.

00:57:44.280 --> 00:57:47.280
Cricket kind of wished she could open up

00:57:47.280 --> 00:57:49.440
sundew's brain and read it like a book.

00:57:49.500 --> 00:57:52.559
Especially all the parts about leaf wings

00:57:52.559 --> 00:57:55.380
and where they'd gone, and how they'd

00:57:55.380 --> 00:57:55.860
survived.

00:57:55.920 --> 00:57:58.619
Sundew wouldn't answer any of those

00:57:58.619 --> 00:58:01.199
questions, except with growling.

00:58:01.260 --> 00:58:03.539
Where's Luna?

00:58:03.599 --> 00:58:06.780
Sortell asked right away, raking another

00:58:06.780 --> 00:58:08.519
talon full of seaweed off his neck.

00:58:08.579 --> 00:58:11.699
I don't know, Cricket said.

00:58:11.760 --> 00:58:14.760
I saw her silk get caught in the wind and

00:58:14.760 --> 00:58:17.219
carry her out to sea, but Blue's

00:58:17.219 --> 00:58:19.199
metamorphosis was starting, so I had to

00:58:19.199 --> 00:58:19.800
bring him down here.

00:58:19.860 --> 00:58:22.199
I don't know what happened next.

00:58:22.260 --> 00:58:23.579
What did you see?

00:58:23.639 --> 00:58:24.780
What happened to you?

00:58:24.840 --> 00:58:27.960
Sortell rubbed his forehead as if it

00:58:27.960 --> 00:58:28.260
hurt.

00:58:28.320 --> 00:58:32.280
I tried to follow her, but the storm.

00:58:32.460 --> 00:58:35.280
He took a step toward the corridor and

00:58:35.280 --> 00:58:37.079
stumbled over a trailing piece of

00:58:37.079 --> 00:58:37.739
seaweed.

00:58:37.800 --> 00:58:39.480
I have to go find her.

00:58:39.539 --> 00:58:42.300
Shouldn't you rest for a bit first?

00:58:42.360 --> 00:58:43.860
Cricket suggested.

00:58:43.920 --> 00:58:47.579
Sundew says it's pouring outside, and you

00:58:47.579 --> 00:58:49.019
are just unconscious.

00:58:49.079 --> 00:58:51.659
I'll be fine, he insisted.

00:58:51.719 --> 00:58:53.219
Luna needs me.

00:58:53.340 --> 00:58:55.860
He took another staggering step toward

00:58:55.860 --> 00:58:56.400
the door.

00:58:56.460 --> 00:59:00.119
Don't be a skunk cabbage, Sundew said

00:59:00.119 --> 00:59:02.219
grumpily, turning her head to frown at

00:59:02.219 --> 00:59:02.519
him.

00:59:02.579 --> 00:59:05.039
You're entirely useless to any dragon in

00:59:05.039 --> 00:59:05.699
the state you're in.

00:59:05.760 --> 00:59:11.159
But he paused, struggling for words, and

00:59:11.159 --> 00:59:13.500
then slumped, perhaps feeling the extent

00:59:13.500 --> 00:59:15.000
of the battering the storm had given

00:59:15.000 --> 00:59:15.900
him.

00:59:15.960 --> 00:59:18.300
Look for her tomorrow, Cricket

00:59:18.300 --> 00:59:18.960
suggested.

00:59:19.019 --> 00:59:21.780
Or as soon as you're dry, or after you

00:59:21.780 --> 00:59:24.300
sleep or whatever you want, but you'll be

00:59:24.300 --> 00:59:26.039
much more likely to find her with well

00:59:26.039 --> 00:59:27.780
rested wings and a clear head.

00:59:27.840 --> 00:59:28.739
Don't you think?

00:59:28.860 --> 00:59:31.860
Maybe we can do some calculations about

00:59:31.860 --> 00:59:34.320
wind, speed, and currents, and figure out

00:59:34.320 --> 00:59:35.159
where she might be.

00:59:35.219 --> 00:59:37.559
It would help if I had some books

00:59:37.559 --> 00:59:37.739
though.

00:59:37.800 --> 00:59:40.440
I've never studied the ocean on this side

00:59:40.440 --> 00:59:41.219
of the continent.

00:59:41.280 --> 00:59:43.980
I wonder how buoyant Flame Soak is.

00:59:44.039 --> 00:59:45.179
Do you know anything about it?

00:59:45.239 --> 00:59:47.460
Swordtail sighed.

00:59:47.519 --> 00:59:49.440
Although Cricket couldn't tell if it was

00:59:49.440 --> 00:59:53.519
an exasperated sigh or a resigned sigh, or

00:59:53.519 --> 00:59:54.539
just exhaustion.

00:59:54.599 --> 00:59:57.780
Not much, he said.

00:59:57.840 --> 01:00:01.139
He turned away from the door, limped over

01:00:01.139 --> 01:00:03.599
to Blue's cocoon, and touched it lightly

01:00:03.599 --> 01:00:04.320
with his talons.

01:00:04.440 --> 01:00:06.480
Poor Blue.

01:00:06.539 --> 01:00:09.239
Was he, did he seem scared?

01:00:09.300 --> 01:00:13.079
Maybe a little, Cricket said, but he was

01:00:13.079 --> 01:00:13.679
very brave.

01:00:13.800 --> 01:00:15.780
He was mostly worried about you and

01:00:15.780 --> 01:00:16.199
Luna.

01:00:16.260 --> 01:00:18.780
Sortow rubbed at his eyes.

01:00:18.840 --> 01:00:21.179
That sucks.

01:00:21.239 --> 01:00:22.800
I wish we'd been here for him.

01:00:22.860 --> 01:00:25.920
She guessed they were both thinking the

01:00:25.920 --> 01:00:28.920
same thing, that they hoped Luna would be

01:00:28.920 --> 01:00:29.820
here when Blue woke up.

01:00:29.880 --> 01:00:33.780
The glow of Blue's cocoon lit Swordtell's

01:00:33.780 --> 01:00:36.059
face as he leaned down to study the

01:00:36.059 --> 01:00:36.960
silken strands.

01:00:37.079 --> 01:00:40.440
So I guess this means blues of flame sold

01:00:40.440 --> 01:00:41.519
too, he said.

01:00:41.579 --> 01:00:43.559
It looks like it.

01:00:43.679 --> 01:00:44.760
Cricket agreed.

01:00:44.820 --> 01:00:47.400
Good, said Sundew.

01:00:47.460 --> 01:00:49.860
They both turned and blinked at her.

01:00:49.920 --> 01:00:51.059
Good?

01:00:51.119 --> 01:00:52.199
Why?

01:00:52.260 --> 01:00:53.340
What does that mean?

01:00:53.460 --> 01:00:54.539
Cricket asked.

01:00:54.599 --> 01:00:57.480
It's useful, Sundu answered.

01:00:57.539 --> 01:01:00.059
Our cause doesn't need another normal

01:01:00.059 --> 01:01:02.760
boring, timid silk wing, but a flame

01:01:02.760 --> 01:01:03.420
silk?

01:01:03.420 --> 01:01:04.679
That's fantastic.

01:01:04.739 --> 01:01:07.619
You think blue is going to be useful?

01:01:07.739 --> 01:01:10.139
For the leaf wings?

01:01:10.199 --> 01:01:13.079
Swartell said, in a dangerous voice.

01:01:13.199 --> 01:01:14.940
How?

01:01:15.000 --> 01:01:17.699
Cricket took an instinctive step closer

01:01:17.699 --> 01:01:18.599
to the cocoon.

01:01:18.719 --> 01:01:21.059
As though Blue might sense her protection

01:01:21.059 --> 01:01:21.719
through the silk.

01:01:21.840 --> 01:01:23.820
What do you think he could do?

01:01:23.880 --> 01:01:26.880
Sundew flicked her wings back and tipped

01:01:26.880 --> 01:01:27.179
her head.

01:01:27.239 --> 01:01:31.440
A few 100 awesome, fiery things, she said

01:01:31.440 --> 01:01:33.179
starting with the most obvious.

01:01:33.239 --> 01:01:35.880
He's going to burn down all the hives for

01:01:35.880 --> 01:01:36.059
us.

01:01:36.119 --> 01:01:40.440
Chapter 3.

01:01:40.679 --> 01:01:44.460
No way, Cricket cried.

01:01:44.519 --> 01:01:45.840
Blue would never do that.

01:01:45.900 --> 01:01:47.699
Burn down.

01:01:47.760 --> 01:01:49.800
All the hives.

01:01:49.860 --> 01:01:53.099
Swordtell echoed, sounding a little more

01:01:53.099 --> 01:01:54.900
awestruck than cricket was comfortable

01:01:54.900 --> 01:01:55.139
with.

01:01:55.199 --> 01:01:57.719
Is that really your plan?

01:01:57.840 --> 01:01:59.760
Cricket asked Sundoo.

01:01:59.880 --> 01:02:02.519
She knew the leaf wings were here for a

01:02:02.519 --> 01:02:04.980
reason, and she thought she understood

01:02:04.980 --> 01:02:07.980
how angry they were at the hive wings, but

01:02:07.980 --> 01:02:10.139
this was so much more violent than she'd

01:02:10.139 --> 01:02:10.559
expected.

01:02:10.619 --> 01:02:13.800
Did the leaf wings want to restart the

01:02:13.800 --> 01:02:14.039
war?

01:02:14.099 --> 01:02:17.219
Even after they lost so badly the last

01:02:17.219 --> 01:02:17.460
time?

01:02:17.519 --> 01:02:20.519
I thought you said you just wanted the

01:02:20.519 --> 01:02:20.820
book.

01:02:20.940 --> 01:02:24.480
Sundew stabbed the pouch with a book of

01:02:24.480 --> 01:02:25.260
clear sight in it.

01:02:25.320 --> 01:02:26.639
Yes.

01:02:26.699 --> 01:02:28.739
When we thought the stupid thing would

01:02:28.739 --> 01:02:31.199
tell us the future, instead, it's

01:02:31.199 --> 01:02:32.099
completely useless.

01:02:32.159 --> 01:02:33.780
So what else are we supposed to do?

01:02:33.840 --> 01:02:36.900
Not burn down the hives?

01:02:36.960 --> 01:02:38.280
Cricket suggested.

01:02:38.340 --> 01:02:42.659
They're so big, Swartell murmured.

01:02:42.719 --> 01:02:45.480
He gazed up at the ceiling, as though he

01:02:45.480 --> 01:02:47.579
was imagining an entire city on fire.

01:02:47.639 --> 01:02:51.360
Even Luna never suggested destroying a

01:02:51.360 --> 01:02:51.960
whole hive.

01:02:52.019 --> 01:02:55.199
You'd be starting the tree wars all over

01:02:55.199 --> 01:02:56.699
again, Cricket said.

01:02:56.760 --> 01:02:59.880
If you try to burn any of the hives, Queen

01:02:59.880 --> 01:03:02.099
Wasp will send her whole army after you.

01:03:02.519 --> 01:03:05.760
She's not the only one with an army, Sundu

01:03:05.760 --> 01:03:06.960
said. scowling.

01:03:07.019 --> 01:03:08.760
This time, we'll be ready.

01:03:08.820 --> 01:03:11.099
The new tree wars will go very

01:03:11.099 --> 01:03:13.800
differently, especially if we start with

01:03:13.800 --> 01:03:15.360
burning the hive wings out of their

01:03:15.360 --> 01:03:15.719
cities.

01:03:15.840 --> 01:03:19.199
Are there that many leaf wings left?

01:03:19.320 --> 01:03:20.519
Cricket wondered.

01:03:20.579 --> 01:03:22.500
A whole army of them?

01:03:22.559 --> 01:03:26.460
Blue won't help you burn cities, Cricket

01:03:26.460 --> 01:03:27.480
said to Sundo.

01:03:27.599 --> 01:03:29.039
She was sure of that.

01:03:29.099 --> 01:03:31.320
He would never do anything to hurt

01:03:31.320 --> 01:03:31.679
anyone.

01:03:31.800 --> 01:03:34.980
Sordell gave her a strange look.

01:03:35.039 --> 01:03:39.300
Excuse me, he said, but you barely know

01:03:39.300 --> 01:03:39.840
Blue.

01:03:39.900 --> 01:03:42.360
I'm the one who's been his best friend

01:03:42.360 --> 01:03:43.619
basically his whole life.

01:03:43.679 --> 01:03:47.340
Well, then, do you see him burning down

01:03:47.340 --> 01:03:49.079
hives all across Pantala?

01:03:49.139 --> 01:03:50.159
Cricket asked.

01:03:50.219 --> 01:03:53.460
Maybe, if he had a good enough reason

01:03:53.460 --> 01:03:55.079
Swartell muttered.

01:03:55.139 --> 01:03:56.880
Exactly.

01:03:56.940 --> 01:04:00.239
Sundew nodded, as though she believed any

01:04:00.239 --> 01:04:02.099
dragon could be turned into a murderer

01:04:02.099 --> 01:04:03.119
with the right motivation.

01:04:03.119 --> 01:04:05.519
Cricket didn't believe that.

01:04:05.579 --> 01:04:08.219
At least, she couldn't believe it of

01:04:08.219 --> 01:04:08.519
blue.

01:04:08.579 --> 01:04:11.280
She'd spent almost her whole life

01:04:11.280 --> 01:04:14.159
watching her friends and family turn into

01:04:14.159 --> 01:04:17.099
cold-eyed tools for the queen, doing

01:04:17.099 --> 01:04:18.900
things they'd never do if they had the

01:04:18.900 --> 01:04:19.320
choice.

01:04:19.380 --> 01:04:21.960
Blue was the absolute opposite of all

01:04:21.960 --> 01:04:22.199
that.

01:04:22.260 --> 01:04:23.940
He had free will.

01:04:24.000 --> 01:04:27.179
And with it, he always chose to be kind

01:04:27.179 --> 01:04:28.260
to do the right thing.

01:04:28.380 --> 01:04:30.239
Didn't he?

01:04:30.300 --> 01:04:33.059
In the 5 days you've known him?

01:04:33.119 --> 01:04:36.360
A voice like sword tails whispered in her

01:04:36.360 --> 01:04:36.599
head.

01:04:36.659 --> 01:04:39.000
You think you know this dragon now?

01:04:39.119 --> 01:04:40.860
Because you hid together?

01:04:40.920 --> 01:04:43.800
Freed sword tail, broke into the temple

01:04:43.800 --> 01:04:44.639
and stole the book?

01:04:44.699 --> 01:04:47.039
Does he always do the right thing?

01:04:47.099 --> 01:04:50.400
Or could it be that you just think that

01:04:50.400 --> 01:04:52.860
the right thing is whatever he chooses to

01:04:52.860 --> 01:04:53.099
do?

01:04:53.219 --> 01:04:56.519
What if he thinks burning down hives is

01:04:56.519 --> 01:04:59.340
the right thing to do to save his tribe?

01:04:59.400 --> 01:05:02.159
Is that why you came back here?

01:05:02.159 --> 01:05:04.139
Instead of going to your parents?

01:05:04.199 --> 01:05:07.500
She asked Sundu, trying to shake off her

01:05:07.500 --> 01:05:07.920
doubts.

01:05:07.980 --> 01:05:09.599
You came for blue?

01:05:09.659 --> 01:05:11.519
Yes?

01:05:11.579 --> 01:05:13.019
Sundoo shrugged.

01:05:13.079 --> 01:05:14.639
I'd rather have Luna.

01:05:14.699 --> 01:05:17.280
She got so excellently mad about the book

01:05:17.280 --> 01:05:19.320
of clear sight that I'm sure she'd help

01:05:19.320 --> 01:05:19.500
us.

01:05:19.559 --> 01:05:22.800
I take her with me to burn the world down

01:05:22.800 --> 01:05:25.679
any day, but if we don't have Luna, we

01:05:25.679 --> 01:05:26.219
need blue.

01:05:26.280 --> 01:05:29.820
We'll have Luna, Sortell blurted.

01:05:29.880 --> 01:05:30.780
She's coming back.

01:05:30.840 --> 01:05:32.579
I'll find her.

01:05:32.699 --> 01:05:36.239
He paced agitatedly from the cocoon to

01:05:36.239 --> 01:05:37.199
the door and back again.

01:05:37.260 --> 01:05:40.559
Sundu crinkled her nose, and drew her

01:05:40.559 --> 01:05:42.539
tail out of the splatter zone from the

01:05:42.539 --> 01:05:44.159
seaweed still dangling off him.

01:05:44.219 --> 01:05:47.280
Blue will help you, but not by hurting

01:05:47.280 --> 01:05:48.000
other dragons.

01:05:48.059 --> 01:05:50.039
Cricket said stubbornly.

01:05:50.099 --> 01:05:52.739
How would burning down all the hives help

01:05:52.739 --> 01:05:53.699
the leaf wings anyway?

01:05:53.760 --> 01:05:56.699
Also, there's a problem.

01:05:56.760 --> 01:05:59.760
Even if Blue or Luna agreed to help you

01:05:59.760 --> 01:06:03.659
Sortell chimed in, one flame silk can't

01:06:03.659 --> 01:06:06.059
burn down a whole hive, let alone all 9

01:06:06.059 --> 01:06:06.780
of them.

01:06:06.840 --> 01:06:10.679
Well, he can try, Sundew said.

01:06:10.739 --> 01:06:13.559
Or we start with Wasp Hive, and then use

01:06:13.559 --> 01:06:15.480
those buried flame cells to help with the

01:06:15.480 --> 01:06:15.780
rest.

01:06:15.840 --> 01:06:17.280
We have to do something.

01:06:17.340 --> 01:06:20.159
Whatever takes out as many hive wings as

01:06:20.159 --> 01:06:20.460
we can.

01:06:20.519 --> 01:06:24.119
Sundew, Cricket cried.

01:06:24.179 --> 01:06:25.980
How can you say that?

01:06:26.039 --> 01:06:27.119
That's my tribe.

01:06:27.179 --> 01:06:30.119
I know some of them are terrible, but you

01:06:30.119 --> 01:06:32.639
don't really want to kill all of them, do

01:06:32.639 --> 01:06:32.880
you?

01:06:32.940 --> 01:06:37.079
Now sundew was scowling so ferociously

01:06:37.079 --> 01:06:39.300
that cricket could almost see sparks

01:06:39.300 --> 01:06:40.320
coming out of her wings.

01:06:40.380 --> 01:06:43.260
Her claws dug into the stone below her.

01:06:43.320 --> 01:06:45.179
Why not?

01:06:45.239 --> 01:06:47.579
That's exactly what they tried to do to

01:06:47.579 --> 01:06:47.820
us.

01:06:47.880 --> 01:06:51.719
I know, but doesn't that make you see how

01:06:51.719 --> 01:06:52.500
wrong it is?

01:06:52.559 --> 01:06:53.639
Cricket said.

01:06:53.699 --> 01:06:57.000
No, Sundu growled.

01:06:57.059 --> 01:06:58.679
We didn't do anything to them.

01:06:58.739 --> 01:07:00.420
They deserve it.

01:07:00.539 --> 01:07:02.219
They deserve to be wiped out.

01:07:02.280 --> 01:07:04.920
Every single hive wing.

01:07:04.980 --> 01:07:08.519
She frowned and dropped her gaze to the

01:07:08.519 --> 01:07:10.139
pout with a book of clear sight in it.

01:07:10.199 --> 01:07:13.559
Except you, but you're different.

01:07:13.679 --> 01:07:16.199
What if I'm not the only one who's

01:07:16.199 --> 01:07:16.559
different?

01:07:16.619 --> 01:07:18.960
Or what about the little dragonettes?

01:07:19.019 --> 01:07:20.880
Cricket said desperately.

01:07:20.940 --> 01:07:23.820
It's been so long since the tree wars.

01:07:23.880 --> 01:07:26.099
So many hive wings weren't even alive

01:07:26.099 --> 01:07:28.619
back then, or what about the ones who

01:07:28.619 --> 01:07:29.519
refused to fight?

01:07:29.579 --> 01:07:31.500
There were protesters.

01:07:31.559 --> 01:07:32.340
I know there were.

01:07:32.400 --> 01:07:33.539
I read about them.

01:07:33.599 --> 01:07:36.239
There were hive wings who tried to say no

01:07:36.239 --> 01:07:37.320
to Queen Wasp.

01:07:37.380 --> 01:07:39.239
There were some who wanted to help the

01:07:39.239 --> 01:07:40.800
leaf wings and save the trees.

01:07:40.860 --> 01:07:42.360
What about them?

01:07:42.480 --> 01:07:44.280
She stopped suddenly.

01:07:44.340 --> 01:07:46.559
Struck by a thought that she couldn't

01:07:46.559 --> 01:07:47.820
believe she'd never had before.

01:07:47.880 --> 01:07:51.119
How could there have been protesters?

01:07:51.239 --> 01:07:54.480
Wouldn't Queen Wasp have shut them down

01:07:54.480 --> 01:07:55.380
with her mind control?

01:07:55.440 --> 01:07:58.320
She wouldn't have allowed dissent during

01:07:58.320 --> 01:07:58.739
her war?

01:07:58.800 --> 01:08:01.260
She would never have let anyone disagree

01:08:01.260 --> 01:08:01.619
with her?

01:08:01.679 --> 01:08:04.440
So, how did they?

01:08:04.500 --> 01:08:06.539
Were they like me?

01:08:06.599 --> 01:08:09.539
Why couldn't she control them?

01:08:09.599 --> 01:08:11.760
Protesters?

01:08:11.820 --> 01:08:15.119
Sundu scoffed, shouting enthusiastic

01:08:15.119 --> 01:08:17.340
rhymes of the sky while their friends

01:08:17.340 --> 01:08:18.180
slaughtered us.

01:08:18.239 --> 01:08:20.340
Maybe that would have been useful if

01:08:20.340 --> 01:08:22.500
they'd kept it up, but they all vanished

01:08:22.500 --> 01:08:22.920
by the end.

01:08:22.979 --> 01:08:25.979
Not a single high wing objected when the

01:08:25.979 --> 01:08:27.239
last tree was cut down.

01:08:27.359 --> 01:08:29.519
Maybe they couldn't.

01:08:29.579 --> 01:08:32.100
Cricket's mind was racing now.

01:08:32.159 --> 01:08:34.920
Maybe the queen had them all in her power

01:08:34.920 --> 01:08:35.520
by then.

01:08:35.579 --> 01:08:38.819
Did she get rid of any dragons who

01:08:38.819 --> 01:08:39.659
couldn't be controlled?

01:08:39.720 --> 01:08:42.659
Or was it possible?

01:08:42.779 --> 01:08:45.239
Wasp hadn't been born with her mind

01:08:45.239 --> 01:08:46.319
control powers.

01:08:46.380 --> 01:08:48.600
Had they come to her sometime during the

01:08:48.600 --> 01:08:48.779
war?

01:08:48.840 --> 01:08:50.939
Personally?

01:08:51.000 --> 01:08:53.640
I vote yes for burning down the hives.

01:08:53.699 --> 01:08:56.039
Sortell offered suddenly.

01:08:56.100 --> 01:08:58.260
I think Luna will be all for it.

01:08:58.319 --> 01:09:00.059
If we can't convince Blue.

01:09:00.119 --> 01:09:02.579
Cricket whirled toward him.

01:09:02.640 --> 01:09:04.979
Haven't you thought about this at all?

01:09:05.039 --> 01:09:07.680
Imagine a hive burning.

01:09:07.739 --> 01:09:09.180
Who dies first?

01:09:09.239 --> 01:09:12.779
She pushed her glasses up, wishing she

01:09:12.779 --> 01:09:14.939
didn't sound so nervous and shaky.

01:09:15.000 --> 01:09:17.159
Silkwing dragonette sore tail.

01:09:17.220 --> 01:09:19.319
They're the ones who won't be able to fly

01:09:19.319 --> 01:09:20.039
to safety.

01:09:20.100 --> 01:09:23.699
Innocent, wingless dragonettes in their

01:09:23.699 --> 01:09:26.760
eggs and cocoons and schools and parks

01:09:26.760 --> 01:09:28.140
and in your webs.

01:09:28.199 --> 01:09:30.659
The webs are connected to the hives.

01:09:30.720 --> 01:09:32.520
If the cities burn.

01:09:32.579 --> 01:09:34.020
So do your homes.

01:09:34.140 --> 01:09:36.479
Most of the high wings will escape and be

01:09:36.479 --> 01:09:36.779
fine.

01:09:36.840 --> 01:09:38.939
But how would you save all the little

01:09:38.939 --> 01:09:39.659
silk wings?

01:09:39.779 --> 01:09:43.619
SoraTail stared down at his claws, looking

01:09:43.619 --> 01:09:44.099
pale.

01:09:44.159 --> 01:09:47.939
Killing off all the hive wings, or trying

01:09:47.939 --> 01:09:51.600
to, won't solve anything, Cricket said to

01:09:51.600 --> 01:09:52.199
Sundo.

01:09:52.260 --> 01:09:55.680
It'll just start another war that'll be

01:09:55.680 --> 01:09:58.079
even bloodier than the last, and this

01:09:58.079 --> 01:10:00.720
time, Queen Wasp will hunt you to the

01:10:00.720 --> 01:10:02.340
very end of the continent to make sure

01:10:02.340 --> 01:10:02.880
you're gone.

01:10:02.939 --> 01:10:06.239
And maybe all the silk wings too, if she

01:10:06.239 --> 01:10:07.560
thinks some of you were in on it.

01:10:07.619 --> 01:10:11.460
She won't kill us, Swordtell said

01:10:11.460 --> 01:10:11.939
bitterly.

01:10:12.000 --> 01:10:14.039
She needs our soak and our fire.

01:10:14.100 --> 01:10:16.199
We're valuable resources.

01:10:16.199 --> 01:10:18.720
She can make your lives worse though.

01:10:18.779 --> 01:10:20.460
Cricket pointed out.

01:10:20.520 --> 01:10:24.180
Sortell seized a talent full of seaweed

01:10:24.180 --> 01:10:26.039
and threw it against the wall with a damp

01:10:26.039 --> 01:10:26.699
splat.

01:10:26.819 --> 01:10:29.640
He stomped on her neat pile again and

01:10:29.640 --> 01:10:32.579
again, flattening it into a dark morass

01:10:32.579 --> 01:10:35.579
like crushed eels and bleeding squids.

01:10:35.640 --> 01:10:38.699
I just want to hurt them, he said.

01:10:38.760 --> 01:10:40.979
I want them to feel what it's like to be

01:10:40.979 --> 01:10:41.460
powerless.

01:10:41.520 --> 01:10:44.100
I want them to be stabbed with nerve

01:10:44.100 --> 01:10:46.560
toxins and have their loved ones ripped

01:10:46.560 --> 01:10:46.859
away.

01:10:46.920 --> 01:10:50.699
Yes, I want them to watch their homes

01:10:50.699 --> 01:10:51.779
burn to the ground.

01:10:51.840 --> 01:10:53.819
Sundew growled.

01:10:53.880 --> 01:10:56.640
I want them to feel in their souls what

01:10:56.640 --> 01:10:57.359
they've done to us.

01:10:57.420 --> 01:11:00.899
Sortell turned to the leaf wing.

01:11:00.960 --> 01:11:03.239
I'm in, he said.

01:11:03.300 --> 01:11:05.520
Whatever you want me to do, I'll follow

01:11:05.520 --> 01:11:06.300
you.

01:11:06.359 --> 01:11:09.239
Cricket buried her face and her talons.

01:11:09.300 --> 01:11:12.119
They were right, but they were also

01:11:12.119 --> 01:11:12.539
wrong.

01:11:12.659 --> 01:11:14.579
She needed blue.

01:11:14.640 --> 01:11:16.920
He was the one who understood Dragon

01:11:16.920 --> 01:11:17.819
Hearts.

01:11:17.880 --> 01:11:19.020
He'd know how to reach them.

01:11:19.079 --> 01:11:22.439
All she knew was chemistry and biology

01:11:22.439 --> 01:11:24.300
and math, and botany.

01:11:24.359 --> 01:11:27.359
How could she stack a pile of scientific

01:11:27.359 --> 01:11:30.479
logic up against their justifiable anger

01:11:30.479 --> 01:11:31.979
and hope to convince them?

01:11:32.039 --> 01:11:33.720
Wait.

01:11:33.779 --> 01:11:36.000
There was something Blue had said.

01:11:36.060 --> 01:11:39.779
The queen, she said suddenly, looking

01:11:39.779 --> 01:11:40.260
up.

01:11:40.319 --> 01:11:41.520
That's it.

01:11:41.579 --> 01:11:44.939
She's the problem, just like Blue said, we

01:11:44.939 --> 01:11:45.840
have to start with her.

01:11:45.960 --> 01:11:50.399
Or end with her. sundew said, or get to

01:11:50.399 --> 01:11:52.439
her in the middle. whenever it's most

01:11:52.439 --> 01:11:55.199
convenient to set her on fire, or bury

01:11:55.199 --> 01:11:58.140
her alive, or feed her to vampire ants.

01:11:58.260 --> 01:12:02.399
No, no, that's not what I mean, Cricket

01:12:02.399 --> 01:12:02.760
said.

01:12:02.819 --> 01:12:06.840
Queen Wasp is the heart of the problem, or

01:12:06.840 --> 01:12:08.399
like the brain, I guess.

01:12:08.460 --> 01:12:10.500
She controls the whole tribe.

01:12:10.560 --> 01:12:12.359
You saw her do it in the temple.

01:12:12.420 --> 01:12:14.579
You'll never have a chance as long as

01:12:14.579 --> 01:12:16.859
she's out there. inside everyone's

01:12:16.859 --> 01:12:17.279
minds.

01:12:17.399 --> 01:12:19.920
And more important, you'll never know

01:12:19.920 --> 01:12:22.199
which high wings might be on your side if

01:12:22.199 --> 01:12:22.800
they could be.

01:12:22.859 --> 01:12:26.340
Swordtail snorted, and Sandu gave him a

01:12:26.340 --> 01:12:28.859
right as if, look.

01:12:28.920 --> 01:12:33.600
They might be, Cricket insisted, like the

01:12:33.600 --> 01:12:34.380
librarian.

01:12:34.380 --> 01:12:36.779
Remember how she helped us as soon as she

01:12:36.779 --> 01:12:38.460
was free of Queen Wasp?

01:12:38.520 --> 01:12:40.920
My sister would too, if she had the

01:12:40.920 --> 01:12:43.380
choice, but none of them has a choice

01:12:43.380 --> 01:12:43.859
right now.

01:12:43.920 --> 01:12:46.680
If you can shut down the queen's mind

01:12:46.680 --> 01:12:48.840
control, you'll see who they really are.

01:12:48.899 --> 01:12:51.960
I think you'll find more allies than you

01:12:51.960 --> 01:12:52.859
realized you had.

01:12:52.920 --> 01:12:54.539
I hope.

01:12:54.600 --> 01:12:56.880
I hope there are good hive wings.

01:12:56.939 --> 01:12:58.380
Clear sight.

01:12:58.439 --> 01:13:00.600
Please let there be good hive wings

01:13:00.600 --> 01:13:01.859
underneath what we can see.

01:13:01.920 --> 01:13:04.739
Shut down the mind control.

01:13:04.859 --> 01:13:06.840
Sundew said thoughtfully.

01:13:06.899 --> 01:13:08.460
That would be useful.

01:13:08.520 --> 01:13:10.199
Is there a way to do that?

01:13:10.260 --> 01:13:12.119
Cricket side.

01:13:12.180 --> 01:13:13.619
I don't know.

01:13:13.680 --> 01:13:16.020
I've been looking for an explanation for

01:13:16.020 --> 01:13:17.340
it practically my whole life.

01:13:17.399 --> 01:13:19.500
Why doesn't it affect me?

01:13:19.560 --> 01:13:22.140
Whatever is wrong with me.

01:13:22.260 --> 01:13:24.659
Can we do it to other hive wings?

01:13:24.720 --> 01:13:27.119
There's nothing wrong with you.

01:13:27.239 --> 01:13:28.979
Swartell said.

01:13:29.039 --> 01:13:31.619
He sat down by the door, folding his

01:13:31.619 --> 01:13:32.279
wings back.

01:13:32.340 --> 01:13:34.560
The orange streaks on his scales

01:13:34.560 --> 01:13:36.720
reflected the flame silk glow like

01:13:36.720 --> 01:13:37.500
distant suns.

01:13:37.619 --> 01:13:40.140
We have to figure out what's right with

01:13:40.140 --> 01:13:42.239
you and wrong with everyone else in your

01:13:42.239 --> 01:13:42.600
tribe.

01:13:42.659 --> 01:13:44.819
Oh, wow.

01:13:44.880 --> 01:13:47.579
Maybe he doesn't completely hate me after

01:13:47.579 --> 01:13:47.760
all.

01:13:47.880 --> 01:13:50.939
Can't the leaf wings do that instead?

01:13:51.000 --> 01:13:53.039
Cricket asked Sundoo.

01:13:53.100 --> 01:13:55.500
Wouldn't it be better to break the mind

01:13:55.500 --> 01:13:57.479
control instead of starting a new war?

01:13:57.539 --> 01:14:01.380
It's a very sweet and silk wingish plan

01:14:01.380 --> 01:14:02.460
but how?

01:14:02.520 --> 01:14:04.079
Sundew demanded.

01:14:04.140 --> 01:14:06.779
Aren't you the smartest dragon around?

01:14:06.840 --> 01:14:08.760
Who else would know if you don't?

01:14:08.880 --> 01:14:11.880
Sortail jumped to his feet and stared at

01:14:11.880 --> 01:14:12.180
them.

01:14:12.239 --> 01:14:13.920
Yes?

01:14:14.039 --> 01:14:16.979
Sundew said, when the pause got awkward.

01:14:17.039 --> 01:14:21.479
I'm not sure, he said excitedly, but I

01:14:21.479 --> 01:14:22.979
think the chrysalis has a committee

01:14:22.979 --> 01:14:23.520
working on this.

01:14:23.579 --> 01:14:25.260
The what?

01:14:25.319 --> 01:14:27.239
Sundu said sharply.

01:14:27.300 --> 01:14:29.939
He bounced on his talons for a moment

01:14:29.939 --> 01:14:30.960
looking torn.

01:14:31.020 --> 01:14:33.600
I'm not supposed to tell anyone about

01:14:33.600 --> 01:14:35.220
them, he said at last.

01:14:35.279 --> 01:14:37.619
That was the most important rule.

01:14:37.680 --> 01:14:42.060
But then Io told Blue, and he told you, he

01:14:42.060 --> 01:14:42.720
said to Cricket.

01:14:42.779 --> 01:14:43.979
So.

01:14:45.180 --> 01:14:47.279
He didn't tell me much, she said

01:14:47.279 --> 01:14:49.920
remembering the soft brush of her wings

01:14:49.920 --> 01:14:52.979
against blues scales in the dark, the

01:14:52.979 --> 01:14:55.079
quiet vibration of his voice whispering

01:14:55.079 --> 01:14:57.180
are you with a chrysalis?

01:14:57.300 --> 01:15:00.119
The shiver that had gone down her spine

01:15:00.119 --> 01:15:02.340
as she wondered what the chrysalis was?

01:15:02.399 --> 01:15:04.920
And how many other secrets this beautiful

01:15:04.920 --> 01:15:08.220
blue dragon knew, and whether he'd stay

01:15:08.220 --> 01:15:10.079
and tell her everything, and be her

01:15:10.079 --> 01:15:10.319
friend?

01:15:10.380 --> 01:15:13.680
She'd felt as though she'd just found a

01:15:13.680 --> 01:15:16.319
new book, something she'd been desperate

01:15:16.319 --> 01:15:18.479
to read her whole life, without even

01:15:18.479 --> 01:15:19.739
knowing it existed.

01:15:19.800 --> 01:15:22.260
I'd really like to know more.

01:15:22.380 --> 01:15:26.159
Sortell hesitated, glancing at sundew.

01:15:26.220 --> 01:15:28.800
I'm sure they'd want to know about the

01:15:28.800 --> 01:15:31.020
leaf wings, but they'd want to know

01:15:31.020 --> 01:15:32.520
before I told you about them.

01:15:32.579 --> 01:15:36.060
I wish I knew what Luna would do right

01:15:36.060 --> 01:15:36.239
now.

01:15:36.300 --> 01:15:38.340
She'd tell us everything.

01:15:38.399 --> 01:15:40.260
Sundew said promptly.

01:15:40.319 --> 01:15:43.319
Cricket laughed, and Sundu gave her a

01:15:43.319 --> 01:15:44.520
sideways approving glance.

01:15:44.579 --> 01:15:49.260
All right, Swartell said, nodding at

01:15:49.260 --> 01:15:49.739
Sundew.

01:15:49.859 --> 01:15:52.140
I said I was with you after all.

01:15:52.199 --> 01:15:55.079
I think you can change everything for

01:15:55.079 --> 01:15:55.380
us.

01:15:55.439 --> 01:15:57.899
He took a deep breath.

01:15:57.960 --> 01:16:00.720
The chrysalis is a secret organization of

01:16:00.720 --> 01:16:02.579
silk wings, who are fighting for our

01:16:02.579 --> 01:16:03.000
freedom.

01:16:03.060 --> 01:16:06.960
That was exactly the thrilling, stirring

01:16:06.960 --> 01:16:08.399
answer cricket had imagined.

01:16:08.460 --> 01:16:12.060
Secret freedom fighters in the hives, she

01:16:12.060 --> 01:16:12.479
thought.

01:16:12.539 --> 01:16:15.000
Dragons who risk their lives to help

01:16:15.000 --> 01:16:15.359
others.

01:16:15.420 --> 01:16:18.600
But Sundew looked skeptical.

01:16:18.659 --> 01:16:21.239
Fighting, she said.

01:16:21.300 --> 01:16:23.760
Silk Wings doesn't match.

01:16:23.880 --> 01:16:27.840
Some of us can fight, Swartell said

01:16:27.840 --> 01:16:28.680
bristling.

01:16:28.739 --> 01:16:30.779
Some of us care about what's happened to

01:16:30.779 --> 01:16:31.380
our tribe.

01:16:31.439 --> 01:16:33.779
What do they do?

01:16:33.840 --> 01:16:35.100
Cricket asked.

01:16:35.159 --> 01:16:36.960
How do they keep it all secret?

01:16:37.020 --> 01:16:40.380
I mean, they must be amazing.

01:16:40.439 --> 01:16:42.060
I've never heard anything about silk

01:16:42.060 --> 01:16:44.220
wings fighting back or any kind of

01:16:44.220 --> 01:16:45.300
underground rebellion.

01:16:45.359 --> 01:16:48.659
Hmm, sundew grunted.

01:16:48.720 --> 01:16:50.760
Maybe because they don't actually do

01:16:50.760 --> 01:16:51.239
anything.

01:16:51.300 --> 01:16:53.159
They do.

01:16:53.220 --> 01:16:54.180
I'm sure they do.

01:16:54.239 --> 01:16:56.220
I don't really know what, though.

01:16:56.340 --> 01:16:58.800
Sore towels shifted on his feet.

01:16:58.859 --> 01:17:01.380
My sister and I just joined them

01:17:01.380 --> 01:17:01.739
recently.

01:17:01.800 --> 01:17:04.020
We haven't been given a mission or

01:17:04.020 --> 01:17:04.439
anything yet.

01:17:04.500 --> 01:17:06.420
They said to wait for further

01:17:06.420 --> 01:17:08.939
instructions after Luna got her wings.

01:17:09.000 --> 01:17:11.340
Luna was kind of the main contact

01:17:11.340 --> 01:17:11.880
person.

01:17:11.939 --> 01:17:13.619
She's the one who found them.

01:17:13.680 --> 01:17:16.319
But you could find them again?

01:17:16.439 --> 01:17:17.880
Sundew demanded.

01:17:17.939 --> 01:17:21.000
I think so, Swartell said.

01:17:21.060 --> 01:17:22.439
Luna could.

01:17:22.680 --> 01:17:23.819
If I find Luna.

01:17:23.939 --> 01:17:27.180
Even if you don't, Sundew said.

01:17:27.239 --> 01:17:30.000
When Blue comes out of that cocoon, we're

01:17:30.000 --> 01:17:31.560
going looking for this chrysalis of

01:17:31.560 --> 01:17:31.739
yours.

01:17:31.800 --> 01:17:34.260
She turned to cricket.

01:17:34.319 --> 01:17:37.199
We'll compare their notes and yours and

01:17:37.199 --> 01:17:38.880
see if we can find an answer to the mind

01:17:38.880 --> 01:17:39.539
control thing.

01:17:39.600 --> 01:17:42.720
Thank you, Cricket said.

01:17:42.779 --> 01:17:46.500
Don't get too excited, Sundu warned.

01:17:46.560 --> 01:17:49.079
Setting your whole tribe on fire is still

01:17:49.079 --> 01:17:50.039
my preferred option.

01:17:50.100 --> 01:17:52.260
But she listened to me.

01:17:52.319 --> 01:17:53.880
They both did.

01:17:53.939 --> 01:17:56.520
There's still a chance I can stop them

01:17:56.520 --> 01:17:58.680
from starting a new war and save my

01:17:58.680 --> 01:17:59.159
tribe.

01:17:59.220 --> 01:18:03.840
Or at least save Katy did, she thought

01:18:03.840 --> 01:18:04.560
anxiously.

01:18:04.619 --> 01:18:07.380
So, we wait for Blue.

01:18:07.439 --> 01:18:11.100
Cricket rested her talons on his cocoon

01:18:11.100 --> 01:18:13.199
feeling the warmth spread through her

01:18:13.199 --> 01:18:13.500
scales.

01:18:13.619 --> 01:18:18.000
I'd better go talk to my parents, Sundu

01:18:18.000 --> 01:18:18.659
said with a sigh.

01:18:18.779 --> 01:18:21.239
She started looping all the pouches

01:18:21.239 --> 01:18:23.819
around herself again, wrinkling her snout

01:18:23.819 --> 01:18:26.460
as the dampest ones squished against her

01:18:26.460 --> 01:18:26.939
scales.

01:18:27.000 --> 01:18:29.520
They're probably wondering where I've

01:18:29.520 --> 01:18:32.100
disappeared to with a book, and why I'm

01:18:32.100 --> 01:18:33.899
letting you lot interfere with my great

01:18:33.899 --> 01:18:34.560
destiny.

01:18:34.619 --> 01:18:37.560
Cricket tilted her head at sundew.

01:18:37.619 --> 01:18:39.899
What great destiny?

01:18:39.960 --> 01:18:42.239
The leaf wing waved her wings

01:18:42.239 --> 01:18:43.260
expressively.

01:18:43.319 --> 01:18:46.319
You know, saving the world, fiery

01:18:46.319 --> 01:18:48.119
vengeance, so on and so forth.

01:18:48.239 --> 01:18:50.579
Everything they raised me to do?

01:18:50.640 --> 01:18:52.739
They are not going to be excited about

01:18:52.739 --> 01:18:55.319
postponing their war so they can sit

01:18:55.319 --> 01:18:57.720
around for several days, waiting for a

01:18:57.720 --> 01:18:58.800
silk wing to wake up.

01:18:58.859 --> 01:19:01.140
Weren't they sitting around in that

01:19:01.140 --> 01:19:02.640
greenhouse before they met him?

01:19:02.699 --> 01:19:03.960
Cricket pointed out.

01:19:04.020 --> 01:19:06.600
I thought leaf wings were supposed to be

01:19:06.600 --> 01:19:09.000
good at acting like great patient trees.

01:19:09.060 --> 01:19:13.020
I'll tell them that, Sundew said with a

01:19:13.020 --> 01:19:15.600
grin, settling the last pouch in place.

01:19:15.659 --> 01:19:17.279
I'm sure it'll help.

01:19:17.340 --> 01:19:20.760
Cricket noticed, with disappointment, that

01:19:20.760 --> 01:19:22.739
Sundew was taking the book of Clearsight

01:19:22.739 --> 01:19:23.039
with her.

01:19:23.100 --> 01:19:25.739
She could understand why, though.

01:19:25.800 --> 01:19:28.020
The leaf wings had gone to a lot of

01:19:28.020 --> 01:19:28.800
trouble to get it.

01:19:28.859 --> 01:19:31.020
They weren't about to leave it in the

01:19:31.020 --> 01:19:32.399
talons of a hive wing again.

01:19:32.460 --> 01:19:34.619
Even a hive wing who'd helped them.

01:19:34.680 --> 01:19:37.140
And I'll go look for Luna again.

01:19:37.199 --> 01:19:40.560
A piece of seaweed slid free from sore

01:19:40.560 --> 01:19:42.840
tail's horns as he glanced out at the

01:19:42.840 --> 01:19:43.680
stone passageways.

01:19:43.739 --> 01:19:46.260
Cricket tried not to look too

01:19:46.260 --> 01:19:47.939
disappointed that they were both leaving

01:19:47.939 --> 01:19:48.779
her alone again.

01:19:48.779 --> 01:19:51.180
After keeping her company for such a

01:19:51.180 --> 01:19:54.239
short time, the boredom of the quiet cave

01:19:54.239 --> 01:19:56.039
loomed ahead of her once more.

01:19:56.100 --> 01:19:58.619
Will you be back soon?

01:19:58.680 --> 01:20:01.739
She said to Sundu, hoping she didn't

01:20:01.739 --> 01:20:03.000
sound completely pathetic.

01:20:03.119 --> 01:20:06.600
Yeah, don't worry, Sundoo said.

01:20:06.659 --> 01:20:09.300
What I do is up to me, not my parents.

01:20:09.420 --> 01:20:12.420
She hesitated for the briefest moment

01:20:12.420 --> 01:20:13.920
like she was about to say something

01:20:13.920 --> 01:20:14.279
else.

01:20:14.340 --> 01:20:16.920
On this mission anyway.

01:20:16.979 --> 01:20:20.340
Cricket wondered what the leaf wing

01:20:20.340 --> 01:20:21.000
wasn't saying.

01:20:21.060 --> 01:20:23.460
Was there something in her life that her

01:20:23.460 --> 01:20:24.359
parents did control?

01:20:24.420 --> 01:20:27.840
Maybe Sundew's not as free as she seems

01:20:27.840 --> 01:20:28.199
to be.

01:20:28.260 --> 01:20:31.079
Can one of you bring back food?

01:20:31.140 --> 01:20:32.220
Cricket asked.

01:20:32.279 --> 01:20:33.600
I mean, for blue?

01:20:33.659 --> 01:20:35.939
He'll be hungry when he comes out, won't

01:20:35.939 --> 01:20:36.180
he?

01:20:36.239 --> 01:20:37.920
After 5 days in there?

01:20:37.979 --> 01:20:39.960
Sortell nodded.

01:20:40.020 --> 01:20:43.140
I'd never been so hungry, he said.

01:20:43.199 --> 01:20:44.579
I'll find something for him.

01:20:44.640 --> 01:20:47.819
What do silk wings eat?

01:20:47.880 --> 01:20:50.220
Sundew said, starting toward the

01:20:50.220 --> 01:20:50.640
tunnels.

01:20:50.699 --> 01:20:51.960
Let me guess.

01:20:52.020 --> 01:20:54.300
Rainbows and honey and starlight.

01:20:54.359 --> 01:20:56.939
Yes, to honey, I think.

01:20:57.119 --> 01:20:58.140
Cricket said.

01:20:58.199 --> 01:21:01.680
She raised her voice as sundew's tail

01:21:01.680 --> 01:21:02.520
disappeared through the gap.

01:21:02.579 --> 01:21:06.060
Oh, and while you're out there, if you

01:21:06.060 --> 01:21:08.340
happen to see any books, I would love

01:21:08.340 --> 01:21:09.239
something to read.

01:21:09.359 --> 01:21:11.760
She wasn't entirely sure.

01:21:11.819 --> 01:21:14.340
But something like the sound of sundew

01:21:14.340 --> 01:21:16.439
laughing came echoing back from the

01:21:16.439 --> 01:21:16.979
walls.

01:21:17.039 --> 01:21:21.119
Chapter 4.

01:21:21.420 --> 01:21:23.640
Is it now?

01:21:23.699 --> 01:21:24.840
Cricket asked.

01:21:24.899 --> 01:21:25.920
Is it happening?

01:21:25.979 --> 01:21:27.300
Is that a sign?

01:21:27.359 --> 01:21:28.500
What does that mean?

01:21:28.560 --> 01:21:31.260
If you don't turn off your beehive

01:21:31.260 --> 01:21:31.680
brain?

01:21:31.739 --> 01:21:33.960
I'm going to stick a sleep flower up your

01:21:33.960 --> 01:21:34.439
snout.

01:21:34.560 --> 01:21:36.479
Sundew said crossly.

01:21:36.539 --> 01:21:37.680
Nothing is happening.

01:21:37.739 --> 01:21:40.199
It's looked exactly like that all day.

01:21:40.260 --> 01:21:43.439
She scowled down the pouch she'd been

01:21:43.439 --> 01:21:45.600
trying to mend, with a strand of sword

01:21:45.600 --> 01:21:46.319
tail silk.

01:21:46.380 --> 01:21:50.460
No, it hasn't, Cricket protested, circling

01:21:50.460 --> 01:21:51.479
Blue's cocoon.

01:21:51.539 --> 01:21:54.060
Look, this end is kind of bulging and

01:21:54.060 --> 01:21:55.979
crinkling, like it's about to split

01:21:55.979 --> 01:21:56.279
open.

01:21:56.340 --> 01:21:57.779
Right, sword tail?

01:21:57.840 --> 01:21:58.500
Don't you think so?

01:21:58.560 --> 01:22:03.180
Sure, he said, sleepily, without lifting

01:22:03.180 --> 01:22:04.739
his head or opening his eyes.

01:22:04.800 --> 01:22:07.500
She knew he'd spent the last 4 days

01:22:07.500 --> 01:22:10.439
flying and searching and scouring every

01:22:10.439 --> 01:22:13.560
island in Dragonfly Bay, snatching sleep

01:22:13.560 --> 01:22:15.600
only in brief moments back in the cave.

01:22:15.659 --> 01:22:18.960
And she knew that not finding Luna was a

01:22:18.960 --> 01:22:21.119
huge disappointment, and they should be

01:22:21.119 --> 01:22:24.239
very worried, and making grave faces, and

01:22:24.239 --> 01:22:25.500
muttering ominously.

01:22:25.500 --> 01:22:29.100
But seriously, Blue was about to come out

01:22:29.100 --> 01:22:30.000
of his cocoon.

01:22:30.119 --> 01:22:32.520
This was an extremely momentous

01:22:32.520 --> 01:22:32.939
occasion.

01:22:33.000 --> 01:22:35.460
Mostly because she'd get to see his

01:22:35.460 --> 01:22:38.159
wonderful face again, but also a little

01:22:38.159 --> 01:22:40.020
bit because she'd finally get to leave

01:22:40.020 --> 01:22:41.100
this cave.

01:22:41.399 --> 01:22:45.060
Hey, Blue, she said, to the shimmering

01:22:45.060 --> 01:22:46.800
blue purple shape beneath the silk.

01:22:46.920 --> 01:22:48.239
Can you hear me?

01:22:48.300 --> 01:22:49.500
We're here.

01:22:49.560 --> 01:22:51.300
We can't wait to see your wings.

01:22:51.420 --> 01:22:53.399
I have so many questions.

01:22:53.460 --> 01:22:54.960
What is it like in there?

01:22:55.020 --> 01:22:57.000
Do you remember any of it?

01:22:57.060 --> 01:22:59.039
Is it like a really long sleep?

01:22:59.100 --> 01:23:00.899
How do your wings feel?

01:23:00.960 --> 01:23:04.020
For the love of trees.

01:23:04.140 --> 01:23:05.520
Sundew growled.

01:23:05.579 --> 01:23:06.720
All right.

01:23:06.779 --> 01:23:09.539
I was afraid to share this because I know

01:23:09.539 --> 01:23:12.239
you're going to freak out, but if you

01:23:12.239 --> 01:23:14.399
promise to be quiet until blue comes out

01:23:14.399 --> 01:23:17.460
I'll tell you about how I saw one of your

01:23:17.460 --> 01:23:18.659
reading monkeys this morning.

01:23:18.720 --> 01:23:20.220
What?

01:23:20.279 --> 01:23:22.859
Cricket nearly flew through the ceiling.

01:23:22.920 --> 01:23:24.119
You did?

01:23:24.180 --> 01:23:26.100
Sundo, really, truly?

01:23:26.159 --> 01:23:27.899
And you're just telling me this now?

01:23:27.960 --> 01:23:33.119
She'd been so quiet and careful every

01:23:33.119 --> 01:23:35.880
time she crept around the caves, hoping

01:23:35.880 --> 01:23:37.619
to run into one of the tiny creatures.

01:23:37.739 --> 01:23:40.380
She couldn't believe it was Sundew who'd

01:23:40.380 --> 01:23:41.039
seen one instead.

01:23:41.100 --> 01:23:46.260
Yes, because of that, Sundoo said

01:23:46.260 --> 01:23:47.159
pointing at her.

01:23:47.220 --> 01:23:50.460
That face you're making, as if I found a

01:23:50.460 --> 01:23:52.439
staircase to the moons instead of just

01:23:52.439 --> 01:23:55.319
another weird animal, calm down or I

01:23:55.319 --> 01:23:55.979
won't tell it.

01:23:56.039 --> 01:23:58.979
I'm calm, Cricket said.

01:23:59.039 --> 01:24:01.800
She realized she was bouncing on her

01:24:01.800 --> 01:24:04.439
front talons and forced herself to sit on

01:24:04.439 --> 01:24:05.939
her tail and stay still.

01:24:06.000 --> 01:24:09.000
So totally calm.

01:24:09.119 --> 01:24:12.840
I already regret this, Sundew said.

01:24:12.960 --> 01:24:16.260
All right, but no questions.

01:24:16.319 --> 01:24:19.680
Cricket clamped her talons over her snout

01:24:19.680 --> 01:24:20.460
and nodded.

01:24:20.520 --> 01:24:23.520
Sundew threw the torn leaf pouch across

01:24:23.520 --> 01:24:25.500
the cave and picked up a bundle of

01:24:25.500 --> 01:24:28.020
berries, which she started sorting as she

01:24:28.020 --> 01:24:28.680
talked.

01:24:28.859 --> 01:24:31.560
This morning, I went down to the cavern

01:24:31.560 --> 01:24:33.359
where my parents and I 1st started

01:24:33.359 --> 01:24:36.539
digging to wasp hive. sundew started.

01:24:36.600 --> 01:24:39.479
I've been checking it regularly to make

01:24:39.479 --> 01:24:41.279
sure the hive wings didn't follow our

01:24:41.279 --> 01:24:42.960
tunnel from the flame silk cavern.

01:24:43.020 --> 01:24:45.180
I figured I'd blocked it up pretty well

01:24:45.180 --> 01:24:46.319
but safer to be sure.

01:24:46.380 --> 01:24:48.539
How did you block?

01:24:48.659 --> 01:24:50.279
Oops, sorry.

01:24:50.340 --> 01:24:53.100
Cricket corrected herself quickly at

01:24:53.100 --> 01:24:54.119
Sundew's glare.

01:24:54.180 --> 01:24:57.000
Our hole was still completely filled in

01:24:57.000 --> 01:24:59.399
but as I scouted the perimeter of the

01:24:59.399 --> 01:25:02.460
cave, I found another much smaller hole

01:25:02.460 --> 01:25:03.300
in the wall.

01:25:03.420 --> 01:25:06.060
I decided to spy on it for a while, in

01:25:06.060 --> 01:25:07.439
case anything edible came out.

01:25:07.500 --> 01:25:10.439
Cricket wasn't sure why she had been

01:25:10.439 --> 01:25:12.659
surprised to discover that leaf wings

01:25:12.659 --> 01:25:13.500
were carnivores.

01:25:13.560 --> 01:25:16.380
It fit with a bloodthirsty, violent

01:25:16.380 --> 01:25:18.359
picture of them that Queen Wasp had

01:25:18.359 --> 01:25:20.939
painted over the last half century, and

01:25:20.939 --> 01:25:23.939
yet, in her own heart of hearts, and

01:25:23.939 --> 01:25:25.680
maybe because of the beautiful drawings

01:25:25.680 --> 01:25:28.500
of them in the oldest books, she'd

01:25:28.500 --> 01:25:31.199
somehow imagined a tranquil green tribe

01:25:31.199 --> 01:25:33.899
sharing sweet potatoes and cranberries

01:25:33.899 --> 01:25:35.100
across the treetops.

01:25:35.159 --> 01:25:38.039
So the 1st time sundew brought back a

01:25:38.039 --> 01:25:40.319
pair of headless pigeons and devoured

01:25:40.319 --> 01:25:42.899
hers in 2 bites, Cricket had been rather

01:25:42.899 --> 01:25:43.380
startled.

01:25:43.500 --> 01:25:47.579
And vegetarian sword tail had been openly

01:25:47.579 --> 01:25:48.119
horrified.

01:25:48.180 --> 01:25:53.579
Finally, sundew went on, I heard a tip

01:25:53.579 --> 01:25:54.899
tap patter kind of noise.

01:25:54.960 --> 01:25:57.600
I squinted at the hole and saw a little

01:25:57.600 --> 01:25:58.319
head poke out.

01:25:58.380 --> 01:26:00.659
It was just like the one you described

01:26:00.659 --> 01:26:03.479
from under the savannah, fluffy black for

01:26:03.479 --> 01:26:06.479
on its head, scraps of silver, silk, and

01:26:06.479 --> 01:26:09.239
gray fur on its body, hairless, long

01:26:09.239 --> 01:26:10.020
brown paws.

01:26:10.079 --> 01:26:12.720
Perfect for holding books.

01:26:12.840 --> 01:26:14.279
Cricket breathed.

01:26:14.340 --> 01:26:16.920
This one didn't have a book.

01:26:17.039 --> 01:26:20.760
Sundew pointed out, it had a stick with a

01:26:20.760 --> 01:26:21.779
bit of fire on the end of it.

01:26:21.840 --> 01:26:24.359
Where did...

01:26:24.720 --> 01:26:27.720
I mean, um, I wish I knew where that came

01:26:27.720 --> 01:26:29.699
from, Cricket said quickly.

01:26:29.760 --> 01:26:32.640
The one she'd seen had had a fire too.

01:26:32.699 --> 01:26:35.399
Did the reading monkeys have access to

01:26:35.399 --> 01:26:36.420
flame silk somehow?

01:26:36.479 --> 01:26:40.260
Anyway, it saw me, shrieked like a snake

01:26:40.260 --> 01:26:42.479
bit panther, and ran away before I could

01:26:42.479 --> 01:26:44.880
eat it, Sundew said grumpily.

01:26:44.939 --> 01:26:48.479
But you wouldn't have, Cricket said

01:26:48.479 --> 01:26:49.319
right?

01:26:49.380 --> 01:26:51.600
You wouldn't eat something that can read

01:26:51.600 --> 01:26:53.220
right, sundew?

01:26:53.279 --> 01:26:56.579
I'm going to need a little more proof

01:26:56.579 --> 01:26:58.859
they can do that before I start giving up

01:26:58.859 --> 01:27:00.779
on prey, Sundew said.

01:27:00.840 --> 01:27:03.659
But really, I wouldn't eat something

01:27:03.659 --> 01:27:05.520
you're so completely obsessed with

01:27:05.520 --> 01:27:08.340
because I know I'd never hear the end of

01:27:08.340 --> 01:27:08.760
it from you.

01:27:08.819 --> 01:27:12.060
Well, if I have to annoy you into

01:27:12.060 --> 01:27:14.579
protecting cool new species, then that's

01:27:14.579 --> 01:27:17.100
what I have to do, Cricket said nobly.

01:27:17.159 --> 01:27:20.220
It's so unfair you saw one instead of

01:27:20.220 --> 01:27:20.520
me.

01:27:20.579 --> 01:27:21.899
You're so lucky.

01:27:22.020 --> 01:27:24.239
Sundew rolled her eyes.

01:27:24.300 --> 01:27:27.600
That's me, the luckiest dragon.

01:27:27.659 --> 01:27:30.899
A tearing sound came from the cocoon.

01:27:30.960 --> 01:27:33.539
Soartell leaped to his feet and joined

01:27:33.539 --> 01:27:35.939
Cricket, crouching by the end with a rip

01:27:35.939 --> 01:27:36.239
in it.

01:27:36.359 --> 01:27:39.359
I was right, she whispered to him.

01:27:39.420 --> 01:27:41.159
I knew it was about to happen.

01:27:41.279 --> 01:27:42.180
It's happening.

01:27:42.239 --> 01:27:44.699
Do you remember your metamorphosis?

01:27:44.760 --> 01:27:46.619
Is there anything we should do when he

01:27:46.619 --> 01:27:46.920
comes out?

01:27:47.039 --> 01:27:51.600
Just give him some space, Sortell said.

01:27:51.659 --> 01:27:54.420
His wings twitching, and his eyes fixed

01:27:54.420 --> 01:27:56.279
on the shape of claws poking through the

01:27:56.279 --> 01:27:56.520
silk.

01:27:56.579 --> 01:28:00.060
He'll want to breathe for a moment, and

01:28:00.060 --> 01:28:00.600
then eat something.

01:28:00.659 --> 01:28:03.600
He swept the pile of fruit they had

01:28:03.600 --> 01:28:04.859
gathered closer with his tail.

01:28:04.979 --> 01:28:08.039
Cricket wished she had her notebook.

01:28:08.100 --> 01:28:10.439
She'd never seen a metamorphosis before

01:28:10.439 --> 01:28:13.020
and the books were always frustratingly

01:28:13.020 --> 01:28:15.420
vague about silkwing details.

01:28:15.479 --> 01:28:17.819
If she could take notes, maybe one day

01:28:17.819 --> 01:28:19.380
she could write a paper about what it

01:28:19.380 --> 01:28:21.899
looked like, and how it worked, and every

01:28:21.899 --> 01:28:23.159
step of the process.

01:28:23.220 --> 01:28:24.600
No.

01:28:24.659 --> 01:28:26.460
I'll never get to do that.

01:28:26.520 --> 01:28:29.100
I'm not going to be a published

01:28:29.100 --> 01:28:29.760
scientist.

01:28:29.819 --> 01:28:32.880
There's no normal hive wing life ahead

01:28:32.880 --> 01:28:33.239
for me.

01:28:33.300 --> 01:28:39.060
Unless, what if we defeat Queen Wasp, then

01:28:39.060 --> 01:28:39.600
what happens?

01:28:39.720 --> 01:28:43.199
Could the hive wings and leaf wings and

01:28:43.199 --> 01:28:45.600
silk wings all start living in harmony?

01:28:45.659 --> 01:28:48.359
Sharing the hives, planting food

01:28:48.359 --> 01:28:50.819
publishing books, going to school

01:28:50.819 --> 01:28:51.300
together?

01:28:51.359 --> 01:28:54.840
Cricket glanced over at sundew, and felt

01:28:54.840 --> 01:28:56.579
like the weight of one of the moons was

01:28:56.579 --> 01:28:57.720
settling on her wings.

01:28:57.779 --> 01:29:00.479
The leaf wings aren't going to forgive

01:29:00.479 --> 01:29:00.720
us.

01:29:00.779 --> 01:29:02.760
How can we ever move on?

01:29:02.760 --> 01:29:05.340
As though we didn't try to wipe out the

01:29:05.340 --> 01:29:08.100
leaf wings or dominate the silk wings.

01:29:08.159 --> 01:29:11.460
How can they ever trust us or want to

01:29:11.460 --> 01:29:12.720
live alongside us again?

01:29:12.779 --> 01:29:14.399
After what we've done.

01:29:14.460 --> 01:29:18.359
She couldn't imagine a path from sundew's

01:29:18.359 --> 01:29:21.000
anger or her plan to wipe out the hive

01:29:21.000 --> 01:29:24.119
wings, to a world in which the 3 tribes

01:29:24.119 --> 01:29:24.899
lived in peace.

01:29:24.960 --> 01:29:26.939
She'd been trying for days.

01:29:27.000 --> 01:29:29.640
But her thoughts kept circling back to

01:29:29.640 --> 01:29:30.479
the mind control.

01:29:30.539 --> 01:29:33.600
As far as she could see, her only hope

01:29:33.600 --> 01:29:36.239
for avoiding a war, was to convince

01:29:36.239 --> 01:29:38.760
Sundew that hive wings with free will

01:29:38.760 --> 01:29:40.859
would be on the leaf wings side.

01:29:40.920 --> 01:29:45.119
Which, if she was honest with herself, she

01:29:45.119 --> 01:29:46.500
wasn't at all sure of.

01:29:46.560 --> 01:29:50.220
A familiar purple snout burst through the

01:29:50.220 --> 01:29:52.800
silk, shaking filaments off his horns.

01:29:52.859 --> 01:29:56.340
Cricket held her breath, as Blue wriggled

01:29:56.340 --> 01:29:58.560
and shoved and slid out onto the stone

01:29:58.560 --> 01:30:01.560
floor, kicking his shredded cocoon away

01:30:01.560 --> 01:30:01.920
from him.

01:30:01.979 --> 01:30:05.520
He struggled free, and finally stood for

01:30:05.520 --> 01:30:07.859
a moment with his head bowed, taking deep

01:30:07.859 --> 01:30:11.220
breaths, and then he looked up, met

01:30:11.220 --> 01:30:14.699
Cricket's eyes, smiled, and spread his

01:30:14.699 --> 01:30:15.000
wings.

01:30:15.060 --> 01:30:18.600
Cricket wondered if her smile could lift

01:30:18.600 --> 01:30:19.319
her through the ceiling.

01:30:19.380 --> 01:30:23.460
Blue's wings were glorious, shimmering

01:30:23.460 --> 01:30:25.979
purple and blue like sapphires and

01:30:25.979 --> 01:30:27.359
violets tumbled together.

01:30:27.420 --> 01:30:29.819
He was glorious.

01:30:29.880 --> 01:30:32.340
She knew she loved more than his

01:30:32.340 --> 01:30:34.739
beautiful scales. and his lovely face.

01:30:34.800 --> 01:30:38.279
She loved his kindness, and his sweetness

01:30:38.279 --> 01:30:40.859
and his sense of humor, and the way he

01:30:40.859 --> 01:30:43.859
thought about other dragons so deeply, and

01:30:43.859 --> 01:30:45.359
the fact that he seemed to have no idea

01:30:45.359 --> 01:30:47.220
at all how handsome he was.

01:30:47.279 --> 01:30:51.300
But oh my goodness, she also really loved

01:30:51.300 --> 01:30:56.399
his lovely face, Cricket, he said, in a

01:30:56.399 --> 01:30:57.060
hoarse voice.

01:30:57.119 --> 01:30:58.800
You stayed.

01:30:58.859 --> 01:31:02.159
Of course I did, she said.

01:31:02.220 --> 01:31:06.840
Thank you. he said, and her heart felt as

01:31:06.840 --> 01:31:08.100
if it might burst.

01:31:08.279 --> 01:31:10.020
I bet that was.

01:31:10.140 --> 01:31:12.720
He paused and thought for a moment.

01:31:12.779 --> 01:31:15.180
Hmm, boring.

01:31:15.239 --> 01:31:16.800
She laughed.

01:31:16.859 --> 01:31:17.819
Just a little.

01:31:17.880 --> 01:31:21.060
Can he see how much I adore him?

01:31:21.119 --> 01:31:22.800
Am I too obvious?

01:31:22.859 --> 01:31:24.899
I wish I knew what he feels.

01:31:24.960 --> 01:31:28.979
Sortel stepped forward and offered a leaf

01:31:28.979 --> 01:31:29.819
cup full of water.

01:31:29.939 --> 01:31:32.640
Blue took it gratefully, and drank the

01:31:32.640 --> 01:31:32.939
whole thing.

01:31:33.000 --> 01:31:36.899
Nice wings, Swartell observed.

01:31:36.960 --> 01:31:39.659
Not as handsome as mine, of course, but

01:31:39.659 --> 01:31:40.140
pretty cool.

01:31:40.199 --> 01:31:41.220
See?

01:31:41.279 --> 01:31:43.140
I told you metamorphosis wasn't that

01:31:43.140 --> 01:31:43.319
bad.

01:31:43.439 --> 01:31:46.380
Blue flicked his friend's tail with his

01:31:46.380 --> 01:31:46.680
own.

01:31:46.739 --> 01:31:49.920
I can't believe it's over, he said.

01:31:50.039 --> 01:31:52.140
After all those years of worrying about

01:31:52.140 --> 01:31:52.319
it.

01:31:52.380 --> 01:31:55.439
He stretched his wings as wide as they

01:31:55.439 --> 01:31:57.899
would go, and wrinkled his snout, as

01:31:57.899 --> 01:31:59.340
though he was trying to stop smiling.

01:31:59.460 --> 01:32:02.579
Remember how Luna and I were waiting for

01:32:02.579 --> 01:32:03.539
you when you came out?

01:32:03.600 --> 01:32:06.600
With a giant box of honey drops, and

01:32:06.600 --> 01:32:08.640
Luna's weird banana mash cake.

01:32:08.699 --> 01:32:10.739
Sortell said, grinning.

01:32:10.859 --> 01:32:13.739
You did a really good job of pretending

01:32:13.739 --> 01:32:15.539
to like it, Blue said.

01:32:15.600 --> 01:32:18.960
He studied his wings, which looked shiny

01:32:18.960 --> 01:32:21.420
and damp in a brand new kind of way.

01:32:21.479 --> 01:32:24.899
I guess the one upside of being fugitives

01:32:24.899 --> 01:32:26.699
she can't make one of those for me.

01:32:26.760 --> 01:32:29.640
His eyes searched the cave.

01:32:29.699 --> 01:32:31.619
Hey, sundew.

01:32:31.680 --> 01:32:35.220
Hey yourself, Silkwing, Sundu said

01:32:35.220 --> 01:32:35.699
gruffly.

01:32:35.760 --> 01:32:38.039
You sure took your time growing those

01:32:38.039 --> 01:32:38.640
flappers.

01:32:38.699 --> 01:32:41.579
Cricket wondered whether Blue could tell

01:32:41.579 --> 01:32:43.319
that the leaf wing was actually happy to

01:32:43.319 --> 01:32:45.659
see him, or whether it was only cricket

01:32:45.659 --> 01:32:47.819
who was getting used to the mostly hidden

01:32:47.819 --> 01:32:49.800
expressions under sundew scows.

01:32:49.859 --> 01:32:53.220
So, are you actually a flame silk?

01:32:53.279 --> 01:32:54.420
Can you make fire?

01:32:54.479 --> 01:32:56.579
I feel like I can.

01:32:56.640 --> 01:33:00.180
Blue held out its talons, and glowing

01:33:00.180 --> 01:33:02.819
flame spiraled from each wrist into

01:33:02.819 --> 01:33:04.619
smoking curls of light on the floor.

01:33:04.680 --> 01:33:08.520
Sundew inspected them, nodded approvingly

01:33:08.520 --> 01:33:10.859
and scooped them into a small stone jar

01:33:10.859 --> 01:33:11.819
from one of her pouches.

01:33:11.880 --> 01:33:15.659
While she did that, Blue took a short

01:33:15.659 --> 01:33:17.460
shuddering breath and looked at Sore

01:33:17.460 --> 01:33:17.760
Tail.

01:33:17.880 --> 01:33:21.239
And by the expression on his face, Cricket

01:33:21.239 --> 01:33:22.979
could tell that he'd already guessed the

01:33:22.979 --> 01:33:23.220
worst.

01:33:23.340 --> 01:33:26.579
Luna, he said anxiously.

01:33:26.640 --> 01:33:30.060
I'm sorry, Blue, Sortell said.

01:33:30.119 --> 01:33:31.439
His wings drooping.

01:33:31.500 --> 01:33:32.880
I can't find her.

01:33:32.939 --> 01:33:34.500
I've looked and looked.

01:33:34.560 --> 01:33:37.380
Blue was quiet for a long moment.

01:33:37.439 --> 01:33:40.079
Cricket took a step closer to those

01:33:40.079 --> 01:33:43.140
iridescent wings, and gently twined her

01:33:43.140 --> 01:33:43.859
tail around his.

01:33:43.920 --> 01:33:47.039
He seemed so much bigger suddenly.

01:33:47.100 --> 01:33:51.539
If you haven't found her, Blue said, and

01:33:51.539 --> 01:33:52.560
she must still be alive.

01:33:52.680 --> 01:33:56.039
We'd feel it if she wasn't, don't you

01:33:56.039 --> 01:33:56.220
think?

01:33:56.279 --> 01:33:58.920
Maybe she's hiding somewhere and hasn't

01:33:58.920 --> 01:33:59.460
made it back yet.

01:33:59.520 --> 01:34:01.319
She'll find us again.

01:34:01.380 --> 01:34:03.600
I'm sure she will, swordtail.

01:34:03.659 --> 01:34:05.819
She's probably out there worrying about

01:34:05.819 --> 01:34:08.460
us, twice as much as we're worrying about

01:34:08.460 --> 01:34:08.760
her.

01:34:08.819 --> 01:34:12.779
Well, she's not finding us here, Sundew

01:34:12.779 --> 01:34:13.920
said, standing up.

01:34:13.979 --> 01:34:16.560
She dropped her sorted berries into

01:34:16.560 --> 01:34:19.319
sections of a leaf bag and put it on, then

01:34:19.319 --> 01:34:21.300
started assembling all her other pouches

01:34:21.300 --> 01:34:21.779
around her.

01:34:21.779 --> 01:34:24.539
In some careful order, Cricket hadn't

01:34:24.539 --> 01:34:24.960
mapped out yet.

01:34:25.020 --> 01:34:27.899
We've already stayed way too long.

01:34:27.960 --> 01:34:30.060
It's a miracle the hive wings searching

01:34:30.060 --> 01:34:31.380
the coast haven't found us yet.

01:34:31.439 --> 01:34:35.039
It's not a miracle, Swordell said.

01:34:35.100 --> 01:34:36.000
It's you.

01:34:36.060 --> 01:34:37.920
You hid the entrance to this tunnel

01:34:37.920 --> 01:34:38.340
really well.

01:34:38.460 --> 01:34:40.920
I've seen high wing guards walk right

01:34:40.920 --> 01:34:42.659
past it as they hunt through the cave.

01:34:42.720 --> 01:34:45.659
I've gotten lost like 8 times coming back

01:34:45.659 --> 01:34:47.699
from the bay because it's so hard to

01:34:47.699 --> 01:34:47.939
spot.

01:34:48.000 --> 01:34:51.960
He hand a blue, a talon full of kumquats

01:34:51.960 --> 01:34:53.159
and sliced yams.

01:34:53.220 --> 01:34:54.899
I don't know how she did it.

01:34:54.960 --> 01:34:57.000
Wait until you see what she did with the

01:34:57.000 --> 01:34:58.020
vines and the moss?

01:34:58.079 --> 01:34:59.579
It's kind of amazing.

01:34:59.640 --> 01:35:02.220
Sunday made the face.

01:35:02.279 --> 01:35:02.939
She always made.

01:35:02.939 --> 01:35:05.220
When cricket or sore tail said something

01:35:05.220 --> 01:35:05.880
nice about her.

01:35:05.939 --> 01:35:08.399
As though her expressions had no practice

01:35:08.399 --> 01:35:10.140
reacting to compliments.

01:35:10.199 --> 01:35:13.020
So they just threw out a few spasms, and

01:35:13.020 --> 01:35:14.220
then went back to scowling.

01:35:14.279 --> 01:35:17.939
Well, it won't last forever, she said.

01:35:18.000 --> 01:35:20.100
Let's get to a hive and find the

01:35:20.100 --> 01:35:20.760
chrysalis.

01:35:20.819 --> 01:35:23.460
The chrysalis.

01:35:23.520 --> 01:35:26.399
Blue echoed between bites, looking at

01:35:26.399 --> 01:35:27.060
sword tail.

01:35:27.119 --> 01:35:30.359
We'll explain on the way, cricket

01:35:30.359 --> 01:35:30.899
offered.

01:35:30.960 --> 01:35:32.460
So what?

01:35:32.520 --> 01:35:34.439
Back to Wasp Pive?

01:35:34.500 --> 01:35:35.520
Sundew asked.

01:35:35.579 --> 01:35:37.020
Blue shuttered.

01:35:37.079 --> 01:35:40.079
Um, is that our only option?

01:35:40.140 --> 01:35:43.140
It's not the best place to find the

01:35:43.140 --> 01:35:43.920
chrysalis.

01:35:43.979 --> 01:35:45.239
Swartell said.

01:35:45.300 --> 01:35:48.060
I mean, it's the most dangerous hive.

01:35:48.119 --> 01:35:49.500
Swarming with soldiers.

01:35:49.560 --> 01:35:51.659
I'm not even sure they have any members

01:35:51.659 --> 01:35:52.380
there.

01:35:52.439 --> 01:35:54.659
Sundew gave him a hard luck.

01:35:54.720 --> 01:35:57.420
I thought you said they were in all the

01:35:57.420 --> 01:35:57.960
hives.

01:35:58.020 --> 01:36:02.640
I think they are, he said, but let's try

01:36:02.640 --> 01:36:04.619
another one, just to be safe, is my

01:36:04.619 --> 01:36:05.039
suggestion.

01:36:05.159 --> 01:36:07.739
Where are we, exactly?

01:36:07.739 --> 01:36:08.880
Cricket said.

01:36:08.939 --> 01:36:12.180
She took sundew's discarded leaf pouch

01:36:12.180 --> 01:36:15.119
flattened out one side of it, and flies

01:36:15.119 --> 01:36:17.520
to rough map of Pentala into the thick

01:36:17.520 --> 01:36:19.439
pale green surface with her claws.

01:36:19.500 --> 01:36:23.100
We came from wasp hives, up here.

01:36:23.159 --> 01:36:25.560
She stabbed a little hole in the spot

01:36:25.560 --> 01:36:27.420
where a wasp hive would be on the map.

01:36:27.479 --> 01:36:29.880
Kind of here.

01:36:30.000 --> 01:36:33.300
Swordtail said, pointing to a spot on the

01:36:33.300 --> 01:36:36.239
coast of Dragonfly Bay, away south of

01:36:36.239 --> 01:36:37.020
Wasp Hive.

01:36:37.079 --> 01:36:39.840
So, let's think.

01:36:39.899 --> 01:36:42.840
The next closest hives are these three.

01:36:42.899 --> 01:36:46.140
Cricket poked 3 holes in the map.

01:36:46.199 --> 01:36:49.199
Yellow jacket hive, bloodworm hive.

01:36:49.260 --> 01:36:51.960
Or jewel hive.

01:36:52.020 --> 01:36:55.560
She hesitated, feeling an old familiar

01:36:55.560 --> 01:36:57.899
twist, like thorns around her heart.

01:36:57.960 --> 01:36:59.640
What is it?

01:36:59.699 --> 01:37:02.100
Blue asked, touching her shoulder.

01:37:02.159 --> 01:37:05.340
Why does jewel hive make you sad?

01:37:05.399 --> 01:37:08.579
It's nothing really, she said.

01:37:08.640 --> 01:37:12.000
Just, that's where my mother moved, when

01:37:12.000 --> 01:37:12.960
she left us.

01:37:13.079 --> 01:37:15.720
Cricket could remember that day really

01:37:15.720 --> 01:37:16.500
clearly.

01:37:16.560 --> 01:37:18.239
She'd been 3 years old.

01:37:18.300 --> 01:37:20.220
Katy did had been 12.

01:37:20.579 --> 01:37:22.500
But still living at home and without a

01:37:22.500 --> 01:37:24.840
partner, chosen or assigned.

01:37:24.960 --> 01:37:27.600
It had felt completely out of the blue to

01:37:27.600 --> 01:37:27.840
her.

01:37:27.899 --> 01:37:30.659
Like a hive suddenly collapsing for no

01:37:30.659 --> 01:37:30.899
reason.

01:37:30.960 --> 01:37:33.840
Mother had been standing with all her

01:37:33.840 --> 01:37:35.640
belongings at the door when they returned

01:37:35.640 --> 01:37:38.159
from school, her books being loaded into

01:37:38.159 --> 01:37:40.439
baskets by a pair of sturdy silk wings.

01:37:40.500 --> 01:37:43.260
She looked faintly annoyed that they had

01:37:43.260 --> 01:37:44.760
returned before she could disappear.

01:37:44.819 --> 01:37:48.119
Katy did had cried, but cricket

01:37:48.119 --> 01:37:48.720
couldn't.

01:37:48.779 --> 01:37:50.520
It was all too confusing.

01:37:50.579 --> 01:37:53.340
She didn't understand why they couldn't

01:37:53.340 --> 01:37:55.800
continue as they always did. with her

01:37:55.800 --> 01:37:56.880
mother ignoring them all.

01:37:56.939 --> 01:37:59.399
Why did she have to go to a whole other

01:37:59.399 --> 01:38:00.300
hive to do that?

01:38:00.359 --> 01:38:04.439
I didn't know your mother left, Blue said

01:38:04.439 --> 01:38:05.220
sympathetically.

01:38:05.279 --> 01:38:08.699
That's not an option for silk wings

01:38:08.699 --> 01:38:10.380
Sortell pointed out.

01:38:10.439 --> 01:38:12.239
At least not by choice.

01:38:12.300 --> 01:38:14.760
Nobody gets to leave the partner they're

01:38:14.760 --> 01:38:17.100
paired with, unless Queen Wasp tells them

01:38:17.100 --> 01:38:17.340
to.

01:38:17.399 --> 01:38:20.579
Hive Wings have to get her approval first

01:38:20.579 --> 01:38:21.779
Cricket said.

01:38:21.840 --> 01:38:24.779
I guess mother really wanted to get away

01:38:24.779 --> 01:38:25.199
from us.

01:38:25.260 --> 01:38:27.000
If she was willing to go through the

01:38:27.000 --> 01:38:28.739
whole separation request process.

01:38:28.800 --> 01:38:32.640
When she left, she said, across the

01:38:32.640 --> 01:38:34.560
continent still isn't far enough from you

01:38:34.560 --> 01:38:36.899
horrible grubs, but it'll have to do.

01:38:36.960 --> 01:38:39.180
Whoa.

01:38:39.239 --> 01:38:41.640
Sundu hissed through her teeth.

01:38:41.699 --> 01:38:43.439
She sounds charming.

01:38:43.560 --> 01:38:46.439
Oh, cricket, Blue said.

01:38:46.560 --> 01:38:49.020
How could anyone say that to her own

01:38:49.020 --> 01:38:49.680
dragonette?

01:38:49.739 --> 01:38:52.560
She had been trying to leave for a

01:38:52.560 --> 01:38:53.039
while.

01:38:53.100 --> 01:38:56.520
It turns out, Cricket said, fiddling with

01:38:56.520 --> 01:38:57.300
the edge of the leaf.

01:38:57.420 --> 01:39:00.119
But I mean, it doesn't matter.

01:39:00.180 --> 01:39:02.039
It's not like we'll run into her.

01:39:02.100 --> 01:39:03.659
It's a big hive.

01:39:03.720 --> 01:39:04.439
Super busy.

01:39:04.500 --> 01:39:07.079
I kind of know my way around from the 2

01:39:07.079 --> 01:39:09.659
times we visited her, so maybe that'll be

01:39:09.659 --> 01:39:10.020
helpful.

01:39:10.079 --> 01:39:13.260
Blue rested one of his wings alongside

01:39:13.260 --> 01:39:16.439
hers, like a warm, azure wave of comfort

01:39:16.439 --> 01:39:17.340
if she wanted it.

01:39:17.399 --> 01:39:20.039
She liked that he didn't push her to talk

01:39:20.039 --> 01:39:20.579
about it more.

01:39:20.640 --> 01:39:22.680
What's the plan?

01:39:22.739 --> 01:39:24.420
She asked Sundu.

01:39:24.479 --> 01:39:27.119
How do we get into the hive if everyone's

01:39:27.119 --> 01:39:27.600
looking for us?

01:39:27.720 --> 01:39:30.840
With punching and biting?

01:39:30.899 --> 01:39:33.840
Sortell suggested, hopefully, and maybe

01:39:33.840 --> 01:39:35.340
some venomous caterpillars?

01:39:35.460 --> 01:39:39.060
I like the way you think, Sundew said.

01:39:39.119 --> 01:39:41.460
But they're centipedes, dingbat.

01:39:41.520 --> 01:39:44.460
Or Blue interjected.

01:39:44.520 --> 01:39:47.399
Is there a way to sneak in where nobody

01:39:47.399 --> 01:39:47.880
gets hurt?

01:39:47.939 --> 01:39:51.479
And nobody gets caught by hive wing

01:39:51.479 --> 01:39:51.960
guards?

01:39:52.020 --> 01:39:53.039
Cricket agreed.

01:39:53.100 --> 01:39:55.380
She looked down at her map again.

01:39:55.439 --> 01:39:58.140
Jewel Hive.

01:39:58.199 --> 01:39:58.560
Hmm.

01:39:58.680 --> 01:40:00.659
What, what, what?

01:40:00.659 --> 01:40:02.100
Sundew demanded.

01:40:02.159 --> 01:40:05.100
Lady Jewel is a little different from the

01:40:05.100 --> 01:40:07.380
other hive rulers, cricket explained.

01:40:07.439 --> 01:40:09.840
Do you guys know anything about her?

01:40:09.899 --> 01:40:13.079
She's Wasp's cousin, not her sister, for

01:40:13.079 --> 01:40:15.359
one thing, and she's famous for her.

01:40:15.420 --> 01:40:19.260
I guess love of art is the best way to

01:40:19.260 --> 01:40:19.800
describe it.

01:40:19.920 --> 01:40:23.939
Oh, right, Swordtail said, lighting up.

01:40:24.000 --> 01:40:26.640
Luna was always talking about how she

01:40:26.640 --> 01:40:28.560
wanted to move to Jewel Hive if we

01:40:28.560 --> 01:40:28.800
could.

01:40:28.920 --> 01:40:31.979
She kept going on about the art scene and

01:40:31.979 --> 01:40:33.060
the glitter bazaar.

01:40:33.119 --> 01:40:36.119
The light went out of his eyes, and he

01:40:36.119 --> 01:40:37.439
looked down at his claws.

01:40:37.500 --> 01:40:39.899
She would love to see the glitter

01:40:39.899 --> 01:40:40.500
bizarre.

01:40:40.560 --> 01:40:42.899
Maybe the chrysalis will know something.

01:40:42.960 --> 01:40:46.140
Blue said to him, maybe she found her way

01:40:46.140 --> 01:40:46.560
to them.

01:40:46.619 --> 01:40:49.260
Or maybe they'd know if she's back in the

01:40:49.260 --> 01:40:50.220
Flameso Cavern.

01:40:50.279 --> 01:40:52.979
Sortell looked hopeful for the 1st time

01:40:52.979 --> 01:40:53.640
in days.

01:40:53.699 --> 01:40:55.739
That's true.

01:40:55.800 --> 01:40:58.079
If she ended up in a hive, that's who

01:40:58.079 --> 01:40:58.680
she'd look for.

01:40:58.739 --> 01:41:01.680
He flicked his tail back and forth.

01:41:01.739 --> 01:41:03.479
We should go ask them.

01:41:03.539 --> 01:41:04.319
Let's do that.

01:41:04.380 --> 01:41:05.220
Let's go now.

01:41:05.279 --> 01:41:06.840
Hang on.

01:41:06.899 --> 01:41:09.720
What in Pantale is a glitter bazaar?

01:41:09.720 --> 01:41:11.279
Sundu asked.

01:41:11.340 --> 01:41:14.220
If it involves sparkles, the answer is

01:41:14.220 --> 01:41:14.819
no.

01:41:14.939 --> 01:41:17.159
I do not do sparkles.

01:41:17.220 --> 01:41:19.859
Which was funny, Cricket thought.

01:41:19.920 --> 01:41:22.619
Coming from a dragon with gold flex all

01:41:22.619 --> 01:41:23.640
across her green scales.

01:41:23.699 --> 01:41:28.260
Only a few sparkles, Cricket said, and I

01:41:28.260 --> 01:41:30.479
think it might be our way in.

01:41:30.539 --> 01:41:34.739
Chapter 5.

01:41:35.039 --> 01:41:38.880
Cricket hadn't realized how nerve

01:41:38.100 --> 01:41:41.100
wracking it must have been, for sore tail

01:41:41.100 --> 01:41:43.199
and sun do to creep out of the cave onto

01:41:43.199 --> 01:41:44.100
the beach every day.

01:41:44.159 --> 01:41:46.680
You couldn't get a full view of the sky

01:41:46.680 --> 01:41:49.199
until you were already exposed on the

01:41:49.199 --> 01:41:49.619
sand.

01:41:49.680 --> 01:41:52.140
If High Wings had been watching from the

01:41:52.140 --> 01:41:54.060
cliffs, they would have spotted her

01:41:54.060 --> 01:41:56.939
friends easily, even at night, with the

01:41:56.939 --> 01:41:58.140
moons lighting up the ocean.

01:41:58.199 --> 01:42:02.100
Raindrops pattered against her scales and

01:42:02.100 --> 01:42:04.500
blurred her glasses as she stepped into

01:42:04.500 --> 01:42:06.659
the open air for the 1st time in days

01:42:06.659 --> 01:42:09.359
keeping her body close to the towering

01:42:09.359 --> 01:42:10.020
cliff face.

01:42:10.079 --> 01:42:12.539
They were lucky tonight.

01:42:12.600 --> 01:42:15.239
Dark clouds covered most of the 3 moons

01:42:15.239 --> 01:42:18.539
driving rain obscured at the sky, and the

01:42:18.539 --> 01:42:20.579
fierce thunderstorm was probably keeping

01:42:20.579 --> 01:42:22.020
most high wing scouts at home.

01:42:22.079 --> 01:42:25.800
Of course, it meant flying to Jewel Hive

01:42:25.800 --> 01:42:27.180
in that very thunderstorm.

01:42:27.239 --> 01:42:30.119
But cricket, for one, would rather battle

01:42:30.119 --> 01:42:31.739
the rain than another dragon.

01:42:31.800 --> 01:42:35.100
Blech, poof, ugh.

01:42:35.159 --> 01:42:38.220
Swordell muttered, shaking wet sand off

01:42:38.220 --> 01:42:39.600
his talons and snout.

01:42:39.659 --> 01:42:43.020
Sorry your 1st flying experience has to

01:42:43.020 --> 01:42:44.159
be in this weather blue.

01:42:44.220 --> 01:42:46.020
It's amazing.

01:42:46.079 --> 01:42:47.399
Blue said.

01:42:47.460 --> 01:42:49.199
I mean, from down here.

01:42:49.260 --> 01:42:52.560
He lifted his face up to the rain and

01:42:52.560 --> 01:42:54.779
held out his faintly glowing wrists.

01:42:54.840 --> 01:42:57.300
Skittering rivulets ran like melted

01:42:57.300 --> 01:42:58.979
amethysts along his wings.

01:42:59.039 --> 01:43:01.260
She wasn't imagining it.

01:43:01.319 --> 01:43:03.779
His wings were decidedly larger than

01:43:03.779 --> 01:43:04.319
crickets.

01:43:04.380 --> 01:43:07.920
It was a little intimidating, until he

01:43:07.920 --> 01:43:09.300
turned and smiled at cricket.

01:43:09.359 --> 01:43:11.279
His smile was still the same.

01:43:11.340 --> 01:43:14.220
It still took up just as much space in

01:43:14.220 --> 01:43:14.520
her heart.

01:43:14.579 --> 01:43:17.520
I'm such a moon moth.

01:43:17.520 --> 01:43:20.100
Didn't I laugh at dragons who said things

01:43:20.100 --> 01:43:21.239
like that in my books?

01:43:21.300 --> 01:43:23.579
You don't even know if he likes you back

01:43:23.579 --> 01:43:26.159
because he seems to be just that sweet to

01:43:26.159 --> 01:43:26.460
everybody.

01:43:26.520 --> 01:43:30.180
Seriously cricket, snap to it.

01:43:30.239 --> 01:43:32.399
You're trying to save your tribe and

01:43:32.399 --> 01:43:33.899
avoid all out war right now.

01:43:33.960 --> 01:43:36.539
And if Sortail is right about the

01:43:36.539 --> 01:43:39.239
chrysalis, you could be this close to

01:43:39.239 --> 01:43:41.220
solving your brain chemistry mystery.

01:43:41.340 --> 01:43:44.520
Lead the way, Sundu said.

01:43:44.579 --> 01:43:45.899
Nudging cricket.

01:43:45.960 --> 01:43:49.140
I'll watch for hive wings, Sortail, you

01:43:49.140 --> 01:43:50.760
keep an eye on Blue and his new wings.

01:43:50.819 --> 01:43:54.720
Will do, Swartell said solemnly.

01:43:54.779 --> 01:43:58.619
It was a shaky flight, punctuated by ear

01:43:58.619 --> 01:44:01.380
splitting thunder and crackling bolts of

01:44:01.380 --> 01:44:02.039
lightning overhead.

01:44:02.100 --> 01:44:05.279
The rain battered Crickets wings and

01:44:05.279 --> 01:44:07.560
blurred her glasses, and flew into her

01:44:07.560 --> 01:44:09.840
eyes, so she could hardly keep track of

01:44:09.840 --> 01:44:11.159
the coastline below her.

01:44:11.579 --> 01:44:14.039
She was very, very glad they didn't have

01:44:14.039 --> 01:44:14.460
far to go.

01:44:14.579 --> 01:44:17.699
She knew her job was to lead the way to

01:44:17.699 --> 01:44:18.539
Jewel Hive.

01:44:18.600 --> 01:44:20.640
But she couldn't help twisting around to

01:44:20.640 --> 01:44:22.020
keep an eye on Blue every few

01:44:22.020 --> 01:44:22.859
heartbeats.

01:44:23.159 --> 01:44:25.079
It was hard enough flying for the 1st

01:44:25.079 --> 01:44:27.180
time, let alone doing it in a

01:44:27.180 --> 01:44:27.659
thunderstorm.

01:44:27.720 --> 01:44:31.260
The 1st time she'd flown in the rain, it

01:44:31.260 --> 01:44:33.359
had been a training exercise at Terrarium

01:44:33.359 --> 01:44:36.300
Academy, and it had been very annoying

01:44:36.300 --> 01:44:39.180
not because of the weather, but because

01:44:39.180 --> 01:44:40.739
of her classmate bombardier.

01:44:40.800 --> 01:44:43.079
He was completely convinced that cricket

01:44:43.079 --> 01:44:45.420
had a crush on him, and was always trying

01:44:45.420 --> 01:44:47.399
to let her down gently.

01:44:47.460 --> 01:44:50.760
When, in fact, cricket would have very

01:44:50.760 --> 01:44:52.500
much liked to throw him through a wall.

01:44:52.560 --> 01:44:55.260
She remembered trying to figure out how

01:44:55.260 --> 01:44:57.479
to flick raindrops off her back wings.

01:44:57.539 --> 01:44:59.760
Bombardier kept hovering around her

01:44:59.760 --> 01:45:01.920
offering unnecessary suggestions.

01:45:01.979 --> 01:45:04.500
I can figure it out myself.

01:45:04.560 --> 01:45:06.600
She finally snapped at him.

01:45:06.659 --> 01:45:09.899
You don't need to act self-confident with

01:45:09.899 --> 01:45:12.420
me, he'd answered condescendingly.

01:45:12.479 --> 01:45:14.699
It won't make me like you more, cricket.

01:45:14.760 --> 01:45:17.279
I keep telling you, I'm not interested in

01:45:17.279 --> 01:45:17.819
you in that way.

01:45:17.880 --> 01:45:23.100
Neither am I. She tried to protest, like

01:45:23.100 --> 01:45:23.819
she always did.

01:45:23.880 --> 01:45:25.500
Of course.

01:45:25.560 --> 01:45:27.119
Of course.

01:45:27.180 --> 01:45:31.260
He'd soothed her insincerely, and then

01:45:31.260 --> 01:45:34.380
smug faced away while she wished she had

01:45:34.380 --> 01:45:36.899
any cool hive wing powers to poison him

01:45:36.899 --> 01:45:37.140
with.

01:45:37.199 --> 01:45:40.439
Blue was the furthest opposite dragon

01:45:40.439 --> 01:45:42.180
from bombardier that cricket had ever

01:45:42.180 --> 01:45:42.359
met.

01:45:42.420 --> 01:45:46.260
He had no idea how wonderful he was, and

01:45:46.260 --> 01:45:47.880
he would never assume that somebody liked

01:45:47.880 --> 01:45:48.119
him.

01:45:48.180 --> 01:45:50.399
He always really wanted to know what

01:45:50.399 --> 01:45:52.739
other dragons were feeling, no matter who

01:45:52.739 --> 01:45:53.039
they were.

01:45:53.100 --> 01:45:56.220
He seemed to have less trouble with a

01:45:56.220 --> 01:45:57.420
storm than she'd feared.

01:45:57.479 --> 01:46:00.539
His wings looked so new and shimmering

01:46:00.539 --> 01:46:02.640
that she kept thinking the wind would

01:46:02.640 --> 01:46:03.659
tear them right in half.

01:46:03.720 --> 01:46:07.020
The blue beat them strongly and smoothly

01:46:07.020 --> 01:46:08.640
as though he'd been flying forever.

01:46:08.699 --> 01:46:12.119
Every time she turned to look at him, he

01:46:12.119 --> 01:46:13.500
gave her his shy smile.

01:46:13.619 --> 01:46:15.899
As though she had something to do with

01:46:15.899 --> 01:46:17.579
the wind that lifted his wings.

01:46:17.640 --> 01:46:19.859
Oh, Blue.

01:46:19.920 --> 01:46:22.319
I won't let them use you to hurt any

01:46:22.319 --> 01:46:22.859
dragons.

01:46:22.920 --> 01:46:25.500
We'll figure out the mind control and

01:46:25.500 --> 01:46:28.380
stop Queen Wasp, and then you can use

01:46:28.380 --> 01:46:30.060
your flame silk to make the world a

01:46:30.060 --> 01:46:31.680
better place instead of worse.

01:46:31.739 --> 01:46:34.979
Soon, she could see the glowing lights of

01:46:34.979 --> 01:46:36.119
Dual Hive up ahead.

01:46:36.180 --> 01:46:38.760
Flame silk lanterns lit many of the

01:46:38.760 --> 01:46:41.579
windows, and as they flew closer, she

01:46:41.579 --> 01:46:43.439
caught glimpses of a bright party taking

01:46:43.439 --> 01:46:45.300
place on one of the upper levels.

01:46:45.359 --> 01:46:48.720
Dragons laughed and danced and whirled

01:46:48.720 --> 01:46:51.539
orange gold scales and green jewels

01:46:51.539 --> 01:46:53.760
flashing through a ballroom, hung with

01:46:53.760 --> 01:46:56.340
vibrant scarlet, and cobalt silk

01:46:56.340 --> 01:46:57.060
tapestries.

01:46:57.119 --> 01:47:00.060
Cricket remembered hiding on the edges of

01:47:00.060 --> 01:47:01.800
that ballroom while her mother danced.

01:47:01.859 --> 01:47:04.979
At a party, neither she nor Katy did had

01:47:04.979 --> 01:47:06.000
wanted to be dragged to.

01:47:06.060 --> 01:47:08.760
But her mother never missed one of Lady

01:47:08.760 --> 01:47:09.659
Jewel's parties.

01:47:09.720 --> 01:47:12.300
Her best chance to get closer to the

01:47:12.300 --> 01:47:13.319
ruler of her new hive.

01:47:13.380 --> 01:47:16.800
Katydid had found a bubbly drink for them

01:47:16.800 --> 01:47:19.859
to share that tasted like limes, and made

01:47:19.859 --> 01:47:20.640
cricket sleepy.

01:47:20.699 --> 01:47:24.060
The wasps on the tapestries had been dyed

01:47:24.060 --> 01:47:26.460
a gold so bright, it hurt her eyes.

01:47:26.520 --> 01:47:29.100
She missed Katy did.

01:47:29.220 --> 01:47:32.460
When cricket flew off with blue, she

01:47:32.460 --> 01:47:34.680
hadn't expected to be gone for so long

01:47:34.680 --> 01:47:36.779
she hadn't thought about the possibility

01:47:36.779 --> 01:47:39.060
that she'd never be able to go home again

01:47:39.060 --> 01:47:42.180
that she might never see her sister again

01:47:42.180 --> 01:47:45.960
but I'd still have gone, even knowing all

01:47:45.960 --> 01:47:46.140
that.

01:47:46.199 --> 01:47:48.060
I think I had to.

01:47:48.119 --> 01:47:52.020
They arced around Jewel Hive and landed a

01:47:52.020 --> 01:47:54.180
fair distance away, farther out on the

01:47:54.180 --> 01:47:56.819
peninsula, at the top of a cliff, where

01:47:56.819 --> 01:47:58.319
they could hear the sound of waves

01:47:58.319 --> 01:48:00.359
roaring below, even through the storm.

01:48:00.420 --> 01:48:03.600
Somehow, standing out in the rain felt

01:48:03.600 --> 01:48:05.699
even harder than flying, as though

01:48:05.699 --> 01:48:07.199
raindrops were trying to beat cricket

01:48:07.199 --> 01:48:07.859
into the earth.

01:48:07.979 --> 01:48:12.060
So there's the hive, Sundew shouted to

01:48:12.060 --> 01:48:13.380
SwordTail.

01:48:13.380 --> 01:48:15.180
Where do we go to find the chrysalis?

01:48:15.300 --> 01:48:18.239
Cricket wasn't great at reading Dragon's

01:48:18.239 --> 01:48:20.579
expressions, but she thought Swordell

01:48:20.579 --> 01:48:22.500
looked decidedly nervous as he answered.

01:48:22.560 --> 01:48:25.619
Well, we don't exactly find them.

01:48:25.680 --> 01:48:28.079
We leave them a message, and they find

01:48:28.079 --> 01:48:28.500
us.

01:48:28.560 --> 01:48:30.899
Leave them a message how?

01:48:30.960 --> 01:48:31.859
Cricket asked.

01:48:31.979 --> 01:48:33.000
Where?

01:48:33.060 --> 01:48:36.720
Um, he shook his wings and tail.

01:48:36.840 --> 01:48:40.739
So, I'm kind of guessing?

01:48:40.800 --> 01:48:43.859
I mean, I sort of know, but I wasn't

01:48:43.859 --> 01:48:46.680
going to be the one who, I mean, I'm just

01:48:46.680 --> 01:48:49.199
saying, this will be a lot easier if Luna

01:48:49.199 --> 01:48:49.680
were here.

01:48:49.739 --> 01:48:51.720
But she's not.

01:48:51.779 --> 01:48:52.739
Sundew said.

01:48:52.800 --> 01:48:56.640
Not yet, she amended, at the look on his

01:48:56.640 --> 01:48:56.819
face.

01:48:56.939 --> 01:48:59.760
You have to figure this out, Silkwing.

01:48:59.819 --> 01:49:00.659
We can't wait for her.

01:49:00.720 --> 01:49:03.239
Wait, why not?

01:49:03.300 --> 01:49:04.500
Blue asked.

01:49:04.560 --> 01:49:07.380
Can't we go hide somewhere new for a few

01:49:07.380 --> 01:49:09.659
days, until we find her, and then decide

01:49:09.659 --> 01:49:10.140
what to do?

01:49:10.199 --> 01:49:13.979
The grass was soggy, and felt like dense

01:49:13.979 --> 01:49:15.840
wet carpet under cricket's claws.

01:49:15.899 --> 01:49:18.779
She blinked away raindrops and looked at

01:49:18.779 --> 01:49:19.140
sundew.

01:49:19.199 --> 01:49:21.960
No, Sundew said.

01:49:22.020 --> 01:49:25.319
We've been waiting for you, you snoozy

01:49:25.319 --> 01:49:26.039
silk wing.

01:49:26.100 --> 01:49:27.899
She turned to Cricket.

01:49:27.960 --> 01:49:30.539
My parents can't put their plans on hold

01:49:30.539 --> 01:49:30.899
forever.

01:49:30.960 --> 01:49:34.380
Lightning flickered deep in the clouds

01:49:34.380 --> 01:49:36.840
reflecting waves of green fire in the

01:49:36.840 --> 01:49:37.140
ocean.

01:49:37.199 --> 01:49:40.260
Cricket felt the tremor of thunder rumble

01:49:40.260 --> 01:49:40.920
through her bones.

01:49:40.979 --> 01:49:43.439
What does that mean?

01:49:43.500 --> 01:49:44.640
Cricket asked.

01:49:44.699 --> 01:49:45.960
What plans?

01:49:46.020 --> 01:49:47.520
How long do you think they'll wait?

01:49:47.640 --> 01:49:51.659
Sundew huffed, and ripped up a muddy tuft

01:49:51.659 --> 01:49:54.119
of grass, then carefully tucked it back

01:49:54.119 --> 01:49:56.520
into the divot she'd made, and covered it

01:49:56.520 --> 01:49:57.359
with her claws.

01:49:57.420 --> 01:49:59.880
All right, she said.

01:49:59.939 --> 01:50:01.439
Two days.

01:50:01.500 --> 01:50:03.359
Two days?

01:50:03.420 --> 01:50:04.680
Cricket cried.

01:50:04.739 --> 01:50:05.699
That's it?

01:50:05.760 --> 01:50:07.979
That's all the time we have to solve the

01:50:07.979 --> 01:50:10.199
entire mystery of Queen Wasp's mind

01:50:10.199 --> 01:50:10.680
control?

01:50:10.739 --> 01:50:12.239
Or what?

01:50:12.420 --> 01:50:14.279
Blue asked anxiously.

01:50:14.340 --> 01:50:16.439
What happens in 2 days?

01:50:16.500 --> 01:50:18.539
That's all I could get?

01:50:18.659 --> 01:50:21.000
Sundew shouted back at cricket.

01:50:21.060 --> 01:50:22.560
I tried, all right?

01:50:22.619 --> 01:50:24.359
It was almost impossible.

01:50:24.420 --> 01:50:28.020
It was like trying to push a tree back up

01:50:28.020 --> 01:50:29.460
when it's already started falling.

01:50:29.520 --> 01:50:32.399
Belladonna and hemlock don't think you

01:50:32.399 --> 01:50:32.760
can do it.

01:50:32.819 --> 01:50:36.000
So I'm sorry, but if I don't have some

01:50:36.000 --> 01:50:38.399
kind of results for them by sunset in 2

01:50:38.399 --> 01:50:41.100
days, they're going to the next phase of

01:50:41.100 --> 01:50:41.460
their plan.

01:50:41.520 --> 01:50:43.739
What are they going to do?

01:50:43.859 --> 01:50:45.119
Cricket asked.

01:50:45.180 --> 01:50:48.300
Blue looked paler and paler with each of

01:50:48.300 --> 01:50:48.840
her questions.

01:50:48.899 --> 01:50:51.300
Are they going to attack a hive?

01:50:51.359 --> 01:50:53.399
Will it restart the tree wars?

01:50:53.460 --> 01:50:55.199
What plan, sundo?

01:50:55.260 --> 01:50:58.800
The leaf wing plan that is not for hive

01:50:58.800 --> 01:50:59.640
wings to know about?

01:50:59.699 --> 01:51:02.460
Sundew said sternly.

01:51:02.520 --> 01:51:05.220
But it involves violence, and you're not

01:51:05.220 --> 01:51:07.920
going to like it as much as this plan, so

01:51:07.920 --> 01:51:10.319
we should get moving on this plan in

01:51:10.319 --> 01:51:12.119
order to make sure that it's the one that

01:51:12.119 --> 01:51:12.479
works.

01:51:12.539 --> 01:51:14.159
Understand?

01:51:14.220 --> 01:51:16.380
Sortell nodded.

01:51:16.439 --> 01:51:19.140
Restart the tree wars?

01:51:19.199 --> 01:51:21.960
Blue whispered, nearly drowned out by the

01:51:21.960 --> 01:51:22.260
storm.

01:51:22.319 --> 01:51:25.380
Cricket's heart was beating very fast.

01:51:25.500 --> 01:51:27.960
She wanted to know the leaf wing plan.

01:51:28.020 --> 01:51:30.479
She wanted to know how many leaf wings

01:51:30.479 --> 01:51:32.159
were out there, and where they would

01:51:32.159 --> 01:51:34.500
attack, and whether Katie did would be in

01:51:34.500 --> 01:51:34.800
danger.

01:51:34.859 --> 01:51:38.399
But the only thing she did know was she

01:51:38.399 --> 01:51:40.199
wouldn't get those answers out of sundo

01:51:40.199 --> 01:51:41.279
by asking for them now.

01:51:41.340 --> 01:51:43.619
And at least she had a chance.

01:51:43.680 --> 01:51:47.460
Two days, 2 days to find the answers and

01:51:47.460 --> 01:51:48.899
stop the leaf wings.

01:51:48.960 --> 01:51:53.039
All right, she said, trying to study her

01:51:53.039 --> 01:51:53.399
breathing.

01:51:53.520 --> 01:51:55.020
We can do this.

01:51:55.079 --> 01:51:56.340
Let's think.

01:51:56.399 --> 01:51:57.539
Soretail.

01:51:57.659 --> 01:52:00.060
Where do you need to get to so you can

01:52:00.060 --> 01:52:01.439
leave a message for the chrysalis?

01:52:01.500 --> 01:52:04.260
A central feature. he said.

01:52:04.319 --> 01:52:06.840
In Cicada Hive, it was the Salvation

01:52:06.840 --> 01:52:08.699
Mosaic in the mosaic garden.

01:52:08.760 --> 01:52:12.960
Does Jewel Hive have a salvation mosaic?

01:52:13.079 --> 01:52:14.279
No.

01:52:14.399 --> 01:52:16.140
Cricket shook her head.

01:52:16.199 --> 01:52:17.520
He looked worried.

01:52:17.579 --> 01:52:20.159
Does it have anything like that?

01:52:20.220 --> 01:52:23.100
Cricket bowed her head and tried to

01:52:23.100 --> 01:52:23.279
think.

01:52:23.340 --> 01:52:25.920
Her visits to her mother hadn't exactly

01:52:25.920 --> 01:52:28.140
involved fun tours of awesome hive

01:52:28.140 --> 01:52:30.779
monuments, but maybe there was an answer

01:52:30.779 --> 01:52:31.739
in something she'd read.

01:52:31.800 --> 01:52:34.319
Her mind started ticking through books

01:52:34.319 --> 01:52:36.899
about other hives, monuments to the

01:52:36.899 --> 01:52:39.600
salvation, architecture and unifying

01:52:39.600 --> 01:52:42.300
features, the history of hive building

01:52:42.300 --> 01:52:44.399
Wasps, Sisters, and Lady Jewel.

01:52:44.460 --> 01:52:47.460
There's the statue in the center of the

01:52:47.460 --> 01:52:49.979
glitter bazaar, she said slowly.

01:52:50.039 --> 01:52:52.319
That's a tribute to the salvation.

01:52:52.380 --> 01:52:54.960
Or there's a garden at the top of the

01:52:54.960 --> 01:52:57.479
hive, like the mosaic garden.

01:52:57.720 --> 01:53:00.060
It doesn't have mosaics or historical

01:53:00.060 --> 01:53:02.819
monuments, but it has a waiting pool and

01:53:02.819 --> 01:53:04.199
a shrine to clear sight.

01:53:04.260 --> 01:53:07.319
The garden, Swordtail said.

01:53:07.380 --> 01:53:10.560
The statue, Sundew said at the same

01:53:10.560 --> 01:53:10.859
time.

01:53:10.920 --> 01:53:13.020
Really?

01:53:13.079 --> 01:53:13.560
he said to her.

01:53:13.619 --> 01:53:15.840
I think it would be in roughly the same

01:53:15.840 --> 01:53:16.859
place.

01:53:16.920 --> 01:53:18.960
Like geographically, don't you?

01:53:19.020 --> 01:53:23.100
No, my revolution would be organized

01:53:23.100 --> 01:53:25.020
around the symbolism, she said.

01:53:25.079 --> 01:53:28.380
If it's in a meaningful place in one hive

01:53:28.380 --> 01:53:30.420
I'd guess the chrysalis in the next hive

01:53:30.420 --> 01:53:32.039
would choose a place with the same

01:53:32.039 --> 01:53:32.340
meaning.

01:53:32.460 --> 01:53:34.199
Hmm.

01:53:34.260 --> 01:53:37.020
Sorte rubbed his face, trying

01:53:37.020 --> 01:53:38.460
unsuccessfully to dry it.

01:53:38.520 --> 01:53:40.260
I don't know.

01:53:40.319 --> 01:53:41.399
I don't know.

01:53:41.460 --> 01:53:42.659
I wish.

01:53:42.779 --> 01:53:44.399
Luna we're here.

01:53:44.460 --> 01:53:46.739
Yes, we know, Sundew said.

01:53:46.800 --> 01:53:48.779
Okay, here's what we do.

01:53:48.840 --> 01:53:51.239
Leave a message in both places.

01:53:51.300 --> 01:53:53.279
Hope the chrysalis finds one of them.

01:53:53.340 --> 01:53:57.000
And the hive wings don't, Blue said.

01:53:57.060 --> 01:53:59.880
It'll be easiest to go to the Glitter

01:53:59.880 --> 01:54:02.100
Bazaar first, Cricket suggested.

01:54:02.220 --> 01:54:05.640
She pointed down toward Jewel Hive, at

01:54:05.640 --> 01:54:07.439
the dark shapes that sprawled in a

01:54:07.439 --> 01:54:08.939
scattered tangle around the bottom of

01:54:08.939 --> 01:54:09.119
it.

01:54:09.180 --> 01:54:12.539
We start on the outskirts, get our

01:54:12.539 --> 01:54:14.699
disguises, and work our way in.

01:54:14.760 --> 01:54:18.300
And pray to clear sight that we can do

01:54:18.300 --> 01:54:19.199
this in 2 days.

01:54:19.260 --> 01:54:24.000
Chapter 6.

01:54:24.060 --> 01:54:27.539
The next morning dawned gray and

01:54:27.539 --> 01:54:28.199
drizzly.

01:54:28.260 --> 01:54:30.420
But at least the pouring rain had moved

01:54:30.420 --> 01:54:33.000
out, along with the apocalyptic thunder.

01:54:33.060 --> 01:54:35.939
One half of cricket was cold and damp

01:54:35.939 --> 01:54:38.399
when she woke up, but the sigh that had

01:54:38.399 --> 01:54:40.560
been pressed to blue while they slept was

01:54:40.560 --> 01:54:41.340
warm.

01:54:41.399 --> 01:54:44.939
He was still asleep, like a small sunlit

01:54:44.939 --> 01:54:46.680
ocean between her and sword tail.

01:54:46.739 --> 01:54:50.340
She put on her glasses, and looked up at

01:54:50.340 --> 01:54:52.680
the thick silk web over them, and then

01:54:52.680 --> 01:54:54.479
around for Sundew, who was gone.

01:54:54.539 --> 01:54:57.720
Carefully Cricket disentangled her tail

01:54:57.720 --> 01:54:59.640
from blues, and slid away from his

01:54:59.640 --> 01:55:00.300
wings.

01:55:00.539 --> 01:55:03.359
He murmured a sleepy complaint and rolled

01:55:03.359 --> 01:55:05.819
closer to swordtail, who grunted and

01:55:05.819 --> 01:55:07.020
flung one wing over him.

01:55:07.079 --> 01:55:10.500
The silk web overhead was part of a vast

01:55:10.500 --> 01:55:13.199
canopy that covered all the stalls of the

01:55:13.199 --> 01:55:13.920
outer bazaar.

01:55:13.979 --> 01:55:16.800
The lowlier shops that had spilled out of

01:55:16.800 --> 01:55:19.079
the hive, when the glitter bazaar got too

01:55:19.079 --> 01:55:19.739
big.

01:55:19.800 --> 01:55:21.899
It wasn't great to have your stall

01:55:21.899 --> 01:55:24.060
outside the hive during the rainy season

01:55:24.060 --> 01:55:26.279
but at least the canopy helped keep the

01:55:26.279 --> 01:55:27.479
wares mostly dry.

01:55:27.539 --> 01:55:30.539
They'd hidden overnight in the musty

01:55:30.539 --> 01:55:32.699
smelling back corners of a curtain shop

01:55:32.699 --> 01:55:35.939
burrowing in between rolls of aquamarine

01:55:35.939 --> 01:55:36.840
and silver silk.

01:55:36.960 --> 01:55:39.539
Cricket crawled out of the fabric pile

01:55:39.539 --> 01:55:41.100
and ducked into the main stall.

01:55:41.159 --> 01:55:44.819
A web hung over the doorway, keeping out

01:55:44.819 --> 01:55:47.279
most of the dim morning light, but a

01:55:47.279 --> 01:55:49.319
flame silk lamp glowed softly in one

01:55:49.319 --> 01:55:49.739
corner.

01:55:49.739 --> 01:55:52.560
Sundew was stretching in the tiny space.

01:55:52.619 --> 01:55:55.739
Morning, Cricket said.

01:55:55.800 --> 01:55:58.739
She sidled up and joined Sundew's series

01:55:58.739 --> 01:56:01.199
of exercises, like she had each morning

01:56:01.199 --> 01:56:02.100
in the cave.

01:56:02.159 --> 01:56:05.520
It was a little harder here, trying to

01:56:05.520 --> 01:56:07.199
keep her wings from colliding with

01:56:07.199 --> 01:56:07.859
sundews.

01:56:07.920 --> 01:56:10.260
When did the dragons come?

01:56:10.380 --> 01:56:12.899
Sundew asked, finishing her last

01:56:12.899 --> 01:56:13.739
stretch.

01:56:13.800 --> 01:56:16.260
She peeked out through the door web at

01:56:16.260 --> 01:56:18.300
the hive, looming in the mist.

01:56:18.359 --> 01:56:22.319
Jewel hive sleeps late, Cricket said

01:56:22.319 --> 01:56:23.100
apologetically.

01:56:23.159 --> 01:56:25.439
The balls sometimes go all night.

01:56:25.500 --> 01:56:27.659
We won't see many hive wings before

01:56:27.659 --> 01:56:28.260
midday.

01:56:28.319 --> 01:56:31.319
Are all leaf wings early risers like

01:56:31.319 --> 01:56:31.619
you?

01:56:31.680 --> 01:56:33.779
Some of them.

01:56:33.899 --> 01:56:36.539
This market must open sooner, though.

01:56:36.600 --> 01:56:38.819
Sundew checked back in the other

01:56:38.819 --> 01:56:40.979
direction, along the path through the

01:56:40.979 --> 01:56:41.399
stalls.

01:56:41.460 --> 01:56:44.520
Aren't some of these places run by Silk

01:56:44.520 --> 01:56:44.819
Wings?

01:56:44.880 --> 01:56:47.939
Most of the ones on the outside are

01:56:47.939 --> 01:56:49.619
Cricket said, nodding.

01:56:49.680 --> 01:56:52.380
We should find what we need now, and then

01:56:52.380 --> 01:56:54.000
blend in with the crowd once it's busy

01:56:54.000 --> 01:56:54.300
enough.

01:56:54.359 --> 01:56:57.659
Sundew cast a wicked smile at the back of

01:56:57.659 --> 01:56:57.960
the shop.

01:56:58.079 --> 01:57:01.500
I'll wake the others, she volunteered

01:57:01.500 --> 01:57:02.399
bounding away.

01:57:02.460 --> 01:57:05.880
A moment later, Cricket heard Swordtell

01:57:05.880 --> 01:57:06.359
Yelp.

01:57:06.420 --> 01:57:08.520
Ow, unnecessary.

01:57:08.640 --> 01:57:11.699
Followed by the unusual sound of sundew

01:57:11.699 --> 01:57:12.060
laughing.

01:57:12.180 --> 01:57:15.060
Cricket took a moment to peer out into

01:57:15.060 --> 01:57:15.720
the market as well.

01:57:15.779 --> 01:57:18.479
She'd walked through it with Katy did

01:57:18.479 --> 01:57:20.279
once, but she didn't know the layout at

01:57:20.279 --> 01:57:20.460
all.

01:57:20.520 --> 01:57:22.920
Was there an order to the stalls?

01:57:23.039 --> 01:57:25.920
Were they organized together by category

01:57:25.920 --> 01:57:28.500
of items they sold, or scattered wherever

01:57:28.500 --> 01:57:30.300
they'd happened to land?

01:57:30.359 --> 01:57:33.479
From what she knew of Jewel Hive, she'd

01:57:33.479 --> 01:57:34.380
guess scattered.

01:57:34.439 --> 01:57:36.840
And she'd also guess that there wasn't a

01:57:36.840 --> 01:57:39.119
map anywhere in the market, if one had

01:57:39.119 --> 01:57:39.779
ever even been made.

01:57:39.899 --> 01:57:42.659
Lady Jewel wasn't exactly known for

01:57:42.659 --> 01:57:44.220
keeping her subjects organized.

01:57:44.279 --> 01:57:46.439
Which is good for us.

01:57:46.500 --> 01:57:49.140
This is probably the hive where we have

01:57:49.140 --> 01:57:51.180
the best chance of going unnoticed

01:57:51.180 --> 01:57:53.520
between the chaos of the dragons who live

01:57:53.520 --> 01:57:55.560
here, and the undisciplined guards.

01:57:55.619 --> 01:57:59.100
Then again, there wasn't really anywhere

01:57:59.100 --> 01:58:00.779
they could go unnoticed.

01:58:00.840 --> 01:58:03.180
If Queen Wasp decided to take over the

01:58:03.180 --> 01:58:05.220
eyes of every dragon in Pantala.

01:58:05.279 --> 01:58:08.460
But it had been 5 days since Luna and

01:58:08.460 --> 01:58:10.199
Blue escaped the Flame Hill Cavern.

01:58:10.260 --> 01:58:12.359
Cricket was hoping the search for them

01:58:12.359 --> 01:58:14.819
might have quieted down, at least a

01:58:14.819 --> 01:58:15.119
little bit.

01:58:15.180 --> 01:58:18.420
Blue and Sore Tail emerged from the back

01:58:18.420 --> 01:58:21.300
of the stall, yawning, with sundew behind

01:58:21.300 --> 01:58:23.699
them, looking mischievously pleased.

01:58:23.699 --> 01:58:27.000
You really take an unholy amount of

01:58:27.000 --> 01:58:29.100
pleasure in ripping happy dragons out of

01:58:29.100 --> 01:58:30.119
their peaceful slumbers.

01:58:30.239 --> 01:58:32.100
Swartell said to her.

01:58:32.159 --> 01:58:35.039
It's the best part of my day, she said.

01:58:35.100 --> 01:58:37.260
A little tiny bit of vengeance every

01:58:37.260 --> 01:58:37.680
morning.

01:58:37.739 --> 01:58:40.680
Blue's expression was slightly trance

01:58:40.680 --> 01:58:43.439
like, as though he'd slipped into a cloud

01:58:43.439 --> 01:58:45.239
of trying to imagine what it was like to

01:58:45.239 --> 01:58:45.960
be sundew.

01:58:46.020 --> 01:58:49.260
We should hurry, Cricket whispered.

01:58:49.319 --> 01:58:51.720
I'm not sure how long we have before the

01:58:51.720 --> 01:58:54.359
1st silk wings arrive, and I don't know

01:58:54.359 --> 01:58:56.159
how long it'll take to find what we want

01:58:56.159 --> 01:58:56.819
in this place.

01:58:56.880 --> 01:58:58.859
It's bigger than I remember.

01:58:58.979 --> 01:59:02.159
They ducked under the door web, and

01:59:02.159 --> 01:59:04.020
cricket led the way along the narrow

01:59:04.020 --> 01:59:05.279
cluttered paths of the market.

01:59:05.399 --> 01:59:08.399
All the stalls had their door webs or

01:59:08.399 --> 01:59:10.800
curtains lowered, but it was easy to tell

01:59:10.800 --> 01:59:12.899
what they sold by the merchandise that

01:59:12.899 --> 01:59:15.060
spilled over the edges and hung from the

01:59:15.060 --> 01:59:15.420
frames.

01:59:15.539 --> 01:59:18.840
The group passed an instrument stall with

01:59:18.840 --> 01:59:21.960
zebra hide drums and curved black metal

01:59:21.960 --> 01:59:22.380
harps.

01:59:22.439 --> 01:59:25.199
The next had a sign listing a selection

01:59:25.199 --> 01:59:27.600
of fruit juices, and the one after that

01:59:27.600 --> 01:59:30.300
featured curious flame silk lanterns

01:59:30.300 --> 01:59:32.760
without the flame silk, shaped like

01:59:32.760 --> 01:59:35.640
snails, or leopards, or birds in flight.

01:59:35.699 --> 01:59:39.720
Totally disorganized, Cricket thought.

01:59:39.779 --> 01:59:42.420
Each stall dropped wherever the shop

01:59:42.420 --> 01:59:44.159
owner could grab a space under the

01:59:44.159 --> 01:59:44.880
canopy.

01:59:44.939 --> 01:59:48.119
It was unhelpful for their search.

01:59:48.180 --> 01:59:50.460
But also kind of wonderfully free.

01:59:50.520 --> 01:59:54.060
Everything in Cicada Hive was regimented

01:59:54.060 --> 01:59:56.460
and orderly, in a way that cricket had

01:59:56.460 --> 01:59:57.300
never quite fit into.

01:59:57.359 --> 01:59:59.819
She wondered if her life would have been

01:59:59.819 --> 02:00:01.560
easier growing up in Jewel Hive.

02:00:01.619 --> 02:00:04.260
She also wondered how her inflexible

02:00:04.260 --> 02:00:05.159
mother could stand it.

02:00:05.220 --> 02:00:10.319
Oh, there, she cried, spotting a flare of

02:00:10.319 --> 02:00:12.180
bright silk poking out under a curtain.

02:00:12.300 --> 02:00:15.300
They hurried over, and she pushed through

02:00:15.300 --> 02:00:17.939
into the dark stall, her eyes adjusted

02:00:17.939 --> 02:00:18.359
slowly.

02:00:18.420 --> 02:00:21.779
There were no flame silk lamps in here, or

02:00:21.779 --> 02:00:23.640
at least, if there were, they were

02:00:23.640 --> 02:00:23.939
empty.

02:00:24.000 --> 02:00:27.239
Cricket squinted at the silk, draped and

02:00:27.239 --> 02:00:28.020
folded on the shelves.

02:00:28.079 --> 02:00:30.840
It was hard to see any colors or details

02:00:30.840 --> 02:00:32.579
with the outer stall curtains down.

02:00:32.699 --> 02:00:35.699
Here, Blue whispered.

02:00:35.760 --> 02:00:38.819
He held out one talon, and a small twist

02:00:38.819 --> 02:00:40.920
of silk spiraled out of his wrist onto

02:00:40.920 --> 02:00:41.579
his palm.

02:00:41.640 --> 02:00:45.239
It glowed there, like a miniature comet

02:00:45.239 --> 02:00:47.220
caught in his claws, lighting up the

02:00:47.220 --> 02:00:47.399
room.

02:00:47.520 --> 02:00:49.979
So cool.

02:00:50.039 --> 02:00:53.100
Thortail leaned toward it, and Blue moved

02:00:53.100 --> 02:00:54.000
it out of his reach.

02:00:54.060 --> 02:00:56.460
Careful, this will burn.

02:00:56.520 --> 02:00:58.500
I'm the only one who can touch it

02:00:58.500 --> 02:00:58.920
safely.

02:00:58.979 --> 02:01:02.039
Flame silk doesn't burn you?

02:01:02.159 --> 02:01:04.199
Cricket asked, surprised.

02:01:04.260 --> 02:01:06.840
Even the kind in the lanterns?

02:01:06.899 --> 02:01:09.539
How had she missed that in her reading?

02:01:09.600 --> 02:01:11.819
My dad said it wouldn't.

02:01:11.939 --> 02:01:13.680
After my metamorphosis.

02:01:13.739 --> 02:01:16.199
Blue lifted the light toward the

02:01:16.199 --> 02:01:16.619
ceiling.

02:01:16.680 --> 02:01:18.600
So it illuminated all the colors around

02:01:18.600 --> 02:01:18.899
them.

02:01:18.960 --> 02:01:22.319
And this is the kind in the lanterns.

02:01:22.380 --> 02:01:24.300
So be careful with it.

02:01:24.359 --> 02:01:26.939
Sundew said, or else you'll set this

02:01:26.939 --> 02:01:27.960
whole place on fire.

02:01:28.020 --> 02:01:31.079
And maybe the hive too, she added

02:01:31.079 --> 02:01:31.739
thoughtfully.

02:01:31.800 --> 02:01:34.859
On 2nd thought, go ahead and wave it

02:01:34.859 --> 02:01:35.039
around.

02:01:35.159 --> 02:01:38.279
Cricket realized, a few moments later

02:01:38.279 --> 02:01:40.199
that she should have been appalled by

02:01:40.199 --> 02:01:42.659
that joke, but she was distracted by the

02:01:42.659 --> 02:01:44.399
thought of how much she didn't know about

02:01:44.399 --> 02:01:45.239
Flame Silk.

02:01:45.359 --> 02:01:48.659
She wished she could stop for a day to

02:01:48.659 --> 02:01:50.699
investigate all the different kinds of

02:01:50.699 --> 02:01:53.159
flame silk blue could make now, and what

02:01:53.159 --> 02:01:53.819
they could each do.

02:01:53.880 --> 02:01:57.840
But we only have until sunset tomorrow to

02:01:57.840 --> 02:01:59.100
stop a new war.

02:01:59.159 --> 02:02:02.340
Fascinating scientific experiments would

02:02:02.340 --> 02:02:03.000
have to wait.

02:02:03.060 --> 02:02:06.840
I think this is what we want, she said

02:02:06.840 --> 02:02:09.600
tugging a waterfall of sunflower yellow

02:02:09.600 --> 02:02:10.680
silk off the wall.

02:02:10.739 --> 02:02:13.020
She flung it over sundew's shoulders.

02:02:13.140 --> 02:02:15.960
The leaf wing was the one who'd stand out

02:02:15.960 --> 02:02:16.800
the most of all of them.

02:02:16.859 --> 02:02:19.920
Her forest green scales might pass for a

02:02:19.920 --> 02:02:22.680
silk wings at a glance, but those 2 wings

02:02:22.680 --> 02:02:25.380
screamed, Leaf wing, arrest me.

02:02:25.439 --> 02:02:28.500
The silk draped along sundew's back and

02:02:28.500 --> 02:02:30.779
halfway down her tail. covering her wings

02:02:30.779 --> 02:02:31.619
and most of her body.

02:02:31.680 --> 02:02:34.800
Sundew twisted her neck to give it a

02:02:34.800 --> 02:02:35.579
suspicious look.

02:02:35.640 --> 02:02:37.920
What is this?

02:02:37.920 --> 02:02:38.880
she asked.

02:02:38.939 --> 02:02:41.579
What self-respecting dragon would wear

02:02:41.579 --> 02:02:42.840
something that would tangle up their

02:02:42.840 --> 02:02:43.439
wings like this?

02:02:43.500 --> 02:02:48.779
It's a cape, Cricket said patiently, tying

02:02:48.779 --> 02:02:50.819
the ribbons around Sundew's neck and

02:02:50.819 --> 02:02:52.380
arranging the folds to cover her

02:02:52.380 --> 02:02:52.920
shoulders.

02:02:52.979 --> 02:02:55.319
My mother thought they were very

02:02:55.319 --> 02:02:56.939
fashionable last time I saw her.

02:02:57.060 --> 02:02:58.800
Oh, good.

02:02:58.859 --> 02:03:01.439
A dragon we already know has excellent

02:03:01.439 --> 02:03:03.420
judgment, Sundew muttered.

02:03:03.479 --> 02:03:06.420
If you keep your wings folded in close

02:03:06.420 --> 02:03:09.060
sore tail said. squinting at her.

02:03:09.119 --> 02:03:12.420
And nobody accidentally pulls it off or

02:03:12.420 --> 02:03:13.140
peaks underneath?

02:03:13.260 --> 02:03:15.300
I'm still not sure it'll work.

02:03:15.359 --> 02:03:18.119
Could a silkwing afford something like

02:03:18.119 --> 02:03:18.420
this?

02:03:18.479 --> 02:03:21.180
Blue asked, touching one of the garments

02:03:21.180 --> 02:03:22.140
with his free talent.

02:03:22.260 --> 02:03:24.720
And she doesn't have antennae.

02:03:24.779 --> 02:03:29.159
Also, it's a little bright, Sundew said.

02:03:29.220 --> 02:03:32.340
If I must wear something ridiculous, I'd

02:03:32.340 --> 02:03:34.680
prefer it in black or dark green, or

02:03:34.680 --> 02:03:36.840
midnight blue if absolutely necessary.

02:03:36.899 --> 02:03:39.779
Nope, Cricket said.

02:03:39.840 --> 02:03:42.359
Swatting sundoes talons away from the

02:03:42.359 --> 02:03:43.920
nearest dark colored silk.

02:03:43.979 --> 02:03:47.100
In Jewel Hive, everyone is devoted to

02:03:47.100 --> 02:03:50.039
bright colors, lots of jewels, accessories

02:03:50.039 --> 02:03:50.579
everywhere.

02:03:50.640 --> 02:03:53.579
That's the only reason I think we have a

02:03:53.579 --> 02:03:54.840
chance of sneaking in.

02:03:54.899 --> 02:03:57.960
It's hard to notice anyone if everyone is

02:03:57.960 --> 02:03:58.680
trying to stand out.

02:03:58.739 --> 02:04:02.520
Unless we slink around in black, looking

02:04:02.520 --> 02:04:05.220
boring, we have to match the glamour

02:04:05.220 --> 02:04:05.819
around us.

02:04:05.880 --> 02:04:08.159
Even the silk wings?

02:04:08.220 --> 02:04:09.060
Blue asked.

02:04:09.119 --> 02:04:11.279
Yes, Cricket said.

02:04:11.340 --> 02:04:13.859
There's an ongoing competition here for

02:04:13.859 --> 02:04:15.659
who can hire the prettiest silkwing.

02:04:15.720 --> 02:04:17.579
Some of them don't even have to do

02:04:17.579 --> 02:04:20.220
anything, except sit in parlors and

02:04:20.220 --> 02:04:23.039
windows and porches and balconies, being

02:04:23.039 --> 02:04:23.460
beautiful.

02:04:23.520 --> 02:04:26.159
Sortail growled softly.

02:04:26.279 --> 02:04:29.279
Dragons as decoration.

02:04:29.340 --> 02:04:32.939
Maybe some of them like it, Blue

02:04:32.939 --> 02:04:33.420
offered.

02:04:33.479 --> 02:04:36.539
It sounds easier than smashing and

02:04:36.539 --> 02:04:38.039
remolding tree stuff all day.

02:04:38.100 --> 02:04:42.720
It sounds mind numbing, Sundew snorted.

02:04:42.779 --> 02:04:44.939
You couldn't pay me to have a bunch of

02:04:44.939 --> 02:04:46.859
hive wings stare at me all day long.

02:04:46.979 --> 02:04:49.800
Cricket privately agreed with her.

02:04:49.859 --> 02:04:52.260
She could only imagine sitting still for

02:04:52.260 --> 02:04:54.359
that long if she had a really interesting

02:04:54.359 --> 02:04:55.500
book to read.

02:04:55.739 --> 02:04:58.319
Well, sorry, that's what you have to be

02:04:58.319 --> 02:04:58.859
for today.

02:04:58.920 --> 02:05:02.579
Cricket said, a very fancy silk wing.

02:05:02.640 --> 02:05:05.399
She turned back to the other silks

02:05:05.399 --> 02:05:07.859
wishing she knew how much detail Queen

02:05:07.859 --> 02:05:09.539
Wasp had given out in the search for

02:05:09.539 --> 02:05:09.779
them.

02:05:09.899 --> 02:05:12.600
Did they all have to wear wing covering

02:05:12.600 --> 02:05:13.140
capes?

02:05:13.199 --> 02:05:15.359
Were veils still in fashion?

02:05:15.479 --> 02:05:17.579
Cricket knew almost nothing about

02:05:17.579 --> 02:05:18.539
accessories?

02:05:18.600 --> 02:05:20.699
They were frowned upon at Terrarium

02:05:20.699 --> 02:05:21.180
Academy.

02:05:21.239 --> 02:05:24.899
She found 2 smaller capes for sword tail

02:05:24.899 --> 02:05:27.779
and blue, in matching shades of rose gold

02:05:27.779 --> 02:05:30.600
with sparkling indigo beetles embroidered

02:05:30.600 --> 02:05:31.020
all over them.

02:05:31.079 --> 02:05:34.380
Her hope was to have them all look so

02:05:34.380 --> 02:05:36.720
bright and busy, that no one's eyes would

02:05:36.720 --> 02:05:39.300
be able to completely land on them, or

02:05:39.300 --> 02:05:40.800
notice the scales underneath.

02:05:40.859 --> 02:05:44.880
These are kind of cool, Blue said

02:05:44.880 --> 02:05:46.619
fighting a basket over to her.

02:05:46.680 --> 02:05:49.859
Inside were several translucent scarves

02:05:49.859 --> 02:05:52.260
and arm sheets woven with glittering

02:05:52.260 --> 02:05:53.340
black markings.

02:05:53.399 --> 02:05:57.840
Oh, wow, Cricket said. pulling one over

02:05:57.840 --> 02:05:58.560
her forearm.

02:05:58.619 --> 02:06:01.140
It looked like the glittering markings

02:06:01.140 --> 02:06:01.979
were part of her scales.

02:06:02.039 --> 02:06:05.819
As though she had extra lines and zigzags

02:06:05.819 --> 02:06:08.819
of black over and around her natural ink

02:06:08.819 --> 02:06:09.479
block patches.

02:06:09.600 --> 02:06:12.600
If she wore several of these on her legs

02:06:12.600 --> 02:06:14.819
tail, and neck, she would look more like

02:06:14.819 --> 02:06:16.920
a black dragon with spots of yellow and

02:06:16.920 --> 02:06:19.500
orange, then vice versa, which would

02:06:19.500 --> 02:06:20.939
hopefully make it harder to recognize

02:06:20.939 --> 02:06:21.180
her.

02:06:21.239 --> 02:06:23.579
She pulled out a few more and started

02:06:23.579 --> 02:06:24.300
putting them on.

02:06:24.359 --> 02:06:27.239
How are we going to pay for all this?

02:06:27.300 --> 02:06:28.680
Blue asked.

02:06:28.739 --> 02:06:31.260
You eternally sweet idiot.

02:06:31.380 --> 02:06:34.020
Swordtail said, poking him in the side.

02:06:34.079 --> 02:06:36.300
We're already on the run from the law

02:06:36.300 --> 02:06:36.840
remember?

02:06:36.899 --> 02:06:40.079
So who cares if we steal a few capes?

02:06:40.140 --> 02:06:42.180
We can't get in any more trouble than we

02:06:42.180 --> 02:06:42.539
already are.

02:06:42.600 --> 02:06:44.520
Blue winced.

02:06:44.579 --> 02:06:47.159
I know, but that's not.

02:06:47.939 --> 02:06:50.939
It's just, some dragon worked hard on all

02:06:50.939 --> 02:06:52.920
this, and they probably need the money

02:06:52.920 --> 02:06:53.579
for their family.

02:06:53.640 --> 02:06:55.500
It's wrong to steal from them.

02:06:55.619 --> 02:07:00.420
Oh, that, Swartell said with a sigh.

02:07:00.539 --> 02:07:03.600
Well, I hope someone's hiding a small

02:07:03.600 --> 02:07:05.399
fortune under one of your wings then.

02:07:05.460 --> 02:07:07.260
Sundew said wryly.

02:07:07.319 --> 02:07:10.560
I guess we could leave those 2 yams I dug

02:07:10.560 --> 02:07:11.100
up yesterday.

02:07:11.220 --> 02:07:14.640
Sordell said, with a wistful expression.

02:07:14.760 --> 02:07:19.260
Your cape is probably worth a 100 yams

02:07:19.260 --> 02:07:20.399
Cricket admitted.

02:07:20.520 --> 02:07:22.020
What?

02:07:22.140 --> 02:07:23.640
SwordTell protested.

02:07:23.699 --> 02:07:25.260
This silly thing?

02:07:25.380 --> 02:07:26.699
It doesn't even do anything.

02:07:26.760 --> 02:07:28.619
Why is it so expensive?

02:07:28.680 --> 02:07:30.000
Is it edible?

02:07:30.060 --> 02:07:32.460
How much is flame silk worth?

02:07:32.579 --> 02:07:33.840
Blue asked.

02:07:33.899 --> 02:07:35.340
Could I leave them this?

02:07:35.399 --> 02:07:38.100
He held out the strand of fire.

02:07:38.159 --> 02:07:40.859
Cricket hesitated.

02:07:40.920 --> 02:07:42.539
Yes.

02:07:42.600 --> 02:07:45.000
Flame Silk is pretty expensive.

02:07:45.060 --> 02:07:47.340
That would cover all of this, I think

02:07:47.340 --> 02:07:50.340
especially since it's brand new, and

02:07:50.340 --> 02:07:52.739
should last them a whole moon cycle, but

02:07:52.739 --> 02:07:54.960
blue, someone will figure out it had to

02:07:54.960 --> 02:07:56.760
be you who left it, don't you think?

02:07:56.819 --> 02:07:59.579
Who else would have bright new flame silk

02:07:59.579 --> 02:08:00.060
like that?

02:08:00.119 --> 02:08:03.239
Maybe somebody ordered it from WASPI.

02:08:03.359 --> 02:08:06.000
Like your school librarian does, Blue

02:08:06.000 --> 02:08:06.420
said.

02:08:06.479 --> 02:08:08.640
It feels like the right thing to do.

02:08:08.699 --> 02:08:10.859
Arrr!

02:08:10.920 --> 02:08:14.579
You are such a silk wing, Sundu groaned.

02:08:14.640 --> 02:08:16.500
This is the worst idea.

02:08:16.560 --> 02:08:19.260
It's basically leaving evidence behind.

02:08:19.319 --> 02:08:21.779
No one will guess it's from the little

02:08:21.779 --> 02:08:24.060
dragonette, who ran away from cicada

02:08:24.060 --> 02:08:24.539
hive.

02:08:24.600 --> 02:08:25.619
Blue said.

02:08:25.739 --> 02:08:28.380
He slipped the strand into the lantern on

02:08:28.380 --> 02:08:30.899
the ceiling, and light filled the stall.

02:08:30.960 --> 02:08:33.060
It could have come from an early morning

02:08:33.060 --> 02:08:33.539
customer.

02:08:33.600 --> 02:08:37.380
He paused and rubbed his wrists with a

02:08:37.380 --> 02:08:38.279
small smile.

02:08:38.340 --> 02:08:41.579
It's kind of awesome, knowing I have

02:08:41.579 --> 02:08:42.479
something everyone needs.

02:08:42.539 --> 02:08:45.659
I could give it away to anyone, anytime I

02:08:45.659 --> 02:08:45.960
want.

02:08:46.020 --> 02:08:50.640
Or Thordell observed, you could set your

02:08:50.640 --> 02:08:53.039
enemies on fire anytime you want.

02:08:53.100 --> 02:08:56.520
Sundew pointed one claw at sword tail.

02:08:56.579 --> 02:09:00.060
You, she said, are growing on me.

02:09:00.119 --> 02:09:03.539
Blue shook his head and met Cricket's

02:09:03.539 --> 02:09:05.340
eyes with a faintly sick expression.

02:09:05.399 --> 02:09:07.439
She guessed he was trying to imagine

02:09:07.439 --> 02:09:09.479
being a dragon who could set another

02:09:09.479 --> 02:09:12.479
living creature on fire, and that it was

02:09:12.479 --> 02:09:13.500
beyond his abilities.

02:09:13.560 --> 02:09:16.319
She brushed one of his wings with hers.

02:09:16.380 --> 02:09:18.600
I like you as you are.

02:09:18.720 --> 02:09:21.479
The dragon who gifts fire to those who

02:09:21.479 --> 02:09:21.840
need it.

02:09:21.960 --> 02:09:26.100
This doll is just silk, Cricket said

02:09:26.100 --> 02:09:27.180
glancing around.

02:09:27.239 --> 02:09:30.359
Come on, we need some jewelry too.

02:09:30.420 --> 02:09:33.119
Jewelry?

02:09:33.239 --> 02:09:34.739
Sundu complained.

02:09:34.800 --> 02:09:37.859
But even she had to admit, a little while

02:09:37.859 --> 02:09:40.560
later, in a shrouded jewelry stall, that

02:09:40.560 --> 02:09:42.479
the long necklaces of little gold leaves

02:09:42.479 --> 02:09:44.939
cricket found were kind of cool, and

02:09:44.939 --> 02:09:46.439
she'd maybe be all right with wearing

02:09:46.439 --> 02:09:47.579
just one of them.

02:09:47.640 --> 02:09:51.180
She was less pleased with cricket's other

02:09:51.180 --> 02:09:53.460
discovery, the thing cricket had really

02:09:53.460 --> 02:09:54.119
been looking for.

02:09:54.180 --> 02:09:57.840
A gold and jade headdress with so many

02:09:57.840 --> 02:10:00.479
points and squiggles and sparkles that it

02:10:00.479 --> 02:10:02.220
hid the fact that sundew had no

02:10:02.220 --> 02:10:02.939
antennae.

02:10:03.000 --> 02:10:06.239
The leaf wing carried on, as though

02:10:06.239 --> 02:10:08.279
cricket was attaching actual snakes to

02:10:08.279 --> 02:10:10.680
her head, but the end result was quite

02:10:10.680 --> 02:10:12.659
dazzling and entirely distracting.

02:10:12.720 --> 02:10:17.880
This is the worst, Sundew grumbled

02:10:17.939 --> 02:10:19.079
glaring into a mirror.

02:10:19.140 --> 02:10:22.859
Well, my tribe would fall over laughing

02:10:22.859 --> 02:10:23.520
at me right now.

02:10:23.579 --> 02:10:27.119
I'm sure they'd understand, that

02:10:27.119 --> 02:10:29.279
sometimes you have to sacrifice your

02:10:29.279 --> 02:10:30.659
dignity for a higher purpose.

02:10:30.779 --> 02:10:32.460
Sortell joked.

02:10:32.520 --> 02:10:35.819
Sundew swatted at him, and he darted out

02:10:35.819 --> 02:10:36.180
of the way.

02:10:36.239 --> 02:10:39.960
In the same stall, they found bejeweled

02:10:39.960 --> 02:10:42.779
head coverings for blue and sword tail

02:10:42.779 --> 02:10:45.180
that hung like masks of dewdrops around

02:10:45.180 --> 02:10:48.060
their eyes, and a bright blue veil shawl

02:10:48.060 --> 02:10:50.640
tiara thing, that mostly hid cricket's

02:10:50.640 --> 02:10:53.220
face and glasses, plus was also gaudy

02:10:53.220 --> 02:10:55.020
enough that sundew was a little

02:10:55.020 --> 02:10:55.560
mollified.

02:10:55.680 --> 02:10:58.560
At least I'm not the only one who looks

02:10:58.560 --> 02:11:01.199
like an exploding peony. she said

02:11:01.199 --> 02:11:02.340
surveying the others.

02:11:02.399 --> 02:11:06.300
I'm surprised these are allowed, Blue

02:11:06.300 --> 02:11:07.260
said to Cricket.

02:11:07.319 --> 02:11:10.079
Trailing his claws along the dangling

02:11:10.079 --> 02:11:11.760
leaves that ornamented a row of

02:11:11.760 --> 02:11:12.359
bracelets.

02:11:12.420 --> 02:11:15.000
I would have thought leaves fit under the

02:11:15.000 --> 02:11:16.140
rules against trees.

02:11:16.199 --> 02:11:18.600
Maybe in cicada hive.

02:11:18.659 --> 02:11:21.600
Lady Jewel allows her dragons to fly a

02:11:21.600 --> 02:11:23.460
little closer to the edges of the rules

02:11:23.460 --> 02:11:26.399
than most hive leaders, Cricket pointed

02:11:26.399 --> 02:11:26.640
out.

02:11:26.699 --> 02:11:29.640
What rules against trees?

02:11:29.699 --> 02:11:31.800
Sundew asked sharply.

02:11:31.859 --> 02:11:37.260
We, um, Blue faltered under her outraged

02:11:37.260 --> 02:11:37.920
glare.

02:11:37.979 --> 02:11:40.920
We are forbidden to put any trees in our

02:11:40.920 --> 02:11:41.220
art.

02:11:41.279 --> 02:11:44.699
No tree sculptures, no trees in the

02:11:44.699 --> 02:11:48.000
background of our paintings, no planting

02:11:48.000 --> 02:11:51.000
trees in our terrariums, cricket said

02:11:51.000 --> 02:11:53.220
thinking wistfully of her secret little

02:11:53.220 --> 02:11:54.420
tree back at school.

02:11:54.479 --> 02:11:56.819
Would anyone take care of it now that she

02:11:56.819 --> 02:11:57.119
was gone?

02:11:57.239 --> 02:12:00.720
Some fruit trees are allowed in the

02:12:00.720 --> 02:12:02.579
greenhouses, but only with special

02:12:02.579 --> 02:12:04.380
permission, and strictly under

02:12:04.380 --> 02:12:07.260
supervision by Queen Wasp, no tree

02:12:07.260 --> 02:12:09.479
planting, or anything that might make a

02:12:09.479 --> 02:12:10.680
tree grow in the savannah.

02:12:10.739 --> 02:12:14.760
Sundew picked up a rope of pearls, wound

02:12:14.760 --> 02:12:17.760
it around her front talons, and snapped

02:12:17.760 --> 02:12:19.979
the cord with one violent tug.

02:12:20.039 --> 02:12:23.279
Pearls flew everywhere, clattering over

02:12:23.279 --> 02:12:24.119
the countertops.

02:12:24.180 --> 02:12:25.979
Let's go.

02:12:26.039 --> 02:12:28.020
She growled at cricket.

02:12:28.079 --> 02:12:31.260
With a whirl of her saffron silk cape, she

02:12:31.260 --> 02:12:32.699
stalked out into the market.

02:12:32.760 --> 02:12:37.260
Whoa, Sortell said, looking up from a

02:12:37.260 --> 02:12:39.119
basket of turquoise earrings near the

02:12:39.119 --> 02:12:39.840
back of the stall.

02:12:39.840 --> 02:12:42.539
Did she just get even angrier?

02:12:42.539 --> 02:12:43.800
Or did I imagine that?

02:12:43.859 --> 02:12:47.399
Definitely angrier, Cricket said.

02:12:47.520 --> 02:12:49.079
I don't know why though.

02:12:49.140 --> 02:12:50.100
Do you, Blue?

02:12:50.159 --> 02:12:55.859
I think, I think maybe erasing trees, even

02:12:55.859 --> 02:12:59.220
from our art, is like Queen Wasp, trying

02:12:59.220 --> 02:13:00.899
to wipe out the leaf wings all over

02:13:00.899 --> 02:13:01.199
again.

02:13:01.260 --> 02:13:02.640
Blue said.

02:13:02.699 --> 02:13:06.359
I mean, maybe that's how it feels to sun

02:13:06.359 --> 02:13:06.779
do.

02:13:06.840 --> 02:13:09.000
I never thought of it like that.

02:13:09.060 --> 02:13:10.859
Cricket said.

02:13:11.100 --> 02:13:12.960
She'd always thought it was a silly

02:13:12.960 --> 02:13:13.380
rule.

02:13:13.439 --> 02:13:16.619
Trees were just another plant, and plants

02:13:16.619 --> 02:13:19.140
were useful for lots of things, and why

02:13:19.140 --> 02:13:20.159
not have more if they could?

02:13:20.220 --> 02:13:23.460
She'd never seen them as a symbol of the

02:13:23.460 --> 02:13:26.279
long gone leaf wings, but now she

02:13:26.279 --> 02:13:29.159
realized that Queen Wasp must think of

02:13:29.159 --> 02:13:30.000
them that way.

02:13:30.000 --> 02:13:33.539
Blue left 3 little coils of flame silk

02:13:33.539 --> 02:13:35.819
and stone vase on the counter and ducked

02:13:35.819 --> 02:13:37.020
outside with sword tail.

02:13:37.079 --> 02:13:39.960
As cricket started to follow them, she

02:13:39.960 --> 02:13:41.640
heard a small clattering sound behind

02:13:41.640 --> 02:13:41.939
her.

02:13:42.000 --> 02:13:45.600
Probably a mouse, she told herself.

02:13:45.659 --> 02:13:47.819
But she edged back toward the counter

02:13:47.819 --> 02:13:48.840
with her heart thumping.

02:13:48.899 --> 02:13:52.140
If there was another dragon in here, who'd

02:13:52.140 --> 02:13:54.359
seen them putting on their disguises, or

02:13:54.359 --> 02:13:56.819
blue, creating flame silk from his

02:13:56.819 --> 02:13:57.359
wrists?

02:13:57.420 --> 02:14:00.600
The baskets of jewelry behind the counter

02:14:00.600 --> 02:14:01.560
were still and quiet.

02:14:01.619 --> 02:14:04.859
Nobody could possibly be hiding back

02:14:04.859 --> 02:14:05.039
there.

02:14:05.100 --> 02:14:08.399
There weren't any corners or shadows big

02:14:08.399 --> 02:14:09.119
enough for a dragon.

02:14:09.180 --> 02:14:11.279
But then something moved.

02:14:11.340 --> 02:14:14.340
Something darted from one basket to

02:14:14.340 --> 02:14:14.640
another.

02:14:14.699 --> 02:14:18.359
Something smaller than a dragon, but

02:14:18.359 --> 02:14:21.000
bigger than a mouse, something with dark

02:14:21.000 --> 02:14:22.619
fur and swift paws.

02:14:22.680 --> 02:14:24.899
A reading monkey.

02:14:24.960 --> 02:14:27.479
I really need a better name for them.

02:14:27.539 --> 02:14:30.960
Cricket leaned over the counter, staring

02:14:30.960 --> 02:14:32.520
at the basket where it had disappeared.

02:14:32.579 --> 02:14:36.359
A long moment past, and then a small head

02:14:36.359 --> 02:14:38.159
poked out and stared back at her.

02:14:38.220 --> 02:14:43.319
Alert brown eyes, a sweet face, narrower

02:14:43.319 --> 02:14:46.020
than a monkey's, and furless, except for

02:14:46.020 --> 02:14:47.100
the top of its head.

02:14:47.159 --> 02:14:51.180
Don't be afraid, Cricket said softly.

02:14:51.239 --> 02:14:53.100
I just want to know what you are.

02:14:53.159 --> 02:14:56.159
The creature gazed at her.

02:14:56.220 --> 02:14:59.100
Was that curiosity in its eyes?

02:14:59.159 --> 02:15:01.260
Did it want to understand her too?

02:15:01.380 --> 02:15:03.300
Cricket.

02:15:03.359 --> 02:15:06.300
Swordell shouted, sticking his head back

02:15:06.300 --> 02:15:06.960
into the stall.

02:15:07.020 --> 02:15:09.659
The little animal jumped, and vanished

02:15:09.659 --> 02:15:10.500
behind the baskets.

02:15:10.560 --> 02:15:13.260
Dragons are coming from the hive.

02:15:13.319 --> 02:15:16.800
Oh, why couldn't I have found one of you

02:15:16.800 --> 02:15:18.359
before all this started happening?

02:15:18.420 --> 02:15:23.220
Cricket cast one last longing look at the

02:15:23.220 --> 02:15:25.260
creature's hiding spot, and then turned

02:15:25.260 --> 02:15:26.100
to hurry outside.

02:15:26.159 --> 02:15:28.439
Sortell was right.

02:15:28.500 --> 02:15:31.020
Dragons were starting to spill out of the

02:15:31.020 --> 02:15:34.020
hives, doors, and flying ledges, swooping

02:15:34.020 --> 02:15:36.060
off into the sky, or down toward the

02:15:36.060 --> 02:15:37.020
market.

02:15:37.079 --> 02:15:38.880
Jewel Hive was waking up for the day.

02:15:38.939 --> 02:15:41.699
Or at least its silk wings were.

02:15:41.760 --> 02:15:44.520
The tricky part was keeping out of sight

02:15:44.520 --> 02:15:46.859
until the market was relatively crowded.

02:15:46.920 --> 02:15:50.880
They managed by moving between stalls, and

02:15:50.880 --> 02:15:52.380
staying in the corners of the ones

02:15:52.380 --> 02:15:55.079
cricket guests were run by hive wings, and

02:15:55.079 --> 02:15:56.520
so more likely to open later.

02:15:56.579 --> 02:16:00.000
There was a close call with a silk wing

02:16:00.000 --> 02:16:02.100
who was sweeping behind the tents, but

02:16:02.100 --> 02:16:04.020
soon the narrow pathways were full of

02:16:04.020 --> 02:16:04.439
dragons.

02:16:04.500 --> 02:16:07.439
Cricket breathed a sigh of relief.

02:16:07.500 --> 02:16:09.720
She'd been right about Jewel Hive.

02:16:09.779 --> 02:16:11.640
Her memories hadn't failed her.

02:16:11.699 --> 02:16:15.180
Everyone wore bright colors and piles of

02:16:15.180 --> 02:16:15.899
gemstones.

02:16:15.960 --> 02:16:19.560
Capes swirled beside wings everywhere, and

02:16:19.560 --> 02:16:21.300
headdresses glittered from half of the

02:16:21.300 --> 02:16:21.960
heads around them.

02:16:22.020 --> 02:16:24.779
Even the silk wings who swept the streets

02:16:24.779 --> 02:16:27.600
had adornments in their ears, or silk

02:16:27.600 --> 02:16:28.680
scarves around their necks.

02:16:28.739 --> 02:16:31.979
They edged through the crowd, making

02:16:31.979 --> 02:16:33.899
their way slowly toward the hive.

02:16:33.959 --> 02:16:36.239
Cricket tried to look as though she was

02:16:36.239 --> 02:16:38.279
shopping, pausing to examine the

02:16:38.279 --> 02:16:40.439
merchandise here and there, smiling

02:16:40.439 --> 02:16:42.479
faintly at the stall owners who tried to

02:16:42.479 --> 02:16:43.079
lure her inside.

02:16:43.200 --> 02:16:46.440
She was the only hive wing in the group.

02:16:46.500 --> 02:16:49.200
So most dragons would assume the other 3

02:16:49.200 --> 02:16:50.700
were her silk wing servants.

02:16:50.760 --> 02:16:53.879
It was weird and uncomfortable to have

02:16:53.879 --> 02:16:55.920
them trailing behind her, heads down.

02:16:55.979 --> 02:16:58.379
It made her feel guilty to think about

02:16:58.379 --> 02:17:00.600
how many times she'd walked past their

02:17:00.600 --> 02:17:03.299
own silkwing cook, without saying hello

02:17:03.299 --> 02:17:05.940
or taken the silken workers at the market

02:17:05.940 --> 02:17:06.479
for granted.

02:17:06.540 --> 02:17:09.540
She wished sundew could lead the way.

02:17:09.659 --> 02:17:13.020
She wished Blue could walk alongside her

02:17:13.020 --> 02:17:15.420
wing to wing, so she could laugh with him

02:17:15.420 --> 02:17:18.239
and talk to him, and let everyone know he

02:17:18.239 --> 02:17:20.940
was wonderful, and just as important and

02:17:20.940 --> 02:17:23.819
interesting and valuable as any hive wing

02:17:23.819 --> 02:17:25.020
dragon in Pantala.

02:17:25.079 --> 02:17:28.620
But she kept up her part, acting like any

02:17:28.620 --> 02:17:31.020
other self-absorbed, fashion obsessed

02:17:31.020 --> 02:17:32.459
hive wing in Jewel Hive.

02:17:32.520 --> 02:17:35.579
Soon, the main doors of the hive were

02:17:35.579 --> 02:17:38.219
ahead of them, swarming with dragons

02:17:38.219 --> 02:17:40.319
coming in and out of the central glitter

02:17:40.319 --> 02:17:42.719
bazaar, which occupied the bottom 3

02:17:42.719 --> 02:17:43.739
levels of the city.

02:17:43.799 --> 02:17:46.379
All the windows were open to let in the

02:17:46.379 --> 02:17:48.779
sun, and the streets and stalls ahead of

02:17:48.779 --> 02:17:50.879
them shone like a shattered frozen

02:17:50.879 --> 02:17:51.599
rainbow.

02:17:51.659 --> 02:17:54.780
Behind her, sundew cleared her throat

02:17:54.780 --> 02:17:55.620
meaningfully.

02:17:55.680 --> 02:17:58.860
Cricket glanced around, and noticed the

02:17:58.860 --> 02:18:00.840
hive wing guards posted on either side of

02:18:00.840 --> 02:18:01.200
the doors.

02:18:01.319 --> 02:18:04.559
They wore sleek black armor and helmets

02:18:04.559 --> 02:18:07.260
that hid their faces, but Cricket guessed

02:18:07.260 --> 02:18:09.239
that the eyes glaring through the little

02:18:09.239 --> 02:18:11.040
slits would be dead white.

02:18:11.100 --> 02:18:14.459
Cricket fell to shiver of terrified

02:18:14.459 --> 02:18:14.819
despair.

02:18:14.879 --> 02:18:18.299
Queen Wasp was watching.

02:18:18.360 --> 02:18:20.159
Queen Wasp was everywhere.

02:18:20.219 --> 02:18:23.819
At the entrance to every hive, flying

02:18:23.819 --> 02:18:26.699
patrols over the savannah, inside every

02:18:26.699 --> 02:18:28.139
hive wing if she wanted to be.

02:18:28.260 --> 02:18:31.260
How could they possibly hope to sneak by

02:18:31.260 --> 02:18:31.500
her?

02:18:31.559 --> 02:18:33.539
How could they ever escape?

02:18:33.600 --> 02:18:36.360
When her gaze and her fury, could follow

02:18:36.360 --> 02:18:37.620
them wherever they went?

02:18:37.680 --> 02:18:41.700
The closest guard turned his head sharply

02:18:41.700 --> 02:18:42.180
toward them.

02:18:42.239 --> 02:18:46.920
Chapter 7.

02:18:46.979 --> 02:18:49.379
Don't look at them.

02:18:49.440 --> 02:18:50.340
Don't react.

02:18:50.459 --> 02:18:53.939
Sundew whispered fiercely, stepping on

02:18:53.939 --> 02:18:54.839
Cricket's tail.

02:18:54.899 --> 02:18:57.479
Cricket turned toward her with what she

02:18:57.479 --> 02:18:59.579
hoped was a lofty hive wing expression.

02:18:59.700 --> 02:19:03.180
This had the added benefit of curving her

02:19:03.180 --> 02:19:04.739
head away from the guard who was staring

02:19:04.739 --> 02:19:05.040
at them.

02:19:05.100 --> 02:19:10.680
It's all so boring, Cricket said, in the

02:19:10.680 --> 02:19:13.139
high, slow way that Jewel Hive Dragons

02:19:13.139 --> 02:19:13.739
often talked.

02:19:13.799 --> 02:19:17.219
I feel like I've seen everything a

02:19:17.219 --> 02:19:18.299
1000000 times.

02:19:18.360 --> 02:19:21.000
Where's the originality?

02:19:21.059 --> 02:19:23.879
I mean, yawn.

02:19:23.940 --> 02:19:26.459
You should try raindrop scales.

02:19:26.579 --> 02:19:28.920
A hive wing beside her in the crowd

02:19:28.920 --> 02:19:30.360
interjected unexpectedly.

02:19:30.420 --> 02:19:33.299
They're only open during the rainy season

02:19:33.299 --> 02:19:35.520
so everything feels brand new.

02:19:35.579 --> 02:19:36.659
I love them.

02:19:36.719 --> 02:19:38.699
Have you heard of Pinacache?

02:19:38.760 --> 02:19:40.559
She's the owner and the designer.

02:19:40.620 --> 02:19:43.139
She has a 100000000 innovative ideas

02:19:43.139 --> 02:19:43.860
every year.

02:19:43.920 --> 02:19:45.180
It's incredible.

02:19:45.239 --> 02:19:47.100
I wish I were that creative.

02:19:47.159 --> 02:19:49.020
Wow, really?

02:19:49.079 --> 02:19:51.540
I don't think I've been there, Cricket

02:19:51.540 --> 02:19:53.940
said, surprised into using her real

02:19:53.940 --> 02:19:54.360
voice.

02:19:54.420 --> 02:19:57.180
The stranger was a summer squash yellow

02:19:57.180 --> 02:19:57.659
color.

02:19:57.719 --> 02:20:00.780
With flecks of red and black scales and

02:20:00.780 --> 02:20:03.299
black wings, but she had covered herself

02:20:03.299 --> 02:20:05.520
with webs of garnets, and what cricket

02:20:05.520 --> 02:20:08.040
guessed were fake diamonds, since there

02:20:08.040 --> 02:20:08.700
were so many of them.

02:20:08.819 --> 02:20:13.139
A long sea green silk scarf was wound

02:20:13.139 --> 02:20:15.239
around her neck and body, all the way

02:20:15.239 --> 02:20:17.819
down her tail, pinned together with an

02:20:17.819 --> 02:20:20.100
enormous dragonfly brooch on her back.

02:20:20.159 --> 02:20:23.040
It's right by the salvation statue.

02:20:23.100 --> 02:20:25.139
The other dragon confided.

02:20:25.200 --> 02:20:26.819
Very expensive though.

02:20:26.879 --> 02:20:30.719
I must admit, I often go there for ideas

02:20:30.719 --> 02:20:32.879
and then see if I can find someone to

02:20:32.879 --> 02:20:33.479
imitate them.

02:20:33.540 --> 02:20:34.739
Don't tell.

02:20:34.860 --> 02:20:38.040
She giggled in a warm, friendly way.

02:20:38.100 --> 02:20:41.940
Your secret is safe with me, Cricket said

02:20:41.940 --> 02:20:43.200
smiling back at her.

02:20:43.260 --> 02:20:46.860
But the reverse would not be true, she

02:20:46.860 --> 02:20:48.899
thought, with a twinge of anxiety.

02:20:48.959 --> 02:20:52.020
The hive wing was all smiles and stories

02:20:52.020 --> 02:20:52.500
now.

02:20:52.559 --> 02:20:54.959
But if this dragon discovered that

02:20:54.959 --> 02:20:57.299
cricket was a fugitive, Wouldn't she turn

02:20:57.299 --> 02:20:58.260
her in immediately?

02:20:58.319 --> 02:21:01.979
Or, even if she understood and wanted to

02:21:01.979 --> 02:21:03.899
help them, she wouldn't be able to

02:21:03.899 --> 02:21:07.260
because at any moment, Queen Wasp could

02:21:07.260 --> 02:21:07.860
steal her mind.

02:21:07.920 --> 02:21:10.799
This other hive wing could never choose

02:21:10.799 --> 02:21:12.540
to run away like cricket had.

02:21:12.600 --> 02:21:15.059
She could never be free of the queen.

02:21:15.120 --> 02:21:17.280
She didn't have the choice to thank for

02:21:17.280 --> 02:21:17.639
herself.

02:21:17.700 --> 02:21:20.760
She'd helped them inadvertently though.

02:21:20.879 --> 02:21:23.879
Cricket snuck a sideways peak of the

02:21:23.879 --> 02:21:26.520
guards, the one who'd looked over must

02:21:26.520 --> 02:21:28.739
have seen 2 hive wings gossiping and lost

02:21:28.739 --> 02:21:29.219
interest.

02:21:29.280 --> 02:21:32.399
He was now staring attentively at the

02:21:32.399 --> 02:21:34.079
movement of birds on the canopy.

02:21:34.139 --> 02:21:37.680
Thank you very much, Cricket said to the

02:21:37.680 --> 02:21:39.479
yellow dragon as they stepped inside.

02:21:39.600 --> 02:21:43.319
I mean, um, for the recommendation.

02:21:43.379 --> 02:21:45.840
Maybe I'll see you there.

02:21:45.899 --> 02:21:47.399
The hive wing chirped.

02:21:47.459 --> 02:21:49.500
She waved and bustled away.

02:21:49.559 --> 02:21:52.379
The walls around them were weirdly, both

02:21:52.379 --> 02:21:54.540
comforting and claustrophobic.

02:21:54.600 --> 02:21:57.659
Cricket was so used to living in a hive

02:21:57.659 --> 02:21:59.399
with walls around her all the time.

02:21:59.459 --> 02:22:02.219
And yet she found her scales prickling

02:22:02.219 --> 02:22:04.860
anxiously, her eyes wishing for the sky

02:22:04.860 --> 02:22:05.280
overhead.

02:22:05.340 --> 02:22:08.639
It's not the walls that are bothering

02:22:08.639 --> 02:22:08.819
me.

02:22:08.879 --> 02:22:10.979
She acknowledged to herself.

02:22:11.040 --> 02:22:13.319
It's the dragons inside them.

02:22:13.379 --> 02:22:15.840
She seemed really nice.

02:22:15.899 --> 02:22:18.540
Blue whispered, as they wound their way

02:22:18.540 --> 02:22:20.100
toward the center of the market.

02:22:20.219 --> 02:22:22.260
For a hive wing.

02:22:22.319 --> 02:22:23.760
Sundew scoffed.

02:22:23.879 --> 02:22:26.040
She did seem nice.

02:22:26.100 --> 02:22:27.360
Cricket agreed.

02:22:27.479 --> 02:22:29.100
Keeping her voice low.

02:22:29.159 --> 02:22:31.739
That's the kind of dragon I'm talking

02:22:31.739 --> 02:22:32.399
about, sundew.

02:22:32.520 --> 02:22:35.159
What would she do if the queen didn't

02:22:35.159 --> 02:22:35.700
control her?

02:22:35.760 --> 02:22:38.340
I mean, if she knew the truth about

02:22:38.340 --> 02:22:38.760
everything.

02:22:38.879 --> 02:22:42.000
The flame silks, the book of clear sight

02:22:42.000 --> 02:22:44.520
and she didn't have the queen in her head

02:22:44.520 --> 02:22:47.100
making her do things, and messing with

02:22:47.100 --> 02:22:47.520
her thoughts.

02:22:47.639 --> 02:22:49.260
Then could we trust her?

02:22:49.319 --> 02:22:51.420
Maybe she would try to help us.

02:22:51.479 --> 02:22:52.979
Like you.

02:22:53.100 --> 02:22:54.719
Blue said.

02:22:54.780 --> 02:22:56.639
Maybe she'd be like you.

02:22:56.700 --> 02:22:58.920
Maybe a lot of them wish they could be

02:22:58.920 --> 02:22:59.159
free.

02:22:59.219 --> 02:23:01.379
Doubtful.

02:23:01.440 --> 02:23:02.700
Sundew said.

02:23:02.760 --> 02:23:05.040
Everything is easy for hive wings like

02:23:05.040 --> 02:23:05.280
her.

02:23:05.340 --> 02:23:07.680
Why would she risk her own happy life?

02:23:07.739 --> 02:23:11.819
Yeah, Soritell said fervently.

02:23:11.879 --> 02:23:14.040
Hive Wings don't care about anyone but

02:23:14.040 --> 02:23:14.399
themselves.

02:23:14.459 --> 02:23:18.239
Cricket flinched, and Blue frowned at

02:23:18.239 --> 02:23:18.840
Swordtail.

02:23:18.899 --> 02:23:21.600
That's really unfair, sword tail.

02:23:21.659 --> 02:23:23.280
You don't know what's going on in their

02:23:23.280 --> 02:23:23.639
hearts.

02:23:23.700 --> 02:23:26.700
The only high wing you know is cricket

02:23:26.700 --> 02:23:27.899
and she cares a lot.

02:23:27.959 --> 02:23:31.319
But I care because of you, cricket

02:23:31.319 --> 02:23:32.879
thought, watching him.

02:23:32.940 --> 02:23:36.299
I might never have known any of this, if

02:23:36.299 --> 02:23:37.079
it wasn't for you.

02:23:37.200 --> 02:23:39.360
I know plenty.

02:23:39.420 --> 02:23:41.819
Swordell grumbled under his breath.

02:23:41.879 --> 02:23:45.180
I think cricket is different from all the

02:23:45.180 --> 02:23:46.920
others, Sundoo said.

02:23:46.979 --> 02:23:49.799
There was something in her voice, as

02:23:49.799 --> 02:23:51.299
though she needed to convince herself

02:23:51.299 --> 02:23:52.379
that was true.

02:23:52.440 --> 02:23:53.819
Maybe not.

02:23:53.879 --> 02:23:56.219
What do you think, cricket?

02:23:56.280 --> 02:23:58.319
Are there any other hive wings who are?

02:23:58.379 --> 02:24:00.360
Who can't be?

02:24:01.079 --> 02:24:03.420
I mean, whose brains are like yours.

02:24:03.479 --> 02:24:06.840
Blue asked Cricket, glancing around

02:24:06.840 --> 02:24:07.799
nervously.

02:24:07.860 --> 02:24:10.799
Not that I've ever met, cricket said.

02:24:10.920 --> 02:24:13.079
But we wouldn't exactly introduce

02:24:13.079 --> 02:24:15.420
ourselves that way, so how would I know?

02:24:15.479 --> 02:24:18.899
She thought of that 1st day she'd seen

02:24:18.899 --> 02:24:20.280
everyone's eyes go white.

02:24:20.340 --> 02:24:22.920
There was one dragon?

02:24:22.979 --> 02:24:23.579
long ago?

02:24:23.700 --> 02:24:25.739
I think he was trying to fight it.

02:24:25.799 --> 02:24:28.559
But the queen used everyone in the hive

02:24:28.559 --> 02:24:30.120
to catch him and bring him to her.

02:24:30.180 --> 02:24:33.540
I don't know what happened to him, but

02:24:33.540 --> 02:24:35.159
I'd guess he's not available for

02:24:35.159 --> 02:24:35.700
interviews.

02:24:35.760 --> 02:24:37.920
Blue shivered.

02:24:37.979 --> 02:24:40.979
And she brushed his wing, trying to be as

02:24:40.979 --> 02:24:42.659
reassuring as she could be in public.

02:24:42.719 --> 02:24:46.200
The dragons around them were so loud and

02:24:46.200 --> 02:24:48.239
moving so quickly that she didn't think

02:24:48.239 --> 02:24:49.739
they'd notice anything beyond the

02:24:49.739 --> 02:24:50.879
bargains in their talons.

02:24:50.940 --> 02:24:54.420
But still, they had to be careful, for

02:24:54.420 --> 02:24:55.260
Blue's sake.

02:24:55.319 --> 02:24:58.200
Is that the salvation statue?

02:24:58.319 --> 02:24:59.879
Swordell whispered.

02:24:59.940 --> 02:25:03.360
Cricket craned her neck up and spotted

02:25:03.360 --> 02:25:05.100
the head of the dragon that loomed over

02:25:05.100 --> 02:25:06.540
the center of the glitter bazaar.

02:25:06.600 --> 02:25:10.020
It wasn't the real queen wasp, but the

02:25:10.020 --> 02:25:11.579
details of the stone work were so

02:25:11.579 --> 02:25:14.280
accurate, the cricket half expected the

02:25:14.280 --> 02:25:16.680
statue to suddenly twist around and glare

02:25:16.680 --> 02:25:17.100
at her.

02:25:17.159 --> 02:25:18.600
But it didn't.

02:25:18.659 --> 02:25:22.020
The stone queen stayed frozen in place

02:25:22.020 --> 02:25:25.979
wings flung out triumphantly, one talon

02:25:25.979 --> 02:25:27.540
holding up the book of clear sight.

02:25:27.659 --> 02:25:31.319
Cricket stumbled, suddenly remembering

02:25:31.319 --> 02:25:33.239
the rest of the statue that commemorated

02:25:33.239 --> 02:25:33.840
the end of the war.

02:25:33.899 --> 02:25:37.680
The marble dragon that lay dead below the

02:25:37.680 --> 02:25:40.260
queen's other talons, with one of her

02:25:40.260 --> 02:25:42.659
deadly wrist stingers plunged through his

02:25:42.659 --> 02:25:43.079
heart.

02:25:43.079 --> 02:25:46.020
She'd never stopped for a moment to think

02:25:46.020 --> 02:25:47.040
about that dragon.

02:25:47.100 --> 02:25:49.440
Because he wasn't anyone in particular.

02:25:49.500 --> 02:25:51.719
He was just the enemy.

02:25:51.780 --> 02:25:55.379
He was a blank nobody, representing the

02:25:55.379 --> 02:25:57.239
tribe who'd been defeated, and

02:25:57.239 --> 02:26:00.479
exterminated, when the hive wings saved

02:26:00.479 --> 02:26:02.100
the silk wings from them.

02:26:02.219 --> 02:26:04.440
He was a leaf wing.

02:26:04.500 --> 02:26:07.079
She glanced back at sundew.

02:26:07.139 --> 02:26:09.299
I should have warned you.

02:26:09.360 --> 02:26:11.819
She said quietly, this could be

02:26:11.819 --> 02:26:12.299
upsetting.

02:26:12.360 --> 02:26:15.959
Don't worry, Hivewing, Sundew muttered

02:26:15.959 --> 02:26:18.059
twitching her cape closer around her

02:26:18.059 --> 02:26:18.540
shoulders.

02:26:18.600 --> 02:26:20.940
I'm at full rage all the time.

02:26:21.059 --> 02:26:22.559
It can't get worse.

02:26:22.680 --> 02:26:24.959
All the time.

02:26:25.020 --> 02:26:26.940
Blue said wonderingly.

02:26:27.059 --> 02:26:28.139
Really?

02:26:28.200 --> 02:26:30.000
Don't you get tired?

02:26:30.059 --> 02:26:32.819
Yes, she growled.

02:26:32.879 --> 02:26:35.100
And that makes me furious too.

02:26:35.219 --> 02:26:38.219
They stepped out of the crowd into the

02:26:38.219 --> 02:26:39.360
space around the statue.

02:26:39.479 --> 02:26:43.200
Like the Salvation Mosaic and Cicada Hive

02:26:43.200 --> 02:26:45.600
this monument was also set apart from its

02:26:45.600 --> 02:26:46.260
surroundings.

02:26:46.319 --> 02:26:49.440
A tranquil circle of grass surrounded it

02:26:49.440 --> 02:26:52.379
strangely peaceful in the chaotic bustle

02:26:52.379 --> 02:26:52.920
of the market.

02:26:52.979 --> 02:26:55.379
Cricket noticed that most of the shopping

02:26:55.379 --> 02:26:58.260
dragons carefully went around the circle

02:26:58.260 --> 02:27:01.139
to avoid treading on the grass, unless

02:27:01.139 --> 02:27:02.760
they were going up to admire the statue.

02:27:02.819 --> 02:27:05.760
It was really extraordinary.

02:27:05.819 --> 02:27:09.719
Twice the size of any actual dragons, and

02:27:09.719 --> 02:27:12.120
carved from stone, cord in the northwest

02:27:12.120 --> 02:27:13.200
mountains of Pantala.

02:27:13.260 --> 02:27:16.440
An enormous ruby glinted from each of the

02:27:16.440 --> 02:27:19.260
queen's eye sockets, and gold letters

02:27:19.260 --> 02:27:21.059
were inlaid on the cover of the marble

02:27:21.059 --> 02:27:22.020
book of Clearsight.

02:27:22.079 --> 02:27:24.959
But the real book doesn't look anything

02:27:24.959 --> 02:27:26.940
like that, Cricket thought.

02:27:27.000 --> 02:27:28.979
Gazing up at the fake book.

02:27:29.040 --> 02:27:31.979
It's not shiny or enormous.

02:27:32.040 --> 02:27:34.739
It doesn't have a title emblazoned on

02:27:34.739 --> 02:27:35.100
it.

02:27:35.159 --> 02:27:37.500
It's not what's on the outside of the

02:27:37.500 --> 02:27:38.340
book that counts.

02:27:38.399 --> 02:27:39.959
It's what's on the inside.

02:27:40.020 --> 02:27:43.559
And that's the part Queen Wasp has been

02:27:43.559 --> 02:27:44.579
lying about to everyone.

02:27:44.700 --> 02:27:47.879
She glanced at the outline of the heavy

02:27:47.879 --> 02:27:50.459
pouch under sundew's cloak.

02:27:50.520 --> 02:27:53.520
We should make a copy of it, in case

02:27:53.520 --> 02:27:54.600
anything happens to it.

02:27:54.719 --> 02:27:58.200
But if anything did happen to it, who

02:27:58.200 --> 02:28:00.000
would believe us that the copy was real?

02:28:00.059 --> 02:28:04.500
Sortail was circling the statue, frowning

02:28:04.500 --> 02:28:06.360
and fiddling anxiously with his jeweled

02:28:06.360 --> 02:28:06.600
mask.

02:28:06.719 --> 02:28:10.920
Well, Sundu hissed as he returned to

02:28:10.920 --> 02:28:11.100
them.

02:28:11.219 --> 02:28:13.260
I don't know.

02:28:13.319 --> 02:28:14.340
He confessed.

02:28:14.399 --> 02:28:16.860
I don't see a place to leave a message

02:28:16.920 --> 02:28:18.479
that wouldn't immediately be seen.

02:28:18.540 --> 02:28:20.219
What would you do?

02:28:20.280 --> 02:28:24.899
Knock it over, she muttered, smash it to

02:28:24.899 --> 02:28:27.540
pieces with my bare talons, throw the

02:28:27.540 --> 02:28:29.159
broken rock chunks at everyone in this

02:28:29.159 --> 02:28:29.520
hive.

02:28:29.579 --> 02:28:33.239
But she stalked forward, and studied the

02:28:33.239 --> 02:28:34.260
statue with sharp eyes.

02:28:34.319 --> 02:28:36.659
Are you all right?

02:28:36.780 --> 02:28:38.579
Blue whispered to Cricket.

02:28:38.639 --> 02:28:39.899
Me?

02:28:39.959 --> 02:28:41.879
she said, startled.

02:28:41.940 --> 02:28:43.200
Sure.

02:28:43.260 --> 02:28:44.280
I don't know.

02:28:44.340 --> 02:28:47.280
This statue makes me feel so guilty now.

02:28:47.340 --> 02:28:49.260
And the book is all wrong.

02:28:49.319 --> 02:28:52.020
I wish dragons could read the real

02:28:52.020 --> 02:28:52.379
version.

02:28:52.440 --> 02:28:53.940
He nodded.

02:28:54.000 --> 02:28:57.659
I've been thinking about Clearsight, he

02:28:57.659 --> 02:28:58.260
said softly.

02:28:58.319 --> 02:29:02.219
She wouldn't want a war or this life for

02:29:02.219 --> 02:29:03.180
her descendants.

02:29:03.239 --> 02:29:04.979
Or for the other 2 tribes.

02:29:05.040 --> 02:29:07.260
But I don't know how we're going to help

02:29:07.260 --> 02:29:07.559
everyone.

02:29:07.620 --> 02:29:11.100
We're just 4 normal little dragons.

02:29:11.159 --> 02:29:13.739
I know, Cricket agreed.

02:29:13.799 --> 02:29:17.399
Well, 3 normal little dragons, and one

02:29:17.399 --> 02:29:19.379
vengeful warrior dragon with an arsenal

02:29:19.379 --> 02:29:20.219
of terrifying bugs.

02:29:20.340 --> 02:29:23.520
Sundew had paused near one corner of the

02:29:23.520 --> 02:29:24.299
statue's base.

02:29:24.360 --> 02:29:27.420
She turned casually and met Cricket's

02:29:27.420 --> 02:29:27.659
eyes.

02:29:27.719 --> 02:29:30.540
Swordtail stepped toward her, and she

02:29:30.540 --> 02:29:32.760
poked him backward, tipping her head to

02:29:32.760 --> 02:29:33.959
beckon cricket to her.

02:29:34.139 --> 02:29:36.420
There were only 2 other dragons on the

02:29:36.420 --> 02:29:37.379
grass circle with them.

02:29:37.500 --> 02:29:40.680
A father with a small dragonette, who

02:29:40.680 --> 02:29:42.120
were sitting on the far side of the

02:29:42.120 --> 02:29:44.819
statue, sharing a lemon pastry and

02:29:44.819 --> 02:29:45.959
talking about the story of the

02:29:45.959 --> 02:29:46.379
salvation.

02:29:46.440 --> 02:29:48.299
What is it?

02:29:48.360 --> 02:29:49.799
Cricket whispered.

02:29:49.860 --> 02:29:52.319
Sundew cut her gaze toward the very

02:29:52.319 --> 02:29:54.420
bottom of the stone slab, where the

02:29:54.420 --> 02:29:55.319
corner met the grass.

02:29:55.379 --> 02:29:58.739
A tiny shard of stone was missing, leaving

02:29:58.739 --> 02:30:00.600
a small gap between the base and the

02:30:00.600 --> 02:30:01.020
ground.

02:30:01.079 --> 02:30:04.559
Something pale green was shoved into the

02:30:04.559 --> 02:30:04.979
gap.

02:30:05.040 --> 02:30:08.760
Cricket realized that sundew had angled

02:30:08.760 --> 02:30:10.739
herself to shield cricket from view of

02:30:10.739 --> 02:30:12.600
anyone passing in the marketplace.

02:30:12.659 --> 02:30:15.780
She reached down and quickly tugged the

02:30:15.780 --> 02:30:16.440
something free.

02:30:16.500 --> 02:30:19.860
It was a leaf, folded into a square.

02:30:19.920 --> 02:30:24.360
Unfolded, a message was revealed, inked

02:30:24.360 --> 02:30:25.680
across the veins on the inside.

02:30:25.799 --> 02:30:30.360
Midnight, library, five.

02:30:30.420 --> 02:30:33.059
Her heart thumping wildly.

02:30:33.120 --> 02:30:35.760
Cricket refolded the leaf and slid it

02:30:35.760 --> 02:30:36.180
back into place.

02:30:36.239 --> 02:30:39.540
She didn't know what the 5 meant, but the

02:30:39.540 --> 02:30:40.379
rest seemed pretty clear.

02:30:40.440 --> 02:30:43.500
I think we have a way to find the

02:30:43.500 --> 02:30:46.500
chrysalis, she said to sundo, under her

02:30:46.500 --> 02:30:47.100
breath.

02:30:47.159 --> 02:30:49.739
And I think, I know where we can hide

02:30:49.739 --> 02:30:50.340
until then.

02:30:50.340 --> 02:30:54.959
Chapter 8.

02:30:55.020 --> 02:30:59.280
Cricket's mother, Cadell. lived about 8

02:30:59.280 --> 02:31:01.680
levels above the glitter bazaar, in a

02:31:01.680 --> 02:31:03.059
neighborhood of little residential

02:31:03.059 --> 02:31:06.299
squares and parks that was respectable

02:31:06.299 --> 02:31:07.799
but not the wealthiest part of the hive.

02:31:07.860 --> 02:31:11.280
It looked fancy enough to cricket, but

02:31:11.280 --> 02:31:12.899
she'd heard her mother complain for hours

02:31:12.899 --> 02:31:15.780
about the classless neighbors, the long

02:31:15.780 --> 02:31:18.239
climb to her job at the university, and

02:31:18.239 --> 02:31:19.680
the shabby condition of the streets.

02:31:19.739 --> 02:31:22.860
And one thing Cadell hated in particular

02:31:22.860 --> 02:31:26.159
was the water tower that stood in the

02:31:26.159 --> 02:31:28.620
center of the square, directly across

02:31:28.620 --> 02:31:29.399
from her house.

02:31:29.459 --> 02:31:31.200
It was ghastly.

02:31:31.260 --> 02:31:33.840
It was covered in rust, there was nothing

02:31:33.840 --> 02:31:34.920
more hideous in the world.

02:31:34.979 --> 02:31:37.379
Why couldn't she have been given a house

02:31:37.379 --> 02:31:39.000
on the sky view side instead?

02:31:39.059 --> 02:31:41.340
Why did she have to look at it every

02:31:41.340 --> 02:31:41.700
day?

02:31:41.760 --> 02:31:44.879
Was this her punishment for the 2 little

02:31:44.879 --> 02:31:46.739
monsters she'd loosed on the world?

02:31:46.799 --> 02:31:49.319
Couldn't the hive do something to make it

02:31:49.319 --> 02:31:50.040
more attractive?

02:31:50.100 --> 02:31:52.500
Why didn't anyone else care?

02:31:52.500 --> 02:31:54.840
If she'd been designing the hive?

02:31:54.899 --> 02:31:57.360
She'd have put all the water tanks under

02:31:57.360 --> 02:31:58.079
the street.

02:31:58.139 --> 02:32:00.840
Or at least on a level where no one

02:32:00.840 --> 02:32:02.100
important had to look at them.

02:32:02.159 --> 02:32:06.600
But on their 1st visit to Jewel Hive, Katy

02:32:06.600 --> 02:32:08.459
did and Cricket had decided that it would

02:32:08.459 --> 02:32:09.780
make a perfect hiding spot.

02:32:09.840 --> 02:32:15.120
Maybe not perfect, Katy did had conceded

02:32:15.120 --> 02:32:17.879
testing the rickety, rusty iron legs that

02:32:17.879 --> 02:32:18.420
held it up.

02:32:18.479 --> 02:32:20.579
You'll probably get wet.

02:32:20.639 --> 02:32:23.100
Not sure how you'll explain that.

02:32:23.159 --> 02:32:25.319
I'll think of something if I need to

02:32:25.319 --> 02:32:26.700
Cricket said.

02:32:26.760 --> 02:32:29.520
She'd flown up to the top of the tower to

02:32:29.520 --> 02:32:31.020
make sure she could open the hatch by

02:32:31.020 --> 02:32:31.319
herself.

02:32:31.379 --> 02:32:34.620
She was 4 then, but she had figured out

02:32:34.620 --> 02:32:36.479
the complicated latch after studying it

02:32:36.479 --> 02:32:36.899
for a moment.

02:32:36.959 --> 02:32:40.079
This was where silkwing workers would

02:32:40.079 --> 02:32:42.659
climb in and out to clean the tank, and

02:32:42.659 --> 02:32:44.100
where they'd pour in the new water

02:32:44.100 --> 02:32:46.500
gathered from sinkholes under the

02:32:46.500 --> 02:32:49.139
savannah, or transported by air from Lake

02:32:49.139 --> 02:32:50.040
Scorpion.

02:32:50.100 --> 02:32:53.100
This was the 1st thing they did wherever

02:32:53.100 --> 02:32:55.139
they went, Cricket and Katie did.

02:32:55.200 --> 02:32:57.659
Cricket was already used to doing it on

02:32:57.659 --> 02:32:58.139
her own too.

02:32:58.200 --> 02:33:00.000
In every new place.

02:33:00.059 --> 02:33:01.920
She looked for somewhere to hide.

02:33:01.979 --> 02:33:04.440
She needed somewhere she could get to

02:33:04.440 --> 02:33:07.680
quickly and quietly, in case Queen Wasp

02:33:07.680 --> 02:33:09.540
suddenly brainwashed everyone with her

02:33:09.540 --> 02:33:09.899
orders.

02:33:09.959 --> 02:33:14.159
Or, as Katie did call them, whole hive

02:33:14.159 --> 02:33:14.579
commands.

02:33:14.639 --> 02:33:17.700
She needed to be ready to vanish at any

02:33:17.700 --> 02:33:18.000
moment.

02:33:18.059 --> 02:33:21.239
She'd never had to use the water tower

02:33:21.239 --> 02:33:21.420
though.

02:33:21.479 --> 02:33:24.780
Their 2 visits had been short, and there

02:33:24.780 --> 02:33:26.940
hadn't been any all hive mind control

02:33:26.940 --> 02:33:29.399
moments while they were in Jewel Hive.

02:33:29.459 --> 02:33:32.700
So she just had to hope it was as good a

02:33:32.700 --> 02:33:34.139
hiding place as they'd thought it would

02:33:34.139 --> 02:33:34.319
be.

02:33:34.379 --> 02:33:37.139
The streets around her mother's house

02:33:37.139 --> 02:33:38.219
were mostly deserted.

02:33:38.280 --> 02:33:40.799
It was still fairly early in the morning

02:33:40.799 --> 02:33:43.260
so most dragons had either gone to work

02:33:43.260 --> 02:33:46.500
already, or, more likely, were still

02:33:46.500 --> 02:33:48.600
asleep after desperately trying to

02:33:48.600 --> 02:33:50.639
outlast everyone else at the parties and

02:33:50.639 --> 02:33:51.899
salons the night before.

02:33:51.959 --> 02:33:55.379
But the posters of Queen Wasps' face

02:33:55.379 --> 02:33:59.280
seemed to loom larger than ever. her eyes

02:33:59.280 --> 02:34:01.139
glaring down at them around every turn.

02:34:01.200 --> 02:34:05.639
Worse yet, new posters had sprung up on

02:34:05.639 --> 02:34:08.940
several of the walls throughout the hive

02:34:08.940 --> 02:34:11.879
wanted, wanted, for crimes against the

02:34:11.879 --> 02:34:13.860
tribe and the sacred memory of clear

02:34:13.860 --> 02:34:14.579
sight.

02:34:14.639 --> 02:34:17.760
Extremely dangerous, approach with

02:34:17.760 --> 02:34:20.700
caution, reward for any information or

02:34:20.700 --> 02:34:22.979
identification that leads to an arrest.

02:34:23.040 --> 02:34:27.299
And underneath all that, drawings of blue

02:34:27.299 --> 02:34:29.940
sword tail, and cricket.

02:34:30.000 --> 02:34:33.719
But not sundew, cricket noticed.

02:34:33.780 --> 02:34:37.559
Queen Wasp doesn't want to admit that a

02:34:37.559 --> 02:34:39.540
leaf wing got all the way inside her own

02:34:39.540 --> 02:34:40.200
hive.

02:34:40.319 --> 02:34:43.139
Even though 100s of dragons must have

02:34:43.139 --> 02:34:45.059
seen her as we escaped with a book.

02:34:45.239 --> 02:34:47.700
But if the queen says it didn't happen

02:34:47.700 --> 02:34:49.260
that's the new truth.

02:34:49.319 --> 02:34:52.139
Is there anyone who would dare to

02:34:52.139 --> 02:34:52.979
disagree with her?

02:34:53.040 --> 02:34:56.219
Her heart seized and jumped every time

02:34:56.219 --> 02:34:58.139
they passed another dragon near one of

02:34:58.139 --> 02:34:58.680
the posters.

02:34:58.739 --> 02:35:01.739
Every time a hive wing glanced at them.

02:35:01.799 --> 02:35:04.139
Every time she caught a glimpse of her

02:35:04.139 --> 02:35:06.540
own face on a wall behind someone's

02:35:06.540 --> 02:35:06.840
wings.

02:35:06.899 --> 02:35:09.899
What will happen to us if we get caught?

02:35:10.020 --> 02:35:12.959
What does Queen Wasp do with traitors?

02:35:13.079 --> 02:35:15.899
I've never heard of one in my lifetime.

02:35:15.959 --> 02:35:18.299
Is that because there haven't been any?

02:35:18.360 --> 02:35:20.700
Or because she made them disappear?

02:35:20.760 --> 02:35:24.299
I wonder what happened to that dragon who

02:35:24.299 --> 02:35:25.979
tried to fight back against the mind

02:35:25.979 --> 02:35:26.459
control.

02:35:26.520 --> 02:35:29.040
The only thing I know for sure?

02:35:29.159 --> 02:35:30.780
If we get caught.

02:35:30.840 --> 02:35:32.819
I'll never see blue again.

02:35:32.879 --> 02:35:35.879
He'll be thrown back in the flame silk

02:35:35.879 --> 02:35:36.360
cavern.

02:35:36.420 --> 02:35:38.159
And the rest of us?

02:35:38.280 --> 02:35:41.280
Will we be executed publicly?

02:35:41.340 --> 02:35:43.979
Or vanish without a trace?

02:35:44.100 --> 02:35:47.760
She'd always lived with a quiet fear at

02:35:47.760 --> 02:35:50.399
the back of her mind, that one day she'd

02:35:50.399 --> 02:35:52.440
be found out, and the queen would be

02:35:52.440 --> 02:35:52.979
furious.

02:35:53.040 --> 02:35:57.000
But this new fear was like termites in

02:35:57.000 --> 02:36:00.239
her skull, much more constant and present

02:36:00.239 --> 02:36:02.159
and squirming through all of her

02:36:02.159 --> 02:36:02.399
thoughts.

02:36:02.459 --> 02:36:05.459
When they reached the square her mother

02:36:05.459 --> 02:36:07.799
lived on, they had to wait out of sight

02:36:07.799 --> 02:36:10.379
around a corner, until a pair of silk

02:36:10.379 --> 02:36:12.239
wings finished polishing the arch around

02:36:12.239 --> 02:36:13.500
the water tower.

02:36:13.559 --> 02:36:17.040
Dragonfly Square was named for a hero of

02:36:17.040 --> 02:36:19.559
the tree wars, as were many spots all

02:36:19.559 --> 02:36:21.959
around the hives, and it was decorated

02:36:21.959 --> 02:36:23.879
with sculptures of dragonflies in her

02:36:23.879 --> 02:36:24.239
honor.

02:36:24.299 --> 02:36:27.840
They ranged from tiny mobiles, each

02:36:27.840 --> 02:36:29.940
dragonfly as long as one of cricket's

02:36:29.940 --> 02:36:32.700
talons, to one the size of a dragon

02:36:32.700 --> 02:36:34.559
perched on the side of the water tank.

02:36:34.620 --> 02:36:37.620
Their shiny metallic blues and greens

02:36:37.620 --> 02:36:40.440
gave the square the strange vibe of an

02:36:40.440 --> 02:36:41.280
electrocuted garden.

02:36:41.399 --> 02:36:45.120
Sundew peered around the square, as the 2

02:36:45.120 --> 02:36:47.340
cleaners packed up their things and set

02:36:47.340 --> 02:36:48.479
off down a side street.

02:36:48.540 --> 02:36:50.520
What's the plan here?

02:36:50.579 --> 02:36:52.079
She hissed.

02:36:52.139 --> 02:36:53.639
We're hiding in one of the houses?

02:36:53.700 --> 02:36:55.020
No.

02:36:55.079 --> 02:36:57.120
Cricket pointed at the tower.

02:36:57.180 --> 02:36:58.379
In there.

02:36:58.440 --> 02:37:01.079
There's a hatch at the very top, near the

02:37:01.079 --> 02:37:01.440
ceiling.

02:37:01.500 --> 02:37:04.260
Sortail wrinkled his snout.

02:37:04.319 --> 02:37:08.280
Um, isn't that full of water?

02:37:08.399 --> 02:37:10.139
Not all the way.

02:37:10.200 --> 02:37:11.399
Cricket said.

02:37:11.459 --> 02:37:13.680
There's a ledge and room to breathe at

02:37:13.680 --> 02:37:13.979
the top.

02:37:14.040 --> 02:37:18.120
He still looked skeptical, but Sundew was

02:37:18.120 --> 02:37:19.440
already striding toward the tallest

02:37:19.440 --> 02:37:19.680
house.

02:37:19.799 --> 02:37:22.620
Staying in its shadow.

02:37:22.680 --> 02:37:24.719
She spread her wings, tossing back the

02:37:24.719 --> 02:37:26.520
cape, and soared up the wall.

02:37:26.579 --> 02:37:29.040
She was in the open for 2 heartbeats

02:37:29.040 --> 02:37:31.379
hopping from the roof to the top of the

02:37:31.379 --> 02:37:33.600
tower, and then she was hidden by the

02:37:33.600 --> 02:37:34.379
curve of the tank.

02:37:34.440 --> 02:37:36.899
Cricket followed her along the same

02:37:36.899 --> 02:37:37.440
path.

02:37:37.500 --> 02:37:39.600
With blue and swordtail behind her.

02:37:39.659 --> 02:37:42.360
They all landed as quietly as they could

02:37:42.360 --> 02:37:45.000
on the top of the tank, but the thunk of

02:37:45.000 --> 02:37:47.340
their talons on the metal still echoed

02:37:47.340 --> 02:37:48.780
enough to make cricket wince.

02:37:48.899 --> 02:37:52.739
There was the hatch, and as before, she

02:37:52.739 --> 02:37:54.000
was able to get it open quickly.

02:37:54.059 --> 02:37:56.159
She slipped inside first.

02:37:56.219 --> 02:37:58.739
Reaching down with her tail to see how

02:37:58.739 --> 02:38:01.139
much space there was between the roof and

02:38:01.139 --> 02:38:01.739
the water level.

02:38:01.799 --> 02:38:05.340
It was higher than last time, just

02:38:05.340 --> 02:38:07.079
covering the ledge that ran around the

02:38:07.079 --> 02:38:08.219
inside at the top.

02:38:08.219 --> 02:38:11.399
Cricket dropped onto the flat, latticed

02:38:11.399 --> 02:38:14.579
surface, with a small splash, and edged

02:38:14.579 --> 02:38:16.979
around to the other side, where she and

02:38:16.979 --> 02:38:19.739
Katydid had stabbed one of 3 peep holes.

02:38:19.739 --> 02:38:22.440
Through the hole in the metal, she could

02:38:22.440 --> 02:38:24.239
see straight down to her mother's house.

02:38:24.299 --> 02:38:26.280
Is she still in there?

02:38:26.340 --> 02:38:28.319
Or did she leave for work already?

02:38:28.440 --> 02:38:32.040
Has she seen my face on the posters?

02:38:32.100 --> 02:38:34.680
Did she tell the queen I'm her daughter?

02:38:34.739 --> 02:38:37.020
Is she disappointed in me?

02:38:37.079 --> 02:38:40.020
Or did this just prove everything she

02:38:40.020 --> 02:38:41.219
thought about me all along?

02:38:41.280 --> 02:38:43.739
Cricket sighed.

02:38:43.799 --> 02:38:46.860
It was dark in the tank, and a little

02:38:46.860 --> 02:38:49.440
eerie, with a vast expanse of water

02:38:49.440 --> 02:38:50.940
silent below them.

02:38:51.000 --> 02:38:53.639
But she could feel the brush of Blue's

02:38:53.639 --> 02:38:55.860
wings as he came and settled next to her

02:38:55.860 --> 02:38:58.079
comforting her without saying a word.

02:38:58.079 --> 02:39:00.659
Mother might be disappointed.

02:39:00.719 --> 02:39:03.120
But being different from the other hive

02:39:03.120 --> 02:39:03.600
wings?

02:39:03.659 --> 02:39:06.299
I think that makes me lucky.

02:39:06.360 --> 02:39:09.239
Sundew closed the hatch behind her.

02:39:09.299 --> 02:39:12.659
And for a very long time, the 4 of them

02:39:12.659 --> 02:39:15.299
sat quietly, each thinking their own

02:39:15.299 --> 02:39:15.659
thoughts.

