02:50:03.299 --> 02:50:05.579
They really looked like cricket.

02:50:05.639 --> 02:50:08.159
Much more than the wanted posters did.

02:50:08.219 --> 02:50:11.639
As far as we know, no one has told the

02:50:11.639 --> 02:50:14.520
queen who you are yet, Katie did said.

02:50:14.579 --> 02:50:17.579
Maybe they haven't recognized you, or

02:50:17.579 --> 02:50:19.139
maybe they're afraid to admit they know

02:50:19.139 --> 02:50:19.379
you.

02:50:19.440 --> 02:50:21.659
I don't know why mother hasn't.

02:50:21.780 --> 02:50:24.000
But I was worried that the queen would

02:50:24.000 --> 02:50:26.340
see these drawings through her eyes and

02:50:26.340 --> 02:50:27.780
realize she must know you.

02:50:27.899 --> 02:50:32.219
But if you take them, Cricket said, then

02:50:32.219 --> 02:50:34.440
isn't it possible she'll see them through

02:50:34.440 --> 02:50:35.040
your eyes?

02:50:35.100 --> 02:50:37.680
I'm going to destroy them.

02:50:37.739 --> 02:50:39.899
Katy did said with a sigh.

02:50:40.020 --> 02:50:42.959
The queen has been mind hopping all over

02:50:42.959 --> 02:50:45.239
the hives, looking for clues about you.

02:50:45.299 --> 02:50:47.760
I'm afraid she must have figured out she

02:50:47.760 --> 02:50:49.020
can't get into your head.

02:50:49.079 --> 02:50:52.559
She has, Cricket said sadly.

02:50:52.620 --> 02:50:54.540
I'm sorry, Katie did.

02:50:54.600 --> 02:50:56.700
I tried to be so careful.

02:50:56.760 --> 02:50:59.520
But she was inside the librarian.

02:50:59.579 --> 02:51:00.899
Did you know that?

02:51:00.959 --> 02:51:04.079
She's always inside the librarian.

02:51:04.139 --> 02:51:06.479
As soon as the dragon becomes the

02:51:06.479 --> 02:51:08.819
librarian and joins the temple of

02:51:08.819 --> 02:51:12.299
Clearsight, Queen Wasp takes over, and

02:51:12.299 --> 02:51:14.459
never lets her control her own body ever

02:51:14.459 --> 02:51:14.879
again.

02:51:15.000 --> 02:51:17.700
Can you imagine how horrible that would

02:51:17.700 --> 02:51:17.940
be?

02:51:18.000 --> 02:51:20.879
But everyone wants to be the librarian

02:51:20.879 --> 02:51:22.559
Katy did pointed out.

02:51:22.620 --> 02:51:24.659
It's such an important position.

02:51:24.719 --> 02:51:27.659
Only because everyone doesn't know about

02:51:27.659 --> 02:51:29.459
this, Cricket cried.

02:51:29.520 --> 02:51:31.979
If they knew it meant giving up your free

02:51:31.979 --> 02:51:34.620
will forever, would anyone sign up for

02:51:34.620 --> 02:51:35.100
that?

02:51:35.159 --> 02:51:37.559
I think you're exaggerating a little.

02:51:37.680 --> 02:51:39.239
Katie did said.

02:51:39.299 --> 02:51:41.819
She started gathering all the drawings.

02:51:41.879 --> 02:51:44.219
Let's talk about this somewhere safer.

02:51:44.340 --> 02:51:47.159
Why isn't she listening to me?

02:51:47.219 --> 02:51:49.920
Cricket watched her sister for a moment?

02:51:49.979 --> 02:51:51.059
Puzzled.

02:51:51.120 --> 02:51:55.079
These were huge world shifting facts, the

02:51:55.079 --> 02:51:57.659
truth about the book, about Queen Wasp

02:51:57.659 --> 02:51:58.620
and the librarian.

02:51:58.680 --> 02:52:01.260
Why didn't Katy Did want to know more?

02:52:01.319 --> 02:52:03.479
How could she brush that information

02:52:03.479 --> 02:52:04.920
aside so easily?

02:52:05.040 --> 02:52:08.459
If someone told cricket, she'd been lied

02:52:08.459 --> 02:52:11.159
to her whole life, she'd want to grab the

02:52:11.159 --> 02:52:13.500
truth and rub it into her eyeballs.

02:52:13.559 --> 02:52:16.079
I can't go with you, Katy did.

02:52:16.139 --> 02:52:19.020
Cricket took one of her sister's talents

02:52:19.020 --> 02:52:19.559
and hers.

02:52:19.680 --> 02:52:21.540
It's too dangerous.

02:52:21.600 --> 02:52:24.120
You could be taken over by WASP at any

02:52:24.120 --> 02:52:24.479
moment.

02:52:24.540 --> 02:52:28.200
A fierce struggle crossed Katy did's

02:52:28.200 --> 02:52:28.440
face.

02:52:28.500 --> 02:52:30.420
That's true.

02:52:30.540 --> 02:52:33.000
But maybe we should go to her and

02:52:33.000 --> 02:52:33.360
confess.

02:52:33.420 --> 02:52:36.239
I was wrong to help you hide it all these

02:52:36.239 --> 02:52:36.659
years.

02:52:36.719 --> 02:52:38.940
Perhaps she can do something to fix you

02:52:38.940 --> 02:52:40.799
and make you like the rest of us.

02:52:40.860 --> 02:52:43.739
No, Cricket said.

02:52:43.799 --> 02:52:45.059
I don't want that.

02:52:45.120 --> 02:52:46.620
I would never want that.

02:52:46.680 --> 02:52:49.319
So what are you going to do?

02:52:49.440 --> 02:52:52.200
Katie did said, exasperated.

02:52:52.260 --> 02:52:54.299
Hide in a water tower forever?

02:52:54.360 --> 02:52:57.780
I have friends, Cricket said.

02:52:57.840 --> 02:52:59.520
We're looking for answers.

02:52:59.639 --> 02:53:01.500
I'm going to finally find out the truth

02:53:01.500 --> 02:53:02.219
about everything.

02:53:02.280 --> 02:53:05.579
Katy did let out a short bark of a

02:53:05.579 --> 02:53:05.819
laugh.

02:53:05.879 --> 02:53:09.239
That really is what you want, isn't it?

02:53:09.299 --> 02:53:12.600
The truth about everything, even if it

02:53:12.600 --> 02:53:14.579
makes your life a 1000000 times harder.

02:53:14.579 --> 02:53:16.139
Katie did.

02:53:16.200 --> 02:53:18.120
Why are you really here?

02:53:18.239 --> 02:53:19.739
Cricket asked.

02:53:19.799 --> 02:53:22.620
I mean, in Jewel Hive.

02:53:22.680 --> 02:53:24.479
You didn't come all this way for a few

02:53:24.479 --> 02:53:25.379
drawings, did you?

02:53:25.440 --> 02:53:27.659
Why aren't you home with father?

02:53:27.719 --> 02:53:30.299
If you're so sure the queen is right

02:53:30.299 --> 02:53:30.719
about everything.

02:53:30.780 --> 02:53:32.700
Why haven't you told her about me

02:53:32.700 --> 02:53:33.120
yourself?

02:53:33.180 --> 02:53:36.120
Her sister stepped over to the balcony

02:53:36.120 --> 02:53:38.219
and peered out through the slats in the

02:53:38.219 --> 02:53:38.399
door.

02:53:38.459 --> 02:53:42.180
Because I'd be in trouble too. she said

02:53:42.360 --> 02:53:44.760
And Lady Scarab wouldn't let me.

02:53:44.879 --> 02:53:47.040
Lady Scarab?

02:53:47.100 --> 02:53:49.920
Cricket clambered over the sleep pallets

02:53:49.920 --> 02:53:52.020
again, and peeked out the window next to

02:53:52.020 --> 02:53:52.680
the balcony.

02:53:52.739 --> 02:53:55.319
She could see the dragon waiting by the

02:53:55.319 --> 02:53:57.420
corner, twitching her wings and tail

02:53:57.420 --> 02:53:58.079
impatiently.

02:53:58.139 --> 02:54:02.159
Holy mother of trees, that was Lady

02:54:02.159 --> 02:54:02.819
Scarab.

02:54:02.879 --> 02:54:06.239
Cricket had met the grouchy, majestic old

02:54:06.239 --> 02:54:09.120
dragon a few times in her life, and it

02:54:09.120 --> 02:54:11.280
had always been very mysterious and

02:54:11.280 --> 02:54:11.879
alarming.

02:54:11.940 --> 02:54:14.879
The other dragonettes at school whispered

02:54:14.879 --> 02:54:16.440
all sorts of rumors about her.

02:54:16.500 --> 02:54:20.219
They swore she was older than the hives

02:54:20.219 --> 02:54:23.040
maybe as old as the book, which couldn't

02:54:23.040 --> 02:54:24.719
possibly be true, but it sounded

02:54:24.719 --> 02:54:25.139
dramatic.

02:54:25.200 --> 02:54:28.260
They said she had once been so powerful

02:54:28.260 --> 02:54:30.360
she could knock over a tree by breathing

02:54:30.360 --> 02:54:30.719
on it.

02:54:30.780 --> 02:54:34.079
They said she boiled silk wings in their

02:54:34.079 --> 02:54:35.579
cocoons and ate them.

02:54:35.639 --> 02:54:37.500
None of that was true.

02:54:37.559 --> 02:54:40.379
But Lady Scarab never bothered correcting

02:54:40.379 --> 02:54:40.799
the stories.

02:54:40.860 --> 02:54:43.260
She didn't seem to care what anyone

02:54:43.260 --> 02:54:43.680
thought of her.

02:54:43.739 --> 02:54:46.620
Not even when 2 of cricket's schoolmates

02:54:46.620 --> 02:54:49.799
saw her in the hall and screamed and flew

02:54:49.799 --> 02:54:51.059
out the nearest windows.

02:54:51.120 --> 02:54:54.780
What was true was that she was Lady

02:54:54.780 --> 02:54:57.239
Jewel's mother and Queen Wasp's aunt.

02:54:57.360 --> 02:55:00.659
She lived all alone in a giant mansion in

02:55:00.659 --> 02:55:03.180
cicada hives, with no servants or anyone

02:55:03.180 --> 02:55:03.479
else.

02:55:03.540 --> 02:55:06.299
No one knew why she didn't live in the

02:55:06.299 --> 02:55:08.459
same hive as her daughter, although she

02:55:08.459 --> 02:55:10.979
also owned a mansion in Jewel Hives, which

02:55:10.979 --> 02:55:12.420
she visited from time to time.

02:55:12.479 --> 02:55:16.559
One day, soon after Cricket's mother left

02:55:16.559 --> 02:55:19.020
Lady Scarab had appeared suddenly on

02:55:19.020 --> 02:55:22.200
their doorstep, their father, bowing and

02:55:22.200 --> 02:55:24.959
confused, led her in, and tried to offer

02:55:24.959 --> 02:55:27.600
her tea in the parlor, but Lady Scarab

02:55:27.600 --> 02:55:29.940
had announced that she wished to see Katy

02:55:29.940 --> 02:55:30.659
did and Cricket.

02:55:30.719 --> 02:55:33.479
So they lined up for her inspection, and

02:55:33.479 --> 02:55:35.100
she studied them through her spectacles.

02:55:35.219 --> 02:55:39.180
You look healthy, she said to Cricket.

02:55:39.299 --> 02:55:43.020
Yes, ma'am, Cricket had answered, thinking

02:55:43.020 --> 02:55:44.700
why are you here?

02:55:44.760 --> 02:55:46.379
Aren't you the dragon with the

02:55:46.379 --> 02:55:46.860
telescope?

02:55:46.920 --> 02:55:48.659
How old are you really?

02:55:48.719 --> 02:55:51.059
Do you ever eat little hive wings?

02:55:51.120 --> 02:55:53.579
Is that why you're pleased that I look

02:55:53.579 --> 02:55:54.000
healthy?

02:55:54.059 --> 02:55:57.059
Terrarium Academy?

02:55:57.120 --> 02:55:59.100
Lady Scarab demanded.

02:55:59.159 --> 02:56:00.600
Really?

02:56:00.659 --> 02:56:03.780
Um, Cricket said nervously.

02:56:03.840 --> 02:56:04.979
My school?

02:56:05.040 --> 02:56:06.540
I didn't choose it.

02:56:06.600 --> 02:56:09.899
I did, their father interjected.

02:56:09.959 --> 02:56:12.540
It's very practical, a down to earth

02:56:12.540 --> 02:56:12.899
place.

02:56:12.959 --> 02:56:15.420
No, pun intended.

02:56:15.540 --> 02:56:18.719
Lady Scarab said, with a wintry smile.

02:56:18.780 --> 02:56:21.239
But father just blinked in confusion.

02:56:21.299 --> 02:56:25.200
Fine, but don't let them grow moss on

02:56:25.200 --> 02:56:26.520
your brain, Dragonette.

02:56:26.579 --> 02:56:30.479
I, I won't, Cricket stammered.

02:56:30.600 --> 02:56:33.719
Although she had no idea how to stop her

02:56:33.719 --> 02:56:36.479
teachers if they decided to do that, and

02:56:36.479 --> 02:56:37.379
could they really do that?

02:56:37.440 --> 02:56:39.239
Had anyone done that before?

02:56:39.299 --> 02:56:40.739
What did they do?

02:56:40.799 --> 02:56:43.440
Put moss seeds in students' ears?

02:56:43.559 --> 02:56:46.379
Did it really work without any light in

02:56:46.379 --> 02:56:46.559
there?

02:56:46.620 --> 02:56:49.799
She'd only gotten rid of the ensuing

02:56:49.799 --> 02:56:51.780
nightmares later by doing a lot of

02:56:51.780 --> 02:56:54.000
research and figuring out that Lady

02:56:54.000 --> 02:56:56.459
Scarab must have been joking, because

02:56:56.459 --> 02:56:58.920
growing moss on a dragon's brain was

02:56:58.920 --> 02:57:00.540
quite scientifically impossible.

02:57:00.659 --> 02:57:04.260
I understand Cadell has left the family.

02:57:04.319 --> 02:57:07.680
Lady Scarab went on, turning to Katy

02:57:07.680 --> 02:57:07.979
did.

02:57:08.040 --> 02:57:10.500
Are you managing without her?

02:57:10.559 --> 02:57:14.520
Yes, your ladyship, Katy did said.

02:57:14.579 --> 02:57:15.959
Thank you for asking.

02:57:16.020 --> 02:57:20.700
Well, let me know if you need anything.

02:57:20.819 --> 02:57:23.879
The old hive wing had said, in a

02:57:23.879 --> 02:57:25.920
ferocious, you'd better tell me if

02:57:25.920 --> 02:57:27.540
anything's wrong, sort of way.

02:57:27.600 --> 02:57:31.559
I'm not far, and I'm not dead yet.

02:57:31.620 --> 02:57:34.379
Don't be a proud, hungry fool.

02:57:34.440 --> 02:57:37.860
And that dragonette needs new glasses.

02:57:37.920 --> 02:57:41.520
She'd flecked a claw at cricket, and the

02:57:41.520 --> 02:57:43.979
unsettling thing was, she'd been right.

02:57:44.040 --> 02:57:47.219
Cricket had needed stronger glasses, but

02:57:47.219 --> 02:57:49.500
she was still amazed that Lady Scarab had

02:57:49.500 --> 02:57:51.420
figured that out just by looking at her.

02:57:51.479 --> 02:57:55.260
Yes, your ladyship, Katy did said

02:57:55.260 --> 02:57:55.559
bowing.

02:57:55.620 --> 02:57:58.799
And then Lady Scarab had swept back out

02:57:58.799 --> 02:57:59.399
of their lives.

02:57:59.459 --> 02:58:03.600
But here she was, standing guard, while

02:58:03.600 --> 02:58:05.459
Katy did stole from her mother's house.

02:58:05.520 --> 02:58:07.440
Wait.

02:58:07.500 --> 02:58:08.819
Why?

02:58:08.819 --> 02:58:10.200
Cricket asked.

02:58:10.260 --> 02:58:12.239
What does Lady Scarab care?

02:58:12.299 --> 02:58:14.639
Did you say she won't let you turn me

02:58:14.639 --> 02:58:14.819
in?

02:58:14.879 --> 02:58:17.879
She came bursting into the house the day

02:58:17.879 --> 02:58:19.260
the wanted posters went up?

02:58:19.319 --> 02:58:20.700
Katie did said.

02:58:20.819 --> 02:58:24.059
She made me pack a bag, and told father

02:58:24.059 --> 02:58:26.700
not to tell Queen Wasp anything, about

02:58:26.700 --> 02:58:30.479
you, or me, or her taking me away, and

02:58:30.479 --> 02:58:32.459
then she brought me here, over the web

02:58:32.459 --> 02:58:33.239
bridges.

02:58:33.239 --> 02:58:35.760
I think she figures Lady Jewel can

02:58:35.760 --> 02:58:37.739
protect us from the queen if necessary.

02:58:37.799 --> 02:58:40.200
But I'm afraid she's wrong about that.

02:58:40.260 --> 02:58:42.719
She is definitely wrong.

02:58:42.780 --> 02:58:45.299
No one can protect anyone.

02:58:45.360 --> 02:58:48.719
As long as Queen Wasp can take over Lady

02:58:48.719 --> 02:58:50.940
Jewel or Scarab herself at any moment.

02:58:51.000 --> 02:58:55.379
I don't understand, Cricket said, trying

02:58:55.379 --> 02:58:56.700
to follow the threads.

02:58:56.760 --> 02:58:59.340
Why would Lady Scarab have anything to do

02:58:59.340 --> 02:58:59.760
with us?

02:58:59.819 --> 02:59:02.639
We're just a pair of random hive wings to

02:59:02.639 --> 02:59:02.879
her.

02:59:02.940 --> 02:59:04.319
Aren't we?

02:59:04.379 --> 02:59:07.440
Katydid started rubbing her face with a

02:59:07.440 --> 02:59:08.399
miserable expression.

02:59:08.520 --> 02:59:10.500
Katie did what?

02:59:10.559 --> 02:59:12.540
What aren't you telling me?

02:59:12.600 --> 02:59:14.219
Cricket?

02:59:14.280 --> 02:59:15.719
Why do you always have to know

02:59:15.719 --> 02:59:16.319
everything?

02:59:16.379 --> 02:59:18.120
Katie did cried.

02:59:18.180 --> 02:59:20.579
Your life would be so much easier if you

02:59:20.579 --> 02:59:23.940
didn't, wondering about silk wings, asking

02:59:23.940 --> 02:59:25.860
impertinent questions about the queen's

02:59:25.860 --> 02:59:26.280
powers.

02:59:26.340 --> 02:59:28.559
And then stealing the book of

02:59:28.559 --> 02:59:29.280
Clearsight?

02:59:29.340 --> 02:59:31.979
I was afraid you'd get in trouble one day

02:59:31.979 --> 02:59:33.719
but I didn't think it would be this bad.

02:59:33.840 --> 02:59:36.840
But wouldn't you rather know the truth

02:59:36.840 --> 02:59:39.299
than live in a cloud of lies?

02:59:39.360 --> 02:59:41.399
Cricket asked, confused.

02:59:41.459 --> 02:59:44.219
I mean, wouldn't everyone?

02:59:44.280 --> 02:59:46.079
No.

02:59:46.139 --> 02:59:49.139
Katy did crushed the drawings between her

02:59:49.139 --> 02:59:49.739
claws.

02:59:49.799 --> 02:59:51.420
Everything was fine.

02:59:51.479 --> 02:59:52.739
You were safe.

02:59:52.799 --> 02:59:54.899
No one ever needed to know about you

02:59:54.899 --> 02:59:56.459
especially you.

02:59:56.520 --> 02:59:59.639
Cricket felt her wings trembling.

02:59:59.700 --> 03:00:01.860
The way they sometimes did when she was

03:00:01.860 --> 03:00:03.420
close to an answer she'd been looking

03:00:03.420 --> 03:00:03.659
for.

03:00:03.719 --> 03:00:05.819
Katie did.

03:00:05.879 --> 03:00:08.159
Cadell is not your mother.

03:00:08.219 --> 03:00:10.139
Katie did blurted.

03:00:10.200 --> 03:00:12.540
And father is not your father either.

03:00:12.600 --> 03:00:14.940
Cricket stared at her.

03:00:15.000 --> 03:00:18.600
That was not what she'd expected to

03:00:18.600 --> 03:00:18.840
hear.

03:00:18.899 --> 03:00:22.200
Although, it explains a lot about the way

03:00:22.200 --> 03:00:23.159
they acted around her.

03:00:23.219 --> 03:00:26.819
But then who?

03:00:26.819 --> 03:00:28.079
She started.

03:00:28.139 --> 03:00:31.020
A loud pounding came from the door

03:00:31.020 --> 03:00:33.299
downstairs, making them both jump.

03:00:33.360 --> 03:00:35.940
They peeked out the window, and saw a

03:00:35.940 --> 03:00:37.799
lady scarab the whacking it impatiently

03:00:37.799 --> 03:00:38.219
with her tail.

03:00:38.340 --> 03:00:42.479
She told me to be quick, Katie did said

03:00:42.479 --> 03:00:44.459
Cricket, come with us.

03:00:44.520 --> 03:00:46.200
I'll tell you everything if I have to.

03:00:46.260 --> 03:00:48.659
Buy the hives.

03:00:48.719 --> 03:00:51.059
Those were words cricket lived for.

03:00:51.120 --> 03:00:52.440
Everything.

03:00:52.559 --> 03:00:56.340
Mysteries explained, puzzles solved, the

03:00:56.340 --> 03:00:58.860
whole truth finally revealed to her.

03:00:58.920 --> 03:01:01.620
But her friends were waiting in the water

03:01:01.620 --> 03:01:02.100
tower.

03:01:02.159 --> 03:01:04.620
They didn't know how to get to the

03:01:04.620 --> 03:01:06.540
library for the midnight meeting with a

03:01:06.540 --> 03:01:07.319
chrysalis.

03:01:07.379 --> 03:01:09.479
They wouldn't understand if she left with

03:01:09.479 --> 03:01:10.139
Katy did.

03:01:10.200 --> 03:01:12.239
And it really wasn't safe.

03:01:12.299 --> 03:01:15.659
Queen Wasp could look out of her sister's

03:01:15.659 --> 03:01:16.379
eyes at any moment.

03:01:16.440 --> 03:01:19.139
Cricket had already stayed too long.

03:01:19.200 --> 03:01:22.620
I can't go with you, she said.

03:01:22.680 --> 03:01:24.719
Can't you tell me everything now?

03:01:24.780 --> 03:01:26.700
Like, really quickly?

03:01:26.760 --> 03:01:29.100
Katie did hugged her fiercely.

03:01:29.159 --> 03:01:31.079
It's not that easy.

03:01:31.139 --> 03:01:33.239
I just want you to be safe.

03:01:33.299 --> 03:01:37.079
I can only be safe if I know the truth

03:01:37.079 --> 03:01:39.239
Cricket said, pulling back.

03:01:39.360 --> 03:01:42.780
Just like our tribe will only be safe if

03:01:42.780 --> 03:01:45.659
they stop believing wasps lies.

03:01:45.719 --> 03:01:47.040
Her sister sighed.

03:01:47.100 --> 03:01:49.020
I don't see why.

03:01:49.079 --> 03:01:51.000
They're perfectly safe now.

03:01:51.059 --> 03:01:53.159
Whatever you think she's lying to them

03:01:53.159 --> 03:01:53.459
about.

03:01:53.520 --> 03:01:55.379
Oh, Cricket.

03:01:55.440 --> 03:01:56.159
I have to go.

03:01:56.219 --> 03:01:58.680
But I'm afraid I'll never see you again.

03:01:58.739 --> 03:02:00.479
Can I find you?

03:02:00.540 --> 03:02:01.799
Cricket asked.

03:02:01.860 --> 03:02:03.659
Tomorrow, around dawn?

03:02:03.719 --> 03:02:06.959
I'll be hiding at Lady Scarab's house

03:02:06.959 --> 03:02:08.219
Katie did said.

03:02:08.280 --> 03:02:10.860
Pressing cricket's front talons between

03:02:10.860 --> 03:02:11.399
hers.

03:02:11.459 --> 03:02:13.139
Please be careful.

03:02:13.200 --> 03:02:14.819
You too.

03:02:14.879 --> 03:02:18.059
Cricket hugged her again and let go.

03:02:18.120 --> 03:02:21.059
Katie did hurried out of the room with

03:02:21.059 --> 03:02:23.399
the drawings, and Cricket hurt her claws

03:02:23.399 --> 03:02:24.180
on the stairs.

03:02:24.239 --> 03:02:25.500
A few moments later.

03:02:25.559 --> 03:02:27.959
She came out the front door and locked it

03:02:27.959 --> 03:02:30.299
behind her, and then the 2 hive wings

03:02:30.299 --> 03:02:33.840
flew away, with lady scarab scolding Katy

03:02:33.840 --> 03:02:35.579
did in a furious undertone.

03:02:35.639 --> 03:02:39.180
Cricket stood in the barren room, looking

03:02:39.180 --> 03:02:41.819
at the empty walls and toilet shelves.

03:02:41.879 --> 03:02:44.159
She had cried herself to sleep in this

03:02:44.159 --> 03:02:46.680
room, wondering why Caddell had taken

03:02:46.680 --> 03:02:48.479
Katydid to dinner and left her behind.

03:02:48.540 --> 03:02:51.420
She had cried in other rooms like this

03:02:51.420 --> 03:02:54.299
wondering what was wrong with her, that

03:02:54.299 --> 03:02:55.739
her own mother didn't care about her.

03:02:55.799 --> 03:02:59.100
She had stared across the breakfast table

03:02:59.100 --> 03:03:01.860
at her blank faced father, who never

03:03:01.860 --> 03:03:04.680
asked questions about school or her life

03:03:04.680 --> 03:03:07.260
unless she got in trouble, and then it

03:03:07.260 --> 03:03:09.540
was usually something like, you still

03:03:09.540 --> 03:03:09.780
here?

03:03:09.840 --> 03:03:11.459
How long until you graduate?

03:03:11.520 --> 03:03:13.979
Quit bothering your teachers and stay out

03:03:13.979 --> 03:03:14.340
of my way.

03:03:14.399 --> 03:03:16.979
A part of her had always thought

03:03:16.979 --> 03:03:18.059
everything would make sense.

03:03:18.180 --> 03:03:20.700
Once she knew why she was different.

03:03:20.760 --> 03:03:23.639
Once she had the whole truth in her

03:03:23.639 --> 03:03:24.059
talents.

03:03:24.120 --> 03:03:27.959
But this wasn't a truth she could get her

03:03:27.959 --> 03:03:28.799
talons around.

03:03:28.860 --> 03:03:31.020
They weren't her parents.

03:03:31.079 --> 03:03:33.719
They never wanted her in the 1st place.

03:03:33.780 --> 03:03:37.319
Someone gave me to them against their

03:03:37.319 --> 03:03:37.559
will.

03:03:37.620 --> 03:03:41.700
So now the question was, Who?

03:03:41.760 --> 03:03:43.260
And why?

03:03:43.319 --> 03:03:47.760
Part two.

03:03:47.819 --> 03:03:50.280
A trail of silk.

03:03:50.399 --> 03:03:52.799
Chapter 10.

03:03:53.100 --> 03:03:57.120
Midnight, Library, 5.

03:03:57.479 --> 03:04:00.659
Cricket tried all day to focus on what

03:04:00.659 --> 03:04:03.180
that 5 meant, but she couldn't keep her

03:04:03.180 --> 03:04:05.040
buzzing mind away from the mystery of her

03:04:05.040 --> 03:04:05.399
parents.

03:04:05.459 --> 03:04:08.819
She leaned over the ledge and trailed her

03:04:08.819 --> 03:04:10.620
claws through the cold, dark water.

03:04:10.680 --> 03:04:14.639
Beside her, Blue shivered, as though he

03:04:14.639 --> 03:04:16.319
felt the chill traveling through her

03:04:16.319 --> 03:04:17.219
bones into his.

03:04:17.280 --> 03:04:19.979
Caddell is not your mother.

03:04:20.040 --> 03:04:23.100
Father is not your father.

03:04:23.159 --> 03:04:26.100
Dragonfly Square was busy in the early

03:04:26.100 --> 03:04:28.440
evening. as everyone bustled home from

03:04:28.440 --> 03:04:30.059
work to change into their nighttime

03:04:30.059 --> 03:04:31.860
glamour before going out again.

03:04:31.920 --> 03:04:35.159
Swordtail, watching through the spy hole

03:04:35.159 --> 03:04:37.559
reported that Cadell had sailed off with

03:04:37.559 --> 03:04:39.239
a very orange male dragon.

03:04:39.299 --> 03:04:41.219
But Cricket couldn't bring herself to

03:04:41.219 --> 03:04:41.520
watch.

03:04:41.639 --> 03:04:44.520
Her whole life, she'd been waiting for

03:04:44.520 --> 03:04:45.600
her mother to care about her.

03:04:45.659 --> 03:04:48.659
She didn't know how to dig up those seeds

03:04:48.659 --> 03:04:49.860
and replant them.

03:04:49.979 --> 03:04:52.500
She'd wanted something true she could put

03:04:52.500 --> 03:04:54.959
in front of her parents, so she could say

03:04:54.959 --> 03:04:57.420
look, here's why I'm different.

03:04:57.420 --> 03:04:59.700
Look, I found all the answers.

03:04:59.760 --> 03:05:02.520
Look, here's why you should love me

03:05:02.520 --> 03:05:02.879
anyway.

03:05:02.940 --> 03:05:05.340
But they would never care.

03:05:05.399 --> 03:05:07.139
She wasn't theirs.

03:05:07.200 --> 03:05:09.479
So whose was she?

03:05:09.540 --> 03:05:12.360
Where were her real parents?

03:05:12.420 --> 03:05:15.959
It was also unsettling, as she thought

03:05:15.959 --> 03:05:18.479
over their conversation, to realize that

03:05:18.479 --> 03:05:20.040
nothing she'd said had made any

03:05:20.040 --> 03:05:22.500
difference to Katy did, who is not

03:05:22.500 --> 03:05:23.399
actually in my sister.

03:05:23.459 --> 03:05:26.879
Cricket thought, before her brain shied

03:05:26.879 --> 03:05:28.379
away from thinking about that.

03:05:28.440 --> 03:05:31.440
Cricket rubbed her forehead, and tried to

03:05:31.440 --> 03:05:33.840
pull her scarves closer, but they didn't

03:05:33.840 --> 03:05:34.500
make her any warmer.

03:05:34.559 --> 03:05:38.280
She'd tried to tell Katy did about wasps

03:05:38.280 --> 03:05:41.459
lies, and Katy did had acted like the

03:05:41.459 --> 03:05:43.979
truth was just another story, another

03:05:43.979 --> 03:05:46.319
version of the world, instead of the only

03:05:46.319 --> 03:05:47.579
real version.

03:05:47.639 --> 03:05:49.739
Wouldn't you rather know the truth?

03:05:49.799 --> 03:05:51.600
No.

03:05:51.659 --> 03:05:53.940
I think you're exaggerating.

03:05:54.000 --> 03:05:56.459
I'm sure she had her reasons.

03:05:56.579 --> 03:05:59.520
How could Katie did say that?

03:05:59.579 --> 03:06:03.420
Queen Wasp lied so that the high wings

03:06:03.420 --> 03:06:04.739
could take over Pantala?

03:06:04.799 --> 03:06:07.020
And she nearly wiped out the leaf wings

03:06:07.020 --> 03:06:07.379
to do it.

03:06:07.440 --> 03:06:09.600
She made them all think they were

03:06:09.600 --> 03:06:11.100
following clear site's plan?

03:06:11.159 --> 03:06:13.739
She convinced everyone she had the right

03:06:13.739 --> 03:06:16.440
to rule over the silk wings, that the

03:06:16.440 --> 03:06:18.899
hive wings were the strongest tribe, that

03:06:18.899 --> 03:06:20.399
they deserved everything they wanted.

03:06:20.459 --> 03:06:24.420
She turned her own dragons into murderers

03:06:24.420 --> 03:06:25.680
and monsters.

03:06:25.739 --> 03:06:28.799
Maybe that's what Katie did, didn't want

03:06:28.799 --> 03:06:29.159
to see.

03:06:29.219 --> 03:06:32.340
Maybe I just need to try again.

03:06:32.399 --> 03:06:35.760
If I show her the book, if she meets blue

03:06:35.760 --> 03:06:37.920
and sundew, and takes a moment to

03:06:37.920 --> 03:06:38.579
understand them.

03:06:38.639 --> 03:06:41.760
If I tell her everything and try harder

03:06:41.760 --> 03:06:42.899
she'll have to see.

03:06:42.959 --> 03:06:44.459
She'll have to hear me.

03:06:44.520 --> 03:06:46.500
Are you all right?

03:06:46.559 --> 03:06:49.559
Blue whispered, taking one of her talons

03:06:49.559 --> 03:06:50.100
in his.

03:06:50.219 --> 03:06:52.860
Oh, sort of.

03:06:52.920 --> 03:06:55.739
Not really, she whispered back.

03:06:55.860 --> 03:06:57.360
Cold.

03:06:57.420 --> 03:07:00.180
Also, my whole life was a lie.

03:07:00.299 --> 03:07:01.620
But mostly cold.

03:07:01.739 --> 03:07:04.680
She nudged her glasses up and tried to

03:07:04.680 --> 03:07:05.280
smile at him.

03:07:05.340 --> 03:07:07.440
I can maybe help with that.

03:07:07.500 --> 03:07:08.760
He said.

03:07:08.819 --> 03:07:11.940
A softly glowing thread of flame silk

03:07:11.940 --> 03:07:14.340
unfolded from his wrist, snaking out

03:07:14.340 --> 03:07:15.899
toward her scales.

03:07:15.959 --> 03:07:18.059
She started to pull away, but he held on

03:07:18.059 --> 03:07:18.600
to her gently.

03:07:18.659 --> 03:07:20.819
Wait, he said.

03:07:20.879 --> 03:07:22.860
I've been experimenting.

03:07:22.979 --> 03:07:25.440
This kind shouldn't burn you.

03:07:25.559 --> 03:07:29.700
Cricket went still, realizing again how

03:07:29.700 --> 03:07:31.139
much she trusted him.

03:07:31.260 --> 03:07:34.020
The gold thread reached for her like a

03:07:34.020 --> 03:07:35.399
vine growing too fast.

03:07:35.459 --> 03:07:39.000
It wound around her claws and his, and

03:07:39.000 --> 03:07:40.260
spiraled up toward her shoulder.

03:07:40.319 --> 03:07:43.200
Everywhere the flame silk touched her

03:07:43.200 --> 03:07:43.680
scales.

03:07:43.739 --> 03:07:47.100
Warmth sank in, quietly spreading into

03:07:47.100 --> 03:07:47.520
her bones.

03:07:47.639 --> 03:07:49.680
Oh, wow.

03:07:49.739 --> 03:07:51.360
She said softly.

03:07:51.420 --> 03:07:53.579
It's like magic blue.

03:07:53.639 --> 03:07:56.219
Right, he said.

03:07:56.280 --> 03:08:00.659
I thought it would be much scarier, but I

03:08:00.659 --> 03:08:02.340
kind of love my flame silk.

03:08:02.399 --> 03:08:03.659
Is that weird?

03:08:03.719 --> 03:08:05.879
She shook her head.

03:08:05.940 --> 03:08:07.379
I love it too.

03:08:07.440 --> 03:08:10.559
She glanced over to the other side of the

03:08:10.559 --> 03:08:13.200
ledge, where Sortell had accidentally

03:08:13.200 --> 03:08:15.059
fallen asleep on Sundew's cape.

03:08:15.120 --> 03:08:17.879
The leaf wing sat pinned beside his

03:08:17.879 --> 03:08:20.760
snoring head, glowering and tapping one

03:08:20.760 --> 03:08:23.040
of her pouches with an ominous look in

03:08:23.040 --> 03:08:23.340
her eyes.

03:08:23.399 --> 03:08:27.479
I miss my mom's, Blue said softly.

03:08:27.540 --> 03:08:32.280
Oh, Cricket said, I'm so sorry, Blue.

03:08:32.340 --> 03:08:36.059
As I was coming out of the cocoon, he

03:08:36.059 --> 03:08:36.540
said.

03:08:36.600 --> 03:08:39.180
For a moment, I forgot everything that

03:08:39.180 --> 03:08:39.659
had happened.

03:08:39.719 --> 03:08:42.959
I thought I would open my eyes, and

03:08:42.959 --> 03:08:45.239
mother and silver spot would be there

03:08:45.239 --> 03:08:49.139
waiting for me, and smiling, and ready to

03:08:49.139 --> 03:08:50.520
hug me and take me flying.

03:08:50.579 --> 03:08:53.280
I've been trying not to think about them

03:08:53.280 --> 03:08:53.700
too much.

03:08:53.760 --> 03:08:58.680
But just for a moment, that felt so

03:08:58.680 --> 03:08:59.219
real.

03:08:59.219 --> 03:09:01.379
I hope they're all right.

03:09:01.440 --> 03:09:04.500
They must be worried about me and Luna

03:09:04.500 --> 03:09:07.260
especially with all those posters up.

03:09:07.319 --> 03:09:08.819
Cricket leaned into him.

03:09:08.879 --> 03:09:12.299
Queen Wasp won't hurt them, she said.

03:09:12.420 --> 03:09:15.059
It wouldn't accomplish anything, and

03:09:15.059 --> 03:09:15.959
she's very efficient.

03:09:16.020 --> 03:09:18.780
Maybe there's a way to get a message to

03:09:18.780 --> 03:09:18.899
them?

03:09:18.959 --> 03:09:20.100
Let's think.

03:09:20.159 --> 03:09:22.680
If we could find a silk wing going to

03:09:22.680 --> 03:09:23.399
cicada hive.

03:09:23.459 --> 03:09:26.280
She tried to think of silk wings who

03:09:26.280 --> 03:09:28.860
traveled between the hives, traitors

03:09:28.860 --> 03:09:32.219
messengers, You've been really quiet all

03:09:32.219 --> 03:09:33.959
day, Blue said.

03:09:34.079 --> 03:09:35.520
She sighed.

03:09:35.639 --> 03:09:36.899
I know.

03:09:36.959 --> 03:09:40.379
It's my sister told me that my parents

03:09:40.379 --> 03:09:41.819
aren't my parents.

03:09:41.940 --> 03:09:44.340
In the glow from the flame silk.

03:09:44.399 --> 03:09:46.020
She saw his eyes widen.

03:09:46.079 --> 03:09:47.399
Wow.

03:09:47.459 --> 03:09:49.979
He thought about that for a moment.

03:09:50.040 --> 03:09:53.459
So, who are your real parents?

03:09:53.520 --> 03:09:55.559
I don't know.

03:09:55.620 --> 03:09:58.979
And how was Lady Scarab connected?

03:09:59.040 --> 03:10:01.680
She couldn't be Lady Scarab's daughter

03:10:01.680 --> 03:10:02.159
could she?

03:10:02.219 --> 03:10:04.860
But then why wouldn't Scarab have kept

03:10:04.860 --> 03:10:05.040
her?

03:10:05.100 --> 03:10:07.920
That was too weird to even brush with her

03:10:07.920 --> 03:10:08.579
wings.

03:10:08.760 --> 03:10:10.799
Scarab had had one daughter.

03:10:10.860 --> 03:10:13.860
Lady Jewel, ages and ages ago.

03:10:13.920 --> 03:10:16.500
Cricket couldn't fit into her brain the

03:10:16.500 --> 03:10:18.239
possibility that scarab had had another

03:10:18.239 --> 03:10:18.780
egg.

03:10:18.840 --> 03:10:22.319
Decades later, with some mystery dragon

03:10:22.319 --> 03:10:24.180
and then given it away to Cadell.

03:10:24.239 --> 03:10:26.700
Katy Did didn't tell you anything else?

03:10:26.819 --> 03:10:27.899
He asked.

03:10:27.959 --> 03:10:29.340
She shook her head.

03:10:29.399 --> 03:10:31.379
She really didn't want to.

03:10:31.440 --> 03:10:35.219
Blue, this has to be connected to why I'm

03:10:35.219 --> 03:10:36.840
different from the other hive wings

03:10:36.840 --> 03:10:37.680
doesn't it?

03:10:37.739 --> 03:10:40.680
Maybe one of my real parents is resistant

03:10:40.680 --> 03:10:42.120
to the mind control too.

03:10:42.180 --> 03:10:45.899
Maybe Queen Wasp found out, and that's

03:10:45.899 --> 03:10:47.219
why they had to hide me with another

03:10:47.219 --> 03:10:47.520
family.

03:10:47.579 --> 03:10:51.059
He was silent, and she tipped her snout

03:10:51.059 --> 03:10:51.540
toward him.

03:10:51.600 --> 03:10:53.100
Blue?

03:10:53.219 --> 03:10:56.340
I just can't imagine leaving my

03:10:56.340 --> 03:10:57.719
dragonette with someone else.

03:10:57.780 --> 03:10:58.860
He said.

03:10:58.920 --> 03:11:00.959
That must have been so hard.

03:11:01.020 --> 03:11:03.719
There must have been a really big reason

03:11:03.719 --> 03:11:04.860
they couldn't keep you.

03:11:04.920 --> 03:11:08.700
His eyes met hers again, and then dropped

03:11:08.700 --> 03:11:09.600
away quickly.

03:11:09.659 --> 03:11:13.620
Like, if they weren't supposed to be

03:11:13.620 --> 03:11:14.579
together at all.

03:11:14.639 --> 03:11:18.540
She gasped and covered her snout with her

03:11:18.540 --> 03:11:19.020
talons.

03:11:19.079 --> 03:11:21.659
Across the water tower.

03:11:21.719 --> 03:11:22.860
Sundew twisted to look at them.

03:11:22.920 --> 03:11:25.500
It would never have entered her head

03:11:25.500 --> 03:11:26.459
before she met Blue.

03:11:26.520 --> 03:11:28.979
She wouldn't have been able to imagine it

03:11:29.040 --> 03:11:30.899
until it changed her own life.

03:11:30.959 --> 03:11:34.979
You think one of my parents was a silk

03:11:34.979 --> 03:11:35.399
wing?

03:11:35.459 --> 03:11:36.360
she whispered.

03:11:36.420 --> 03:11:37.860
Do you?

03:11:37.920 --> 03:11:39.299
He whispered back.

03:11:39.360 --> 03:11:41.760
It's not possible, is it?

03:11:41.819 --> 03:11:44.100
Am I a hybrid?

03:11:44.159 --> 03:11:46.799
Would hybrids be immune to the mind

03:11:46.799 --> 03:11:47.280
control?

03:11:47.340 --> 03:11:49.139
Silk wings are?

03:11:49.200 --> 03:11:50.579
Is that why I am?

03:11:50.639 --> 03:11:53.579
It seems like such an obvious possible

03:11:53.579 --> 03:11:54.180
answer.

03:11:54.239 --> 03:11:56.639
Why didn't I ever think of it before?

03:11:56.700 --> 03:12:00.059
Because I thought I knew my parents.

03:12:00.120 --> 03:12:01.920
Is that the answer?

03:12:02.040 --> 03:12:05.879
But if that's the answer, how do we save

03:12:05.879 --> 03:12:08.459
the other hive wings, we can't exactly

03:12:08.459 --> 03:12:10.079
turn them all into hybrids.

03:12:10.139 --> 03:12:12.000
I don't know.

03:12:12.059 --> 03:12:15.000
She tried to think of all the silk wings

03:12:15.000 --> 03:12:15.719
she'd ever met.

03:12:15.780 --> 03:12:19.379
Had any of them acted strange, like maybe

03:12:19.379 --> 03:12:21.299
they were secretly her mother or father?

03:12:21.360 --> 03:12:23.459
Not that she could remember.

03:12:23.520 --> 03:12:26.639
There was no science on potential silk

03:12:26.639 --> 03:12:28.079
wing hive wing hybrids.

03:12:28.139 --> 03:12:29.760
They were so forbidden.

03:12:29.819 --> 03:12:32.159
It wasn't even conceivable to study the

03:12:32.159 --> 03:12:32.399
idea.

03:12:32.459 --> 03:12:35.159
Wouldn't there be something more?

03:12:35.579 --> 03:12:39.059
More silkwing about her if she were a

03:12:39.059 --> 03:12:39.479
hybrid?

03:12:39.540 --> 03:12:42.299
Blue's antennae twitched?

03:12:42.360 --> 03:12:45.059
It's almost midnight, he said.

03:12:45.120 --> 03:12:49.079
Thank the trees, Sundoo responded.

03:12:49.139 --> 03:12:51.420
She yanked her cape out from under sword

03:12:51.420 --> 03:12:53.819
tail, dumping him into the vat of water.

03:12:53.879 --> 03:12:56.280
When he came up, sputtering and indignant

03:12:56.280 --> 03:12:58.440
she flung her tail around its snout.

03:12:58.500 --> 03:13:01.020
Shush, you great screech owl.

03:13:01.079 --> 03:13:01.920
It's time to go.

03:13:01.979 --> 03:13:03.959
It'll be all right.

03:13:04.020 --> 03:13:06.420
Blue said softly to Cricket.

03:13:06.479 --> 03:13:09.659
Under the noise of swordtail hauling

03:13:09.659 --> 03:13:10.440
himself out of the water.

03:13:10.500 --> 03:13:13.200
I'm sure whatever happened.

03:13:13.260 --> 03:13:15.840
Your real parents loved you, and wished

03:13:15.840 --> 03:13:16.860
they could have kept you.

03:13:16.920 --> 03:13:20.399
Cricket was not so sure, but she was

03:13:20.399 --> 03:13:22.799
relieved to be moving again, out of the

03:13:22.799 --> 03:13:25.860
tower, and on their way to the library, a

03:13:25.860 --> 03:13:27.479
place that had always been full of

03:13:27.479 --> 03:13:28.379
answers for her.

03:13:28.440 --> 03:13:31.979
She hoped the chrysalis silk wings would

03:13:31.979 --> 03:13:34.319
be like that too, full of answers.

03:13:34.379 --> 03:13:38.399
If she could figure out what 5 meant and

03:13:38.399 --> 03:13:39.059
find them.

03:13:39.059 --> 03:13:42.120
The library was a few levels up from

03:13:42.120 --> 03:13:44.579
Cadell's neighborhood, just above the

03:13:44.579 --> 03:13:47.219
Jewel Hive Nest, and below several levels

03:13:47.219 --> 03:13:49.200
of expensive ballrooms and wealthy

03:13:49.200 --> 03:13:49.739
mansions.

03:13:49.799 --> 03:13:52.500
It was one of cricket's favorite places

03:13:52.500 --> 03:13:55.440
in all the hives, and she always wondered

03:13:55.440 --> 03:13:57.540
why Jewel Hive was only famous for the

03:13:57.540 --> 03:13:58.440
glitter bazaar.

03:13:58.500 --> 03:14:01.139
Why didn't other dragons ever talk about

03:14:01.139 --> 03:14:03.479
the library that took up an entire level

03:14:03.479 --> 03:14:06.540
containing every book ever written by a

03:14:06.540 --> 03:14:07.139
hive wing?

03:14:07.200 --> 03:14:09.780
Perhaps because it didn't fit with the

03:14:09.780 --> 03:14:11.040
image of Jewel Hive?

03:14:11.100 --> 03:14:14.219
No one imagined the dragons here, choosing

03:14:14.219 --> 03:14:16.620
reading over shopping, or jewelry

03:14:16.620 --> 03:14:16.860
making.

03:14:16.920 --> 03:14:21.299
And yet, for some reason, Lady Jewel

03:14:21.299 --> 03:14:24.479
wanted this library, Cricket thought, as

03:14:24.479 --> 03:14:26.100
they crept up to the enormous double

03:14:26.100 --> 03:14:27.299
doors at the front entrance.

03:14:27.360 --> 03:14:30.780
She made sure it was built into her hive

03:14:30.780 --> 03:14:31.260
plans.

03:14:31.319 --> 03:14:34.020
None of the other hives have one quite

03:14:34.020 --> 03:14:37.739
this big, not even mantis hive, which is

03:14:37.739 --> 03:14:39.719
supposed to be the smart hive, the

03:14:39.719 --> 03:14:41.459
academic center of innovation.

03:14:41.520 --> 03:14:44.280
Cricket looked up at the flying beetles

03:14:44.280 --> 03:14:45.420
carved over the doors.

03:14:45.479 --> 03:14:48.239
The joke in the other hives was that Lady

03:14:48.239 --> 03:14:49.440
Jewel couldn't even read.

03:14:49.500 --> 03:14:51.899
Although surely that wasn't really true.

03:14:52.020 --> 03:14:56.760
Still, why did Jewel want a library that

03:14:56.760 --> 03:14:58.079
she apparently never goes into?

03:14:58.139 --> 03:15:02.459
Despite Joel Hive's reputation, the

03:15:02.459 --> 03:15:03.659
library was never empty.

03:15:03.719 --> 03:15:05.879
At least as far as cricket had seen.

03:15:05.940 --> 03:15:08.520
There were always dragonettes everywhere

03:15:08.520 --> 03:15:11.280
sprawled along the tops of bookshelves

03:15:11.280 --> 03:15:13.979
curled in the window nooks, lying in the

03:15:13.979 --> 03:15:16.620
hammocks, and reading, reading, reading.

03:15:16.680 --> 03:15:21.000
But now, near midnight, it was closed and

03:15:21.000 --> 03:15:21.479
deserted.

03:15:21.600 --> 03:15:24.299
The front doors faced the entrance from

03:15:24.299 --> 03:15:24.840
the ramps.

03:15:24.899 --> 03:15:27.899
There was a small plaza here, outside the

03:15:27.899 --> 03:15:30.360
library walls, with a circle of benches

03:15:30.360 --> 03:15:32.340
arranged around a statue of clear sight.

03:15:32.459 --> 03:15:35.459
Cricket loved this statue too.

03:15:35.520 --> 03:15:39.180
Clearsight had her nose in a book, not

03:15:39.180 --> 03:15:42.420
the book, just a book, and she was

03:15:42.420 --> 03:15:42.840
reading.

03:15:42.899 --> 03:15:45.540
She didn't look like an avenging prophet

03:15:45.540 --> 03:15:47.399
announcing the doom of all the tribes.

03:15:47.459 --> 03:15:49.979
She looked as though she might glance up

03:15:49.979 --> 03:15:53.280
at any moment, see cricket and say, oh my

03:15:53.280 --> 03:15:54.899
gosh, have you read this one?

03:15:54.959 --> 03:15:55.860
It's amazing.

03:15:55.920 --> 03:15:59.700
The entire library level was vibrating

03:15:59.700 --> 03:16:01.379
from the shouts and music of a party

03:16:01.379 --> 03:16:02.100
above them.

03:16:02.159 --> 03:16:05.280
The flame silk globes overhead shook and

03:16:05.280 --> 03:16:08.040
swayed, and sent shadows wobbling across

03:16:08.040 --> 03:16:09.659
the front of the library.

03:16:09.719 --> 03:16:12.540
Tiny flecks of tree stuff drifted down

03:16:12.540 --> 03:16:14.280
making cricket sneeze.

03:16:14.340 --> 03:16:16.920
Where's the chrysalis?

03:16:16.979 --> 03:16:19.139
Sundew whispered to sword tail.

03:16:19.200 --> 03:16:22.139
He spread his wings in a how would I know

03:16:22.139 --> 03:16:23.940
gesture, and she rolled her eyes.

03:16:24.000 --> 03:16:27.479
You're not the most useful revolutionary

03:16:27.479 --> 03:16:28.739
she hissed.

03:16:28.799 --> 03:16:30.239
Has anyone ever told you that?

03:16:30.299 --> 03:16:33.899
I'm better with Luna around, he said

03:16:33.899 --> 03:16:34.559
wistfully.

03:16:34.620 --> 03:16:37.620
Sundu hopped up the library steps and

03:16:37.620 --> 03:16:40.379
tried the doors, but they were locked.

03:16:40.440 --> 03:16:43.680
So if we can't get in, she said.

03:16:43.739 --> 03:16:45.840
Turning with a swirl of her cape.

03:16:45.899 --> 03:16:48.059
The meeting must be out here in the plaza

03:16:48.059 --> 03:16:48.180
right?

03:16:48.239 --> 03:16:50.159
Cricket looked around.

03:16:50.219 --> 03:16:52.860
It felt as if they were completely alone

03:16:52.860 --> 03:16:53.639
on this level.

03:16:53.700 --> 03:16:56.399
They'd passed other dragons on the ramps

03:16:56.399 --> 03:16:58.920
up and down, but it was the glittering

03:16:58.920 --> 03:16:59.819
hours of the night.

03:16:59.879 --> 03:17:01.920
All of them were going past the library

03:17:01.920 --> 03:17:04.739
to the gatherings above, to glitter and

03:17:04.739 --> 03:17:07.020
sea and be seen glittering.

03:17:07.260 --> 03:17:09.899
Have you ever noticed that glitter is a

03:17:09.899 --> 03:17:11.700
word that quickly loses its meaning if

03:17:11.700 --> 03:17:12.420
you say it too much?

03:17:12.420 --> 03:17:13.799
she said to Blue.

03:17:13.860 --> 03:17:17.159
Glitter, glitter, glittering.

03:17:17.219 --> 03:17:19.139
Isn't it super weird now?

03:17:19.260 --> 03:17:22.260
You're super weird, he said

03:17:22.260 --> 03:17:23.040
affectionately.

03:17:23.100 --> 03:17:26.100
Why isn't this library as sparkly as the

03:17:26.100 --> 03:17:26.700
rest of the hive?

03:17:26.819 --> 03:17:30.059
She glanced up at the towering walls of

03:17:30.059 --> 03:17:30.659
tree stuff.

03:17:30.719 --> 03:17:31.860
It was true.

03:17:31.920 --> 03:17:34.979
Unlike most of the jewel hive, the

03:17:34.979 --> 03:17:37.139
library wasn't shimmering with embedded

03:17:37.139 --> 03:17:39.120
jewels and tiles and decorations.

03:17:39.239 --> 03:17:43.079
It did have expensive wooden doors, saved

03:17:43.079 --> 03:17:45.059
from some long ago building that must

03:17:45.059 --> 03:17:47.520
also have been a library, because they

03:17:47.520 --> 03:17:49.500
had books carved all over them.

03:17:49.559 --> 03:17:52.379
Cricket remembered sundew slashing her

03:17:52.379 --> 03:17:54.420
claws through the sculpted face of Queen

03:17:54.420 --> 03:17:57.180
Wasp on the doors of Wasp Hive.

03:17:57.239 --> 03:17:59.639
She wondered how long it had taken to

03:17:59.639 --> 03:18:02.639
carve the doors there. and here, and

03:18:02.639 --> 03:18:04.319
whether there was any way to repair the

03:18:04.319 --> 03:18:07.079
damage, and who still knew the skills of

03:18:07.079 --> 03:18:09.360
wood carving, and what kinds of tools

03:18:09.360 --> 03:18:09.899
were required.

03:18:09.959 --> 03:18:13.559
Blue climbed the steps, and touched the

03:18:13.559 --> 03:18:15.120
wooden door lightly with his talons.

03:18:15.180 --> 03:18:18.899
She saw a sad look cross his face as he

03:18:18.899 --> 03:18:20.340
glanced over at sundew.

03:18:20.399 --> 03:18:22.920
He's thinking about what she might be

03:18:22.920 --> 03:18:23.340
feeling.

03:18:23.399 --> 03:18:24.959
Cricket guessed.

03:18:25.020 --> 03:18:28.079
That thing he does, where he's always in

03:18:28.079 --> 03:18:28.920
someone else's head.

03:18:28.979 --> 03:18:31.920
She thought it was fascinating.

03:18:31.979 --> 03:18:33.899
She wished she could remember to do it

03:18:33.899 --> 03:18:34.379
like he did.

03:18:34.440 --> 03:18:36.600
I could try now.

03:18:36.659 --> 03:18:40.200
He's thinking, hmm.

03:18:40.319 --> 03:18:43.680
Maybe that thing wood used for doors must

03:18:43.680 --> 03:18:44.879
make sundo sad.

03:18:45.000 --> 03:18:47.459
Because she misses the trees?

03:18:47.579 --> 03:18:49.680
Any ideas?

03:18:49.739 --> 03:18:52.260
sundew barked, poking cricket's

03:18:52.260 --> 03:18:52.620
shoulder.

03:18:52.680 --> 03:18:54.780
You 3 look half asleep.

03:18:54.840 --> 03:18:57.120
Do I need to bring up Belladonna's other

03:18:57.120 --> 03:18:58.920
plan and our time limit?

03:18:58.979 --> 03:19:02.100
You do want to find the chrysalis?

03:19:02.159 --> 03:19:02.760
Don't you?

03:19:02.819 --> 03:19:05.399
Cricket shivered at the reminder.

03:19:05.520 --> 03:19:08.040
The chrysalis had to have answers for

03:19:08.040 --> 03:19:08.340
them.

03:19:08.399 --> 03:19:11.219
If they wanted to stop Belladonna and the

03:19:11.219 --> 03:19:12.120
other leaf wings.

03:19:12.299 --> 03:19:14.700
It doesn't seem like they're coming

03:19:14.700 --> 03:19:16.079
Swordtell said.

03:19:16.139 --> 03:19:18.479
He peered off along the walls in either

03:19:18.479 --> 03:19:18.840
direction.

03:19:18.899 --> 03:19:22.200
We are missing something, Cricket said.

03:19:22.260 --> 03:19:23.399
Five.

03:19:23.459 --> 03:19:25.799
That was the 3rd part of the message.

03:19:25.860 --> 03:19:27.180
Five.

03:19:27.420 --> 03:19:29.639
Doors of the library?

03:19:29.700 --> 03:19:33.180
But there are only these, from the ramps

03:19:33.180 --> 03:19:35.280
and another set at the back that open out

03:19:35.280 --> 03:19:36.000
to the Savannah.

03:19:36.059 --> 03:19:38.100
Those will be closed at night too.

03:19:38.159 --> 03:19:40.739
She scanned the plaza.

03:19:40.799 --> 03:19:42.780
There are only 4 benches.

03:19:42.840 --> 03:19:45.360
Nothing with a 5 on it, right?

03:19:45.420 --> 03:19:47.639
Blue squinted at the doors.

03:19:47.700 --> 03:19:50.159
I don't see any 5s up here.

03:19:50.219 --> 03:19:52.620
Maybe the statue.

03:19:52.680 --> 03:19:54.780
Like where the message was hidden in the

03:19:54.780 --> 03:19:55.500
glitter bazaar?

03:19:55.559 --> 03:19:58.379
Cricket walked around the statue of

03:19:58.379 --> 03:20:01.559
Clearsight, looking for tiny cracks where

03:20:01.559 --> 03:20:03.120
another leaf might be stuffed.

03:20:03.180 --> 03:20:06.420
Nothing in the base, nothing under clear

03:20:06.420 --> 03:20:07.799
sight talons.

03:20:07.860 --> 03:20:10.079
Her neck curved toward the book.

03:20:10.200 --> 03:20:12.899
The row of spines spiraling along her

03:20:12.899 --> 03:20:13.739
back down her tail.

03:20:13.860 --> 03:20:17.280
The spines were the only thing cricket

03:20:17.280 --> 03:20:19.440
could see where there were more than 5 of

03:20:19.440 --> 03:20:19.620
them.

03:20:19.680 --> 03:20:23.159
She hopped up onto the statue's base, and

03:20:23.159 --> 03:20:24.899
reached up to the top of Clearsight's

03:20:24.899 --> 03:20:25.079
head.

03:20:25.200 --> 03:20:31.799
One, two, three, four, five spines down

03:20:31.799 --> 03:20:32.280
her back.

03:20:32.340 --> 03:20:35.100
And there was something lodged under the

03:20:35.100 --> 03:20:35.700
5th one.

03:20:35.819 --> 03:20:37.620
A key.

03:20:37.739 --> 03:20:40.979
She tugged it out and studied it in the

03:20:40.979 --> 03:20:42.719
light of the flickering flame silk

03:20:42.719 --> 03:20:43.139
globes.

03:20:43.260 --> 03:20:45.059
What is it?

03:20:45.120 --> 03:20:48.479
sundew asked, resting her front talons on

03:20:48.479 --> 03:20:50.159
the base of the statue and lifting her

03:20:50.159 --> 03:20:50.579
neck to see.

03:20:50.639 --> 03:20:55.020
Our way into the library, I think, Cricket

03:20:55.020 --> 03:20:55.319
said.

03:20:55.379 --> 03:20:58.739
Sure enough, the key fit the lock on the

03:20:58.739 --> 03:20:58.979
doors.

03:20:59.100 --> 03:21:02.040
Sortell heaved one side open and they

03:21:02.040 --> 03:21:05.340
slipped inside, one by one, while Cricket

03:21:05.340 --> 03:21:07.620
returned the key to its hiding spot, and

03:21:07.620 --> 03:21:08.399
then followed them.

03:21:08.459 --> 03:21:11.760
Inside, there was a bolt to lock the

03:21:11.760 --> 03:21:12.959
doors again behind them.

03:21:13.020 --> 03:21:16.620
A kind of peace settled over cricket as

03:21:16.620 --> 03:21:17.819
she stepped into the library.

03:21:17.879 --> 03:21:21.000
She always felt this way when she was

03:21:21.000 --> 03:21:21.899
surrounded by books.

03:21:21.959 --> 03:21:25.200
She belonged here, even if she didn't fit

03:21:25.200 --> 03:21:25.799
anywhere else.

03:21:25.860 --> 03:21:29.040
In here, there were answers and

03:21:29.040 --> 03:21:31.739
information, and 1000s of stories waiting

03:21:31.739 --> 03:21:33.479
for her to fold herself into them.

03:21:33.540 --> 03:21:36.420
She was always safe inside a book.

03:21:36.479 --> 03:21:40.079
And this was her favorite of all the

03:21:40.079 --> 03:21:41.280
libraries she knew.

03:21:41.399 --> 03:21:44.340
Shelves radiated out from the central

03:21:44.340 --> 03:21:47.579
desk in every direction, like a sunburst

03:21:47.579 --> 03:21:49.979
and more aisles with more books filled

03:21:49.979 --> 03:21:51.180
the balconies overhead.

03:21:51.180 --> 03:21:54.000
Beloved characters were painted on the

03:21:54.000 --> 03:21:57.120
walls, golden glass, and copper wire

03:21:57.120 --> 03:21:59.700
dragons holding books, hung from the

03:21:59.700 --> 03:22:02.700
ceiling far overhead, and blue silk

03:22:02.700 --> 03:22:04.440
tapestries filled the rest of the open

03:22:04.440 --> 03:22:07.200
space, woven with quotes about reading.

03:22:07.260 --> 03:22:11.459
Hmm, sundew said quietly, glancing

03:22:11.459 --> 03:22:11.819
around.

03:22:11.879 --> 03:22:14.579
There's a lot of dead trees in here.

03:22:14.639 --> 03:22:17.520
Cricket was startled out of her peace.

03:22:17.579 --> 03:22:19.020
They're not.

03:22:19.680 --> 03:22:22.559
I mean, maybe, but they're books. books

03:22:22.559 --> 03:22:23.280
are everything.

03:22:23.340 --> 03:22:26.399
And they're not all made from trees

03:22:26.399 --> 03:22:26.639
right?

03:22:26.700 --> 03:22:28.079
Blue offered.

03:22:28.139 --> 03:22:29.280
Right.

03:22:29.340 --> 03:22:32.700
Cricket shook out her wings, taking a

03:22:32.700 --> 03:22:33.719
calming breath.

03:22:33.780 --> 03:22:36.479
We mostly make paper from silk now.

03:22:36.540 --> 03:22:39.659
Oh, good, Sundu answered.

03:22:39.719 --> 03:22:42.600
You used up our resources and moved on to

03:22:42.600 --> 03:22:43.680
exploiting a different tribe.

03:22:43.739 --> 03:22:48.420
But the books are for us too, Blue said

03:22:48.420 --> 03:22:49.379
for everyone.

03:22:49.440 --> 03:22:52.319
I'd give all my soak to help build a

03:22:52.319 --> 03:22:52.979
place like this.

03:22:53.040 --> 03:22:55.979
He ducked his head and looked at cricket

03:22:55.979 --> 03:22:58.079
and she wished she could throw her wings

03:22:58.079 --> 03:23:00.420
around him and tell him how wonderful he

03:23:00.420 --> 03:23:00.659
was.

03:23:00.719 --> 03:23:02.940
Sundew wasn't wrong.

03:23:03.000 --> 03:23:05.940
She kept opening Cricket's eyes in

03:23:05.940 --> 03:23:08.219
moments when Cricket hadn't realized they

03:23:08.219 --> 03:23:11.040
were closed, but blue was the reason she

03:23:11.040 --> 03:23:13.739
could keep them open and still feel all

03:23:13.739 --> 03:23:14.639
the things she felt.

03:23:14.700 --> 03:23:16.920
He saw cricket.

03:23:16.979 --> 03:23:19.020
He understood completely what this place

03:23:19.020 --> 03:23:19.799
meant to her.

03:23:19.860 --> 03:23:22.680
Shh, Sundu said.

03:23:22.739 --> 03:23:25.260
Flicking her tail in front of Swordtail's

03:23:25.260 --> 03:23:27.420
face, even though he hadn't said anything

03:23:27.420 --> 03:23:27.719
at all.

03:23:27.780 --> 03:23:30.659
She pointed up, and gave cricket a

03:23:30.659 --> 03:23:31.319
quizzical look.

03:23:31.379 --> 03:23:33.239
She could hear it too.

03:23:33.360 --> 03:23:36.780
Voices, arguing, somewhere upstairs.

03:23:36.840 --> 03:23:39.600
They could have flown up to the balcony

03:23:39.600 --> 03:23:42.059
that overlooked the 1st floor, but their

03:23:42.059 --> 03:23:43.620
wing beats might have scared away the

03:23:43.620 --> 03:23:44.219
other dragons.

03:23:44.280 --> 03:23:47.399
If they can hear anything over their own

03:23:47.399 --> 03:23:50.760
voices, that is, Cricket thought, as they

03:23:50.760 --> 03:23:52.079
crept up the stairs instead.

03:23:52.200 --> 03:23:55.319
This was certainly the loudest stealth

03:23:55.319 --> 03:23:57.360
meeting of a secret rebellion she'd ever

03:23:57.360 --> 03:23:58.139
heard.

03:23:58.200 --> 03:24:00.780
No, you're doing it wrong.

03:24:00.840 --> 03:24:02.520
One of them shouted.

03:24:02.579 --> 03:24:04.440
It's like you don't even care about what

03:24:04.440 --> 03:24:05.340
we're trying to do here.

03:24:05.459 --> 03:24:08.100
I'm focusing on what's actually

03:24:08.100 --> 03:24:08.579
important.

03:24:08.639 --> 03:24:10.500
Another one yelled back.

03:24:10.559 --> 03:24:13.020
Tearing apart other silk wings isn't

03:24:13.020 --> 03:24:13.799
going to get us anywhere.

03:24:13.920 --> 03:24:17.399
We have to fix the problems in our own

03:24:17.399 --> 03:24:19.559
tribe before we can stand together.

03:24:19.620 --> 03:24:21.959
The 1st voice insisted.

03:24:22.020 --> 03:24:25.319
I mean, if I think Argus is a lazy

03:24:25.319 --> 03:24:27.000
caterpillar who doesn't understand our

03:24:27.000 --> 03:24:29.760
mission, then it's useful for me to yell

03:24:29.760 --> 03:24:31.319
at him until he sorts himself out.

03:24:31.379 --> 03:24:33.659
I think it's cowardly.

03:24:33.719 --> 03:24:36.540
The 2nd voice snapped back.

03:24:36.600 --> 03:24:38.579
It's easy to yell at Argus because he's

03:24:38.579 --> 03:24:39.059
on our side.

03:24:39.120 --> 03:24:41.760
It's a lot easier than standing out to

03:24:41.760 --> 03:24:43.139
the dragons we're supposed to be

03:24:43.139 --> 03:24:43.739
fighting.

03:24:43.860 --> 03:24:47.459
I'm sure your intentions are good, Morpho

03:24:47.520 --> 03:24:50.520
pleaded a 3rd voice, as Cricket and her

03:24:50.520 --> 03:24:52.079
friends crept through the stacks.

03:24:52.139 --> 03:24:54.600
But what if you've scared him away, and

03:24:54.600 --> 03:24:55.739
he never comes back.

03:24:55.799 --> 03:24:57.659
Then good riddance.

03:24:57.780 --> 03:24:59.879
The 1st voice snapped.

03:25:00.000 --> 03:25:02.520
No, shouted the second.

03:25:02.579 --> 03:25:04.739
We need every dragon we can get on our

03:25:04.739 --> 03:25:05.040
side.

03:25:05.100 --> 03:25:08.159
I'd rather have 50 silk wings or at least

03:25:08.159 --> 03:25:11.219
trying to do the right thing than 3 who

03:25:11.219 --> 03:25:13.020
are perfect in every way by your

03:25:13.020 --> 03:25:13.680
standards.

03:25:13.739 --> 03:25:17.639
Sundew crouched and snuck a glance around

03:25:17.639 --> 03:25:18.780
the last corner.

03:25:18.840 --> 03:25:21.120
Through the bookshelves, Cricket could

03:25:21.120 --> 03:25:23.280
see bright blue wings flashing open and

03:25:23.280 --> 03:25:26.159
closed, and the pale yellow scales of

03:25:26.159 --> 03:25:27.360
another dragon close by.

03:25:27.420 --> 03:25:29.940
They were in the back corner of the

03:25:29.940 --> 03:25:32.459
library, farthest from the front doors.

03:25:32.579 --> 03:25:35.399
Near a wall of windows that looked out

03:25:35.399 --> 03:25:36.719
onto the dark savannah.

03:25:36.780 --> 03:25:39.420
Cricket remembered this reading nook with

03:25:39.420 --> 03:25:40.680
its hammocks and pillows.

03:25:40.739 --> 03:25:43.139
The flame silk lamps were covered for the

03:25:43.139 --> 03:25:45.899
night, but their light still glowed dimly

03:25:45.899 --> 03:25:48.600
through the dark silk shades, illuminating

03:25:48.600 --> 03:25:50.520
the books scattered on the windowsills

03:25:50.520 --> 03:25:51.479
and the floor.

03:25:51.540 --> 03:25:54.899
They should be more careful, Cricket

03:25:54.899 --> 03:25:55.739
thought nervously.

03:25:55.799 --> 03:25:58.680
Dragons flew between the levels all night

03:25:58.680 --> 03:26:01.319
in Jewel Hive, flitting from one party to

03:26:01.319 --> 03:26:01.620
another.

03:26:01.680 --> 03:26:04.920
Someone could easily fly past the library

03:26:04.920 --> 03:26:08.280
windows, glance inside, and wonder why a

03:26:08.280 --> 03:26:09.780
group of Silk Wings was in the library

03:26:09.780 --> 03:26:10.620
after dark.

03:26:10.739 --> 03:26:15.000
You go out there first, Sundew whispered

03:26:15.000 --> 03:26:17.520
to SwordTail, make sure they don't freak

03:26:17.520 --> 03:26:18.719
out when they see the rest of us.

03:26:18.840 --> 03:26:20.819
Me?

03:26:20.879 --> 03:26:21.899
Swordtail said.

03:26:22.020 --> 03:26:23.760
I mean, right.

03:26:23.819 --> 03:26:24.479
Me.

03:26:24.540 --> 03:26:27.120
Introductions, no freaking out.

03:26:27.239 --> 03:26:28.379
No problem.

03:26:28.440 --> 03:26:31.200
He squared his shoulders and took a deep

03:26:31.200 --> 03:26:31.739
breath.

03:26:31.799 --> 03:26:33.299
What should I say?

03:26:33.360 --> 03:26:37.620
Just figure it out, sundew hissed.

03:26:37.680 --> 03:26:41.760
You'll be great, Blue added reassuringly

03:26:41.760 --> 03:26:44.159
as sundew shoved sore tail toward the

03:26:44.159 --> 03:26:45.180
squabbling dragons.

03:26:45.299 --> 03:26:46.620
Right.

03:26:46.680 --> 03:26:48.239
Soratell said.

03:26:48.360 --> 03:26:51.120
He cleared his throat, and stepped

03:26:51.120 --> 03:26:53.280
between the hammocks into the dim circle

03:26:53.280 --> 03:26:53.639
of light.

03:26:53.700 --> 03:26:55.379
Excuse me?

03:26:55.440 --> 03:26:56.639
Hi.

03:26:56.700 --> 03:26:59.819
The silk wings whirled around and stared

03:26:59.819 --> 03:27:00.239
at him.

03:27:00.299 --> 03:27:03.420
I'm looking for the chrysalis, said

03:27:03.420 --> 03:27:04.200
Swordtail.

03:27:04.260 --> 03:27:07.200
One of the dragons snorted and spread his

03:27:07.200 --> 03:27:09.479
wings at the other 2 silk wings with

03:27:09.479 --> 03:27:09.780
him.

03:27:09.840 --> 03:27:12.959
Well, congratulations, he said.

03:27:13.020 --> 03:27:14.879
You've found us.

03:27:15.000 --> 03:27:19.319
Chapter 11.

03:27:19.680 --> 03:27:23.879
Oh, good, Swordtell said.

03:27:23.940 --> 03:27:24.659
Great.

03:27:24.719 --> 03:27:27.059
Hello, Chrysalis.

03:27:27.120 --> 03:27:29.879
What kind of secret organization?

03:27:29.940 --> 03:27:32.760
Just admits who they are to any idiot who

03:27:32.760 --> 03:27:33.360
walks in?

03:27:33.420 --> 03:27:34.979
Sundew muttered.

03:27:35.040 --> 03:27:37.680
She flicked her tail, swiping cricket

03:27:37.680 --> 03:27:38.879
with a billow of her cape.

03:27:38.940 --> 03:27:41.819
They have no idea who he is or who he's

03:27:41.819 --> 03:27:42.000
with.

03:27:42.059 --> 03:27:45.360
Cricket crouched to get a clearer view

03:27:45.360 --> 03:27:47.459
through the shelves, but she could still

03:27:47.459 --> 03:27:49.500
only see 3 dragons in the reading nook.

03:27:49.559 --> 03:27:50.940
Was that it?

03:27:51.000 --> 03:27:53.940
The whole Jewel Hive faction of the

03:27:53.940 --> 03:27:57.600
secret Silkwing rebellion was 3 arguing

03:27:57.600 --> 03:27:58.200
dragons.

03:27:58.319 --> 03:28:00.780
Why were you looking for us?

03:28:00.840 --> 03:28:03.299
demanded the dragon with bright blue

03:28:03.299 --> 03:28:03.899
wings?

03:28:03.959 --> 03:28:07.739
He was the owner of the 1st voice, Morpho

03:28:07.739 --> 03:28:08.819
if cricket remembered right.

03:28:08.940 --> 03:28:11.940
His torso was dappled with iridescent sea

03:28:11.940 --> 03:28:14.399
green scales, and little patches of white

03:28:14.399 --> 03:28:15.600
ran down his tail.

03:28:15.659 --> 03:28:18.299
But he had clearly been named for the

03:28:18.299 --> 03:28:20.579
color of his wings, which were nearly as

03:28:20.579 --> 03:28:21.659
vibrant as blues.

03:28:21.780 --> 03:28:25.559
Maybe he wants to join us, said the pale

03:28:25.559 --> 03:28:26.940
yellow dragon, hopefully.

03:28:27.000 --> 03:28:29.399
Do you dream of a better world, friend?

03:28:29.459 --> 03:28:32.459
Do you agree that all silk wings should

03:28:32.459 --> 03:28:34.559
refuse to serve any hive wings in the

03:28:34.559 --> 03:28:35.340
glitter bazaar?

03:28:35.399 --> 03:28:38.219
The blue dragon demanded, and that we

03:28:38.219 --> 03:28:40.620
should make lists of all the silk wings

03:28:40.620 --> 03:28:42.600
who do so we can go yell at them?

03:28:42.659 --> 03:28:47.280
Oh, honestly, morpho. said the 3rd dragon

03:28:47.280 --> 03:28:48.120
rolling her eyes.

03:28:48.180 --> 03:28:50.760
Soartail cleared his throat nervously.

03:28:50.819 --> 03:28:54.420
Um, my name is Swordtail.

03:28:54.479 --> 03:28:57.000
I am part of the cicada hive chrysalis.

03:28:57.059 --> 03:28:58.559
I mean, sort of.

03:28:58.620 --> 03:29:01.319
I was about to be, me and Luna.

03:29:01.379 --> 03:29:02.700
And now she's missing.

03:29:02.760 --> 03:29:04.979
Have you heard anything about a dragon

03:29:04.979 --> 03:29:06.420
named Luna recently?

03:29:06.479 --> 03:29:08.399
Has she come to you for help, maybe?

03:29:08.459 --> 03:29:11.040
The 3 dragons blanked at him in

03:29:11.040 --> 03:29:11.459
confusion.

03:29:11.520 --> 03:29:15.479
I don't know anyone named Luna, said the

03:29:15.479 --> 03:29:16.200
Yellow Dragon.

03:29:16.260 --> 03:29:20.579
I'm sorry, she added, as sore tails wings

03:29:20.579 --> 03:29:21.120
drooped.

03:29:21.180 --> 03:29:24.239
She's a flame silk, he said.

03:29:24.299 --> 03:29:26.940
We rescued her, but she might have been

03:29:26.940 --> 03:29:28.680
recaptured by Wasp Pive.

03:29:28.739 --> 03:29:30.239
Have you heard anything like that?

03:29:30.299 --> 03:29:33.479
A silk wing taken prisoner over Dragonfly

03:29:33.479 --> 03:29:34.799
Bay in the last 5 days.

03:29:34.860 --> 03:29:37.680
They all shook their heads, and

03:29:37.680 --> 03:29:39.899
swordtail's wings drooped even more.

03:29:39.959 --> 03:29:41.520
Are you sure?

03:29:41.520 --> 03:29:42.360
he asked.

03:29:42.420 --> 03:29:45.000
Maybe she's hiding with another wing of

03:29:45.000 --> 03:29:45.719
the chrysalis?

03:29:45.780 --> 03:29:49.260
Maybe, the yellow dragon said gently.

03:29:49.319 --> 03:29:51.420
We haven't heard anything.

03:29:51.479 --> 03:29:54.659
Cricket reached over and squeezed one of

03:29:54.659 --> 03:29:55.559
Blue's talons.

03:29:55.620 --> 03:29:57.780
He looked so worried and sad.

03:29:57.840 --> 03:30:00.719
She wished she had a tiny fraction of

03:30:00.719 --> 03:30:03.360
Clearsight's power, so she could have a

03:30:03.360 --> 03:30:05.940
vision of Luna, and let Blue know his

03:30:05.940 --> 03:30:06.840
sister was all right.

03:30:06.959 --> 03:30:09.299
Is that why you're here?

03:30:09.360 --> 03:30:10.979
asked Morpho.

03:30:11.040 --> 03:30:12.959
Just looking for another silkwing.

03:30:13.020 --> 03:30:14.639
Not just that.

03:30:14.700 --> 03:30:16.920
My friends and I were hoping you could

03:30:16.920 --> 03:30:17.459
help us.

03:30:17.579 --> 03:30:18.899
Sortell said.

03:30:18.959 --> 03:30:21.659
Morpho squinted at the shelves behind

03:30:21.659 --> 03:30:24.299
Swordtail, while the other 2 dragons

03:30:24.299 --> 03:30:26.159
exchanged a worried glance.

03:30:26.219 --> 03:30:27.899
Your friend.

03:30:27.959 --> 03:30:29.159
Who's with you?

03:30:29.280 --> 03:30:32.100
Sortell turned and beckoned.

03:30:32.159 --> 03:30:34.500
Sundew rolled her eyes at cricket.

03:30:34.559 --> 03:30:37.739
Very thorough introduction, sworn tail

03:30:37.739 --> 03:30:38.459
she whispered.

03:30:38.520 --> 03:30:40.200
This is going to go great.

03:30:40.260 --> 03:30:44.760
Blue stepped out first, sliding up beside

03:30:44.760 --> 03:30:45.479
SwordTail.

03:30:45.540 --> 03:30:47.940
Before he could speak, the yellow silk

03:30:47.940 --> 03:30:49.379
wing jumped forward with a gasp.

03:30:49.440 --> 03:30:52.860
You're the one from the wanted posters.

03:30:52.920 --> 03:30:55.739
Her pale yellow antennae unfurled all the

03:30:55.739 --> 03:30:58.200
way, and she stared at him as if he were

03:30:58.200 --> 03:31:01.319
a tree who'd just sprouted illegally in

03:31:01.319 --> 03:31:02.579
the middle of the library floor.

03:31:02.639 --> 03:31:07.200
Hey, I was on the posters too, Sortell

03:31:07.200 --> 03:31:07.860
pointed out.

03:31:07.920 --> 03:31:10.680
Are you really a flame silk?

03:31:10.739 --> 03:31:13.500
The 3rd dragon asked, reaching toward

03:31:13.500 --> 03:31:15.420
Blue's talons and then catching herself

03:31:15.420 --> 03:31:16.260
and pulling back.

03:31:16.319 --> 03:31:20.819
Yes, he said, turning his wrists upward

03:31:20.819 --> 03:31:22.860
so she could see the embers glowing under

03:31:22.860 --> 03:31:23.700
his scales.

03:31:23.760 --> 03:31:26.879
Oh, wow, she said.

03:31:27.000 --> 03:31:29.340
That was the rumor, but no one will

03:31:29.340 --> 03:31:30.239
officially confirm it.

03:31:30.299 --> 03:31:31.500
How did you escape?

03:31:31.559 --> 03:31:35.219
And wasn't there a hive wing on that

03:31:35.219 --> 03:31:35.760
poster with you?

03:31:35.819 --> 03:31:38.159
Morpho asked suspiciously.

03:31:38.280 --> 03:31:40.799
That's how.

03:31:40.920 --> 03:31:43.739
Blue said to the dark orange dragon who

03:31:43.739 --> 03:31:44.639
was studying his wrists.

03:31:44.760 --> 03:31:47.340
And that's why she's wanted by the queen

03:31:47.340 --> 03:31:47.700
too.

03:31:47.760 --> 03:31:49.260
She helped me escape.

03:31:49.319 --> 03:31:52.440
He turned and held out one talent toward

03:31:52.440 --> 03:31:52.920
cricket.

03:31:52.979 --> 03:31:54.360
Cricket?

03:31:54.420 --> 03:31:57.540
Cricket took a deep breath and stepped

03:31:57.540 --> 03:31:58.559
out to stand beside him.

03:31:58.680 --> 03:32:02.040
Morpho leaped back and hissed an alarm.

03:32:02.100 --> 03:32:04.799
The other 2 seized blankets off the floor

03:32:04.799 --> 03:32:06.719
and threw them over their heads with high

03:32:06.719 --> 03:32:08.040
pitched yelps of terror.

03:32:08.100 --> 03:32:10.260
It's too late.

03:32:10.319 --> 03:32:11.940
Morvo snapped at them.

03:32:12.000 --> 03:32:13.799
She's already seen your faces.

03:32:13.860 --> 03:32:15.840
I told you this was a stupid meeting

03:32:15.840 --> 03:32:16.319
place.

03:32:16.379 --> 03:32:20.219
No, you didn't, cried the small, dark

03:32:20.219 --> 03:32:22.079
orange dragon from under her blanket.

03:32:22.139 --> 03:32:23.639
You suggested it.

03:32:23.760 --> 03:32:27.600
Cinnabar's right, agreed the muffled

03:32:27.600 --> 03:32:28.860
voice of the yellow dragon.

03:32:28.920 --> 03:32:31.440
It's not important who's right.

03:32:31.500 --> 03:32:34.260
Morphos shouted, although it was me.

03:32:34.319 --> 03:32:37.379
But what's important is that there's a

03:32:37.379 --> 03:32:38.340
hive wing right here.

03:32:38.399 --> 03:32:40.260
And what are we going to do about it?

03:32:40.440 --> 03:32:42.899
And also, it was your fault we couldn't

03:32:42.899 --> 03:32:44.340
meet at my better suggestions.

03:32:44.399 --> 03:32:45.059
So there.

03:32:45.180 --> 03:32:48.479
The yellow dragon winced, and Cricket

03:32:48.479 --> 03:32:50.340
noticed that one of her back wings

03:32:50.340 --> 03:32:52.739
sticking out from under the blanket at an

03:32:52.739 --> 03:32:54.840
awkward angle, was smaller than all the

03:32:54.840 --> 03:32:55.319
others.

03:32:55.319 --> 03:32:57.600
She wondered if the silk wing could fly

03:32:57.600 --> 03:32:57.959
at all.

03:32:58.020 --> 03:33:02.579
Wait, wait, Cricket said, as the yellow

03:33:02.579 --> 03:33:04.500
dragon started edging toward the nearest

03:33:04.500 --> 03:33:06.719
aisle, with a blanket still over her

03:33:06.719 --> 03:33:07.260
head.

03:33:07.319 --> 03:33:08.940
You don't have to hide.

03:33:09.000 --> 03:33:11.100
I'm a friend, I promise.

03:33:11.159 --> 03:33:13.440
Friends, don't let their brains get

03:33:13.440 --> 03:33:16.020
invaded and betray the revolution, said

03:33:16.020 --> 03:33:18.299
Cinnabar, pulling her wings and tail

03:33:18.299 --> 03:33:20.579
under her blanket and huddling into a

03:33:20.579 --> 03:33:22.860
small boulder, as if she hoped everyone

03:33:22.860 --> 03:33:24.000
would forget she'd been there.

03:33:24.059 --> 03:33:27.180
That won't happen, Cricket said.

03:33:27.239 --> 03:33:29.340
The mind control doesn't work on me.

03:33:29.459 --> 03:33:32.700
The Silkwings fell silent for a moment

03:33:32.700 --> 03:33:35.579
even Morpho, with his mouth half open.

03:33:35.639 --> 03:33:38.040
Then the yellow dragon threw her blanket

03:33:38.040 --> 03:33:39.600
off and stared at cricket.

03:33:39.659 --> 03:33:40.799
Her wings.

03:33:40.860 --> 03:33:44.879
Well, 3 of them were long and narrow, and

03:33:44.879 --> 03:33:47.040
her scales were a mix of pale yellow and

03:33:47.040 --> 03:33:50.219
pale brown, like bananas and cashews

03:33:50.219 --> 03:33:51.059
mashed together.

03:33:51.120 --> 03:33:54.780
She had dark amber eyes, and gold stripes

03:33:54.780 --> 03:33:55.739
painted on her claws.

03:33:55.860 --> 03:33:58.139
What are you talking about?

03:33:58.200 --> 03:33:59.219
she asked.

03:33:59.280 --> 03:34:03.180
Nope, not possible, Morpho declared.

03:34:03.239 --> 03:34:05.100
Hive wing lie.

03:34:05.159 --> 03:34:09.899
But it is possible, because there's me

03:34:09.899 --> 03:34:11.040
Cricket said.

03:34:11.159 --> 03:34:12.780
I know.

03:34:12.840 --> 03:34:14.579
It's weird, and I can't explain it.

03:34:14.639 --> 03:34:17.280
The queen can't get into my head, I

03:34:17.280 --> 03:34:17.819
promise you.

03:34:17.879 --> 03:34:19.319
I wish I knew why.

03:34:19.379 --> 03:34:22.200
I've been trying to figure it out my

03:34:22.200 --> 03:34:22.680
whole life.

03:34:22.739 --> 03:34:27.000
And the closest I've gotten is the theory

03:34:27.000 --> 03:34:28.379
that I'm half Silkwing.

03:34:28.440 --> 03:34:31.739
But nothing about me is very silkwing.

03:34:31.799 --> 03:34:34.620
I mean, I think I look like a hive wing

03:34:34.620 --> 03:34:36.059
from horns to claw tips.

03:34:36.120 --> 03:34:38.940
I don't have a natural weapon, but

03:34:38.940 --> 03:34:40.559
neither do a lot of hive wings.

03:34:40.620 --> 03:34:43.260
I know I'm different somehow.

03:34:43.319 --> 03:34:46.260
But I still feel like a hive wing.

03:34:46.319 --> 03:34:49.739
She decided not to mention the silk wing

03:34:49.739 --> 03:34:50.940
theory yet.

03:34:50.940 --> 03:34:52.079
She needed more evidence first.

03:34:52.139 --> 03:34:56.280
This seems like a trick, Morpho

03:34:56.280 --> 03:34:56.700
muttered.

03:34:56.760 --> 03:34:59.340
He stalked toward her and peered into her

03:34:59.340 --> 03:34:59.579
eyes.

03:34:59.639 --> 03:35:02.700
His were the same emerald green as his

03:35:02.700 --> 03:35:05.579
antennae, which curled and waved, as

03:35:05.579 --> 03:35:07.020
though he was trying to sense the

03:35:07.020 --> 03:35:08.760
presence of Queen Wasp inside her.

03:35:08.819 --> 03:35:12.059
It could be true, said the yellow

03:35:12.059 --> 03:35:12.719
dragon.

03:35:12.719 --> 03:35:14.520
She could be like the ones we heard

03:35:14.520 --> 03:35:14.819
about.

03:35:14.879 --> 03:35:17.700
Cricket felt her heart speed up.

03:35:17.760 --> 03:35:19.620
Other dragons like me?

03:35:19.680 --> 03:35:20.760
Who?

03:35:20.819 --> 03:35:22.799
We don't know for sure.

03:35:22.860 --> 03:35:25.559
Cinnabar, come out and tell her about the

03:35:25.559 --> 03:35:26.100
story you heard.

03:35:26.159 --> 03:35:30.780
The blanket boulder side enormously, and

03:35:30.780 --> 03:35:32.940
then the small orange silk wing poked her

03:35:32.940 --> 03:35:33.299
head out.

03:35:33.360 --> 03:35:36.239
If you're going to keep using my name in

03:35:36.239 --> 03:35:38.579
front of total strangers, you could at

03:35:38.579 --> 03:35:40.319
least introduce yourself too, Tao.

03:35:40.440 --> 03:35:43.860
Oh, sorry, said the yellow dragon

03:35:43.860 --> 03:35:44.520
gently.

03:35:44.579 --> 03:35:45.719
I'm Tao.

03:35:45.780 --> 03:35:48.059
That's Cinnabar, and that's Morpho.

03:35:48.120 --> 03:35:51.360
And I never said I believed that story.

03:35:51.420 --> 03:35:53.639
Cinnabara pointed out.

03:35:53.700 --> 03:35:56.520
Her scales were a burnt orange, with

03:35:56.520 --> 03:35:58.620
glints of dark red under her wings and

03:35:58.620 --> 03:36:01.440
along her spine, with a few black scales

03:36:01.440 --> 03:36:04.020
slightly different wings, and a much

03:36:04.020 --> 03:36:06.360
scarier expression, she could almost have

03:36:06.360 --> 03:36:07.620
passed for a hive wing.

03:36:07.799 --> 03:36:09.180
What story?

03:36:09.239 --> 03:36:10.260
Cricket asked.

03:36:10.319 --> 03:36:13.020
Cinnabar flicked the blanket off with her

03:36:13.020 --> 03:36:15.719
wings and edged closer to Tao.

03:36:15.780 --> 03:36:17.579
It's just a rumor.

03:36:17.639 --> 03:36:20.159
I heard it from a silkwing, who heard it

03:36:20.159 --> 03:36:22.020
from his cousin, who heard it from a

03:36:22.020 --> 03:36:23.340
traveling theater performer.

03:36:23.399 --> 03:36:27.000
The whisper is that there is a home for

03:36:27.000 --> 03:36:30.000
old dragons in Setsy Hive where none of

03:36:30.000 --> 03:36:32.100
them are allowed to leave ever, because

03:36:32.100 --> 03:36:33.959
the queen can't mind control them.

03:36:34.020 --> 03:36:38.459
Fairy tale nonsense, Morpho Spat.

03:36:38.520 --> 03:36:39.600
She controls everyone.

03:36:39.659 --> 03:36:44.579
Now, Morpho, you know that's not true, Tao

03:36:44.579 --> 03:36:46.920
said, she doesn't hive mind her sisters

03:36:46.920 --> 03:36:48.420
or Lady Jewel.

03:36:48.479 --> 03:36:50.639
She doesn't?

03:36:50.700 --> 03:36:52.559
Cricket tilted her head.

03:36:52.620 --> 03:36:54.059
She had never heard that before.

03:36:54.120 --> 03:36:59.040
But she could, if she wanted to, Morpho

03:36:59.040 --> 03:36:59.520
insisted.

03:36:59.579 --> 03:37:02.520
She just doesn't, because she likes to

03:37:02.520 --> 03:37:04.139
give them the illusion of control.

03:37:04.139 --> 03:37:06.780
As long as they think they have their own

03:37:06.780 --> 03:37:10.379
hives to run, they'll bow and scrape and

03:37:10.379 --> 03:37:12.180
let her be the one who's really in charge

03:37:12.180 --> 03:37:13.020
of everything.

03:37:13.079 --> 03:37:16.559
You've said that before, Tao said.

03:37:16.620 --> 03:37:19.200
A tiny sliver of impatience slipping

03:37:19.200 --> 03:37:20.700
through her peaceful mask.

03:37:20.760 --> 03:37:22.979
But I am sure it doesn't work on Lady

03:37:22.979 --> 03:37:23.459
Jewel.

03:37:23.520 --> 03:37:26.219
I've been with her when the whole hive is

03:37:26.219 --> 03:37:28.500
taken over, like when the entire tribe

03:37:28.500 --> 03:37:29.579
was sent to find these two.

03:37:29.700 --> 03:37:32.340
She gestured at blue and cricket.

03:37:32.399 --> 03:37:36.180
Three, Sword Tow protested, finally

03:37:36.180 --> 03:37:37.379
looking up from his talons.

03:37:37.440 --> 03:37:38.940
They're hunting for me too.

03:37:39.000 --> 03:37:42.899
She finds it very irritating.

03:37:42.959 --> 03:37:44.399
Tao went on.

03:37:44.459 --> 03:37:48.059
Her whole day is disrupted, and all jewel

03:37:48.059 --> 03:37:50.579
hive business has to be put on hold, and

03:37:50.579 --> 03:37:52.860
she has to sit for hours waiting for her

03:37:52.860 --> 03:37:53.700
subjects to come back.

03:37:53.760 --> 03:37:56.879
She can't even hide how annoyed she is

03:37:56.879 --> 03:37:58.739
from the silk wings who work for her.

03:37:58.799 --> 03:38:03.239
That's true, Cinnabar agreed, even in the

03:38:03.239 --> 03:38:03.959
kitchen we can tell.

03:38:04.020 --> 03:38:06.780
It's nonstop sugar orders all day.

03:38:06.840 --> 03:38:09.180
That doesn't prove anything.

03:38:09.239 --> 03:38:13.260
Morpho argued, WASP probably enjoys

03:38:13.260 --> 03:38:15.059
knowing how annoyed Jewel is.

03:38:15.120 --> 03:38:17.819
I don't believe there's a single hive

03:38:17.819 --> 03:38:19.680
wing she can't control if she wants to.

03:38:19.739 --> 03:38:21.299
Listen.

03:38:21.420 --> 03:38:23.280
Cricket said reasonably.

03:38:23.340 --> 03:38:26.940
If Queen Wasp could control me, would I

03:38:26.940 --> 03:38:28.079
be on a wanted poster?

03:38:28.139 --> 03:38:30.659
Wouldn't she just march me into her hive

03:38:30.659 --> 03:38:33.899
from inside my brain and use me to catch

03:38:33.899 --> 03:38:34.440
these two?

03:38:34.559 --> 03:38:38.159
Morpho opened and closed his mouth a few

03:38:38.159 --> 03:38:38.399
times.

03:38:38.459 --> 03:38:40.680
Oh, wow.

03:38:40.739 --> 03:38:44.100
Cinnabar said, you actually shut Morpho

03:38:44.100 --> 03:38:44.879
up for a moment.

03:38:44.940 --> 03:38:47.639
You can definitely be in my chrysalis.

03:38:47.760 --> 03:38:51.479
This is a trap, Morpho exploded.

03:38:51.540 --> 03:38:54.420
Hive Wings can't be trusted. of them.

03:38:54.479 --> 03:38:57.840
You're just mad because this proves what

03:38:57.840 --> 03:39:00.360
Tao and I have been saying, Cinnabar

03:39:00.360 --> 03:39:01.079
snapped back.

03:39:01.139 --> 03:39:04.979
We could get high wings on our side, if

03:39:04.979 --> 03:39:06.000
they were allowed to think for

03:39:06.000 --> 03:39:06.420
themselves.

03:39:06.479 --> 03:39:10.860
I don't know about that, Swordtell said.

03:39:10.920 --> 03:39:12.659
Cricket might be the only one.

03:39:12.719 --> 03:39:16.379
Cricket's scarves felt too tight around

03:39:16.379 --> 03:39:16.799
her neck.

03:39:16.860 --> 03:39:18.420
He had to be wrong.

03:39:18.540 --> 03:39:20.760
The other high wings couldn't be lost

03:39:20.760 --> 03:39:21.239
forever.

03:39:21.299 --> 03:39:23.760
She just had to find a way to set them

03:39:23.760 --> 03:39:23.940
free.

03:39:24.000 --> 03:39:26.100
I think you're right.

03:39:26.159 --> 03:39:28.139
She said to Cinnabar.

03:39:28.200 --> 03:39:29.879
I mean, I hope so.

03:39:29.940 --> 03:39:32.639
Do you know anything else about Queen

03:39:32.639 --> 03:39:34.139
Wasp's mind control?

03:39:34.200 --> 03:39:37.319
Like how it works or whether anyone's

03:39:37.319 --> 03:39:39.239
ever managed to break free from it?

03:39:39.299 --> 03:39:43.020
Tao blinked and shook her head sadly.

03:39:43.079 --> 03:39:46.319
Oh, I see, she said.

03:39:46.379 --> 03:39:48.360
You're trying to free someone too.

03:39:48.420 --> 03:39:49.680
I'm sorry.

03:39:49.739 --> 03:39:52.440
I've never heard of anyone escaping the

03:39:52.440 --> 03:39:53.100
mind control.

03:39:53.159 --> 03:39:57.780
And even if they did, Morpho growled.

03:39:57.840 --> 03:40:01.200
All the hive wings have had Queen Wasp in

03:40:01.200 --> 03:40:02.459
their heads for so long.

03:40:02.520 --> 03:40:04.620
They can't think for themselves anyway.

03:40:04.680 --> 03:40:08.040
They'll keep believing her lies, no

03:40:08.040 --> 03:40:09.780
matter how free you think they are.

03:40:09.840 --> 03:40:12.120
Cricket shivered.

03:40:12.239 --> 03:40:14.940
Remembering her conversation with Katy

03:40:14.940 --> 03:40:15.239
did.

03:40:15.420 --> 03:40:17.700
I will get through to her.

03:40:17.760 --> 03:40:20.940
If I keep telling her the truth, She'll

03:40:20.940 --> 03:40:21.479
have to hear me.

03:40:21.540 --> 03:40:23.459
She'll have to believe me.

03:40:23.520 --> 03:40:27.719
Something flashed outside the window, like

03:40:27.719 --> 03:40:30.180
silver catching the moonlight, but when

03:40:30.180 --> 03:40:32.760
cricket turned to look, it was gone.

03:40:32.819 --> 03:40:35.280
The night beyond the glass was empty.

03:40:35.340 --> 03:40:38.159
Only Savannah grasses waved in the

03:40:38.159 --> 03:40:39.000
midnight breeze.

03:40:39.059 --> 03:40:42.540
I am not interested in wasting time on

03:40:42.540 --> 03:40:43.379
hive wings.

03:40:43.440 --> 03:40:45.239
Morpho said firmly.

03:40:45.299 --> 03:40:48.059
I want to save silk wings.

03:40:48.120 --> 03:40:50.159
There are enough of us to win if we join

03:40:50.159 --> 03:40:51.659
together and rise up.

03:40:51.959 --> 03:40:53.879
Tao was shaking her head.

03:40:53.940 --> 03:40:56.819
There aren't, she said.

03:40:56.879 --> 03:40:58.440
It's too dangerous.

03:40:58.500 --> 03:41:00.780
Too many silk wings would die.

03:41:00.840 --> 03:41:04.020
I'm sorry, Morpho, but we have no weapons

03:41:04.020 --> 03:41:06.959
and they have the queen's hive mind.

03:41:07.319 --> 03:41:10.440
Also, Stingers, said Swordtell

03:41:10.440 --> 03:41:10.979
helpfully.

03:41:11.040 --> 03:41:15.059
And venom, and toxic paralysis stabber

03:41:15.059 --> 03:41:15.420
bits.

03:41:15.479 --> 03:41:17.819
Sounds like you need an army.

03:41:17.879 --> 03:41:21.840
Sundew said, timing her dramatic entrance

03:41:21.840 --> 03:41:22.739
perfectly.

03:41:22.799 --> 03:41:25.440
She emerged from behind the bookshelves

03:41:25.440 --> 03:41:26.879
and threw off her cape.

03:41:26.940 --> 03:41:30.420
Her leaf shaped wings gleamed gold and

03:41:30.420 --> 03:41:31.319
green in the lamplight.

03:41:31.440 --> 03:41:34.920
The chrysalis silk wings all gasped.

03:41:34.979 --> 03:41:37.680
Tao sat back, and pressed her front

03:41:37.680 --> 03:41:38.700
talons to her heart.

03:41:38.760 --> 03:41:42.000
Cinnabar crouched as though she didn't

03:41:42.000 --> 03:41:44.700
know whether to fly or fight or scream.

03:41:44.760 --> 03:41:47.940
Morpho's eyeballs looked like they were

03:41:47.940 --> 03:41:49.260
full of sunbeams.

03:41:49.559 --> 03:41:53.639
Luckily for you, said Sundew, we've got

03:41:53.639 --> 03:41:53.940
one.

03:41:54.000 --> 03:41:57.360
Wait, but you're not going to use it.

03:41:57.479 --> 03:41:58.739
Blue interjected.

03:41:58.799 --> 03:42:00.299
Right, sundo?

03:42:00.360 --> 03:42:02.639
That's why we're here, because we're

03:42:02.639 --> 03:42:03.600
looking for a better solution.

03:42:03.719 --> 03:42:06.299
We're going to find an answer for your

03:42:06.299 --> 03:42:08.760
parents so they don't restart the tree

03:42:08.760 --> 03:42:09.180
wars.

03:42:09.239 --> 03:42:11.340
You heard these dragons.

03:42:11.399 --> 03:42:15.059
There isn't one, she said, tossing her

03:42:15.059 --> 03:42:15.299
head.

03:42:15.360 --> 03:42:18.000
There's no way to break the hive mind.

03:42:18.059 --> 03:42:19.860
So, backup plan.

03:42:19.920 --> 03:42:22.020
I'm here to make contact with the

03:42:22.020 --> 03:42:22.739
chrysalis.

03:42:22.799 --> 03:42:24.899
If the silk wings are ready to join the

03:42:24.899 --> 03:42:27.600
leaf wings this time, maybe the new tree

03:42:27.600 --> 03:42:29.639
wars will turn out the right way.

03:42:29.700 --> 03:42:34.620
But Sundew, Cricket started, horrified.

03:42:34.739 --> 03:42:38.040
The leaf wing brushed pastor and held out

03:42:38.040 --> 03:42:39.479
one talent cinnabar.

03:42:39.540 --> 03:42:40.920
What do you say?

03:42:40.979 --> 03:42:43.739
Care to destroy the hive wings together?

03:42:43.799 --> 03:42:48.000
Chapter 12.

03:42:48.360 --> 03:42:52.200
Sundo, Blue cried.

03:42:52.260 --> 03:42:55.079
Cricket felt as though the floor was

03:42:55.079 --> 03:42:57.420
turning to glue, trapping her claws in

03:42:57.420 --> 03:42:58.620
place.

03:42:58.680 --> 03:43:00.120
Sundew couldn't give up so quickly.

03:43:00.180 --> 03:43:02.940
There had to be something, some answer

03:43:02.940 --> 03:43:04.379
they just hadn't found yet.

03:43:04.440 --> 03:43:08.760
Some way to save my tribe, to save all

03:43:08.760 --> 03:43:10.860
our tribes, from a new war.

03:43:10.920 --> 03:43:16.020
Yes, Morpho shouted, elbowing cinnabar

03:43:16.020 --> 03:43:16.559
out of the way.

03:43:16.620 --> 03:43:20.100
He took sundew's talon between his and

03:43:20.100 --> 03:43:21.659
pumped it up and down.

03:43:21.719 --> 03:43:22.379
We're in.

03:43:22.440 --> 03:43:25.739
You don't speak for the whole chrysalis

03:43:25.739 --> 03:43:26.879
Tao said to him.

03:43:26.940 --> 03:43:30.000
Cricket realized there were tears in her

03:43:30.000 --> 03:43:31.920
eyes as she stepped toward sundew.

03:43:32.040 --> 03:43:35.459
You're alive, she whispered.

03:43:35.520 --> 03:43:37.379
I thought you were all dead.

03:43:37.440 --> 03:43:39.840
I thought we'd lost your whole tribe

03:43:39.840 --> 03:43:40.379
forever.

03:43:40.440 --> 03:43:42.899
Sundew looked taken aback.

03:43:42.959 --> 03:43:46.620
We had no idea any of you cowards cared

03:43:46.620 --> 03:43:49.139
she said, a little awkwardly.

03:43:49.200 --> 03:43:52.079
And no, we are not all dead.

03:43:52.139 --> 03:43:54.959
I cared, Cricket thought.

03:43:55.020 --> 03:43:58.739
I was so thrilled to find real, actual

03:43:58.739 --> 03:44:02.100
alive, leaf wings, hiding in Queen Wasp's

03:44:02.100 --> 03:44:02.639
greenhouse.

03:44:02.700 --> 03:44:04.680
Didn't she see that I cared?

03:44:04.739 --> 03:44:06.659
Sundu?

03:44:06.719 --> 03:44:08.700
What about freeing the hive wings?

03:44:08.700 --> 03:44:09.360
she said.

03:44:09.420 --> 03:44:11.879
We wanted to give them a chance to make

03:44:11.879 --> 03:44:12.959
the right choice, remember?

03:44:13.020 --> 03:44:15.600
We agreed that breaking the mind control

03:44:15.600 --> 03:44:16.319
would help everyone.

03:44:16.440 --> 03:44:19.260
Sundu shrugged.

03:44:19.319 --> 03:44:21.420
Cascades of reflected gold glittering

03:44:21.420 --> 03:44:22.139
along her wings.

03:44:22.200 --> 03:44:25.860
Like I suspected all along, it can't be

03:44:25.860 --> 03:44:26.100
done.

03:44:26.159 --> 03:44:29.040
The only option is to crush the hive

03:44:29.040 --> 03:44:29.879
wings completely.

03:44:29.940 --> 03:44:31.920
Yes!

03:44:31.979 --> 03:44:33.719
Morvo shouted again.

03:44:33.780 --> 03:44:36.719
Fine by me, said Swortail.

03:44:36.780 --> 03:44:37.860
I'm with sundew.

03:44:37.979 --> 03:44:41.159
Blue took a step closer to cricket so he

03:44:41.159 --> 03:44:42.540
could brush her wings with his.

03:44:42.600 --> 03:44:45.659
This isn't right, he said.

03:44:45.719 --> 03:44:47.639
There are good hive wings.

03:44:47.760 --> 03:44:48.420
I'm sure of it.

03:44:48.479 --> 03:44:51.000
I don't think we can solve a tragedy of

03:44:51.000 --> 03:44:52.799
the past by just repeating it in

03:44:52.799 --> 03:44:53.520
reverse.

03:44:53.579 --> 03:44:56.399
Well, I don't think we can solve a

03:44:56.399 --> 03:44:58.979
current tragedy. by sitting around trying

03:44:58.979 --> 03:45:01.500
to understand the bad guys.

03:45:01.559 --> 03:45:02.520
Sundew snapped.

03:45:02.639 --> 03:45:05.219
I don't want to hug a bunch of hive wings

03:45:05.219 --> 03:45:06.360
and listen to their problems.

03:45:06.420 --> 03:45:08.459
I want them all punished.

03:45:08.520 --> 03:45:11.579
Cricket buried her face and her talons.

03:45:11.639 --> 03:45:14.760
I would feel the same way in her place

03:45:14.760 --> 03:45:15.299
wouldn't I?

03:45:15.360 --> 03:45:17.940
But these were still her dragons.

03:45:18.059 --> 03:45:20.940
She couldn't give up on her entire tribe

03:45:20.940 --> 03:45:24.180
on Katy Did, and Lady Scarab, and the

03:45:24.180 --> 03:45:26.760
librarian, and the little dragonettes on

03:45:26.760 --> 03:45:29.700
her street, and her father, even if he

03:45:29.700 --> 03:45:32.219
wasn't her real father, and the students

03:45:32.219 --> 03:45:34.799
who'd shared books, and seeds with her at

03:45:34.799 --> 03:45:37.319
school, she had to believe they were

03:45:37.319 --> 03:45:39.360
better than what Queen Wasp had turned

03:45:39.360 --> 03:45:41.760
them into, and that they could still be

03:45:41.760 --> 03:45:42.059
saved.

03:45:42.180 --> 03:45:44.639
Where do we start?

03:45:44.700 --> 03:45:46.079
Morpho asked.

03:45:46.139 --> 03:45:47.159
What do we have to do?

03:45:47.219 --> 03:45:49.680
Cinnabar glanced at Tao.

03:45:49.799 --> 03:45:51.120
Wait.

03:45:51.180 --> 03:45:53.879
Not all of us want to kill all the hive

03:45:53.879 --> 03:45:55.260
wings, she said.

03:45:55.319 --> 03:45:58.139
Or any hive wings.

03:45:58.200 --> 03:45:59.520
Blue interjected.

03:45:59.639 --> 03:46:01.979
How many silk wings are in the

03:46:01.979 --> 03:46:02.760
chrysalis?

03:46:02.819 --> 03:46:04.799
Sundu asked, ignoring them.

03:46:04.860 --> 03:46:07.260
Tell me there are more than 3 of you.

03:46:07.319 --> 03:46:10.620
Oh yes, said Morpho.

03:46:10.680 --> 03:46:12.780
In this hive, there are 7 of us.

03:46:12.840 --> 03:46:15.959
Sundew did not look impressed.

03:46:16.079 --> 03:46:18.000
Seven.

03:46:18.059 --> 03:46:20.219
Yes, he said.

03:46:20.280 --> 03:46:22.739
Well, maybe six.

03:46:22.799 --> 03:46:27.360
If you scared Argus away forever, Cinnabar

03:46:27.360 --> 03:46:27.659
added.

03:46:27.719 --> 03:46:30.000
Why aren't the others here?

03:46:30.059 --> 03:46:33.000
Sundu flict your gays over the 3 of them

03:46:33.000 --> 03:46:34.200
and frowned slightly.

03:46:34.260 --> 03:46:36.840
They couldn't make it tonight?

03:46:37.079 --> 03:46:37.979
Tao said.

03:46:38.100 --> 03:46:40.079
One had to make costumes for her

03:46:40.079 --> 03:46:41.459
Dragonette's school play.

03:46:41.520 --> 03:46:43.860
Another has an early morning meeting.

03:46:43.920 --> 03:46:45.959
And what did Tamara say?

03:46:46.079 --> 03:46:47.760
She asked Cenabar.

03:46:47.819 --> 03:46:52.079
That she was too tired, Morpho answered

03:46:52.079 --> 03:46:52.979
disapprovingly.

03:46:53.040 --> 03:46:56.399
Really, Sundoo said.

03:46:56.459 --> 03:46:59.040
Very dedicated to this rebellion, are

03:46:59.040 --> 03:46:59.280
they?

03:46:59.340 --> 03:47:03.360
To be fair, Cinnabar said, we haven't

03:47:03.360 --> 03:47:05.100
exactly done much at the last few

03:47:05.100 --> 03:47:06.840
meetings or ever.

03:47:06.899 --> 03:47:08.639
Actually, ever.

03:47:08.700 --> 03:47:11.219
I mean, how can 7 dragons change

03:47:11.219 --> 03:47:11.700
anything?

03:47:11.760 --> 03:47:14.159
We know there are more silk wings and

03:47:14.159 --> 03:47:16.079
other hives who want to fight back too

03:47:16.079 --> 03:47:19.739
but it's just, everyone's busy with their

03:47:19.739 --> 03:47:22.979
lives, and no one knows what to do, and I

03:47:22.979 --> 03:47:23.579
don't know.

03:47:23.639 --> 03:47:24.840
It's overwhelming.

03:47:24.899 --> 03:47:28.739
But now that you're here, Morvo said to

03:47:28.739 --> 03:47:31.079
Sundu, it's very clear, right?

03:47:31.200 --> 03:47:34.020
Bring in your army, violence everywhere.

03:47:34.079 --> 03:47:36.479
Silk Wings help you, things get better.

03:47:36.540 --> 03:47:38.040
How?

03:47:38.100 --> 03:47:39.479
Sundu asked.

03:47:39.540 --> 03:47:42.600
How exactly do the silk wings help us?

03:47:42.659 --> 03:47:45.719
Morpho shifted his wings with a confused

03:47:45.719 --> 03:47:46.620
expression.

03:47:46.680 --> 03:47:50.700
By doing whatever you want us to do?

03:47:50.819 --> 03:47:54.120
Maybe pointing to the worst hive wings?

03:47:54.120 --> 03:47:55.799
Cheering when you kill them?

03:47:55.860 --> 03:47:58.979
Sundew side and rubbed her forehead.

03:47:59.040 --> 03:48:02.159
There was another flash outside the

03:48:02.159 --> 03:48:02.399
window.

03:48:02.520 --> 03:48:05.639
Again, Cricket only saw it out of the

03:48:05.639 --> 03:48:07.799
corner of her eye, and when she turned

03:48:07.799 --> 03:48:08.819
nothing was there.

03:48:08.879 --> 03:48:11.399
Maybe it was distant lightning.

03:48:11.459 --> 03:48:14.399
She pulled her scarves closer, and

03:48:14.399 --> 03:48:15.840
stepped up to the dark glass.

03:48:15.899 --> 03:48:19.559
For a moment, all she saw was her

03:48:19.559 --> 03:48:21.780
reflection and the reflections of the

03:48:21.780 --> 03:48:22.559
dragons behind her.

03:48:22.620 --> 03:48:26.280
For a moment, she was inside a glass box

03:48:26.280 --> 03:48:29.100
with strangers, the piece that didn't

03:48:29.100 --> 03:48:29.280
fit.

03:48:29.340 --> 03:48:33.120
And then her eyes adjusted, just in time

03:48:33.120 --> 03:48:35.639
to see a pair of dragons swoop by right

03:48:35.639 --> 03:48:37.020
below the level of the window.

03:48:37.079 --> 03:48:41.459
A pair of hive wings, wearing armor and

03:48:41.459 --> 03:48:43.979
carrying weapons, and heading around the

03:48:43.979 --> 03:48:46.260
curve of the hive toward the back door of

03:48:46.260 --> 03:48:46.739
the library.

03:48:46.799 --> 03:48:49.020
She whirled around.

03:48:49.079 --> 03:48:50.940
I think we've been seen.

03:48:51.000 --> 03:48:52.680
Unlikely.

03:48:52.739 --> 03:48:55.739
No one pays attention to the library

03:48:55.739 --> 03:48:56.520
Morpho argued.

03:48:56.579 --> 03:48:57.659
Shh.

03:48:57.719 --> 03:49:00.420
Sundew commanded, raising one claw.

03:49:00.479 --> 03:49:02.760
They all fell silent.

03:49:02.819 --> 03:49:06.120
A soft, rattling sound came from the

03:49:06.120 --> 03:49:08.940
front door of the library, as though

03:49:08.940 --> 03:49:11.340
someone was trying a series of keys in

03:49:11.340 --> 03:49:11.639
the lock.

03:49:11.760 --> 03:49:15.479
Cinnabar and Tau exchanged wide eyed

03:49:15.479 --> 03:49:15.780
looks.

03:49:15.840 --> 03:49:18.059
They're at the back too.

03:49:18.120 --> 03:49:19.500
Cricket whispered.

03:49:19.559 --> 03:49:21.780
Do we fight our way out?

03:49:21.840 --> 03:49:24.059
Soratel asked Sundoo.

03:49:24.180 --> 03:49:27.719
We don't know how many there are, Cinnabar

03:49:27.719 --> 03:49:30.479
said, and if any of them have Queen Wasp

03:49:30.479 --> 03:49:32.760
in them, she can summon a whole lot more

03:49:32.760 --> 03:49:33.719
in a heartbeat.

03:49:33.780 --> 03:49:35.760
Can you do that?

03:49:35.819 --> 03:49:38.040
Morpho asked Sundu.

03:49:38.100 --> 03:49:40.739
Summon a whole bunch of ferocious leaf

03:49:40.739 --> 03:49:41.159
wings.

03:49:41.219 --> 03:49:45.239
Not with my mind, she said crossly.

03:49:45.299 --> 03:49:47.459
Is there any other way out of the

03:49:47.459 --> 03:49:47.940
library?

03:49:48.059 --> 03:49:49.920
Tao shook her head.

03:49:49.979 --> 03:49:53.399
Maybe if a couple of us attack them, the

03:49:53.399 --> 03:49:54.059
others can escape.

03:49:54.120 --> 03:49:57.659
She suggested, I don't want to leave

03:49:57.659 --> 03:49:59.700
anyone in the claws of the hive wings

03:49:59.700 --> 03:50:01.319
Blue said quietly.

03:50:01.379 --> 03:50:04.860
Sundew whirled toward Cricket.

03:50:04.920 --> 03:50:06.239
Your hiding place.

03:50:06.299 --> 03:50:07.680
You must have one nearby.

03:50:07.739 --> 03:50:10.739
Show us where you'd go if wasp hive

03:50:10.739 --> 03:50:12.540
minded everyone while you're in here.

03:50:12.600 --> 03:50:14.579
Cricket hesitated.

03:50:14.639 --> 03:50:16.799
She didn't know of all 7 of them would

03:50:16.799 --> 03:50:17.040
fit.

03:50:17.100 --> 03:50:19.559
She also felt like there should be some

03:50:19.559 --> 03:50:21.780
conversation about betrayal and broken

03:50:21.780 --> 03:50:24.239
promises here, but there wasn't exactly

03:50:24.239 --> 03:50:24.540
time.

03:50:24.600 --> 03:50:26.340
This way.

03:50:26.459 --> 03:50:28.920
She hurried through the aisles with all

03:50:28.920 --> 03:50:30.180
of them wrestling behind her.

03:50:30.239 --> 03:50:33.180
At the edge of the balcony, she vaulted

03:50:33.180 --> 03:50:35.700
over without stopping, and sailed down to

03:50:35.700 --> 03:50:36.180
the 1st floor.

03:50:36.239 --> 03:50:40.020
When she looked back, she saw Cinnabar

03:50:40.020 --> 03:50:42.059
throw Tao's weak pair of wings over one

03:50:42.059 --> 03:50:44.100
of her shoulders, so she could support

03:50:44.100 --> 03:50:45.780
the yellow dragon down to the next

03:50:45.780 --> 03:50:46.200
level.

03:50:46.260 --> 03:50:49.440
As soon as they landed, Tao's wings

03:50:49.440 --> 03:50:51.059
folded back in, and she was running

03:50:51.059 --> 03:50:51.360
again.

03:50:51.420 --> 03:50:55.260
On either side of the front doors, and on

03:50:55.260 --> 03:50:57.719
either side of the back doors, stood a

03:50:57.719 --> 03:51:00.239
tall column, built into the wall and

03:51:00.239 --> 03:51:02.459
stretching from floor to ceiling.

03:51:02.520 --> 03:51:05.219
This was the book drop, with slots on the

03:51:05.219 --> 03:51:07.620
outer walls, where dragons could slide in

03:51:07.620 --> 03:51:08.639
their returned books.

03:51:08.700 --> 03:51:12.479
On the inner walls, each column had a

03:51:12.479 --> 03:51:15.059
door half as tall as a dragon, which the

03:51:15.059 --> 03:51:16.739
librarians could open to pull out the

03:51:16.739 --> 03:51:17.760
returned books.

03:51:17.819 --> 03:51:20.219
Cricket tugged one open and pointed

03:51:20.219 --> 03:51:20.579
inside.

03:51:20.700 --> 03:51:23.940
Got it, Cinnabar whispered.

03:51:24.000 --> 03:51:25.200
Come on, Tao.

03:51:25.260 --> 03:51:27.420
The 2 of them ran off toward the back

03:51:27.420 --> 03:51:27.840
doors.

03:51:27.899 --> 03:51:29.819
To hide in one of the columns there.

03:51:29.940 --> 03:51:33.360
I'm going with a leaf wing, Morpho

03:51:33.360 --> 03:51:33.719
declared.

03:51:33.780 --> 03:51:35.639
He ducked in through the door, Cricket

03:51:35.639 --> 03:51:37.799
was holding open, scrunching himself

03:51:37.799 --> 03:51:40.260
around the pile of books inside, and held

03:51:40.260 --> 03:51:41.940
out one talon towards sundew.

03:51:42.000 --> 03:51:45.360
I can see how I deserve that, Sundu

03:51:45.360 --> 03:51:45.719
said.

03:51:45.780 --> 03:51:48.059
But no, you get sword tail.

03:51:48.120 --> 03:51:51.360
She bundled Swordtail into the cramped

03:51:51.360 --> 03:51:53.879
space with Morpho and closed the door on

03:51:53.879 --> 03:51:54.959
their protesting faces.

03:51:55.020 --> 03:51:57.420
Don't you want to be with your new

03:51:57.420 --> 03:51:58.620
chrysalis friends?

03:51:58.680 --> 03:52:00.420
Cricket couldn't help asking.

03:52:00.479 --> 03:52:03.899
Sundu hurried across to the other column

03:52:03.899 --> 03:52:06.299
just as they all heard a click from the

03:52:06.299 --> 03:52:06.780
front door.

03:52:06.840 --> 03:52:09.659
Cricket's heart tried to hurl itself out

03:52:09.659 --> 03:52:10.260
of her chest.

03:52:10.379 --> 03:52:12.780
She scrambled inside the book drop

03:52:12.780 --> 03:52:15.180
burrowing through and up the pile of

03:52:15.180 --> 03:52:16.739
teetering library books inside.

03:52:16.860 --> 03:52:20.219
A moment later, Blue squeezed in beside

03:52:20.219 --> 03:52:23.159
her, and then the space went dark as

03:52:23.159 --> 03:52:25.139
sundew leaped inside and shut the door

03:52:25.139 --> 03:52:25.559
behind her.

03:52:25.620 --> 03:52:28.860
Cricket braced herself against the walls

03:52:28.860 --> 03:52:31.920
and edged upward a little, but her wings

03:52:31.920 --> 03:52:34.680
were tangled with blues, and their scales

03:52:34.680 --> 03:52:37.079
were pressed so close together that she

03:52:37.079 --> 03:52:39.059
could feel his heart beating all the way

03:52:39.059 --> 03:52:39.899
through her own chest.

03:52:40.020 --> 03:52:43.139
He rested one talon on the wall behind

03:52:43.139 --> 03:52:45.899
her, his cape drifting around them like

03:52:45.899 --> 03:52:47.280
extra silken wings.

03:52:47.340 --> 03:52:49.739
She tucked her head under his chin

03:52:49.739 --> 03:52:52.680
breathing in the scent of old books, and

03:52:52.680 --> 03:52:55.020
blue, who smelled a bit like fried

03:52:55.020 --> 03:52:55.680
bananas.

03:52:55.739 --> 03:52:59.520
Below them, she could sense the poised

03:52:59.520 --> 03:53:02.399
still form of sundew, still half buried

03:53:02.399 --> 03:53:02.819
in books.

03:53:02.879 --> 03:53:05.639
The slide for the books from the upper

03:53:05.639 --> 03:53:08.760
slot ended near Cricket's head, and the

03:53:08.760 --> 03:53:11.219
edge dug into her neck, but she didn't

03:53:11.219 --> 03:53:13.020
dare try to move away from it.

03:53:13.079 --> 03:53:15.360
I hope everyone else can be quiet.

03:53:15.479 --> 03:53:17.459
She thought anxiously.

03:53:17.520 --> 03:53:20.459
If the soldiers found dragons in one book

03:53:20.459 --> 03:53:23.040
drop, they'd check the rest and find all

03:53:23.040 --> 03:53:23.399
of them.

03:53:23.459 --> 03:53:26.760
This wasn't the smartest hiding place.

03:53:26.819 --> 03:53:28.559
We should have spread out more.

03:53:28.620 --> 03:53:32.280
Finally, said a voice outside the book

03:53:32.280 --> 03:53:32.700
drop.

03:53:32.760 --> 03:53:35.520
Blue tensed, sending little shivers

03:53:35.520 --> 03:53:36.840
through cricket's scales.

03:53:36.899 --> 03:53:38.760
Sorry that took so long.

03:53:38.819 --> 03:53:40.680
Lady Jewel has a lot of keys.

03:53:40.739 --> 03:53:44.579
And I suppose half of them are entirely

03:53:44.579 --> 03:53:47.639
decorative, sneered another voice

03:53:47.639 --> 03:53:51.239
unfamiliar, but also unmistakably in the

03:53:51.239 --> 03:53:52.559
thrall of Queen Wasp.

03:53:52.620 --> 03:53:55.559
Cricket had heard that sinister cadence

03:53:55.559 --> 03:53:58.260
so many times in situations just like

03:53:58.260 --> 03:54:01.440
this, hiding in the dark, while the queen

03:54:01.440 --> 03:54:03.239
used her subjects as puppets.

03:54:03.299 --> 03:54:05.459
Not just like this.

03:54:05.520 --> 03:54:09.659
She felt Blue's shoulder, cool and smooth

03:54:09.659 --> 03:54:10.739
against her neck.

03:54:10.799 --> 03:54:13.260
This time, I'm not alone.

03:54:13.319 --> 03:54:17.159
Open the back doors for the others, and

03:54:17.159 --> 03:54:18.600
then search every corner.

03:54:18.659 --> 03:54:22.319
The queen ordered through the hive wing's

03:54:22.319 --> 03:54:22.500
mouth.

03:54:22.559 --> 03:54:25.559
Cricket heard 2 sets of talons walking

03:54:25.559 --> 03:54:26.040
away.

03:54:26.100 --> 03:54:28.620
She wondered why the queen wasn't inside

03:54:28.620 --> 03:54:29.159
them too.

03:54:29.219 --> 03:54:30.719
Or if she was now.

03:54:30.780 --> 03:54:33.959
She might have needed one of them inside

03:54:33.959 --> 03:54:36.180
his own brain to get the library doors

03:54:36.180 --> 03:54:36.479
open.

03:54:36.540 --> 03:54:37.979
She guessed.

03:54:38.040 --> 03:54:40.500
The hive wing would supposedly have a

03:54:40.500 --> 03:54:42.299
better idea of which key would work than

03:54:42.299 --> 03:54:42.899
the queen would.

03:54:43.020 --> 03:54:46.620
It still took a while though, she thought

03:54:46.620 --> 03:54:47.219
gratefully.

03:54:47.340 --> 03:54:49.020
Was that on purpose?

03:54:49.079 --> 03:54:51.420
Did that hive wing help us by taking

03:54:51.420 --> 03:54:52.860
longer than he needed to?

03:54:52.920 --> 03:54:55.620
Perhaps that was wishful thinking?

03:54:55.680 --> 03:54:58.799
He didn't know who was in here, if

03:54:58.799 --> 03:54:59.280
anyone.

03:54:59.399 --> 03:55:01.979
Maybe he just wanted to annoy the queen.

03:55:02.040 --> 03:55:05.700
Whatever his reasons, or even if he'd

03:55:05.700 --> 03:55:08.219
done it by accident, she was thankful.

03:55:08.280 --> 03:55:11.639
A long time seemed to pass.

03:55:11.700 --> 03:55:15.000
They heard talon steps and thumps, as

03:55:15.000 --> 03:55:16.620
though boxes were being overturned

03:55:16.620 --> 03:55:17.040
somewhere.

03:55:17.100 --> 03:55:21.180
No sign of anyone, your majesty, a voice

03:55:21.180 --> 03:55:22.860
reported, after a long while.

03:55:22.920 --> 03:55:26.700
I know I saw dragons in here.

03:55:26.760 --> 03:55:29.340
The hive wing with the queen inside

03:55:29.340 --> 03:55:30.000
hissed.

03:55:30.120 --> 03:55:32.639
Find them, or you will die.

03:55:32.760 --> 03:55:36.780
Blue flinched, and Cricket tensed for a

03:55:36.780 --> 03:55:39.180
moment, wondering if she had accidentally

03:55:39.180 --> 03:55:39.840
scratched him.

03:55:39.899 --> 03:55:41.700
But then she realized.

03:55:41.819 --> 03:55:45.719
Oh, he's worried about the hive wings out

03:55:45.719 --> 03:55:45.959
there.

03:55:46.020 --> 03:55:49.079
And what Queen Wasp will do to them if

03:55:49.079 --> 03:55:50.459
they don't find us.

03:55:50.520 --> 03:55:53.159
She didn't dare risk whispering.

03:55:53.219 --> 03:55:55.500
But she wished she could tell him that

03:55:55.500 --> 03:55:57.719
she'd never seen the queen force a dragon

03:55:57.719 --> 03:56:00.120
to hurt himself while she was controlling

03:56:00.120 --> 03:56:00.360
him.

03:56:00.360 --> 03:56:03.000
As they'd seen in the Temple of

03:56:03.000 --> 03:56:06.000
Clearsight, Wasp felt the same pain as

03:56:06.000 --> 03:56:08.700
the dragons she was controlling, and she

03:56:08.700 --> 03:56:10.500
would jump out of their minds if the pain

03:56:10.500 --> 03:56:11.100
was too much.

03:56:11.219 --> 03:56:14.340
But she could still force a dragon to

03:56:14.340 --> 03:56:14.940
hurt someone else.

03:56:15.000 --> 03:56:17.520
There was nothing they could do, though

03:56:17.520 --> 03:56:20.280
except turn themselves in, and cricket

03:56:20.280 --> 03:56:21.959
wasn't going to let Blue do that.

03:56:22.020 --> 03:56:24.659
She was pretty sure Sundoo wouldn't let

03:56:24.659 --> 03:56:25.139
him either.

03:56:25.200 --> 03:56:28.559
Come out, you sniveling cowards.

03:56:28.620 --> 03:56:31.200
Wasp's voice roared suddenly.

03:56:31.260 --> 03:56:34.620
I know there are dragons hiding in this

03:56:34.620 --> 03:56:35.399
library.

03:56:35.459 --> 03:56:39.239
Show yourselves, or I will burn all the

03:56:39.239 --> 03:56:42.000
books until you die choking on the

03:56:42.000 --> 03:56:42.360
smoke.

03:56:42.420 --> 03:56:44.760
Burn the books?

03:56:44.819 --> 03:56:46.139
She can't.

03:56:46.200 --> 03:56:47.459
She wouldn't.

03:56:47.579 --> 03:56:49.379
Jewel wouldn't let her.

03:56:49.440 --> 03:56:51.719
Could she stop the queen though?

03:56:51.780 --> 03:56:54.420
Wouldn't burning the books put the rest

03:56:54.420 --> 03:56:55.979
of the hive in danger too?

03:56:56.100 --> 03:56:58.920
Maybe wasp doesn't care about that.

03:56:58.979 --> 03:57:02.040
Maybe she'd burn down the whole hive to

03:57:02.040 --> 03:57:02.579
smoke us out.

03:57:02.700 --> 03:57:06.659
Cricket heard a soft hiss from sundew

03:57:06.659 --> 03:57:07.260
below her.

03:57:07.319 --> 03:57:09.840
Sundew couldn't give herself up.

03:57:09.899 --> 03:57:12.479
She was the one holding the book of

03:57:12.479 --> 03:57:15.059
Clearsight, and they needed that to prove

03:57:15.059 --> 03:57:16.500
Queen Wasp was lying.

03:57:16.559 --> 03:57:19.020
She wouldn't let Blue go either.

03:57:19.079 --> 03:57:21.479
As long as his flame silk was part of the

03:57:21.479 --> 03:57:22.620
leaf wing plan.

03:57:22.680 --> 03:57:24.420
But Cricket.

03:57:24.479 --> 03:57:27.299
She wasn't any use to the leaf wings

03:57:27.299 --> 03:57:27.659
really.

03:57:27.719 --> 03:57:29.879
What would happen to her if she turned

03:57:29.879 --> 03:57:30.899
herself into the queen?

03:57:30.959 --> 03:57:33.059
Would she kill me?

03:57:33.120 --> 03:57:36.299
Her wings were trembling, and she

03:57:36.299 --> 03:57:37.200
couldn't make them stop.

03:57:37.260 --> 03:57:39.360
I am not brave.

03:57:39.420 --> 03:57:40.920
I am not a warrior.

03:57:40.979 --> 03:57:43.500
I don't want to put myself in Queen

03:57:43.500 --> 03:57:46.680
Wasp's talents, not even to save all the

03:57:46.680 --> 03:57:47.040
books.

03:57:47.100 --> 03:57:51.360
But if I don't, what happens to blue and

03:57:51.360 --> 03:57:51.959
sundo?

03:57:52.020 --> 03:57:55.260
As if he could hear her thoughts, Blue

03:57:55.260 --> 03:57:57.540
curled himself closer to her and held her

03:57:57.540 --> 03:58:00.059
tightly, absorbing her trembling in his

03:58:00.059 --> 03:58:00.840
own wings.

03:58:01.020 --> 03:58:05.760
Very well, said the queen's voice, build

03:58:05.760 --> 03:58:09.000
me a bonfire of books right here. she

03:58:09.000 --> 03:58:09.420
ordered.

03:58:09.479 --> 03:58:12.959
We'll use flame silk from the lanterns.

03:58:13.020 --> 03:58:15.719
But, Your Majesty.

03:58:15.840 --> 03:58:17.760
What if the fire spreads?

03:58:17.879 --> 03:58:20.340
asked one of the hive wings.

03:58:20.399 --> 03:58:23.700
Then we'll have to throw you into it to

03:58:23.700 --> 03:58:26.579
slow the flames, the queen snarled.

03:58:26.639 --> 03:58:29.399
You are a tedious talon ringer.

03:58:29.459 --> 03:58:30.659
I'll do it myself.

03:58:30.719 --> 03:58:34.319
Cricket heard the dragons snap suddenly

03:58:34.319 --> 03:58:36.360
to attention, and run off toward the

03:58:36.360 --> 03:58:38.340
stacks without any further argument.

03:58:38.399 --> 03:58:41.879
She guessed that Queen Wasp had taken

03:58:41.879 --> 03:58:43.260
them over as well.

03:58:43.319 --> 03:58:44.700
Wait.

03:58:44.760 --> 03:58:46.260
Below her.

03:58:46.319 --> 03:58:48.420
Cricket heard a book slide down the

03:58:48.420 --> 03:58:48.840
pile.

03:58:48.899 --> 03:58:51.780
Sundew caught it deftly before it could

03:58:51.780 --> 03:58:52.860
thunk against the side.

03:58:52.920 --> 03:58:56.040
They all held their breaths, frozen in

03:58:56.040 --> 03:58:59.100
place, caught by the sound of Cinnabar's

03:58:59.100 --> 03:58:59.760
voice in the library.

03:58:59.879 --> 03:59:01.979
We are sorry.

03:59:02.040 --> 03:59:03.299
We're sorry, my queen.

03:59:03.360 --> 03:59:05.159
Very sorry.

03:59:05.219 --> 03:59:06.840
That was Tao.

03:59:06.959 --> 03:59:08.520
What are they doing?

03:59:08.579 --> 03:59:12.780
We were hiding from Lady Jewel, Cinnabar

03:59:12.780 --> 03:59:13.680
said breathlessly.

03:59:13.739 --> 03:59:16.079
She said we were spending too much time

03:59:16.079 --> 03:59:18.360
reading, and not enough time on our work

03:59:18.360 --> 03:59:18.719
for her.

03:59:18.780 --> 03:59:22.139
So, we've been sneaking out at night to

03:59:22.139 --> 03:59:23.940
read here, Tao said.

03:59:24.000 --> 03:59:25.680
We didn't mean to anger you.

03:59:25.739 --> 03:59:27.600
Please don't tell Lady Jewel.

03:59:27.659 --> 03:59:29.579
She'll punish us terribly.

03:59:29.700 --> 03:59:31.860
As she should.

03:59:31.920 --> 03:59:34.200
The queen's voice snapped.

03:59:34.260 --> 03:59:37.079
I told her this library would be

03:59:37.079 --> 03:59:37.379
trouble.

03:59:37.440 --> 03:59:41.280
I don't stand for disobedient silk wings

03:59:41.280 --> 03:59:42.360
in my hive.

03:59:42.420 --> 03:59:44.819
Who else is with you?

03:59:44.940 --> 03:59:47.700
Cricket squeezed her eyes shut?

03:59:47.819 --> 03:59:49.920
As though the darkness around her could

03:59:49.920 --> 03:59:50.700
get any darker.

03:59:50.819 --> 03:59:54.659
No one, your majesty, said Tao.

03:59:54.719 --> 03:59:58.620
My cousin Morpho came to scold us earlier

03:59:58.620 --> 04:00:01.260
Cinnabar offered, but he left a little

04:00:01.260 --> 04:00:01.739
while ago.

04:00:01.799 --> 04:00:07.620
Blue wings, said the queen suspiciously.

04:00:07.739 --> 04:00:09.959
I thought I saw blue wings.

04:00:10.020 --> 04:00:15.000
That would be Morpho, Cinnabar said, or

04:00:15.000 --> 04:00:17.100
the blankets we sometimes use up there.

04:00:17.159 --> 04:00:19.379
Do you want me to show those to you?

04:00:19.500 --> 04:00:20.700
No.

04:00:20.760 --> 04:00:24.000
The shell of the dragon that held the

04:00:24.000 --> 04:00:24.959
queen hissed.

04:00:25.020 --> 04:00:27.239
This is a waste of time.

04:00:27.299 --> 04:00:28.680
You.

04:00:28.739 --> 04:00:32.280
Take these 2 back to Lady Jewel and tell

04:00:32.280 --> 04:00:34.979
her, I said, to punish them severely.

04:00:35.040 --> 04:00:37.860
Sorry again, Your Majesty.

04:00:37.920 --> 04:00:39.180
Tao said.

04:00:39.239 --> 04:00:41.639
Cricket tried to figure out how many

04:00:41.639 --> 04:00:43.559
talon steps were leaving the library.

04:00:43.620 --> 04:00:46.139
How many were left?

04:00:46.200 --> 04:00:48.719
Was the queen still inside all of them?

04:00:48.780 --> 04:00:51.000
Would anyone lock the door again?

04:00:51.059 --> 04:00:53.579
Would the queen leave guards on the

04:00:53.579 --> 04:00:54.059
library?

04:00:54.120 --> 04:00:56.459
How long do they have to wait before it

04:00:56.459 --> 04:00:57.659
was safe to come out?

04:00:57.719 --> 04:01:00.840
The tramping of most of the feet faded

04:01:00.840 --> 04:01:01.079
away.

04:01:01.139 --> 04:01:04.139
But she could still hear claws scraping

04:01:04.139 --> 04:01:05.340
across the floor.

04:01:05.399 --> 04:01:06.719
Someone was still out there.

04:01:06.780 --> 04:01:11.040
It felt as though a long time passed, but

04:01:11.040 --> 04:01:12.780
sundew didn't open the door of the book

04:01:12.780 --> 04:01:15.239
drop, and Cricket figured she would know

04:01:15.239 --> 04:01:16.860
when it was safe to do that.

04:01:16.920 --> 04:01:19.739
She had just shifted to lean against

04:01:19.739 --> 04:01:22.020
Blue's shoulder when she heard running

04:01:22.020 --> 04:01:22.739
steps outside.

04:01:22.799 --> 04:01:26.040
Your Majesty, are you still there?

04:01:26.040 --> 04:01:27.059
said a voice.

04:01:27.180 --> 04:01:28.979
Yes.

04:01:29.100 --> 04:01:33.420
Wasp answered coldly. sounding as if she

04:01:33.420 --> 04:01:35.280
was standing directly on the other side

04:01:35.280 --> 04:01:36.600
of the wall from cricket.

04:01:36.659 --> 04:01:38.459
What is it?

04:01:38.520 --> 04:01:41.579
We've had a tip that Lady Scarab is here

04:01:41.579 --> 04:01:44.040
in Dual Hive, and she may be hiding

04:01:44.040 --> 04:01:45.540
another dragon in her mansion.

04:01:45.600 --> 04:01:48.540
Lady scarab.

04:01:48.659 --> 04:01:52.620
The queen's voice hissed, she would.

04:01:52.680 --> 04:01:56.700
Let's go pay Lady Scarab a visit.

04:01:56.760 --> 04:02:00.059
Their talent steps crashed out of the

04:02:00.059 --> 04:02:03.120
library, and cricket looked up so quickly

04:02:03.120 --> 04:02:05.159
her snout knocked into Blue's chin.

04:02:05.219 --> 04:02:08.760
They're talking about Katy did, she

04:02:08.760 --> 04:02:09.239
whispered.

04:02:09.360 --> 04:02:11.459
They're going to arrest my sister.

04:02:11.520 --> 04:02:16.139
Chapter 13.

04:02:16.319 --> 04:02:19.920
Cricket tried to scramble downward, but

04:02:19.920 --> 04:02:22.319
accidentally started a cascade of books.

04:02:22.379 --> 04:02:23.940
Ow!

04:02:24.000 --> 04:02:25.979
Sundew whispered from below her.

04:02:26.040 --> 04:02:27.000
Quit that.

04:02:27.059 --> 04:02:28.319
Stop moving right now.

04:02:28.379 --> 04:02:31.739
I have to get to Katy did, Cricket

04:02:31.739 --> 04:02:32.520
whispered back.

04:02:32.579 --> 04:02:34.979
Her wings bent awkwardly against the

04:02:34.979 --> 04:02:36.000
curving walls.

04:02:36.059 --> 04:02:37.799
To do what?

04:02:37.860 --> 04:02:39.180
Sundew demanded.

04:02:39.239 --> 04:02:41.340
There's nothing you can do to help her.

04:02:41.399 --> 04:02:43.260
I could try to warn her.

04:02:43.319 --> 04:02:46.559
Won't Queen Wasp have jumped into Katy

04:02:46.559 --> 04:02:48.659
did already, now that she knows where she

04:02:48.659 --> 04:02:49.079
is?

04:02:49.139 --> 04:02:50.280
Blue whispered.

04:02:50.340 --> 04:02:51.659
Maybe not.

04:02:51.719 --> 04:02:54.239
Cricket tried to edge down a bit

04:02:54.239 --> 04:02:54.600
farther.

04:02:54.659 --> 04:02:57.540
Sometimes it seems like she needs to know

04:02:57.540 --> 04:03:00.780
who a dragon is or see her before she can

04:03:00.780 --> 04:03:01.620
get inside her head.

04:03:01.739 --> 04:03:05.459
So she'll jump into Scarab, Sundew

04:03:05.459 --> 04:03:06.059
pointed out.

04:03:06.120 --> 04:03:08.819
Take one look at your sister, jump into

04:03:08.819 --> 04:03:09.899
her and off they go.

04:03:09.959 --> 04:03:12.180
There's no way you can get there in

04:03:12.180 --> 04:03:12.360
time.

04:03:12.420 --> 04:03:14.399
Couldn't I try?

04:03:14.520 --> 04:03:16.020
Cricket pleaded.

04:03:16.079 --> 04:03:17.459
She thought for a moment.

04:03:17.520 --> 04:03:20.280
Wait, I don't need your permission.

04:03:20.340 --> 04:03:22.500
You've already decided you're not going

04:03:22.500 --> 04:03:22.920
to help me.

04:03:22.979 --> 04:03:24.600
So why should I listen to you?

04:03:24.719 --> 04:03:27.899
She started scrambling down the column

04:03:27.899 --> 04:03:29.819
again, kicking more books aside.

04:03:29.879 --> 04:03:34.680
Ah, stop, Sundew said, squishing herself

04:03:34.680 --> 04:03:36.659
to one side to get out of cricket's way.

04:03:36.719 --> 04:03:39.719
Listen, I'm not going to help your try

04:03:39.719 --> 04:03:42.840
because they're a lost cause, and they

04:03:42.840 --> 04:03:44.040
deserve everything they get.

04:03:44.100 --> 04:03:46.020
But you're not like them.

04:03:46.079 --> 04:03:48.540
You can join our side and be safe.

04:03:48.600 --> 04:03:51.719
As long as I forget about Katy did

04:03:51.719 --> 04:03:54.360
Cricket said, and let you heart a whole

04:03:54.360 --> 04:03:56.159
lot of dragons who never fought in any

04:03:56.159 --> 04:03:58.559
war against you, no, thank you.

04:03:58.680 --> 04:04:02.219
She wrestled Sunday's tale out of her way

04:04:02.219 --> 04:04:05.159
and shoved the door open, tumbling out

04:04:05.159 --> 04:04:07.440
into the library in a small avalanche of

04:04:07.440 --> 04:04:07.680
books.

04:04:07.739 --> 04:04:10.680
The front lobby of the library was

04:04:10.680 --> 04:04:13.500
deserted, the main door is standing wide

04:04:13.500 --> 04:04:13.680
open.

04:04:13.739 --> 04:04:17.340
The door on the column opposite hers

04:04:17.340 --> 04:04:20.399
snuck open a crack, and SwordTail's snout

04:04:20.399 --> 04:04:21.180
poked out.

04:04:21.239 --> 04:04:23.940
Oh, thank goodness, he said.

04:04:24.000 --> 04:04:26.100
The sun do think it's safe to come out?

04:04:26.159 --> 04:04:29.219
This guy is insufferable, even in total

04:04:29.219 --> 04:04:29.700
silence.

04:04:29.819 --> 04:04:30.840
Ow.

04:04:30.899 --> 04:04:33.600
He twisted around to glare at the blue

04:04:33.600 --> 04:04:35.760
tail point that was jabbing him in the

04:04:35.760 --> 04:04:36.299
head.

04:04:36.299 --> 04:04:39.600
I'm telling you, Sundew said.

04:04:39.659 --> 04:04:41.459
Climbing out behind Cricket.

04:04:41.520 --> 04:04:43.979
It's not going to do any good to go watch

04:04:43.979 --> 04:04:45.120
your sister get arrested.

04:04:45.180 --> 04:04:48.420
It'll just upset you, and you might get

04:04:48.420 --> 04:04:48.659
caught.

04:04:48.780 --> 04:04:50.819
I'm going anyway.

04:04:50.879 --> 04:04:53.340
Cricket said, starting toward the

04:04:53.340 --> 04:04:53.879
courtyard.

04:04:53.940 --> 04:04:57.299
And I'm going with her, said Blue.

04:04:57.360 --> 04:04:59.760
He clambered out of the book drop and

04:04:59.760 --> 04:05:01.500
started shoveling books back into it.

04:05:01.559 --> 04:05:04.260
I'm going wherever cricket goes.

04:05:04.319 --> 04:05:07.319
Sundew stamped her foot in frustration.

04:05:07.379 --> 04:05:08.879
All right, fine.

04:05:08.940 --> 04:05:11.219
Let me get my stupid cape.

04:05:11.280 --> 04:05:13.500
She stormed off to the upper level.

04:05:13.559 --> 04:05:17.040
Cricket came back to help Blue shoulder

04:05:17.040 --> 04:05:19.020
the door of the book drop closed with all

04:05:19.020 --> 04:05:19.739
the books inside.

04:05:19.799 --> 04:05:23.760
Good idea, she said to him, in case we

04:05:23.760 --> 04:05:25.020
need these hiding spots again.

04:05:25.079 --> 04:05:28.680
Oh, right, he said.

04:05:28.739 --> 04:05:30.840
Yes, absolutely that.

04:05:30.959 --> 04:05:33.299
She couldn't help smiling at him.

04:05:33.420 --> 04:05:36.120
You were trying to save the librarians

04:05:36.120 --> 04:05:37.260
some work, weren't you?

04:05:37.319 --> 04:05:40.860
They have enough mess to clean up, he

04:05:40.860 --> 04:05:43.620
said sheepishly, waving his wings at the

04:05:43.620 --> 04:05:44.639
rest of the library.

04:05:44.700 --> 04:05:47.159
Where boxes of books lay tumbled on their

04:05:47.159 --> 04:05:47.579
sides.

04:05:47.639 --> 04:05:50.219
A few shelves had been knocked completely

04:05:50.219 --> 04:05:52.739
over, and it looked as if everything on

04:05:52.739 --> 04:05:55.079
the desks that wasn't nailed down had

04:05:55.079 --> 04:05:55.739
been thrown around.

04:05:55.860 --> 04:05:57.840
Where are we going?

04:05:57.959 --> 04:06:01.020
SwordTell asked, as Sundew came flying

04:06:01.020 --> 04:06:01.500
back toward them.

04:06:01.559 --> 04:06:06.299
Ow, again, he yelped, as Marfo fell out

04:06:06.299 --> 04:06:08.219
of the book drop and squashed his tail.

04:06:08.280 --> 04:06:11.040
To get cricket arrested as far as I can

04:06:11.040 --> 04:06:13.920
tell, Sundu grumbled, throwing the

04:06:13.920 --> 04:06:15.840
saffron colored silk cape over her

04:06:15.840 --> 04:06:16.379
wings.

04:06:16.440 --> 04:06:20.159
I have to get home, Morpo said.

04:06:20.219 --> 04:06:21.780
My dad worries if I'm out too late.

04:06:21.840 --> 04:06:25.319
I want to meet everyone in the Jewel Hive

04:06:25.319 --> 04:06:26.280
Chrysalis today.

04:06:26.399 --> 04:06:30.600
Sundew said to him, outside the hive, next

04:06:30.600 --> 04:06:32.399
to the farthest stall of the glitter

04:06:32.399 --> 04:06:34.500
bazaar, when the sun is at its highest

04:06:34.500 --> 04:06:34.860
point.

04:06:34.860 --> 04:06:38.819
He nodded, his eyes shining, and flew

04:06:38.819 --> 04:06:39.299
off.

04:06:39.360 --> 04:06:42.120
Cricket was already leading the way up to

04:06:42.120 --> 04:06:43.920
the higher levels. thinking about

04:06:43.920 --> 04:06:44.459
sunset.

04:06:44.579 --> 04:06:47.819
That's how long we have until Bella Dawn

04:06:47.819 --> 04:06:48.299
is deadline.

04:06:48.360 --> 04:06:50.639
We have to bring her something real by

04:06:50.639 --> 04:06:52.979
then, or hive wings will start to die.

04:06:53.040 --> 04:06:56.159
Her heart thudded painfully in her

04:06:56.159 --> 04:06:56.459
chest.

04:06:56.579 --> 04:07:00.600
She liked sundew, most of the time, and

04:07:00.600 --> 04:07:02.159
being with sundew had made her start

04:07:02.159 --> 04:07:04.079
thinking all leaf wings were like that.

04:07:04.139 --> 04:07:07.379
But when she stopped to remember Sundew's

04:07:07.379 --> 04:07:10.620
parents, Belladonna and hemlock, she felt

04:07:10.620 --> 04:07:12.719
an almost crushing fear for the rest of

04:07:12.719 --> 04:07:13.379
her tribe.

04:07:13.379 --> 04:07:16.260
The higher levels were the busiest at

04:07:16.260 --> 04:07:19.020
this time of night, as hive wings swarmed

04:07:19.020 --> 04:07:21.840
from one party to another, always rushing

04:07:21.840 --> 04:07:24.239
to make sure they didn't miss anything, to

04:07:24.239 --> 04:07:25.860
make sure they made at least an

04:07:25.860 --> 04:07:26.700
appearance everywhere.

04:07:26.819 --> 04:07:29.639
Many of them had their most beautiful

04:07:29.639 --> 04:07:32.340
silk wings along with them, although at

04:07:32.340 --> 04:07:34.200
this hour, Cricket could see that the

04:07:34.200 --> 04:07:35.340
rules were more relaxed.

04:07:35.399 --> 04:07:38.459
Silk Wings and Hive Wings chatted to one

04:07:38.459 --> 04:07:41.280
another, as they walked or browsed the

04:07:41.280 --> 04:07:42.120
appetizer tables.

04:07:42.180 --> 04:07:45.059
Silkwings joined the dances in the

04:07:45.059 --> 04:07:47.340
ballrooms, laughing and singing along.

04:07:47.399 --> 04:07:51.299
There are hive wings here, who see the

04:07:51.299 --> 04:07:52.680
silk wings as equals.

04:07:52.739 --> 04:07:54.299
She was sure of it.

04:07:54.360 --> 04:07:57.059
Hive wings who might be willing to join a

04:07:57.059 --> 04:07:59.760
revolution to stop the queen and change

04:07:59.760 --> 04:08:00.840
the rules of this world.

04:08:00.959 --> 04:08:02.520
If they could.

04:08:02.639 --> 04:08:05.700
If they were given a chance, before the

04:08:05.700 --> 04:08:07.739
leaf wings started a new war.

04:08:07.799 --> 04:08:11.100
Lady Scarab's mansion was one of the only

04:08:11.100 --> 04:08:12.299
quiet ones up here.

04:08:12.360 --> 04:08:15.659
No music rang from the windows, no

04:08:15.659 --> 04:08:18.659
dragons fluttered in and out, but a squad

04:08:18.659 --> 04:08:20.399
of hive wings were gathered on her front

04:08:20.399 --> 04:08:23.340
steps, some of them tapping their claws

04:08:23.340 --> 04:08:23.940
impatiently.

04:08:24.059 --> 04:08:27.299
Open this door, scarab.

04:08:27.420 --> 04:08:29.579
The queen roared from inside one of the

04:08:29.579 --> 04:08:30.000
soldiers.

04:08:30.120 --> 04:08:33.059
A short way down the street, Cricket

04:08:33.059 --> 04:08:35.219
ducked into a party that overflowed the

04:08:35.219 --> 04:08:36.780
edges of an elegant courtyard.

04:08:36.840 --> 04:08:40.379
Nearly invisible strands of silk draped

04:08:40.379 --> 04:08:42.959
from the hedges and arches and gazebo

04:08:42.959 --> 04:08:46.379
hung with tiny firefly sculptures, each

04:08:46.379 --> 04:08:49.139
one with a small dot of flame silk inside

04:08:49.139 --> 04:08:51.600
so the party seemed to be dotted with

04:08:51.600 --> 04:08:52.559
real fireflies.

04:08:52.680 --> 04:08:56.159
A trio of silk wings played quiet string

04:08:56.159 --> 04:08:57.479
instruments in a corner.

04:08:57.479 --> 04:09:00.360
Several of the guests turned around with

04:09:00.360 --> 04:09:02.399
disapproving looks when they heard the

04:09:02.399 --> 04:09:04.799
shouting at scarab's house, then turned

04:09:04.799 --> 04:09:07.319
back quickly, making their faces blank

04:09:07.319 --> 04:09:09.540
when they realized who was doing the

04:09:09.540 --> 04:09:09.899
shouting.

04:09:10.020 --> 04:09:13.020
Cricket slipped through the crowd and

04:09:13.020 --> 04:09:15.000
picked up a fizzy coconut scented drink

04:09:15.000 --> 04:09:17.520
from one of the tables, trying to look as

04:09:17.520 --> 04:09:19.020
though she went to parties all the time.

04:09:19.079 --> 04:09:20.940
This was perfectly normal.

04:09:21.000 --> 04:09:22.799
Parties were easy and fun.

04:09:22.920 --> 04:09:24.059
Ha ha.

04:09:24.120 --> 04:09:24.719
Yes.

04:09:24.780 --> 04:09:26.280
Hooray for socializing.

04:09:26.340 --> 04:09:28.739
That was absolutely a thing she liked to

04:09:28.739 --> 04:09:28.920
do.

04:09:28.979 --> 04:09:32.579
The other 3 stayed close to her. looking

04:09:32.579 --> 04:09:34.620
possibly even more conspicuous than she

04:09:34.620 --> 04:09:39.059
did. wide eyed blue, scowling sundew, and

04:09:39.059 --> 04:09:40.379
twitchy sword tail.

04:09:40.440 --> 04:09:43.079
But the crush of dragons made it unlikely

04:09:43.079 --> 04:09:44.700
anyone would stop and examine them

04:09:44.700 --> 04:09:45.059
closely.

04:09:45.120 --> 04:09:47.579
Try this one.

04:09:47.639 --> 04:09:50.579
Cricket heard his silkwing say, scooping

04:09:50.579 --> 04:09:52.500
a glass of something fuchsia from one of

04:09:52.500 --> 04:09:54.719
the many sparkling punch bowls scattered

04:09:54.719 --> 04:09:55.799
on tables around the party.

04:09:55.860 --> 04:09:58.739
The hive wing he handed it to tasted the

04:09:58.739 --> 04:09:59.639
drink and made a face.

04:09:59.700 --> 04:10:04.500
Scarab. bellowed the queen, and Cricket

04:10:04.500 --> 04:10:06.360
saw everyone at the party trying to hide

04:10:06.360 --> 04:10:09.540
their reactions. irritation here, fear

04:10:09.540 --> 04:10:12.120
over there, that one perhaps glee.

04:10:12.180 --> 04:10:14.819
Those 2 definitely curiosity.

04:10:14.879 --> 04:10:17.879
The soldiers pounded on the door with

04:10:17.879 --> 04:10:20.879
talons and tails and spiky clubs.

04:10:20.940 --> 04:10:23.940
Open this door or I'll.

04:10:24.659 --> 04:10:25.440
The door flew open.

04:10:25.500 --> 04:10:27.360
And one of the soldiers nearly fell

04:10:27.360 --> 04:10:27.840
inside.

04:10:27.899 --> 04:10:30.840
Lady Scarab glared out at the knot of

04:10:30.840 --> 04:10:32.040
dragons on her doorstep.

04:10:32.100 --> 04:10:34.739
Cricket had to crane her neck to see the

04:10:34.739 --> 04:10:36.659
elderly dragon around a few other party

04:10:36.659 --> 04:10:37.500
goers.

04:10:37.559 --> 04:10:38.940
She wasn't the only one.

04:10:39.000 --> 04:10:42.059
Now, several guests were staring openly

04:10:42.059 --> 04:10:43.440
down the street at a commotion.

04:10:43.500 --> 04:10:46.379
Or you'll what?

04:10:46.500 --> 04:10:48.659
Lady Scarab demanded.

04:10:48.719 --> 04:10:53.040
Oh no, whispered a hive wing standing

04:10:53.040 --> 04:10:53.700
near cricket.

04:10:53.760 --> 04:10:56.219
Do you think she's going to do that smell

04:10:56.219 --> 04:10:56.879
thing?

04:10:56.879 --> 04:10:58.079
whispered another.

04:10:58.200 --> 04:10:59.700
Her friend nodded.

04:10:59.819 --> 04:11:03.180
Come on, let's sneak out before it

04:11:03.180 --> 04:11:04.500
becomes unbearable up here.

04:11:04.559 --> 04:11:07.920
The 2 hive wings wove away toward the

04:11:07.920 --> 04:11:08.760
ramps in a hurry.

04:11:08.819 --> 04:11:11.819
Cricket saw a crimson dragon by the food

04:11:11.819 --> 04:11:14.760
table, probably the host, glanced

04:11:14.760 --> 04:11:16.500
despairingly around as a few others

04:11:16.500 --> 04:11:17.639
sidled off too.

04:11:17.700 --> 04:11:19.860
Who else is here?

04:11:19.920 --> 04:11:21.299
The queen demanded.

04:11:21.360 --> 04:11:23.700
A young friend of mine?

04:11:23.760 --> 04:11:25.559
Lady Scarab snapped.

04:11:25.620 --> 04:11:28.500
She's asleep, like a sensible dragon.

04:11:28.559 --> 04:11:31.260
So take your goons and shut up and go

04:11:31.260 --> 04:11:31.440
away.

04:11:31.500 --> 04:11:34.920
Small gasps sounded from around the

04:11:34.920 --> 04:11:35.280
party.

04:11:35.340 --> 04:11:37.799
And cricket saw one silk wing

04:11:37.799 --> 04:11:39.719
accidentally drop her glass with a tiny

04:11:39.719 --> 04:11:40.200
smash.

04:11:40.260 --> 04:11:42.600
Bring her out.

04:11:42.659 --> 04:11:44.399
Wasp.

04:11:44.459 --> 04:11:46.020
She's none of your concern.

04:11:46.079 --> 04:11:48.780
Surely you have more important things to

04:11:48.780 --> 04:11:49.020
do.

04:11:49.079 --> 04:11:51.000
Just leave her be.

04:11:51.120 --> 04:11:54.479
The wide-eyed soldier hissed and lashed

04:11:54.479 --> 04:11:54.840
his tail.

04:11:54.899 --> 04:11:58.260
Prove to me she's not the traitor we're

04:11:58.260 --> 04:11:58.559
looking for.

04:11:58.620 --> 04:12:00.840
She is not.

04:12:00.959 --> 04:12:03.719
Scarab snapped exasperated.

04:12:03.780 --> 04:12:07.260
Haven't you taken enough from me, WASP?

04:12:07.379 --> 04:12:09.959
This dragon has done you no harm.

04:12:10.079 --> 04:12:12.780
Scarab is arguing with her.

04:12:12.840 --> 04:12:15.780
Cricket suddenly realized with a jolt.

04:12:15.840 --> 04:12:18.659
She's arguing with Queen Wasp.

04:12:18.719 --> 04:12:20.340
She's saying no to her.

04:12:20.399 --> 04:12:23.520
Queen Wasp wouldn't cause a scene like

04:12:23.520 --> 04:12:25.020
this if she could avoid it.

04:12:25.079 --> 04:12:29.100
That must mean, she can't control Lady

04:12:29.100 --> 04:12:29.760
Scarab.

04:12:29.819 --> 04:12:31.440
Scarab is like me.

04:12:31.500 --> 04:12:33.840
She's free from the mind control.

04:12:33.899 --> 04:12:37.379
Who is in there, scarab?

04:12:37.440 --> 04:12:38.639
The queen demanded.

04:12:38.700 --> 04:12:41.760
All of the soldiers' eyes turned white.

04:12:41.819 --> 04:12:44.520
The party suddenly went very quiet behind

04:12:44.520 --> 04:12:45.120
cricket.

04:12:45.180 --> 04:12:46.920
Uh-oh.

04:12:46.979 --> 04:12:49.979
She darted a glance sideways.

04:12:50.040 --> 04:12:52.440
The hive wing beside her had white eyes

04:12:52.440 --> 04:12:52.860
as well.

04:12:52.920 --> 04:12:55.739
Cricket guessed everyone at the party had

04:12:55.739 --> 04:12:56.219
been taken over.

04:12:56.280 --> 04:12:59.340
The silkwings were still murmuring to one

04:12:59.340 --> 04:13:02.219
another, but their voices slowly faded to

04:13:02.219 --> 04:13:02.579
silence.

04:13:02.639 --> 04:13:06.420
Cricket kept her head down, hoping her

04:13:06.420 --> 04:13:08.159
eyes were hidden by the folds of the blue

04:13:08.159 --> 04:13:09.479
veil around her horns.

04:13:09.540 --> 04:13:12.479
All the hive wings had their heads turned

04:13:12.479 --> 04:13:16.200
toward scarab's house, alert, and coiled

04:13:16.200 --> 04:13:17.459
like angry snakes.

04:13:17.520 --> 04:13:21.239
So far, they were a threat, not yet a

04:13:21.239 --> 04:13:21.840
weapon.

04:13:21.899 --> 04:13:25.620
As long as she stayed still, with luck, no

04:13:25.620 --> 04:13:26.940
one would look closer at her.

04:13:27.000 --> 04:13:30.719
Her heart constricted, eating all the air

04:13:30.719 --> 04:13:31.379
in her chest.

04:13:31.440 --> 04:13:35.159
You stay out of my house, wasp.

04:13:35.159 --> 04:13:37.500
Lady Scarab said furiously.

04:13:37.559 --> 04:13:40.860
You have no right to poke your snout in.

04:13:40.860 --> 04:13:42.840
I have every right.

04:13:42.899 --> 04:13:44.700
I am your queen.

04:13:44.760 --> 04:13:47.940
The voice came from all the hive wings on

04:13:47.940 --> 04:13:48.540
the street now.

04:13:48.600 --> 04:13:51.299
It was chilling to hear it so close.

04:13:51.360 --> 04:13:54.000
The breath of all the stolen guests

04:13:54.000 --> 04:13:56.399
shivering across cricket's wings.

04:13:56.459 --> 04:14:00.479
On scarab's steps, 2 of the hive wings

04:14:00.479 --> 04:14:03.120
stepped forward, and menacing stingers

04:14:03.120 --> 04:14:05.040
slid out from under their claws.

04:14:05.100 --> 04:14:08.700
You're a creepy old bat.

04:14:08.760 --> 04:14:09.659
Scarab shouted.

04:14:09.719 --> 04:14:12.120
Your mother would hate to see what you've

04:14:12.120 --> 04:14:12.959
done with her tribe.

04:14:13.020 --> 04:14:16.799
Lucky for us that she's dead then.

04:14:16.920 --> 04:14:20.399
Scarab hissed at the stingers reaching

04:14:20.399 --> 04:14:20.760
toward her.

04:14:20.819 --> 04:14:24.239
Suddenly, the soldiers staggered back

04:14:24.239 --> 04:14:25.440
their eyes watering.

04:14:25.500 --> 04:14:27.959
All the dragons on her front steps

04:14:27.959 --> 04:14:29.100
covered their snouts.

04:14:29.159 --> 04:14:31.260
A moment later.

04:14:31.379 --> 04:14:33.600
The smell rolled over the party.

04:14:33.659 --> 04:14:36.540
Cricket had heard of dragons with

04:14:36.540 --> 04:14:39.420
scarab's power, and she'd even smelled a

04:14:39.420 --> 04:14:41.760
fraction of it once, when Scarab was

04:14:41.760 --> 04:14:43.799
annoyed by some dragonettes in her way at

04:14:43.799 --> 04:14:44.159
the market.

04:14:44.219 --> 04:14:47.340
But this had to be the full force

04:14:47.340 --> 04:14:50.219
weaponized version of it, like dead

04:14:50.219 --> 04:14:52.739
rotting things pickled in sulfur.

04:14:52.799 --> 04:14:55.079
It made her want to claw off her own

04:14:55.079 --> 04:14:55.379
nose.

04:14:55.440 --> 04:14:58.620
She saw the white eyes flicker out of the

04:14:58.620 --> 04:14:59.280
faces around her.

04:14:59.340 --> 04:15:02.100
She guessed the queen couldn't stand to

04:15:02.100 --> 04:15:03.840
experience it through so many dragons.

04:15:03.959 --> 04:15:07.139
Several of the party guests dropped their

04:15:07.139 --> 04:15:08.459
drinks and ran for the stairs.

04:15:08.579 --> 04:15:12.540
I will come here and kill you myself if I

04:15:12.540 --> 04:15:13.979
have to.

04:15:14.100 --> 04:15:15.959
Wasp snarled from one of the soldiers

04:15:15.959 --> 04:15:16.559
mouths.

04:15:16.620 --> 04:15:20.459
Ha, said Lady Scarab, doing your own

04:15:20.459 --> 04:15:21.239
dirty work.

04:15:21.299 --> 04:15:23.459
Doesn't sound like you wasp.

04:15:23.579 --> 04:15:25.500
Lady scarab.

04:15:25.559 --> 04:15:28.680
Cricket felt cracked shiver across her

04:15:28.680 --> 04:15:29.100
heart.

04:15:29.159 --> 04:15:33.180
Katy did had appeared beside scarab

04:15:33.180 --> 04:15:35.040
touching the older dragon's shoulder

04:15:35.040 --> 04:15:35.459
gently.

04:15:35.520 --> 04:15:38.280
Scarab's wings drooped.

04:15:38.340 --> 04:15:39.959
Idiot child.

04:15:40.079 --> 04:15:42.239
I could have kept you safe.

04:15:42.299 --> 04:15:45.120
I don't want you to get in trouble for me

04:15:45.120 --> 04:15:46.680
Katie did said.

04:15:46.739 --> 04:15:48.540
There's no reason to.

04:15:48.600 --> 04:15:50.280
I haven't done anything wrong.

04:15:50.340 --> 04:15:53.520
I'll come with you willingly, she said to

04:15:53.520 --> 04:15:53.940
the guards.

04:15:54.000 --> 04:15:55.559
Hmm.

04:15:55.680 --> 04:15:58.799
Familiar, but not the dragon I'm looking

04:15:58.799 --> 04:15:59.100
for.

04:15:59.159 --> 04:16:02.940
What an interesting mystery, said the

04:16:02.940 --> 04:16:03.299
queen.

04:16:03.360 --> 04:16:06.479
Some relation to my missing friend, I'm

04:16:06.479 --> 04:16:06.780
guessing.

04:16:06.840 --> 04:16:11.340
Lady Scarab only glared at her, but Katy

04:16:11.340 --> 04:16:12.719
did dropped her gaze to her feet.

04:16:12.780 --> 04:16:17.459
Well, said the queen, perhaps we can find

04:16:17.459 --> 04:16:18.360
a use for her.

04:16:18.420 --> 04:16:22.379
Katy did, looked up again, and her eyes

04:16:22.379 --> 04:16:24.840
were blank as the faces of the moon's

04:16:24.840 --> 04:16:28.200
empty, like the husks of spider eaten

04:16:28.200 --> 04:16:28.680
grubs.

04:16:28.799 --> 04:16:33.479
Nice try, lady scarab, the queen said

04:16:33.479 --> 04:16:36.780
with Katy did's mouth, Katy did's voice

04:16:36.780 --> 04:16:38.520
Katy did's mind.

04:16:38.579 --> 04:16:41.819
I'm sure I'll be seeing you again soon.

04:16:41.879 --> 04:16:44.940
And then Katy did stepped out of the

04:16:44.940 --> 04:16:47.399
house, joined the group of high wing

04:16:47.399 --> 04:16:49.200
soldiers, and marched away.

04:16:49.260 --> 04:16:53.940
Chapter 14.

04:16:54.120 --> 04:16:57.840
Lady Scarab slammed the door of her

04:16:57.840 --> 04:17:00.299
mansion hard enough to make the firefly

04:17:00.299 --> 04:17:02.520
lanterns rattle all over the courtyard

04:17:02.520 --> 04:17:03.000
down the street.

04:17:03.120 --> 04:17:06.239
The trio of Silk Wings quickly started

04:17:06.239 --> 04:17:08.639
the music again, and the babble of

04:17:08.639 --> 04:17:11.760
conversation rose, a little strained, and

04:17:11.760 --> 04:17:13.440
a little higher pitched than before.

04:17:13.500 --> 04:17:16.920
A few more guests made excuses to the

04:17:16.920 --> 04:17:19.559
host, who was stirring a pale green tea

04:17:19.559 --> 04:17:22.559
dejectedly, and vanished toward the ramps

04:17:22.559 --> 04:17:25.200
to find safer, better smelling parties.

04:17:25.260 --> 04:17:29.219
Sundew came up beside cricket, twitching

04:17:29.219 --> 04:17:30.780
her cape a little closer around her.

04:17:30.840 --> 04:17:34.260
I don't understand how you all live like

04:17:34.260 --> 04:17:36.059
this, she whispered.

04:17:36.120 --> 04:17:39.299
We don't have a choice, Cricket whispered

04:17:39.299 --> 04:17:39.659
back.

04:17:39.719 --> 04:17:42.540
But did you see Scarab fighting back?

04:17:42.600 --> 04:17:44.879
Don't you think she must be like me?

04:17:44.940 --> 04:17:47.700
Maybe she knows how the mind control

04:17:47.700 --> 04:17:48.120
works.

04:17:48.180 --> 04:17:49.920
And if she does.

04:17:49.979 --> 04:17:52.860
Maybe she can help me save Katy did.

04:17:52.920 --> 04:17:55.379
That's the only thing I can do.

04:17:55.440 --> 04:17:58.860
There's no way to rescue Katie did, unless

04:17:58.860 --> 04:18:00.540
I can free her from the mind control.

04:18:00.600 --> 04:18:02.280
Oh no.

04:18:02.340 --> 04:18:04.920
Sundew muttered, you want to go over

04:18:04.920 --> 04:18:07.440
there, to the house your queen literally

04:18:07.440 --> 04:18:08.340
just rated.

04:18:08.399 --> 04:18:11.159
So she's hardly likely to come back right

04:18:11.159 --> 04:18:12.180
away, right?

04:18:12.239 --> 04:18:13.500
Cricket said.

04:18:13.559 --> 04:18:16.620
Sundoo shook her head and moved to one of

04:18:16.620 --> 04:18:19.500
the bowls, scooping a dark purple liquid

04:18:19.500 --> 04:18:21.959
out of it, and sniffing it suspiciously.

04:18:22.139 --> 04:18:23.819
I should go find my parents.

04:18:23.879 --> 04:18:26.459
I have to tell them that our plan didn't

04:18:26.459 --> 04:18:26.639
work.

04:18:26.700 --> 04:18:28.139
She sighed.

04:18:28.200 --> 04:18:31.079
The chrysalis knew nothing helpful about

04:18:31.079 --> 04:18:33.780
the mind control, nor did they seem like

04:18:33.780 --> 04:18:36.659
particularly useful allies, but I'll ask

04:18:36.659 --> 04:18:38.459
Belladonna what she wants me to do with

04:18:38.459 --> 04:18:38.639
them.

04:18:38.700 --> 04:18:42.719
Wait, Cricket said, feeling a surge of

04:18:42.719 --> 04:18:43.139
panic.

04:18:43.200 --> 04:18:46.139
Send you, please, we still have until

04:18:46.139 --> 04:18:46.620
sunset.

04:18:46.680 --> 04:18:47.760
Don't go yet.

04:18:47.819 --> 04:18:50.819
Give me the rest of today to try to find

04:18:50.819 --> 04:18:51.479
some answers.

04:18:51.540 --> 04:18:55.440
The party host advanced and perfume, and

04:18:55.440 --> 04:18:57.780
was wandering the courtyard, trying to

04:18:57.780 --> 04:18:59.520
inconspicuously spritz it everywhere.

04:18:59.639 --> 04:19:02.280
Sundew wrinkled her snout at him.

04:19:02.340 --> 04:19:03.540
Fine.

04:19:03.600 --> 04:19:07.079
You can try, she whispered, but don't get

04:19:07.079 --> 04:19:07.799
your hopes up.

04:19:07.860 --> 04:19:10.260
And you can't take Blue to Scarab's house

04:19:10.260 --> 04:19:10.559
with you.

04:19:10.620 --> 04:19:12.959
We don't know if we can trust that old

04:19:12.959 --> 04:19:15.479
hive wing, and he's too valuable to

04:19:15.479 --> 04:19:16.020
risk.

04:19:16.079 --> 04:19:19.620
Blue protested, but Cricket agreed with

04:19:19.620 --> 04:19:19.799
her.

04:19:19.860 --> 04:19:22.440
She didn't know how Lady Scarab would

04:19:22.440 --> 04:19:25.139
react to blue. or how she felt about silk

04:19:25.139 --> 04:19:25.799
wings in general.

04:19:25.920 --> 04:19:28.680
She was the only wealthy high wing

04:19:28.680 --> 04:19:31.020
cricket knew of who had no silk wing

04:19:31.020 --> 04:19:31.500
servants.

04:19:31.559 --> 04:19:34.379
Cricket got the impression she disliked

04:19:34.379 --> 04:19:36.420
them only about as much as she disliked

04:19:36.420 --> 04:19:39.360
all dragons, but Lady Scarab was very

04:19:39.360 --> 04:19:41.819
unpredictable, and Cricket didn't want to

04:19:41.819 --> 04:19:42.959
put blue in any danger.

04:19:43.020 --> 04:19:45.840
All right, she whispered.

04:19:45.959 --> 04:19:48.059
If I don't come back before the party

04:19:48.059 --> 04:19:48.659
ends.

04:19:48.719 --> 04:19:50.879
Meet me at the statue in the glitter

04:19:50.879 --> 04:19:51.299
bazaar.

04:19:51.360 --> 04:19:54.479
She turned and touched one of Blue's

04:19:54.479 --> 04:19:56.760
talons lightly with hers, wishing she

04:19:56.760 --> 04:19:58.979
could hug him, but not sure whether the

04:19:58.979 --> 04:20:00.360
rules could bend quite that far.

04:20:00.420 --> 04:20:04.920
Be careful, he said softly, as she

04:20:04.920 --> 04:20:05.520
slipped away.

04:20:05.579 --> 04:20:08.639
The guests who remained were valiantly

04:20:08.639 --> 04:20:10.799
trying to ignore Lady Scarab's residence

04:20:10.799 --> 04:20:13.079
and the odor that still lingered around

04:20:13.079 --> 04:20:13.500
it.

04:20:13.559 --> 04:20:16.559
Still, Cricket was afraid that knocking

04:20:16.559 --> 04:20:18.420
on the front door might catch the

04:20:18.420 --> 04:20:21.299
attention of the more gossipy dragons, so

04:20:21.299 --> 04:20:22.620
she tried walking in the opposite

04:20:22.620 --> 04:20:24.600
direction, and circling through the

04:20:24.600 --> 04:20:26.940
streets until she reached the side of the

04:20:26.940 --> 04:20:29.579
mansion, where a smaller door was set

04:20:29.579 --> 04:20:30.180
into the wall.

04:20:30.239 --> 04:20:34.020
She knocked nervously, and stood for a

04:20:34.020 --> 04:20:37.020
long, anxious moment, gazing up at the

04:20:37.020 --> 04:20:39.239
weathered tree stuff that formed the

04:20:39.239 --> 04:20:40.559
outside of the mansion.

04:20:40.620 --> 04:20:44.219
Most wealthy dragons, kept their homes

04:20:44.219 --> 04:20:46.799
neatly maintained, and constantly updated

04:20:46.799 --> 04:20:48.059
with new features.

04:20:48.120 --> 04:20:51.600
But the green jade beetles inlaid in even

04:20:51.600 --> 04:20:53.940
rows, looked as though they had been put

04:20:53.940 --> 04:20:54.840
in decades ago.

04:20:54.899 --> 04:20:57.420
Maybe when the house was 1st built.

04:20:57.479 --> 04:20:59.700
Some of them were even missing.

04:20:59.760 --> 04:21:01.979
Although Cricket couldn't tell whether

04:21:01.979 --> 04:21:04.620
they'd been pried loose and stolen, or

04:21:04.620 --> 04:21:06.600
whether they had fallen out, and nobody

04:21:06.600 --> 04:21:07.260
cared.

04:21:07.319 --> 04:21:10.379
The door swung open abruptly, making

04:21:10.379 --> 04:21:11.280
cricket jump.

04:21:11.340 --> 04:21:15.780
No, Lady Scarab barked. and slammed the

04:21:15.780 --> 04:21:16.440
door shut again.

04:21:16.559 --> 04:21:17.940
Wait.

04:21:18.000 --> 04:21:19.920
Cricket knocked more firmly.

04:21:19.979 --> 04:21:22.620
Lady Scarab, wait.

04:21:22.739 --> 04:21:26.100
The door flew open mid knock, and Cricket

04:21:26.100 --> 04:21:28.020
nearly wrapped the elderly dragon on the

04:21:28.020 --> 04:21:28.260
nose.

04:21:28.319 --> 04:21:30.659
Go away.

04:21:30.780 --> 04:21:32.639
Lady Scarab shouted.

04:21:32.700 --> 04:21:33.899
It's me.

04:21:33.959 --> 04:21:36.899
Cricket said quickly, shoving her veil

04:21:36.899 --> 04:21:38.340
aside to reveal her face.

04:21:38.399 --> 04:21:40.620
Please, lady scarab.

04:21:40.680 --> 04:21:44.940
Oh, by all the stupid moons, scarab

04:21:44.940 --> 04:21:45.540
growled.

04:21:45.600 --> 04:21:47.760
She grabbed Cricket by one of the scarves

04:21:47.760 --> 04:21:50.940
and yanked her inside, almost throttling

04:21:50.940 --> 04:21:51.659
her in the process.

04:21:51.719 --> 04:21:54.840
Cricket stumbled into a poorly lit

04:21:54.840 --> 04:21:56.940
kitchen, bare and cold.

04:21:57.000 --> 04:21:59.940
One flame silk lamp sat alone on the

04:21:59.940 --> 04:22:03.059
central table, its light dim, as though

04:22:03.059 --> 04:22:05.040
the thread had almost faded completely.

04:22:05.159 --> 04:22:09.059
Next to it were 2 plates, neatly stacked

04:22:09.059 --> 04:22:11.639
and a small glass jar of pale lavender

04:22:11.639 --> 04:22:12.540
sugar cubes.

04:22:12.600 --> 04:22:15.059
In the sink, she spotted the bones of a

04:22:15.059 --> 04:22:17.219
bird, but there was no other food in

04:22:17.219 --> 04:22:17.520
sight.

04:22:17.639 --> 04:22:19.500
The walls were empty.

04:22:19.559 --> 04:22:22.379
Except for 2 small paintings on either

04:22:22.379 --> 04:22:26.219
side of the stove, one, a lemon tree, the

04:22:26.219 --> 04:22:29.340
other, an orange tree, trees?

04:22:29.399 --> 04:22:31.739
Cricket thought, startled.

04:22:31.799 --> 04:22:34.079
No one was allowed to make art with trees

04:22:34.079 --> 04:22:36.959
in it, no one was allowed to have art

04:22:36.959 --> 04:22:37.920
with trees in it.

04:22:38.040 --> 04:22:41.940
She squinted at them and saw the spidery

04:22:41.940 --> 04:22:43.260
cracks in the canvas.

04:22:43.319 --> 04:22:46.260
Maybe they were quite old, from before

04:22:46.260 --> 04:22:48.059
the laws about trees and art.

04:22:48.120 --> 04:22:51.360
Still, it was bold of scarab to have kept

04:22:51.360 --> 04:22:51.600
them.

04:22:51.659 --> 04:22:54.540
Come on, you nuisance.

04:22:54.659 --> 04:22:57.659
Scarab muttered, grabbing the lamp and

04:22:57.659 --> 04:22:59.399
stomping past cricket into the next

04:22:59.399 --> 04:22:59.639
room.

04:22:59.700 --> 04:23:03.239
This one was much bigger, reaching all

04:23:03.239 --> 04:23:04.920
the way to the back wall of the mansion

04:23:04.920 --> 04:23:07.739
where tall sliding glass doors led to a

04:23:07.739 --> 04:23:10.020
balcony, overlooking the moonlit

04:23:10.020 --> 04:23:10.500
savannah.

04:23:10.559 --> 04:23:13.799
Perhaps it had been a ballroom once, or

04:23:13.799 --> 04:23:15.600
at least intended for hosting grand

04:23:15.600 --> 04:23:16.200
parties.

04:23:16.260 --> 04:23:18.899
But now it felt like a giant empty

04:23:18.899 --> 04:23:22.020
terrarium, with only one seed rattling

04:23:22.020 --> 04:23:22.739
around inside it.

04:23:22.860 --> 04:23:26.819
It was also cold and sparsely decorated

04:23:26.819 --> 04:23:29.459
especially for a dragon who seemed as

04:23:29.459 --> 04:23:30.959
rich as Lady Scarab.

04:23:31.020 --> 04:23:34.200
A polished old wood bookcase filled the

04:23:34.200 --> 04:23:37.079
opposite wall, lined with books that

04:23:37.079 --> 04:23:38.520
looked as though they might crumble if

04:23:38.520 --> 04:23:39.420
you actually touched them.

04:23:39.540 --> 04:23:42.959
One dark green floor pillow was set by

04:23:42.959 --> 04:23:45.299
the balcony doors, as though the only

04:23:45.299 --> 04:23:47.819
place she wanted to sit was near the exit

04:23:47.819 --> 04:23:49.260
with a view of the stars.

04:23:49.319 --> 04:23:52.559
Lady Scarab set the lamp on the low table

04:23:52.559 --> 04:23:55.440
and sat down on the pillow, leaving

04:23:55.440 --> 04:23:57.479
Cricket standing awkwardly in the middle

04:23:57.479 --> 04:23:57.899
of the room.

04:23:57.959 --> 04:24:02.280
Well, the old dragon demanded.

04:24:02.340 --> 04:24:06.059
After all this trouble, at least tell me

04:24:06.059 --> 04:24:06.899
you brought the book.

04:24:06.959 --> 04:24:09.420
Surprised, cricket said.

04:24:09.479 --> 04:24:11.579
My friend has it.

04:24:11.639 --> 04:24:13.020
What do you know about the book?

04:24:13.079 --> 04:24:18.000
Not enough, Lady Scarab growled.

04:24:18.059 --> 04:24:20.639
I wanted to get my claws on it for

04:24:20.639 --> 04:24:20.940
years.

04:24:21.000 --> 04:24:23.280
I assume you read it.

04:24:23.340 --> 04:24:24.719
What happens next?

04:24:24.780 --> 04:24:28.559
Say the words, wasp dies slowly and

04:24:28.559 --> 04:24:30.780
horribly, and I'll make you my heir.

04:24:30.840 --> 04:24:33.059
Cricket was startled into almost

04:24:33.059 --> 04:24:33.659
laughing.

04:24:33.719 --> 04:24:38.520
No, no, she said, recovering quickly.

04:24:38.579 --> 04:24:39.959
It's not like that.

04:24:40.020 --> 04:24:42.540
That's the thing.

04:24:42.600 --> 04:24:44.760
There are no more predictions in it.

04:24:44.819 --> 04:24:47.819
Clearside only saw a few 100 years into

04:24:47.819 --> 04:24:48.360
the future.

04:24:48.420 --> 04:24:50.219
There's nothing about now.

04:24:50.280 --> 04:24:53.280
Nothing about the last 1000 years.

04:24:53.340 --> 04:24:56.100
Queen Wasp has been lying to us.

04:24:56.159 --> 04:25:00.059
Lady Scarab's eyes were like small, dark

04:25:00.059 --> 04:25:03.239
coals, with flickers of dark red in their

04:25:03.239 --> 04:25:03.719
depths.

04:25:03.719 --> 04:25:06.719
Those eyes pinned cricket to the bare

04:25:06.719 --> 04:25:09.719
floor for a long, agonizing moment.

04:25:09.780 --> 04:25:11.760
What?

04:25:11.760 --> 04:25:13.559
Scarab spat.

04:25:13.620 --> 04:25:16.379
The tree wars were all a lie.

04:25:16.440 --> 04:25:18.059
Clearsight never saw that.

04:25:18.120 --> 04:25:21.059
The silkwing queen giving up her throne

04:25:21.059 --> 04:25:23.280
so her tribe would bow to Queen Wasp.

04:25:23.280 --> 04:25:25.440
That wasn't in there either.

04:25:25.500 --> 04:25:29.159
Scarab breathed deeply in and out through

04:25:29.159 --> 04:25:29.579
her nose.

04:25:29.639 --> 04:25:33.840
I suppose, she said icily.

04:25:33.899 --> 04:25:36.899
There wasn't a list of the hive wing

04:25:36.899 --> 04:25:38.459
queen succession line either.

04:25:38.520 --> 04:25:42.840
No, Cricket said.

04:25:42.899 --> 04:25:44.100
What's that?

04:25:44.159 --> 04:25:46.620
A list.

04:25:46.680 --> 04:25:47.879
Allegedly?

04:25:48.000 --> 04:25:50.280
Of who should be queen, and who should

04:25:50.280 --> 04:25:50.940
succeed her?

04:25:51.000 --> 04:25:53.940
From Clearside's time all the way until

04:25:53.940 --> 04:25:54.360
now.

04:25:54.420 --> 04:25:58.379
Lady Scarab let out her breath again in a

04:25:58.379 --> 04:25:59.700
long hiss through her teeth.

04:25:59.760 --> 04:26:03.000
So my mother was lying about the book

04:26:03.000 --> 04:26:03.239
too.

04:26:03.360 --> 04:26:05.700
And so was my sister.

04:26:05.760 --> 04:26:10.139
Both lying, in fact, about the fact that

04:26:10.139 --> 04:26:12.180
my sister cochineal had to be queen.

04:26:12.239 --> 04:26:16.079
I suppose mother realized she was always

04:26:16.079 --> 04:26:18.299
a much better liar than I was.

04:26:18.360 --> 04:26:21.239
The most essential quality for a queen

04:26:21.239 --> 04:26:23.399
who had to rule by deceiving her entire

04:26:23.399 --> 04:26:26.219
tribe about their most sacred artifact.

04:26:26.280 --> 04:26:30.059
What a lovely, lovely royal family we

04:26:30.059 --> 04:26:30.239
are.

04:26:30.299 --> 04:26:33.659
She picked up a paintbrush from a tray

04:26:33.659 --> 04:26:36.000
beside the pillow, and Cricket realized

04:26:36.000 --> 04:26:38.219
there was a small easel there as well.

04:26:38.280 --> 04:26:41.579
The half finished painting, as far as she

04:26:41.579 --> 04:26:44.459
could see, was of a wasp, being eaten by

04:26:44.459 --> 04:26:45.180
ants.

04:26:45.239 --> 04:26:46.440
She shivered.

04:26:46.559 --> 04:26:50.280
Lady Scarab shoved her spectacles higher

04:26:50.280 --> 04:26:52.860
up her nose and squinted at cricket.

04:26:52.920 --> 04:26:55.799
The queen would very much like to kill

04:26:55.799 --> 04:26:56.940
you, you know.

04:26:57.000 --> 04:26:58.200
Tell me.

04:26:58.260 --> 04:27:01.200
Why aren't you hiding in some distant

04:27:01.200 --> 04:27:02.159
corner of the continent?

04:27:02.280 --> 04:27:05.940
I have some questions, Cricket said.

04:27:06.000 --> 04:27:07.559
Ah.

04:27:07.920 --> 04:27:09.780
Lady Scarab interrupted.

04:27:09.840 --> 04:27:11.159
Curiosity.

04:27:11.219 --> 04:27:13.440
That never ends badly.

04:27:13.500 --> 04:27:14.760
Carry on.

04:27:14.819 --> 04:27:18.600
The queen can't mind control me, Cricket

04:27:18.600 --> 04:27:19.139
blurted.

04:27:19.200 --> 04:27:22.319
Yes, said Lady Scarab.

04:27:22.379 --> 04:27:25.440
I gathered that from the you not marching

04:27:25.440 --> 04:27:26.940
yourself off to jail right now.

04:27:27.000 --> 04:27:28.620
But why?

04:27:28.680 --> 04:27:31.440
Why can't the queen mind control you?

04:27:31.559 --> 04:27:32.520
Cricket asked.

04:27:32.579 --> 04:27:33.659
Or me?

04:27:33.719 --> 04:27:35.760
I have no idea.

04:27:35.879 --> 04:27:39.180
Lady Scarab waved the paintbrush at

04:27:39.180 --> 04:27:39.479
cricket.

04:27:39.540 --> 04:27:41.399
Next question.

04:27:41.459 --> 04:27:44.100
How can you have no idea?

04:27:44.159 --> 04:27:45.479
Cricket asked.

04:27:45.540 --> 04:27:46.920
Don't you know how it works?

04:27:46.979 --> 04:27:50.760
Apparently, I am not among those blessed

04:27:50.760 --> 04:27:53.040
with the secrets of my noble family.

04:27:53.100 --> 04:27:55.559
Lady Scarab snarked.

04:27:55.620 --> 04:27:59.940
In any case, nobody knows why WASP can do

04:27:59.940 --> 04:28:00.600
what she does.

04:28:00.659 --> 04:28:03.420
No other dragon has ever done it before.

04:28:03.479 --> 04:28:05.100
Ever?

04:28:05.159 --> 04:28:06.540
Cricket echoed.

04:28:06.659 --> 04:28:09.000
In all of Penthalen history?

04:28:09.059 --> 04:28:10.379
Are you sure?

04:28:10.440 --> 04:28:13.620
Of course, I'm sure.

04:28:13.680 --> 04:28:17.100
The Royal Hivewing stabbed her paintbrush

04:28:17.100 --> 04:28:19.379
into a puddle of red paint and started

04:28:19.379 --> 04:28:22.079
adding thin lines of blood coming out of

04:28:22.079 --> 04:28:23.159
the wasp in her painting.

04:28:23.219 --> 04:28:26.040
Cricket had a feeling this particular

04:28:26.040 --> 04:28:29.040
piece of art might be even more poorly

04:28:29.040 --> 04:28:30.659
received than the trees in the kitchen.

04:28:30.719 --> 04:28:33.659
I've got history books going back

04:28:33.659 --> 04:28:34.379
centuries.

04:28:34.440 --> 04:28:37.680
I've traced the family trees as far out

04:28:37.680 --> 04:28:38.219
as I can.

04:28:38.280 --> 04:28:41.819
Not a single hive wing with mind control

04:28:41.819 --> 04:28:45.659
powers, all the way back to Clearsight, as

04:28:45.659 --> 04:28:46.559
far as I could find.

04:28:46.680 --> 04:28:49.379
And it certainly didn't come from her

04:28:49.379 --> 04:28:50.700
silk wing husband's.

04:28:50.760 --> 04:28:52.559
Silkwing?

04:28:52.620 --> 04:28:55.500
Cricket said, extremely startled.

04:28:55.559 --> 04:28:57.000
Husbands?

04:28:57.059 --> 04:28:59.459
Yes, of course.

04:28:59.579 --> 04:29:01.079
Lady Scarab snapped.

04:29:01.139 --> 04:29:04.079
Maybe they weren't called silk wings back

04:29:04.079 --> 04:29:04.260
then.

04:29:04.319 --> 04:29:08.040
Shimmer Wings, or Flibberty Gibbets, or

04:29:08.040 --> 04:29:09.239
something in the old language.

04:29:09.299 --> 04:29:10.020
I don't know.

04:29:10.139 --> 04:29:12.479
But Clearsight married one.

04:29:12.540 --> 04:29:14.940
And then another one when the 1st one

04:29:14.940 --> 04:29:17.760
died, and had an alarming number of

04:29:17.760 --> 04:29:20.399
dragonettes with each one, and then their

04:29:20.399 --> 04:29:24.000
dragonettes, dragonettes kept going

04:29:24.000 --> 04:29:27.059
marrying ye old silk wings, or what have

04:29:27.059 --> 04:29:29.579
you, until there was enough of them to be

04:29:29.579 --> 04:29:31.079
considered their own tribe.

04:29:31.200 --> 04:29:33.059
Hive wings.

04:29:33.180 --> 04:29:36.420
Stupid, menacing name, if you ask me.

04:29:36.540 --> 04:29:40.860
It was only about 500 years ago that we

04:29:40.860 --> 04:29:42.959
officially split into 2 separate tribes

04:29:42.959 --> 04:29:43.319
you know.

04:29:43.379 --> 04:29:47.340
My charming great great grandmother was

04:29:47.340 --> 04:29:49.860
the queen who ordered no more mingling of

04:29:49.860 --> 04:29:50.520
the bloodlines.

04:29:50.579 --> 04:29:52.979
She was a nightmare.

04:29:53.040 --> 04:29:56.459
We're related to Silk Wings?

04:29:56.520 --> 04:29:57.719
Cricket said again.

04:29:57.780 --> 04:29:58.799
Really?

04:29:58.860 --> 04:30:01.920
Mighty scarab squinted at her with

04:30:01.920 --> 04:30:02.219
concern.

04:30:02.280 --> 04:30:04.379
Oh, dear.

04:30:04.440 --> 04:30:06.120
Are you thick?

04:30:06.120 --> 04:30:07.440
she asked.

04:30:07.500 --> 04:30:10.500
I thought Katie did, said you were rather

04:30:10.500 --> 04:30:10.920
clever.

04:30:11.040 --> 04:30:15.180
It is perfectly obvious that hive wings

04:30:15.180 --> 04:30:17.340
must have started with clear sight

04:30:17.340 --> 04:30:18.719
marrying a silk wing.

04:30:18.840 --> 04:30:21.899
Cricket did feel like rather an idiot.

04:30:21.959 --> 04:30:24.780
In her defense, history was the most

04:30:24.780 --> 04:30:27.719
neglected subject at Terrarium Academy.

04:30:27.959 --> 04:30:31.739
Well, she said indignantly, it is also

04:30:31.739 --> 04:30:34.440
perfectly obvious that hive wing books

04:30:34.440 --> 04:30:37.139
leave that out on purpose because they

04:30:37.139 --> 04:30:39.420
don't want any of us to know that.

04:30:39.479 --> 04:30:43.799
True, said Lady Scarab, settling back to

04:30:43.799 --> 04:30:46.500
her painting, which was getting Gorier by

04:30:46.500 --> 04:30:47.100
the moment.

04:30:47.159 --> 04:30:51.180
That was probably also my great great

04:30:51.180 --> 04:30:52.260
grandmother's idea.

04:30:52.319 --> 04:30:55.200
Ooh, she was a whore show.

04:30:55.260 --> 04:30:59.280
Did any of Clearsight's children inherit

04:30:59.280 --> 04:31:00.420
her prophecy powers?

04:31:00.479 --> 04:31:01.739
Cricket asked.

04:31:01.799 --> 04:31:03.719
She'd always wondered about that.

04:31:03.780 --> 04:31:06.840
Hivewings had all sorts of weird powers

04:31:06.840 --> 04:31:09.420
pop up throughout the tribe, but nothing

04:31:09.420 --> 04:31:10.680
like clear sights.

04:31:10.739 --> 04:31:13.440
The mind control had seemed the closest

04:31:13.440 --> 04:31:16.319
to her, being at least kind of mental.

04:31:16.440 --> 04:31:19.260
Not according to the records.

04:31:19.319 --> 04:31:21.719
Scarab coughed violently.

04:31:21.780 --> 04:31:26.280
But then, if I were clear sight, I tell

04:31:26.280 --> 04:31:28.079
my kids to keep that information to

04:31:28.079 --> 04:31:28.620
themselves.

04:31:28.739 --> 04:31:32.340
If you know the future, but no one else

04:31:32.340 --> 04:31:36.000
knows you know the future, you've got an

04:31:36.000 --> 04:31:37.020
advantage.

04:31:37.079 --> 04:31:37.379
See?

04:31:37.440 --> 04:31:38.819
Ha!

04:31:38.879 --> 04:31:41.579
She started coughing again, finally

04:31:41.579 --> 04:31:43.319
sputtering to a wheezing stop.

04:31:43.440 --> 04:31:46.860
Maybe I am related to my family after

04:31:46.860 --> 04:31:47.219
all.

04:31:47.280 --> 04:31:50.700
Crickets started to pace up and down the

04:31:50.700 --> 04:31:51.659
long empty room.

04:31:51.780 --> 04:31:54.360
Through the haze of drizzling rain

04:31:54.360 --> 04:31:54.899
outside.

04:31:54.959 --> 04:31:57.420
She thought she could see a faint line of

04:31:57.420 --> 04:31:59.639
gray along the horizon, which meant

04:31:59.639 --> 04:32:02.219
sunrise was coming, which meant sunset

04:32:02.219 --> 04:32:04.139
was getting ever closer.

04:32:04.200 --> 04:32:07.799
So why doesn't the mind control work on

04:32:07.799 --> 04:32:09.000
us, she said.

04:32:09.059 --> 04:32:10.319
Let's think.

04:32:10.379 --> 04:32:12.239
Do we have anything in common?

04:32:12.299 --> 04:32:14.700
Is there anyone else who's free of it?

04:32:14.760 --> 04:32:19.200
Wasps sisters, answered Lady Scarab.

04:32:19.260 --> 04:32:22.979
And Jewel, although a wasp has threatened

04:32:22.979 --> 04:32:23.819
her with it a few times.

04:32:23.879 --> 04:32:26.040
Threatened her with it?

04:32:26.100 --> 04:32:28.799
Cricket echoed, pausing for a moment.

04:32:28.860 --> 04:32:33.840
Like, she could mind control her, if she

04:32:33.840 --> 04:32:34.620
wanted to?

04:32:34.680 --> 04:32:37.559
Lady Scarab shrugged helpfully.

04:32:37.620 --> 04:32:41.219
Hmm, Cricket went back to pacing.

04:32:41.280 --> 04:32:44.159
Do you know anything about a home for old

04:32:44.159 --> 04:32:47.459
dragons in Setsy Hive, where they're kept

04:32:47.459 --> 04:32:49.020
because none of them are controllable?

04:32:49.079 --> 04:32:53.700
No, Lady Scarab said, narrowing her

04:32:53.700 --> 04:32:54.000
eyes.

04:32:54.059 --> 04:32:58.500
But I have noticed that I am the oldest

04:32:58.500 --> 04:32:59.639
dragon I know.

04:32:59.760 --> 04:33:04.080
All of my friends started dying off, or

04:33:04.080 --> 04:33:06.299
vanishing during the tree wars.

04:33:06.360 --> 04:33:10.020
Most of them were loudly against the war

04:33:10.020 --> 04:33:11.939
so I wasn't too surprised.

04:33:12.000 --> 04:33:17.040
But some of them went funny before they

04:33:17.040 --> 04:33:20.099
went, saying weird things that weren't

04:33:20.099 --> 04:33:20.819
like themselves.

04:33:20.880 --> 04:33:25.020
Strange flutters, like curtains in their

04:33:25.020 --> 04:33:25.259
eyes.

04:33:25.319 --> 04:33:28.439
Cricket tipped her head to the side.

04:33:28.500 --> 04:33:31.979
As though their eyes were flashing white

04:33:31.979 --> 04:33:33.180
then back to normal.

04:33:33.240 --> 04:33:35.400
Scarab nodded.

04:33:35.459 --> 04:33:38.279
I saw that happen to a dragon too.

04:33:38.400 --> 04:33:41.700
She described the dragon she'd seen out

04:33:41.700 --> 04:33:42.959
the window when she was two.

04:33:43.020 --> 04:33:47.580
Charming story, said Lady Scarab.

04:33:47.639 --> 04:33:50.279
She added some more red paint fountaining

04:33:50.279 --> 04:33:51.540
out of the wasp's head.

04:33:51.599 --> 04:33:56.039
Maybe what we saw, were wasps' experiments

04:33:56.039 --> 04:33:58.199
Crickets said slowly.

04:33:58.259 --> 04:34:01.859
Maybe she was testing out whether she

04:34:01.859 --> 04:34:04.259
could control those dragons, but she

04:34:04.259 --> 04:34:06.959
couldn't for some reason, or maybe she

04:34:06.959 --> 04:34:07.619
couldn't yet.

04:34:07.680 --> 04:34:10.319
Maybe her power was still getting

04:34:10.319 --> 04:34:11.520
stronger at that point.

04:34:11.639 --> 04:34:14.520
Makes no sense.

04:34:14.639 --> 04:34:17.340
Scarab jabbed the paintbrush at cricket

04:34:17.340 --> 04:34:17.700
again.

04:34:17.759 --> 04:34:20.759
Hive wings are born with their powers.

04:34:20.819 --> 04:34:23.580
They don't wander in 50 years later.

04:34:23.639 --> 04:34:27.299
Why couldn't she do any of this when she

04:34:27.299 --> 04:34:27.840
was younger?

04:34:27.900 --> 04:34:31.860
Those 40 or so blissful years before she

04:34:31.860 --> 04:34:32.819
became queen.

04:34:33.000 --> 04:34:36.479
Not that my sister was any picnic as a

04:34:36.479 --> 04:34:36.900
ruler.

04:34:36.959 --> 04:34:39.779
But at least she wasn't a dictatorial

04:34:39.779 --> 04:34:41.580
zombie making maniac.

04:34:41.639 --> 04:34:43.919
And why doesn't it work on us?

04:34:43.979 --> 04:34:45.599
Cricket said again.

04:34:45.659 --> 04:34:49.020
She sat down opposite Lady Scarab, and

04:34:49.020 --> 04:34:50.580
tried not to look at the painting of the

04:34:50.580 --> 04:34:53.220
dying wasp, which now looked as though it

04:34:53.220 --> 04:34:55.259
might drown in blood before the ants

04:34:55.259 --> 04:34:55.740
could eat it.

04:34:55.799 --> 04:34:59.520
I, I have one theory.

04:34:59.580 --> 04:35:01.319
About me anyway.

04:35:01.380 --> 04:35:05.099
I don't know if it's possible, but I

04:35:05.099 --> 04:35:06.419
wondered maybe.

04:35:06.419 --> 04:35:08.639
Spit it out?

04:35:08.700 --> 04:35:10.380
Lady Scarab ordered.

04:35:10.439 --> 04:35:13.559
Could I be half silkwing?

04:35:13.619 --> 04:35:14.639
Cricket asked.

04:35:14.700 --> 04:35:17.700
Katy did said my parents aren't my real

04:35:17.700 --> 04:35:20.759
parents, and so I thought, maybe one of

04:35:20.759 --> 04:35:23.759
my parents was a silk wing, and his blood

04:35:23.759 --> 04:35:26.459
or her blood, is why the mind control

04:35:26.459 --> 04:35:31.259
doesn't, no, Lady Scarab said, with a

04:35:31.259 --> 04:35:31.919
bitter little laugh.

04:35:31.979 --> 04:35:33.360
No?

04:35:33.419 --> 04:35:36.959
No, you're not half Silkwing.

04:35:37.020 --> 04:35:38.939
Cricket blinked.

04:35:39.000 --> 04:35:40.380
How do you know?

04:35:40.439 --> 04:35:42.239
Maybe you are too.

04:35:42.299 --> 04:35:45.659
Maybe that's, I am getting worried about

04:35:45.659 --> 04:35:47.159
your brain, Dragonette.

04:35:47.220 --> 04:35:49.860
I knew that school would be worthless for

04:35:49.860 --> 04:35:50.040
you.

04:35:50.159 --> 04:35:52.200
But I didn't think all your mental

04:35:52.200 --> 04:35:54.479
functions would atrophy so quickly.

04:35:54.540 --> 04:35:58.259
Lady Scarab set down the paintbrush, and

04:35:58.259 --> 04:36:00.900
clasped her front talons together, leaning

04:36:00.900 --> 04:36:01.979
toward cricket.

04:36:02.040 --> 04:36:05.520
I know you are not half Silkwing, because

04:36:05.520 --> 04:36:06.900
I know both your parents.

04:36:06.959 --> 04:36:09.840
And they are hive wings through and

04:36:09.840 --> 04:36:12.119
through, zombie eyes and all.

04:36:12.240 --> 04:36:14.099
You know them?

04:36:14.159 --> 04:36:17.099
Cricket cried, leaping to her feet.

04:36:17.159 --> 04:36:18.299
They're still alive?

04:36:18.360 --> 04:36:19.439
Who are they?

04:36:19.500 --> 04:36:21.299
Why didn't they keep me?

04:36:21.360 --> 04:36:25.319
One of them did, said Lady Scarab.

04:36:25.380 --> 04:36:28.139
She just couldn't tell anyone you were

04:36:28.139 --> 04:36:28.740
hers.

04:36:28.799 --> 04:36:31.680
I can't believe you haven't figured it

04:36:31.680 --> 04:36:32.639
out before now.

04:36:32.759 --> 04:36:36.179
Cricket felt as if the hive was falling

04:36:36.179 --> 04:36:40.619
in on her slowly, level by level, like in

04:36:40.619 --> 04:36:40.859
a dream.

04:36:40.979 --> 04:36:44.459
Katie did isn't your sister, little

04:36:44.459 --> 04:36:45.000
snail.

04:36:45.060 --> 04:36:46.619
She's your mother.

04:36:46.680 --> 04:36:51.180
Chapter 15.

04:36:51.599 --> 04:36:55.619
It felt like the entire world flipped

04:36:55.619 --> 04:36:55.919
over.

04:36:55.979 --> 04:36:58.560
It felt like someone picked up the hive

04:36:58.560 --> 04:37:01.380
turned it over, and shook it really hard

04:37:01.380 --> 04:37:05.279
until all the pieces fell out, except one

04:37:05.279 --> 04:37:07.740
and that one was the heart of

04:37:07.740 --> 04:37:08.099
everything.

04:37:08.159 --> 04:37:10.319
Haiti did.

04:37:10.380 --> 04:37:12.060
She said softly.

04:37:12.180 --> 04:37:13.619
My mother.

04:37:13.740 --> 04:37:16.020
Katy did is my mother.

04:37:16.080 --> 04:37:17.700
Katie did.

04:37:17.819 --> 04:37:20.819
I gather this is going to go on for a

04:37:20.819 --> 04:37:21.180
while.

04:37:21.240 --> 04:37:24.479
Scarab muttered, producing a new easel

04:37:24.479 --> 04:37:25.439
from behind the pillow.

04:37:25.500 --> 04:37:28.860
On this one, a horde of shiny green

04:37:28.860 --> 04:37:31.979
beetles was dragging a dying wasp into a

04:37:31.979 --> 04:37:34.740
dark hole, where little eyes and teeth

04:37:34.740 --> 04:37:36.240
glinted from the shadows.

04:37:36.360 --> 04:37:38.400
I wish she had told me.

04:37:38.459 --> 04:37:40.139
Why didn't she tell me?

04:37:40.200 --> 04:37:42.360
She knew I could keep a secret.

04:37:42.419 --> 04:37:45.659
Cricket flicked her tail back and forth.

04:37:45.720 --> 04:37:48.720
She just lied to me.

04:37:48.779 --> 04:37:51.599
Was she planning to hide the truth from

04:37:51.599 --> 04:37:52.379
me my whole life?

04:37:52.439 --> 04:37:56.279
Would it have made any difference, knowing

04:37:56.279 --> 04:37:56.639
the truth?

04:37:56.700 --> 04:37:59.099
Scarab asked sharply.

04:37:59.159 --> 04:38:01.680
Yes, Cricket said.

04:38:01.740 --> 04:38:04.020
It would have made everything make more

04:38:04.020 --> 04:38:04.860
sense.

04:38:04.919 --> 04:38:07.619
Well, all right, I would have had a few

04:38:07.619 --> 04:38:08.159
questions.

04:38:08.220 --> 04:38:09.779
Really?

04:38:09.840 --> 04:38:11.040
You.

04:38:11.040 --> 04:38:13.740
Ladies Scara raised her eyebrows.

04:38:13.799 --> 04:38:16.619
But at least it would have explained a

04:38:16.619 --> 04:38:17.459
whole lot of things.

04:38:17.520 --> 04:38:18.720
Oh.

04:38:18.779 --> 04:38:20.519
Oh.

04:38:20.639 --> 04:38:23.819
That's why mom, not mom.

04:38:23.880 --> 04:38:27.360
Cadell hates me, Cricket said.

04:38:27.419 --> 04:38:30.059
There were answers to all her

04:38:30.059 --> 04:38:32.699
unanswerable questions, the way her

04:38:32.699 --> 04:38:35.159
parents fought, why they barely looked at

04:38:35.159 --> 04:38:35.579
her.

04:38:35.639 --> 04:38:38.159
The reason Katy did always looked sad.

04:38:38.220 --> 04:38:41.880
That's why Katie did always took care of

04:38:41.880 --> 04:38:42.060
me.

04:38:42.180 --> 04:38:43.979
Oh my goodness.

04:38:44.040 --> 04:38:46.439
That's what Cadell meant whenever she

04:38:46.439 --> 04:38:48.599
said, you're no daughter of mine.

04:38:48.720 --> 04:38:50.939
It was true.

04:38:51.000 --> 04:38:54.540
Lucky for you, Scarab snorted.

04:38:54.599 --> 04:38:56.879
That one has a personality like

04:38:56.879 --> 04:38:57.779
sandpaper.

04:38:57.840 --> 04:39:00.540
Cricket thought this was rather funny

04:39:00.540 --> 04:39:03.119
coming from Lady Scarab, but she didn't

04:39:03.119 --> 04:39:03.599
point that out.

04:39:03.659 --> 04:39:06.599
How did they keep it a secret?

04:39:06.659 --> 04:39:07.680
She wondered.

04:39:07.799 --> 04:39:10.799
She tried to puzzle through what they

04:39:10.799 --> 04:39:11.459
would have had to do.

04:39:11.520 --> 04:39:14.459
It was possible no one had noticed that

04:39:14.459 --> 04:39:15.840
Katy did was with egg.

04:39:15.900 --> 04:39:18.659
Many dragons grew plumper in the rainy

04:39:18.659 --> 04:39:21.240
months, when there was more food, unless

04:39:21.240 --> 04:39:22.799
opportunity for outdoor flying.

04:39:22.919 --> 04:39:25.799
And Katy did was good at keeping secrets

04:39:25.799 --> 04:39:27.179
obviously.

04:39:27.240 --> 04:39:30.599
But what did she do once she had the

04:39:30.599 --> 04:39:30.959
egg?

04:39:31.020 --> 04:39:34.740
All high wing eggs in each hive were kept

04:39:34.740 --> 04:39:37.259
in a central nest until they hatched.

04:39:37.319 --> 04:39:39.779
Maybe Cadell simply had to present

04:39:39.779 --> 04:39:42.659
herself at the nest with Katy did's egg

04:39:42.659 --> 04:39:45.720
claiming it was hers, it would be marked

04:39:45.720 --> 04:39:48.720
as hers, protected as the dragonette

04:39:48.720 --> 04:39:51.360
inside grew, and then returned to Cadell

04:39:51.360 --> 04:39:52.919
a day before it was due to hatch.

04:39:53.040 --> 04:39:56.700
It's so hard to imagine Caddell agreeing

04:39:56.700 --> 04:39:57.479
to a lie like that.

04:39:57.540 --> 04:39:59.639
Cricket said aloud.

04:39:59.700 --> 04:40:03.360
She didn't want to, said Lady Scarab.

04:40:03.479 --> 04:40:06.840
There was an enormous fight when she

04:40:06.840 --> 04:40:08.939
found out Katy did was hiding your egg.

04:40:09.000 --> 04:40:11.639
If it was up to your delightful

04:40:11.639 --> 04:40:13.680
grandmother, they would have taken it out

04:40:13.680 --> 04:40:15.720
to the ocean and dropped you on a rock

04:40:15.720 --> 04:40:16.139
somewhere.

04:40:16.200 --> 04:40:20.520
This cricket could imagine very easily.

04:40:20.639 --> 04:40:23.639
Although it was so strange to hear a

04:40:23.639 --> 04:40:25.919
Cadell referred to as her grandmother.

04:40:26.040 --> 04:40:28.020
I was still her family.

04:40:28.080 --> 04:40:30.479
Even if I wasn't her daughter.

04:40:30.540 --> 04:40:33.540
But my existence was against the rules.

04:40:33.659 --> 04:40:38.459
I represented Katy did lying to her, and

04:40:38.459 --> 04:40:40.500
Queen Wasp being furious if she found

04:40:40.500 --> 04:40:40.740
out.

04:40:40.799 --> 04:40:44.520
Having me around put Cadal at risk.

04:40:44.580 --> 04:40:47.639
She must have seen danger and crime and

04:40:47.639 --> 04:40:50.220
disorder, and lies that could ruin her

04:40:50.220 --> 04:40:51.720
every time she looked at me.

04:40:51.779 --> 04:40:56.400
In the end, Katie did agreed to sneak the

04:40:56.400 --> 04:40:59.400
egg into the cicada hive nest, so it

04:40:59.400 --> 04:41:01.740
could come back official and approved

04:41:01.740 --> 04:41:04.139
instead of you being a secret forever.

04:41:04.200 --> 04:41:07.380
And Cadell agreed to pretend it was

04:41:07.380 --> 04:41:07.740
hers.

04:41:07.799 --> 04:41:11.459
Lady Scarab grinned with all of her

04:41:11.459 --> 04:41:12.000
teeth.

04:41:12.060 --> 04:41:14.700
I might have helped with that little

04:41:14.700 --> 04:41:15.540
compromise.

04:41:15.599 --> 04:41:19.139
Cricket wondered whether Lady Scarab's

04:41:19.139 --> 04:41:21.900
help came in the form of threats, or

04:41:21.900 --> 04:41:24.540
offers to help Cadell's social climb.

04:41:24.599 --> 04:41:26.759
Weren't there official records, though?

04:41:26.880 --> 04:41:27.900
She asked.

04:41:27.959 --> 04:41:30.419
I helped with those too.

04:41:30.479 --> 04:41:34.020
Lady Scarab looked extremely pleased with

04:41:34.020 --> 04:41:34.439
herself.

04:41:34.500 --> 04:41:38.880
A little bribery, a little distraction, a

04:41:38.880 --> 04:41:41.279
forged document, and then you were

04:41:41.279 --> 04:41:43.560
Cadell's, and everything was in order.

04:41:43.560 --> 04:41:46.619
But why would you help my assist?

04:41:46.740 --> 04:41:50.939
I mean, Katie did, at all, Cricket asked

04:41:51.060 --> 04:41:52.979
guessing part of the answer already.

04:41:53.040 --> 04:41:55.259
Did you?

04:41:55.319 --> 04:41:56.759
Did you know my dad?

04:41:56.819 --> 04:42:01.020
Lady scarab's grin disappeared, like

04:42:01.020 --> 04:42:03.299
waves pulling back off the beach before a

04:42:03.299 --> 04:42:03.840
tsunami.

04:42:03.900 --> 04:42:06.840
She stared down at her painting for a

04:42:06.840 --> 04:42:09.599
long moment, then set down the paintbrush

04:42:09.599 --> 04:42:11.939
and heaved herself upright with a growl.

04:42:12.060 --> 04:42:15.599
Cricket moved out of the way as the old

04:42:15.599 --> 04:42:18.060
dragon stomped over to the bookshelf.

04:42:18.360 --> 04:42:21.419
Lady Scarab pulled out an old, dark green

04:42:21.419 --> 04:42:22.979
book, and flipped it open.

04:42:23.040 --> 04:42:26.279
Inside, the pages have been carved away

04:42:26.279 --> 04:42:28.799
to leave a hollow for a small painting.

04:42:28.860 --> 04:42:31.799
The dragon and the portrait had kind

04:42:31.799 --> 04:42:32.220
eyes.

04:42:32.279 --> 04:42:34.979
That was the 1st thing cricket noticed.

04:42:35.040 --> 04:42:37.680
He wore glasses, just like her.

04:42:37.740 --> 04:42:40.500
His scales were a warm orange color

04:42:40.500 --> 04:42:43.200
except for his wings, which were dark red

04:42:43.200 --> 04:42:46.080
with spots of black scales here and

04:42:46.080 --> 04:42:46.319
there.

04:42:46.380 --> 04:42:50.040
Some of them even looked like ink blots

04:42:50.040 --> 04:42:51.000
like hers did.

04:42:51.119 --> 04:42:54.540
He was holding a book, which made cricket

04:42:54.540 --> 04:42:55.319
want to cry.

04:42:55.439 --> 04:42:57.360
Who is he?

04:42:57.479 --> 04:43:00.419
she whispered, touching the painting

04:43:00.419 --> 04:43:01.560
lightly with one claw.

04:43:01.619 --> 04:43:04.380
Definitely a hive wing.

04:43:04.439 --> 04:43:06.840
So I'm really not a hybrid.

04:43:06.900 --> 04:43:10.740
Malachite, said Lady Scarab.

04:43:10.799 --> 04:43:12.840
My secretary.

04:43:12.900 --> 04:43:15.659
Back when I was still allegedly, the

04:43:15.659 --> 04:43:19.740
Minister of Education, brilliant, talented

04:43:19.740 --> 04:43:22.979
made excellent coffee, full of exciting

04:43:22.979 --> 04:43:23.700
ideas.

04:43:23.759 --> 04:43:27.659
The 1st dragon in years, who gave me hope

04:43:27.659 --> 04:43:29.520
for the future of our tribe.

04:43:29.580 --> 04:43:31.560
She sighed.

04:43:31.680 --> 04:43:34.080
It was my fault, really.

04:43:34.200 --> 04:43:37.259
Queen Wasp has always hated me.

04:43:37.319 --> 04:43:40.259
I should have known better than to let

04:43:40.259 --> 04:43:42.479
her see there was a dragon I cared

04:43:42.479 --> 04:43:42.840
about.

04:43:42.900 --> 04:43:44.819
To spite me.

04:43:44.880 --> 04:43:48.060
She forbade his marriage to the dragon he

04:43:48.060 --> 04:43:48.720
fell in love with.

04:43:48.779 --> 04:43:51.900
Katie did, Cricket said.

04:43:51.959 --> 04:43:53.639
Yes.

04:43:53.700 --> 04:43:56.400
And then she took him away from me.

04:43:56.459 --> 04:43:58.919
Before he even knew you existed.

04:43:58.979 --> 04:44:01.380
He works for her now.

04:44:01.439 --> 04:44:04.799
He's really still alive, Cricket

04:44:04.799 --> 04:44:06.540
whispered, looking up at her.

04:44:06.599 --> 04:44:08.159
In a sense.

04:44:08.279 --> 04:44:10.200
Scarab said bitterly.

04:44:10.259 --> 04:44:13.860
She parades him past me whenever she

04:44:13.860 --> 04:44:14.099
can.

04:44:14.159 --> 04:44:17.639
Always with those hateful white eyes.

04:44:17.759 --> 04:44:20.880
I don't know if he ever gets to be

04:44:20.880 --> 04:44:21.299
himself.

04:44:21.360 --> 04:44:24.900
I haven't seen him with his own eyes

04:44:24.900 --> 04:44:27.779
since the day she took him over, and

04:44:27.779 --> 04:44:29.819
summoned him to Wasp Hive.

04:44:29.880 --> 04:44:31.500
She hissed.

04:44:31.560 --> 04:44:34.740
I have to pretend like I don't care.

04:44:34.799 --> 04:44:37.560
If she doesn't get a reaction from me

04:44:37.560 --> 04:44:41.400
maybe one day she'll lose interest and

04:44:41.400 --> 04:44:41.939
let him go.

04:44:42.000 --> 04:44:45.720
That's why Lady Scarab has no servants

04:44:45.720 --> 04:44:47.580
Cricket realized.

04:44:47.580 --> 04:44:49.680
That's why she's always alone.

04:44:49.799 --> 04:44:53.759
So there's no one wasp can hurt to get to

04:44:53.759 --> 04:44:54.060
her.

04:44:54.119 --> 04:44:57.479
Is that what's going to happen to Katy

04:44:57.479 --> 04:44:57.779
did?

04:44:57.900 --> 04:44:58.680
She asked.

04:44:58.740 --> 04:45:02.759
I hope not, said Scarab.

04:45:02.819 --> 04:45:05.880
Queen Wasp usually gets bored rather

04:45:05.880 --> 04:45:06.419
quickly.

04:45:06.479 --> 04:45:09.599
If Katie did, can't lead her to you.

04:45:09.659 --> 04:45:11.939
She won't have much use for her.

04:45:12.000 --> 04:45:14.400
I wish I could rescue them.

04:45:14.459 --> 04:45:17.099
Cricket said, twisting her talons

04:45:17.099 --> 04:45:17.520
together.

04:45:17.580 --> 04:45:21.659
Well, you can't, Lady Scarab pointed

04:45:21.659 --> 04:45:21.840
out.

04:45:21.900 --> 04:45:24.959
Because WASP can control them any time

04:45:24.959 --> 04:45:27.659
she wants, and she'll just march them

04:45:27.659 --> 04:45:28.619
right back to prison.

04:45:28.680 --> 04:45:32.580
A wave of anger rushed through cricket

04:45:32.580 --> 04:45:34.139
strong and sudden.

04:45:34.200 --> 04:45:36.720
There has to be a way to stop her.

04:45:36.779 --> 04:45:40.139
Scarab snapped the cover closed over the

04:45:40.139 --> 04:45:41.459
portrait of Malachite.

04:45:41.520 --> 04:45:44.520
I was hoping you'd found one in the

04:45:44.520 --> 04:45:44.759
book.

04:45:44.819 --> 04:45:48.299
But if there are no more predictions, then

04:45:48.299 --> 04:45:49.439
it's all chaos.

04:45:49.560 --> 04:45:51.779
She waved her talons in the air.

04:45:51.840 --> 04:45:53.520
Anything could happen.

04:45:53.580 --> 04:45:56.340
She doesn't have secret knowledge of the

04:45:56.340 --> 04:45:57.240
future after all.

04:45:57.360 --> 04:45:58.979
Scarab chuckled.

04:45:59.040 --> 04:46:01.680
No wonder she wants you dead.

04:46:01.740 --> 04:46:04.860
Cricket ran her claws along the bookshelf

04:46:04.860 --> 04:46:05.340
thinking.

04:46:05.459 --> 04:46:08.400
She still didn't have an answer to the

04:46:08.400 --> 04:46:09.419
mind control question.

04:46:09.479 --> 04:46:12.299
She didn't know if the hive wings could

04:46:12.299 --> 04:46:13.020
be saved from it.

04:46:13.080 --> 04:46:15.119
But she did have one thing.

04:46:15.180 --> 04:46:17.040
The truth about the book.

04:46:17.099 --> 04:46:20.400
Katy did should have trusted me with the

04:46:20.400 --> 04:46:22.200
truth about her and Malachite.

04:46:22.259 --> 04:46:25.200
My tribe deserves the truth too.

04:46:25.259 --> 04:46:28.319
They need to know that Queen Wasp has

04:46:28.319 --> 04:46:29.040
been lying to them.

04:46:29.099 --> 04:46:31.740
Cricket looked around the room.

04:46:31.799 --> 04:46:35.580
If this was her last day in the hives, she

04:46:35.580 --> 04:46:36.299
had to use it well.

04:46:36.360 --> 04:46:38.939
She couldn't just look for answers

04:46:38.939 --> 04:46:39.479
anymore.

04:46:39.540 --> 04:46:42.299
She had to make sure other dragons also

04:46:42.299 --> 04:46:42.900
knew them.

04:46:42.959 --> 04:46:45.720
Lady Scarab, she said.

04:46:45.840 --> 04:46:48.180
Can I borrow a paintbrush?

04:46:48.240 --> 04:46:52.680
Part three.

04:46:52.740 --> 04:46:55.500
The Queen's Secrets.

04:46:55.560 --> 04:46:58.139
Chapter 16.

04:46:58.560 --> 04:47:01.259
Sundude didn't like it.

04:47:01.319 --> 04:47:03.599
And so Sortell didn't like it either.

04:47:03.659 --> 04:47:06.299
Although Cricket suspected he would have

04:47:06.299 --> 04:47:07.439
been all for it otherwise.

04:47:07.560 --> 04:47:11.040
Blue loved the idea though, and that was

04:47:11.040 --> 04:47:11.759
what she cared about.

04:47:11.880 --> 04:47:16.080
This is way too dangerous, Sundew

04:47:16.080 --> 04:47:16.619
protested.

04:47:16.680 --> 04:47:20.159
Exactly, said Sword Tail.

04:47:20.220 --> 04:47:23.700
Queen Wasp may already suspect we're in

04:47:23.700 --> 04:47:24.540
Jewel Hive.

04:47:24.599 --> 04:47:27.419
This will just prove it to her, Sundew

04:47:27.419 --> 04:47:27.959
pointed out.

04:47:28.020 --> 04:47:31.500
It'll be snake eyes and everyone talking

04:47:31.500 --> 04:47:34.139
at the same time again in a heartbeat, and

04:47:34.139 --> 04:47:36.180
then we'll be surrounded, and then we'll

04:47:36.180 --> 04:47:38.040
be caught, and then none of our plans

04:47:38.040 --> 04:47:38.819
will have a chance.

04:47:38.939 --> 04:47:43.319
None of them, Swordell said, waving his

04:47:43.319 --> 04:47:46.080
wings around dramatically, because we'll

04:47:46.080 --> 04:47:48.419
be in the clutches of zombie hive wings.

04:47:48.540 --> 04:47:52.319
All right, simmer down, Sundew said

04:47:52.319 --> 04:47:53.340
rolling her eyes.

04:47:53.459 --> 04:47:56.340
They were huddled inside one of the

04:47:56.340 --> 04:47:58.740
indoor stalls of the glitter bazaar, not

04:47:58.740 --> 04:48:00.419
far from the salvation statue.

04:48:00.479 --> 04:48:02.400
This one sold books.

04:48:02.459 --> 04:48:05.639
Wonderful, beautiful books, with gold

04:48:05.639 --> 04:48:08.220
leaf on the spines and feathery edges to

04:48:08.220 --> 04:48:09.060
the silk pages.

04:48:09.180 --> 04:48:11.759
Cricket couldn't stop picking them up

04:48:11.759 --> 04:48:14.520
just to feel something safe and beloved

04:48:14.520 --> 04:48:15.599
in her talents again.

04:48:15.659 --> 04:48:18.540
A part of her wish she could abandon this

04:48:18.540 --> 04:48:21.540
plan. crawl under one of the tables and

04:48:21.540 --> 04:48:23.459
read all the books in this stall for the

04:48:23.459 --> 04:48:24.419
rest of her life instead.

04:48:24.540 --> 04:48:27.360
Hanging from the top of the doorway?

04:48:27.479 --> 04:48:29.939
Wind chimes with little hummingbirds

04:48:29.939 --> 04:48:31.500
dangling from them sounded in the

04:48:31.500 --> 04:48:31.860
breeze.

04:48:31.919 --> 04:48:34.979
Dawn was coming, and the market was

04:48:34.979 --> 04:48:35.639
virtually empty.

04:48:35.700 --> 04:48:38.759
Even on the upper levels, most of the

04:48:38.759 --> 04:48:40.680
dragons they'd seen had been dragging

04:48:40.680 --> 04:48:42.419
themselves sleepily off to bed.

04:48:42.479 --> 04:48:45.360
I know, Cricket said.

04:48:45.419 --> 04:48:46.860
But I have to do something.

04:48:46.919 --> 04:48:50.580
It's no use knowing the truth, if

04:48:50.580 --> 04:48:52.680
everyone else still believes the lies.

04:48:52.799 --> 04:48:56.159
My tribe needs to know that Queen Wasp is

04:48:56.159 --> 04:48:56.700
lying to them.

04:48:56.759 --> 04:48:59.759
Maybe I can't set them free from the mind

04:48:59.759 --> 04:49:02.279
control yet, but knowing the truth about

04:49:02.279 --> 04:49:02.759
the book.

04:49:02.880 --> 04:49:06.180
She looked down at the scarf she'd been

04:49:06.180 --> 04:49:07.259
twisting between her claws.

04:49:07.319 --> 04:49:11.340
I think knowing the truth is the 1st step

04:49:11.340 --> 04:49:13.020
toward their freedom.

04:49:13.080 --> 04:49:13.740
I hope.

04:49:13.799 --> 04:49:15.720
I hope so too.

04:49:15.779 --> 04:49:17.279
Blue agreed.

04:49:17.340 --> 04:49:20.939
I mean, imagine you've only been told one

04:49:20.939 --> 04:49:21.840
thing your whole life.

04:49:21.900 --> 04:49:24.900
Imagine you don't even know it could be a

04:49:24.900 --> 04:49:25.139
lie.

04:49:25.200 --> 04:49:27.119
He hesitated.

04:49:27.180 --> 04:49:30.240
This is going to be hard for dragons to

04:49:30.240 --> 04:49:30.419
hear.

04:49:30.540 --> 04:49:33.000
What are we supposed to do with all

04:49:33.000 --> 04:49:33.299
this?

04:49:33.419 --> 04:49:35.159
Sundew asked.

04:49:35.220 --> 04:49:37.680
Flicking her claws at the stacks of silk

04:49:37.680 --> 04:49:39.299
paper that cricket had taken from a

04:49:39.299 --> 04:49:40.560
nearby stationery stall.

04:49:40.619 --> 04:49:43.619
We're going to write out clear site's

04:49:43.619 --> 04:49:45.840
letter from the end of her book, Cricket

04:49:45.840 --> 04:49:46.200
said.

04:49:46.259 --> 04:49:49.799
Over and over again, as many copies as we

04:49:49.799 --> 04:49:50.159
can make.

04:49:50.220 --> 04:49:53.400
At the top, right, this is what the book

04:49:53.400 --> 04:49:56.700
really says, and at the bottom, right

04:49:56.700 --> 04:50:00.360
there are no more predictions, Queen Wasp

04:50:00.360 --> 04:50:01.020
is lying.

04:50:01.080 --> 04:50:05.099
Sortell groaned and flopped his head down

04:50:05.099 --> 04:50:06.119
onto his talons.

04:50:06.180 --> 04:50:09.540
Riding, he whined.

04:50:09.599 --> 04:50:11.459
That sounds like homework.

04:50:11.520 --> 04:50:14.040
Nobody said the revolution would involve

04:50:14.040 --> 04:50:14.759
homework.

04:50:14.819 --> 04:50:17.459
Sundu whacked him on the head with one of

04:50:17.459 --> 04:50:18.119
her wings.

04:50:18.180 --> 04:50:21.240
You are lucky that you can write, she

04:50:21.240 --> 04:50:21.540
said.

04:50:21.599 --> 04:50:23.880
We were told that silk wings weren't

04:50:23.880 --> 04:50:24.540
allowed to go to school.

04:50:24.599 --> 04:50:26.340
What?

04:50:26.400 --> 04:50:27.720
Cricket yelped.

04:50:27.779 --> 04:50:29.939
She couldn't imagine being forbidden to

04:50:29.939 --> 04:50:30.360
go to school.

04:50:30.419 --> 04:50:33.659
That would be cruel and awful and

04:50:33.659 --> 04:50:34.200
barbaric.

04:50:34.259 --> 04:50:37.500
The leaf wing shot her an amused look.

04:50:37.560 --> 04:50:40.560
Well, exactly, she said.

04:50:40.619 --> 04:50:44.639
Sounds all right to me, Swordell muttered

04:50:44.639 --> 04:50:46.979
but he accepted the inkwell and chief of

04:50:46.979 --> 04:50:48.419
papers with only a little more

04:50:48.419 --> 04:50:49.080
grumbling.

04:50:49.139 --> 04:50:52.860
Cricket made the 1st copies, as she was

04:50:52.860 --> 04:50:54.959
the fastest rider, and then they all

04:50:54.959 --> 04:50:57.419
copied from those, working as quickly as

04:50:57.419 --> 04:50:57.720
they could.

04:50:57.779 --> 04:51:01.139
When they had well over 100, and the sun

04:51:01.139 --> 04:51:03.000
was starting to sidle in through the far

04:51:03.000 --> 04:51:05.400
windows, she stopped them and collected

04:51:05.400 --> 04:51:05.939
the papers.

04:51:06.000 --> 04:51:09.360
Now you have to go, she said.

04:51:09.419 --> 04:51:11.520
Go where?

04:51:11.520 --> 04:51:12.419
Blue asked.

04:51:12.479 --> 04:51:15.599
To hide for the day, Cricket answered.

04:51:15.659 --> 04:51:18.299
Somewhere far away from Jewel Hive.

04:51:18.360 --> 04:51:20.459
I'm doing the next part by myself.

04:51:20.520 --> 04:51:24.060
Then I'm going back out to look for Luna

04:51:24.060 --> 04:51:25.259
Swartel said.

04:51:25.319 --> 04:51:28.919
Well, I get to meet with a chrysalis

04:51:28.919 --> 04:51:30.180
sundew side.

04:51:30.240 --> 04:51:32.939
Blue took one of Cricket's talons in

04:51:32.939 --> 04:51:33.240
his.

04:51:33.299 --> 04:51:34.860
No way.

04:51:34.919 --> 04:51:36.900
I got you into this mess.

04:51:36.959 --> 04:51:39.240
I'm not leaving you alone to deal with

04:51:39.240 --> 04:51:39.419
it.

04:51:39.540 --> 04:51:41.159
She shook her head.

04:51:41.220 --> 04:51:44.340
You didn't get me into this mess, Blue.

04:51:44.400 --> 04:51:46.619
Queen Wasp did this.

04:51:46.680 --> 04:51:50.159
She kept my parents apart, and she stole

04:51:50.159 --> 04:51:50.580
my father.

04:51:50.639 --> 04:51:53.099
She used the book to make herself

04:51:53.099 --> 04:51:56.159
powerful. and lied to the entire tribe to

04:51:56.159 --> 04:51:56.459
do it.

04:51:56.580 --> 04:51:59.520
You helped me find the truth.

04:51:59.580 --> 04:52:02.400
And now I have to help my tribe the same

04:52:02.400 --> 04:52:02.639
way.

04:52:02.700 --> 04:52:06.299
Technically, I helped you find the truth

04:52:06.299 --> 04:52:09.779
Sundu observed, since it was my idea to

04:52:09.779 --> 04:52:10.860
steal the book in the 1st place.

04:52:10.919 --> 04:52:13.860
I, too, have been important to this whole

04:52:13.860 --> 04:52:15.180
everything.

04:52:15.240 --> 04:52:17.459
Sort tell chimed in.

04:52:17.520 --> 04:52:19.919
Cricket put her wings around blue.

04:52:19.979 --> 04:52:22.799
Awkwardly, now that his own wings were in

04:52:22.799 --> 04:52:25.979
the way, and hugged him close, you have

04:52:25.979 --> 04:52:28.860
to stay safe to help the silk wings and

04:52:28.860 --> 04:52:30.599
the leaf wings, she said.

04:52:30.659 --> 04:52:32.939
But the hive wings are my

04:52:32.939 --> 04:52:33.599
responsibility.

04:52:33.659 --> 04:52:34.799
All right?

04:52:34.919 --> 04:52:39.299
Also, Sundew said, it's better if only

04:52:39.299 --> 04:52:41.400
one of us gets caught, then the others

04:52:41.400 --> 04:52:42.540
can maybe rescue her.

04:52:42.599 --> 04:52:47.639
Maybe, she repeated, wagging one claw in

04:52:47.639 --> 04:52:51.479
cricket's face, but also, maybe not, so

04:52:51.479 --> 04:52:52.080
don't get caught.

04:52:52.200 --> 04:52:54.720
I won't, cricket said.

04:52:54.779 --> 04:52:55.919
I'll try.

04:52:55.979 --> 04:52:57.419
Go hide.

04:52:57.479 --> 04:52:59.639
I'll meet you by the last stall outside

04:52:59.639 --> 04:53:00.479
before sunset.

04:53:00.540 --> 04:53:04.799
We can go look for Luna together, Sortell

04:53:04.799 --> 04:53:06.959
said, nudging Blue's side.

04:53:07.020 --> 04:53:09.720
We can split up and cover a lot more of

04:53:09.720 --> 04:53:10.799
the bay with 2 of us.

04:53:10.860 --> 04:53:12.779
Three if sundew helps.

04:53:12.900 --> 04:53:16.319
Maybe she's hurt and stuck on an island.

04:53:16.380 --> 04:53:18.360
We're in a cave and can't find us.

04:53:18.419 --> 04:53:20.279
Please help me, Blue.

04:53:20.340 --> 04:53:22.200
Luna and I need your help.

04:53:22.259 --> 04:53:25.560
Cricket guessed that SwordTell meant it

04:53:25.560 --> 04:53:28.139
but daddy was also trying to give Blue a

04:53:28.139 --> 04:53:29.279
way to be able to leave her.

04:53:29.340 --> 04:53:32.220
By reminding him of another dragon who

04:53:32.220 --> 04:53:34.500
needed his help, even more than she did.

04:53:34.560 --> 04:53:39.119
Blue opened and closed his talons, looking

04:53:39.119 --> 04:53:41.040
at them as if he was hoping they'd tell

04:53:41.040 --> 04:53:41.819
him what to do.

04:53:41.880 --> 04:53:44.340
I will, but.

04:53:45.180 --> 04:53:48.000
Cricket, Blue said woefully.

04:53:48.060 --> 04:53:49.919
I don't want to leave you.

04:53:49.979 --> 04:53:54.659
I know, she said, her voice catching in

04:53:54.659 --> 04:53:57.419
her throat, but you can understand what

04:53:57.419 --> 04:53:58.319
I'm feeling, right?

04:53:58.380 --> 04:54:01.380
You can imagine how important this is to

04:54:01.380 --> 04:54:04.919
me and and how important you are to me.

04:54:04.979 --> 04:54:09.360
He blinked back tears, and leaned closer

04:54:09.360 --> 04:54:12.240
so their noses touched, and then Sortail

04:54:12.240 --> 04:54:14.279
dragged him away, and the 3 of them were

04:54:14.279 --> 04:54:14.520
gone.

04:54:14.580 --> 04:54:17.459
Blue still looking over his shoulder the

04:54:17.459 --> 04:54:17.880
last moment.

04:54:17.939 --> 04:54:21.180
It was hard to watch them hurry away

04:54:21.180 --> 04:54:22.680
through the displays of the glitter

04:54:22.680 --> 04:54:23.220
bazaar.

04:54:23.279 --> 04:54:25.799
It was really hard to stop herself from

04:54:25.799 --> 04:54:28.080
shouting, wait, come back.

04:54:28.139 --> 04:54:29.939
I don't want to do this by myself.

04:54:30.000 --> 04:54:31.919
I'm actually terrified.

04:54:32.040 --> 04:54:35.099
But she took deep breaths and stayed

04:54:35.099 --> 04:54:35.700
quiet.

04:54:35.759 --> 04:54:37.680
And as soon as they were out of sight.

04:54:37.740 --> 04:54:40.200
She set out to complete the next part of

04:54:40.200 --> 04:54:40.560
her plan.

04:54:40.680 --> 04:54:43.799
She knew the queen would tear down

04:54:43.799 --> 04:54:45.900
anything she put up as fast as possible

04:54:45.900 --> 04:54:48.119
so she focused on quantity.

04:54:48.180 --> 04:54:51.299
As many messages in as many places as she

04:54:51.299 --> 04:54:51.479
could.

04:54:51.540 --> 04:54:55.560
Lady Scarab's largest pot of paint was

04:54:55.560 --> 04:54:58.080
the bright pink color of hibiscus flowers

04:54:58.080 --> 04:55:00.180
so that was what she used on every

04:55:00.180 --> 04:55:00.659
poster.

04:55:00.779 --> 04:55:04.380
Every open surface, every blank unguarded

04:55:04.380 --> 04:55:04.619
wall.

04:55:04.680 --> 04:55:07.500
She especially enjoyed painting over the

04:55:07.500 --> 04:55:10.200
wanted posters, covering her own face

04:55:10.200 --> 04:55:11.759
with tall pink letters.

04:55:11.819 --> 04:55:14.700
The queen is lying to you.

04:55:14.759 --> 04:55:17.880
Clear sight never predicted the tree

04:55:17.880 --> 04:55:18.360
wars.

04:55:18.479 --> 04:55:22.200
Clear sight never said the other tribes

04:55:22.200 --> 04:55:23.819
should bow to the hive wings.

04:55:23.880 --> 04:55:27.000
Everything Queen Wasp says about the book

04:55:27.000 --> 04:55:27.840
is a lie.

04:55:27.900 --> 04:55:31.080
Clear Sight's predictions ended a 1000

04:55:31.080 --> 04:55:31.740
years ago.

04:55:31.799 --> 04:55:33.900
The queen is lying to you.

04:55:33.959 --> 04:55:37.020
The queen is lying to you.

04:55:37.080 --> 04:55:38.580
The queen is lying to you.

04:55:38.700 --> 04:55:42.060
She slid the paper with Clearsight's

04:55:42.060 --> 04:55:44.400
letter on it under doors and scattered

04:55:44.400 --> 04:55:45.180
them through the parks.

04:55:45.240 --> 04:55:47.819
She left one on top of the book, The

04:55:47.819 --> 04:55:49.860
Clear Site Statue was reading outside the

04:55:49.860 --> 04:55:50.340
library.

04:55:50.400 --> 04:55:52.860
She couldn't bring herself to do anything

04:55:52.860 --> 04:55:55.380
else to that statue, but she had no

04:55:55.380 --> 04:55:57.900
trouble defacing the salvation statue in

04:55:57.900 --> 04:56:01.680
the glitter bazaar, scrawling, liar, in

04:56:01.680 --> 04:56:03.779
enormous pink letters all over the

04:56:03.779 --> 04:56:07.200
queen's face and wings, and then WASP is

04:56:07.200 --> 04:56:08.400
lying around the base.

04:56:08.459 --> 04:56:12.180
The sun was well above the horizon, and

04:56:12.180 --> 04:56:13.619
the streets were starting to fill when

04:56:13.619 --> 04:56:14.400
she ran out of paint.

04:56:14.520 --> 04:56:17.099
A few dragonettes on their way to school

04:56:17.099 --> 04:56:19.439
saw her slipping the papers under doors

04:56:19.439 --> 04:56:21.900
and asked what they were, so she gave

04:56:21.900 --> 04:56:22.319
them one.

04:56:22.380 --> 04:56:25.439
This is the truth, she said.

04:56:25.500 --> 04:56:27.599
I've seen the book of Clear Sight.

04:56:27.720 --> 04:56:32.220
They gazed up at her, wide eyed, 3 tiny

04:56:32.220 --> 04:56:34.740
hive wings and 2 wingless silk wings.

04:56:34.799 --> 04:56:36.299
Really?

04:56:36.299 --> 04:56:37.319
said one of them.

04:56:37.380 --> 04:56:38.759
Is it amazing?

04:56:38.819 --> 04:56:42.540
It is amazing, but not the way you'd

04:56:42.540 --> 04:56:43.560
think, she said.

04:56:43.619 --> 04:56:45.299
She tapped the paper.

04:56:45.360 --> 04:56:47.580
This is what it really says.

04:56:47.639 --> 04:56:51.599
They all gathered around to sound out the

04:56:51.599 --> 04:56:54.000
words together, and she hurried away to

04:56:54.000 --> 04:56:56.340
the next level, wondering how long she

04:56:56.340 --> 04:56:58.799
had before Queen Wasp saw the messages

04:56:58.799 --> 04:57:00.000
through someone's eyes.

04:57:00.119 --> 04:57:04.560
Two levels up, a door opened just as she

04:57:04.560 --> 04:57:05.700
slipped the paper underneath.

04:57:05.759 --> 04:57:08.459
A startled hive wing stood there on her

04:57:08.459 --> 04:57:09.240
way out to work.

04:57:09.299 --> 04:57:13.020
Hey, said the strange dragon.

04:57:13.080 --> 04:57:13.500
Who are you?

04:57:13.560 --> 04:57:14.279
What's this?

04:57:14.340 --> 04:57:18.900
It's Cricket took a deep breath.

04:57:18.959 --> 04:57:20.700
Be brave.

04:57:20.759 --> 04:57:23.340
It's the truth, she said.

04:57:23.400 --> 04:57:26.099
She picked up the paper and held it out

04:57:26.099 --> 04:57:26.700
to the dragon.

04:57:26.819 --> 04:57:29.520
I thought everyone should know what the

04:57:29.520 --> 04:57:31.500
book of Clear Sight really says.

04:57:31.500 --> 04:57:34.380
The dragon's jaw dropped open.

04:57:34.439 --> 04:57:37.200
You're the one from the wanted posters.

04:57:37.259 --> 04:57:40.200
She seized the paper from Cricket's

04:57:40.200 --> 04:57:40.560
Talons.

04:57:40.619 --> 04:57:43.740
You really did read the book?

04:57:43.799 --> 04:57:44.459
By the stars.

04:57:44.520 --> 04:57:46.080
I've always wanted to know what it says.

04:57:46.139 --> 04:57:49.500
Me too, Cricket said.

04:57:49.560 --> 04:57:51.959
And now I think everyone should know.

04:57:52.080 --> 04:57:55.020
She left the hive wing standing there.

04:57:55.139 --> 04:57:56.880
Reading with shining eyes.

04:57:57.000 --> 04:57:59.340
They are listening.

04:57:59.400 --> 04:58:00.779
They want the truth.

04:58:00.840 --> 04:58:02.639
Maybe this will work.

04:58:02.700 --> 04:58:05.819
But her luck ran out on the way to the

04:58:05.819 --> 04:58:07.919
water tower. where she had hoped to hide

04:58:07.919 --> 04:58:08.400
for the day.

04:58:08.520 --> 04:58:11.340
She was hurrying through the streets

04:58:11.340 --> 04:58:13.380
ducking her head to avoid meeting

04:58:13.380 --> 04:58:15.900
anyone's eyes when she turned a corner

04:58:15.900 --> 04:58:17.880
and ran into Cadell.

04:58:17.880 --> 04:58:21.840
Oh, Cricket yelped, looking straight into

04:58:21.840 --> 04:58:22.319
her mother.

04:58:22.380 --> 04:58:25.560
No, her grandmother's face.

04:58:25.560 --> 04:58:28.860
I mean, sorry, sorry, ma'am.

04:58:28.919 --> 04:58:32.040
She tried to cover her confusion, to bow

04:58:32.040 --> 04:58:34.139
and turn away and continue on like any

04:58:34.139 --> 04:58:35.400
other stranger in a hurry.

04:58:35.459 --> 04:58:38.639
But Cadal seized her arm in an iron

04:58:38.639 --> 04:58:39.119
grip.

04:58:39.240 --> 04:58:42.419
You, she snarled.

04:58:42.479 --> 04:58:44.099
What are you doing here?

04:58:44.099 --> 04:58:45.659
In my hive.

04:58:45.720 --> 04:58:47.400
Are you trying to get me arrested?

04:58:47.520 --> 04:58:50.700
She dragged Cricket through the dragonfly

04:58:50.700 --> 04:58:53.220
square to her house and threw her inside

04:58:53.220 --> 04:58:54.659
slamming the door behind them.

04:58:54.720 --> 04:58:58.680
Cricket stumbled on the gray silk carpet

04:58:58.680 --> 04:59:00.540
trying to put some distance between

04:59:00.540 --> 04:59:01.799
herself and Cadell.

04:59:01.919 --> 04:59:04.080
There was so much in this living room

04:59:04.080 --> 04:59:06.060
that reminded Cricket of her childhood.

04:59:06.119 --> 04:59:09.540
The square black marble side tables her

04:59:09.540 --> 04:59:10.560
mother had taken with her.

04:59:10.619 --> 04:59:13.560
The ivory reproduction of the salvation

04:59:13.560 --> 04:59:17.580
statue, with tiny garnet eyes, the smell

04:59:17.580 --> 04:59:20.340
of chamomile tea, and boiled rabbits

04:59:20.340 --> 04:59:21.119
coming from the kitchen.

04:59:21.180 --> 04:59:24.000
Everything in the house was exactly the

04:59:24.000 --> 04:59:25.500
same as it had been a year ago.

04:59:25.560 --> 04:59:28.560
Every book exactly even with the edge of

04:59:28.560 --> 04:59:31.200
the shelf, every painting perfectly

04:59:31.200 --> 04:59:34.319
aligned with the next, Queen Wasp glaring

04:59:34.319 --> 04:59:37.080
at Lady Jewel, who stared blankly at the

04:59:37.080 --> 04:59:39.060
most boring clear sight and portrait

04:59:39.060 --> 04:59:39.299
history.

04:59:39.360 --> 04:59:42.840
Even the terror wasn't entirely new.

04:59:42.900 --> 04:59:45.180
She'd never been able to predict what

04:59:45.180 --> 04:59:46.500
Cadell would do next.

04:59:46.619 --> 04:59:48.959
She'd always been afraid of something

04:59:48.959 --> 04:59:51.299
sudden and terrible striking out of the

04:59:51.299 --> 04:59:51.540
blue.

04:59:51.599 --> 04:59:56.159
But this time, the room felt colder, the

04:59:56.159 --> 04:59:57.360
smell of meat stronger.

04:59:57.419 --> 05:00:00.900
And this time, the threat of Queen Wasp

05:00:00.900 --> 05:00:02.099
poisoned everything.

05:00:02.159 --> 05:00:05.459
This time, instead of yelling or throwing

05:00:05.459 --> 05:00:07.919
things, Cadell might deliver cricket

05:00:07.919 --> 05:00:10.500
right into the queen's waiting claws.

05:00:10.619 --> 05:00:13.860
I kept my mouth shut.

05:00:13.919 --> 05:00:15.419
Caddell hissed.

05:00:15.479 --> 05:00:17.700
I didn't want anyone to know I had

05:00:17.700 --> 05:00:18.659
anything to do with you.

05:00:18.720 --> 05:00:20.400
And then you show up here.

05:00:20.459 --> 05:00:22.680
Did you think I would help you?

05:00:22.740 --> 05:00:24.360
No.

05:00:24.419 --> 05:00:27.299
Cricket rubbed her scales where Cadell

05:00:27.299 --> 05:00:28.680
had dug her claws in.

05:00:28.919 --> 05:00:30.599
I didn't want to see you at all.

05:00:30.659 --> 05:00:33.299
Caddell's wings flared.

05:00:33.360 --> 05:00:34.799
Then why here?

05:00:34.919 --> 05:00:36.599
Why this hive?

05:00:36.659 --> 05:00:38.220
Why so close to my house?

05:00:38.279 --> 05:00:40.560
I came here to get away from you.

05:00:40.680 --> 05:00:43.619
I know, Cricket said.

05:00:43.680 --> 05:00:44.819
And I know why.

05:00:44.880 --> 05:00:47.700
Don't worry, I want to get away from you

05:00:47.700 --> 05:00:48.180
too.

05:00:48.240 --> 05:00:51.540
She took a step toward the door, but

05:00:51.540 --> 05:00:54.000
Caddell blocked her path, bearing the

05:00:54.000 --> 05:00:56.759
venomous teeth that neither her child nor

05:00:56.759 --> 05:00:58.200
grandchild had inherited.

05:00:58.259 --> 05:01:01.020
Cricket had seen her use them a few times

05:01:01.020 --> 05:01:03.900
to bring down prey, especially larger

05:01:03.900 --> 05:01:06.959
animals, like antelopes or water buffalo

05:01:06.959 --> 05:01:10.139
but she'd also once seen Cadell bite a

05:01:10.139 --> 05:01:10.560
dragon.

05:01:10.619 --> 05:01:14.279
A new silkwing cook who had accidentally

05:01:14.279 --> 05:01:16.380
burned Cadell's favorite meal on a bad

05:01:16.380 --> 05:01:16.680
day.

05:01:16.740 --> 05:01:19.799
The venom had spread quickly from the

05:01:19.799 --> 05:01:21.840
wound on his neck, and there had been

05:01:21.840 --> 05:01:24.659
screaming, and he'd only survived because

05:01:24.659 --> 05:01:27.900
father, grandfather, got him to the

05:01:27.900 --> 05:01:28.680
hospital in time.

05:01:28.740 --> 05:01:32.279
Cricket mostly remembered the screaming.

05:01:32.400 --> 05:01:36.479
That, and the realization that Cadell was

05:01:36.479 --> 05:01:38.400
even more dangerous than she'd thought.

05:01:38.459 --> 05:01:40.560
Would she do that to me?

05:01:40.680 --> 05:01:43.080
Just let me go.

05:01:43.139 --> 05:01:46.139
Pretend you didn't see me, Cricket said.

05:01:46.200 --> 05:01:48.779
If we're both lucky, you'll never see me

05:01:48.779 --> 05:01:49.439
again.

05:01:49.560 --> 05:01:51.360
Caddell frowned.

05:01:51.419 --> 05:01:55.020
She's not used to me talking back, Cricket

05:01:55.020 --> 05:01:55.439
thought.

05:01:55.500 --> 05:01:57.900
She's never seen me try to push her

05:01:57.900 --> 05:01:58.139
away.

05:01:58.200 --> 05:02:00.540
She's always been the one doing the

05:02:00.540 --> 05:02:01.020
pushing.

05:02:01.080 --> 05:02:03.060
Do you have the book?

05:02:03.119 --> 05:02:06.060
Cadell asked, her tail lashing.

05:02:06.180 --> 05:02:08.759
No, cricket answered.

05:02:08.819 --> 05:02:10.080
But I've seen it.

05:02:10.139 --> 05:02:13.200
I've read it, and I know Queen Wasp has

05:02:13.200 --> 05:02:14.400
been lying to everyone about it.

05:02:14.459 --> 05:02:18.659
Caddell brought her wings in close, and

05:02:18.659 --> 05:02:20.819
squinted at cricket with her professor

05:02:20.819 --> 05:02:21.240
face.

05:02:21.299 --> 05:02:23.099
Is that so?

05:02:23.159 --> 05:02:26.279
I must say, teaching the history of

05:02:26.279 --> 05:02:29.159
Pantala feels quite incomplete without a

05:02:29.159 --> 05:02:30.119
resource like the book.

05:02:30.180 --> 05:02:32.279
I've always thought it should be

05:02:32.279 --> 05:02:33.060
available for study.

05:02:33.119 --> 05:02:36.060
Me too, Cricket said.

05:02:36.119 --> 05:02:38.099
Maybe we do have something in common

05:02:38.099 --> 05:02:38.639
after all.

05:02:38.700 --> 05:02:42.720
You could give me the book.

05:02:42.779 --> 05:02:46.380
Cadell said, advancing toward cricket.

05:02:46.439 --> 05:02:49.500
Her teeth seemed to grow longer and

05:02:49.500 --> 05:02:50.939
sharper as she smiled.

05:02:51.000 --> 05:02:54.479
I am actually qualified enough to know

05:02:54.479 --> 05:02:55.200
what to do with it.

05:02:55.259 --> 05:02:57.840
It shouldn't be in the talons of some

05:02:57.840 --> 05:02:59.099
grubby silk wings.

05:02:59.159 --> 05:03:01.740
I told you, I don't have it.

05:03:01.860 --> 05:03:05.220
Cricket said, backing up until her tail

05:03:05.220 --> 05:03:07.380
hit the wall behind her, and her wings

05:03:07.380 --> 05:03:09.720
nearly knocked down a map of Pantala.

05:03:09.779 --> 05:03:12.419
And I wouldn't give it to you even if I

05:03:12.419 --> 05:03:12.659
did.

05:03:12.720 --> 05:03:15.840
You'd probably give it back to Queen Wasp

05:03:15.840 --> 05:03:18.119
in exchange for an invitation to a

05:03:18.119 --> 05:03:18.360
party.

05:03:18.419 --> 05:03:21.180
Caddell hissed furiously.

05:03:21.180 --> 05:03:25.200
Maybe, but I'd read it first, she

05:03:25.200 --> 05:03:25.740
snapped.

05:03:25.860 --> 05:03:28.979
Well, there's a copy of a piece of it on

05:03:28.979 --> 05:03:31.560
the statue outside the library, Cricket

05:03:31.560 --> 05:03:31.919
said.

05:03:31.979 --> 05:03:34.319
Let me go, and you can go read it

05:03:34.319 --> 05:03:34.619
yourself.

05:03:34.680 --> 05:03:37.860
Cadell suddenly went very still.

05:03:37.979 --> 05:03:39.720
Outside.

05:03:39.779 --> 05:03:42.419
Cricket could hear running talon steps

05:03:42.419 --> 05:03:44.700
and dragons shouting.

05:03:44.759 --> 05:03:47.639
Among the clamor of words, she heard one

05:03:47.639 --> 05:03:48.840
dragon call to another.

05:03:48.900 --> 05:03:51.240
It says the queen is lying.

05:03:51.360 --> 05:03:54.479
And someone else yell, I found another

05:03:54.479 --> 05:03:54.779
one.

05:03:54.840 --> 05:03:57.599
Her messages were getting the attention

05:03:57.599 --> 05:03:58.740
she'd hoped for.

05:03:58.799 --> 05:04:01.560
But she'd also hoped she'd be hidden away

05:04:01.560 --> 05:04:03.299
inside the water tower by now.

05:04:03.360 --> 05:04:06.240
Because if the news was spreading through

05:04:06.240 --> 05:04:09.060
the hive, WASP only needed to be inside

05:04:09.060 --> 05:04:11.939
one listening soldier, and then she'd

05:04:11.939 --> 05:04:14.220
realize, cricket must be here somewhere.

05:04:14.279 --> 05:04:18.000
And then she'd, Cadell's eyes flicked

05:04:18.000 --> 05:04:20.279
over to white, as though all the color

05:04:20.279 --> 05:04:21.959
had suddenly been leached out of her

05:04:21.959 --> 05:04:23.099
eyeballs.

05:04:23.159 --> 05:04:27.299
Aha, said the queen of the hive wings

05:04:27.299 --> 05:04:29.880
tipping Cadell's head toward cricket.

05:04:29.939 --> 05:04:31.680
There you are.

05:04:31.740 --> 05:04:36.479
Chapter 17.

05:04:36.659 --> 05:04:40.080
Cricket whirled and bolted up the

05:04:40.080 --> 05:04:40.439
stairs.

05:04:40.500 --> 05:04:43.319
Behind her, the queen laughed and laughed

05:04:43.319 --> 05:04:46.500
an eerie, awful cackle that was like

05:04:46.500 --> 05:04:48.119
something else trying to crawl out

05:04:48.119 --> 05:04:49.979
through Caddell's normal laugh.

05:04:50.040 --> 05:04:53.880
She made it to the next floor, just as 3

05:04:53.880 --> 05:04:56.220
more white eyed hive wings burst through

05:04:56.220 --> 05:04:59.099
the windows, shattering the shutters, and

05:04:59.099 --> 05:05:01.500
ripping down the dark gray curtains.

05:05:01.560 --> 05:05:04.080
Cricket threw the empty paint pot and

05:05:04.080 --> 05:05:06.419
paintbrush at them, splattering bright

05:05:06.419 --> 05:05:09.360
pink droplets everywhere, and hurtled up

05:05:09.360 --> 05:05:11.700
to the top level, across the guest room

05:05:11.700 --> 05:05:13.020
and out onto the balcony.

05:05:13.080 --> 05:05:16.740
Hive wings were swarming toward Caddell's

05:05:16.740 --> 05:05:16.979
house.

05:05:17.040 --> 05:05:19.560
She could see dragons on every street

05:05:19.560 --> 05:05:21.659
running or flying in her direction.

05:05:21.720 --> 05:05:24.599
The queen had watched cricket slipped

05:05:24.599 --> 05:05:25.799
through her claws at the temple of

05:05:25.799 --> 05:05:26.400
Clearsight.

05:05:26.459 --> 05:05:28.560
She wasn't going to let her escape

05:05:28.560 --> 05:05:28.740
again.

05:05:28.799 --> 05:05:32.580
Cricket threw herself off the balcony. and

05:05:32.580 --> 05:05:34.740
flew as hard as she could toward the open

05:05:34.740 --> 05:05:36.360
ledges that led to the savannah.

05:05:36.419 --> 05:05:38.700
I escaped the temple.

05:05:38.759 --> 05:05:40.139
I can do it again.

05:05:40.200 --> 05:05:42.060
If I fly and fly.

05:05:42.180 --> 05:05:45.540
But this time, she didn't have sun do

05:05:45.540 --> 05:05:48.180
with her, and the sky was too far away

05:05:48.180 --> 05:05:51.180
and there were too many hive wings, and

05:05:51.180 --> 05:05:52.799
the queen controlled them all.

05:05:52.860 --> 05:05:57.060
They came from everywhere, boiling up

05:05:57.060 --> 05:05:59.459
from the ground, and the windows and the

05:05:59.459 --> 05:06:02.279
ceilings, like an explosion of fire ants

05:06:02.279 --> 05:06:05.700
they were tiny dragonettes, and hulking

05:06:05.700 --> 05:06:08.400
soldiers. and glittering socialites in

05:06:08.400 --> 05:06:11.400
their jewels and sparkles and finery, but

05:06:11.400 --> 05:06:13.439
none of them were themselves anymore.

05:06:13.500 --> 05:06:15.900
They were a swarm.

05:06:15.959 --> 05:06:19.619
They were the 1000 claws of Queen Wasp.

05:06:19.680 --> 05:06:22.619
They had become mindless weapons.

05:06:22.680 --> 05:06:25.799
Cricket had been terrified of the white

05:06:25.799 --> 05:06:28.139
eyed dragons ever since that morning when

05:06:28.139 --> 05:06:29.459
she was 2 years old.

05:06:29.459 --> 05:06:32.340
Now she was the dragon they hunted.

05:06:32.400 --> 05:06:35.159
The dragon who didn't move in unison with

05:06:35.159 --> 05:06:37.799
everyone else, the dragon who couldn't

05:06:37.799 --> 05:06:38.040
escape.

05:06:38.099 --> 05:06:42.060
She felt talons slam into her back and

05:06:42.060 --> 05:06:42.840
throw her to the ground.

05:06:42.900 --> 05:06:46.380
A red striped hive wing shot a blast of

05:06:46.380 --> 05:06:49.259
acid that just missed her shoulder, and

05:06:49.259 --> 05:06:51.060
hissed into the tree stuff beside her

05:06:51.060 --> 05:06:51.299
head.

05:06:51.360 --> 05:06:54.840
As she tried to roll away, another drove

05:06:54.840 --> 05:06:57.000
his wrist stingers into the edge of her

05:06:57.000 --> 05:06:58.860
wings, pinning her to the ground.

05:06:58.919 --> 05:07:03.000
Cricket shrieked with pain as Caddell

05:07:03.000 --> 05:07:04.200
landed on her chest.

05:07:04.259 --> 05:07:07.319
Her grandmother did not look triumphant

05:07:07.319 --> 05:07:10.259
or enraged, or even interested.

05:07:10.319 --> 05:07:13.919
Her face was entirely blank, while she

05:07:13.919 --> 05:07:16.439
held down her granddaughter, so a black

05:07:16.439 --> 05:07:19.080
hive wing with yellow spots could shoot

05:07:19.080 --> 05:07:21.299
something painful and paralyzing into

05:07:21.299 --> 05:07:22.200
cricket's wings.

05:07:22.259 --> 05:07:24.900
Cricket turned her head away from

05:07:24.900 --> 05:07:28.259
Caddell's empty face, and saw silk wings

05:07:28.259 --> 05:07:29.939
watching from the windows and the

05:07:29.939 --> 05:07:31.259
sidewalks.

05:07:31.319 --> 05:07:32.700
Last chance.

05:07:32.819 --> 05:07:36.720
Through the haze of pain, she yelled, The

05:07:36.720 --> 05:07:37.799
queen is lying to you.

05:07:37.860 --> 05:07:40.860
The book never said she should rule you.

05:07:40.919 --> 05:07:42.779
It was all a lie.

05:07:42.900 --> 05:07:45.060
And she thought she saw something.

05:07:45.119 --> 05:07:50.700
Sympathy, confusion, surprise, flicker in

05:07:50.700 --> 05:07:51.119
their faces.

05:07:51.180 --> 05:07:54.419
And then the yellow spotted hive wing

05:07:54.419 --> 05:07:55.860
shoved his stinger into her neck.

05:07:55.919 --> 05:07:59.220
Her throat closed over the words she

05:07:59.220 --> 05:08:00.119
still wanted to say.

05:08:00.240 --> 05:08:04.439
Her vocal cords radiated with agony, and

05:08:04.439 --> 05:08:06.959
her head flopped over, her neck muscles

05:08:06.959 --> 05:08:08.459
refusing to work for her anymore.

05:08:08.520 --> 05:08:12.000
The hive wings seized her frozen wings

05:08:12.000 --> 05:08:14.580
and dragged her away. away from the

05:08:14.580 --> 05:08:16.979
frightened silk wing faces, and up the

05:08:16.979 --> 05:08:21.299
ramps, up and up and up, to the prison at

05:08:21.299 --> 05:08:23.220
the center of Lady Jules' palace.

05:08:23.279 --> 05:08:26.040
Every time Cricket thought about the

05:08:26.040 --> 05:08:29.400
library in Jewel Hive and thought, Maybe

05:08:29.400 --> 05:08:33.000
Lady Jewel isn't so bad after all, She

05:08:33.000 --> 05:08:34.680
always made herself remember the prison.

05:08:34.740 --> 05:08:37.259
Which Jewel had insisted on building

05:08:37.259 --> 05:08:40.080
within her own palace walls, instead of

05:08:40.080 --> 05:08:41.880
somewhere a civilized distance away.

05:08:41.939 --> 05:08:45.599
No one knew why she wanted her prison so

05:08:45.599 --> 05:08:48.659
close, or what happened to the dragons

05:08:48.659 --> 05:08:49.919
that disappeared inside it.

05:08:49.979 --> 05:08:52.740
I guess I'm about to find out.

05:08:52.799 --> 05:08:55.560
Cricket thought bleakly.

05:08:55.619 --> 05:08:58.020
As they passed through the blue and gold

05:08:58.020 --> 05:09:00.900
and beetle green, silk spangled gates of

05:09:00.900 --> 05:09:01.799
Jules Palace.

05:09:01.860 --> 05:09:05.099
All the walls inside seemed to be full of

05:09:05.099 --> 05:09:05.639
windows.

05:09:05.700 --> 05:09:08.520
So the gray afternoon light, and the

05:09:08.520 --> 05:09:10.860
sound of raindrops, and the scent of a

05:09:10.860 --> 05:09:13.439
storm carried through the entire palace.

05:09:13.500 --> 05:09:16.500
For a moment, the breeze brushed

05:09:16.500 --> 05:09:19.259
Cricket's face, whispering of the freedom

05:09:19.259 --> 05:09:19.740
outside.

05:09:19.799 --> 05:09:22.860
And then the hive wings descended a

05:09:22.860 --> 05:09:25.560
staircase, and crickets' wings scraped

05:09:25.560 --> 05:09:27.840
over the black stone threshold that

05:09:27.840 --> 05:09:30.299
marked the end of Jewel's public palace

05:09:30.299 --> 05:09:32.700
and the beginning of the secret prison.

05:09:32.759 --> 05:09:35.639
She wished she could lift her head to see

05:09:35.639 --> 05:09:38.099
where she was being taken, but all she

05:09:38.099 --> 05:09:40.080
could do was watch the scuffed floor pass

05:09:40.080 --> 05:09:40.680
below her.

05:09:40.740 --> 05:09:43.860
Scarred with long trails of desperate

05:09:43.860 --> 05:09:44.639
claw marks.

05:09:44.700 --> 05:09:48.659
Down here, there were no windows, and the

05:09:48.659 --> 05:09:50.459
flame silk lanterns were few and far

05:09:50.459 --> 05:09:52.979
between, leaving patches of darkness

05:09:52.979 --> 05:09:54.659
between dim pools of light.

05:09:54.720 --> 05:09:57.659
Cricket could hear mournful singing

05:09:57.659 --> 05:09:59.459
coming from one of the cells as they

05:09:59.459 --> 05:10:00.000
passed by.

05:10:00.060 --> 05:10:03.779
Another prisoner called to her, hey, what

05:10:03.779 --> 05:10:04.259
did you do?

05:10:04.319 --> 05:10:05.819
What did she do?

05:10:05.880 --> 05:10:07.259
Come on, tell me something.

05:10:07.319 --> 05:10:10.619
But she couldn't answer, and her guards

05:10:10.619 --> 05:10:11.220
ignored him.

05:10:11.340 --> 05:10:14.939
At the end of an interminable corridor

05:10:14.939 --> 05:10:17.099
the dragons holding her finally stopped

05:10:17.099 --> 05:10:18.779
and unlocked a cell.

05:10:18.840 --> 05:10:21.659
They tossed her inside and she fell face

05:10:21.659 --> 05:10:24.720
first, barely catching herself on numb

05:10:24.720 --> 05:10:27.360
talons before the weight of her paralyzed

05:10:27.360 --> 05:10:28.439
wings knocked her down.

05:10:28.500 --> 05:10:30.659
With an enormous effort.

05:10:30.779 --> 05:10:32.819
She rolled onto her back to see her

05:10:32.819 --> 05:10:33.299
captors.

05:10:33.419 --> 05:10:37.860
That was easier than I expected, said the

05:10:37.860 --> 05:10:40.139
Queen, as one of the hive wings locked

05:10:40.139 --> 05:10:40.439
the door.

05:10:40.500 --> 05:10:43.560
Another hive wing leaned against the bars

05:10:43.560 --> 05:10:44.700
grinning at her.

05:10:44.759 --> 05:10:47.340
The queen's voice came from both of them

05:10:47.340 --> 05:10:49.740
at once, which was still immensely

05:10:49.740 --> 05:10:50.279
creepy.

05:10:50.340 --> 05:10:53.700
You really were a fool to come back into

05:10:53.700 --> 05:10:54.479
a hive.

05:10:54.540 --> 05:10:55.619
And for what?

05:10:55.680 --> 05:10:57.720
A little bit of graffiti.

05:10:57.779 --> 05:11:00.659
A few pamphlets that will be ash by

05:11:00.659 --> 05:11:01.080
evening.

05:11:01.139 --> 05:11:05.279
Poor, naive little dragonette, as though

05:11:05.279 --> 05:11:07.080
anyone would believe you over their

05:11:07.080 --> 05:11:07.500
queen.

05:11:07.560 --> 05:11:10.200
Cricket couldn't speak.

05:11:10.259 --> 05:11:12.540
She wasn't sure she would have been able

05:11:12.540 --> 05:11:14.340
to, even if her throat hadn't been

05:11:14.340 --> 05:11:14.819
paralyzed.

05:11:14.939 --> 05:11:17.580
She'd never been so scared in her entire

05:11:17.580 --> 05:11:18.000
life.

05:11:18.060 --> 05:11:20.819
Except maybe the moment when the queen

05:11:20.819 --> 05:11:22.979
had seen her through the librarian's eyes

05:11:22.979 --> 05:11:26.040
and she'd realized her secret was lost

05:11:26.040 --> 05:11:26.459
forever.

05:11:26.520 --> 05:11:30.119
It must have been so hard for you.

05:11:30.240 --> 05:11:33.599
The queen went on, making one of the

05:11:33.599 --> 05:11:35.759
dragons run his claws along the bars.

05:11:35.819 --> 05:11:40.319
Feeling so different, so alone, watching

05:11:40.319 --> 05:11:42.720
everyone else come together in my hive

05:11:42.720 --> 05:11:45.180
mind, but always left out.

05:11:45.299 --> 05:11:49.319
The 2 hive wings leaned closer, and

05:11:49.319 --> 05:11:51.840
pressed their faces to the bars, as

05:11:51.840 --> 05:11:53.639
though she might force them to squeeze

05:11:53.639 --> 05:11:54.180
through.

05:11:54.240 --> 05:11:57.479
But I have good news for you, little

05:11:57.479 --> 05:11:58.139
dragon.

05:11:58.200 --> 05:12:00.840
You don't have to be different anymore.

05:12:00.900 --> 05:12:05.220
Their tongues flickered out and in and

05:12:05.220 --> 05:12:07.740
out in terrifying unison.

05:12:07.799 --> 05:12:11.700
I can fix you, hissed the queen.

05:12:11.759 --> 05:12:13.799
I'm on my way right now.

05:12:13.860 --> 05:12:17.700
And when I get there, I can make you just

05:12:17.700 --> 05:12:19.139
like everybody else.

05:12:19.200 --> 05:12:21.060
Aren't you lucky?

05:12:21.180 --> 05:12:25.439
The hive wings stepped back, their pale

05:12:25.439 --> 05:12:27.119
eyes still fixed on cricket.

05:12:27.180 --> 05:12:30.180
She felt a tear run down her face and

05:12:30.180 --> 05:12:31.619
couldn't do anything to stop it.

05:12:31.680 --> 05:12:36.000
See you soon, little problem dragon.

05:12:36.060 --> 05:12:39.419
The sound of their tails slithering away

05:12:39.419 --> 05:12:42.540
seemed to last forever, as cricket lay

05:12:42.540 --> 05:12:44.639
there, alone in the near dark.

05:12:44.759 --> 05:12:47.939
Sundew and blue weren't expecting her

05:12:47.939 --> 05:12:48.720
until sunset.

05:12:48.779 --> 05:12:51.000
They wouldn't even look for her until

05:12:51.000 --> 05:12:52.919
after the queen had already come and done

05:12:52.919 --> 05:12:55.500
whatever she was going to do.

05:12:55.560 --> 05:12:58.680
No one is coming to rescue me.

05:12:58.740 --> 05:13:01.200
They'll never find me in time.

05:13:01.259 --> 05:13:04.319
The queen is going to take my mind and

05:13:04.319 --> 05:13:05.340
make it hers.

05:13:05.400 --> 05:13:08.639
Cricket covered her ears and closed her

05:13:08.639 --> 05:13:11.759
eyes, and prayed to the only dragon who

05:13:11.759 --> 05:13:13.080
could possibly hear her.

05:13:13.139 --> 05:13:14.819
Clear sight.

05:13:14.880 --> 05:13:16.860
Please be listening.

05:13:16.919 --> 05:13:19.680
Please, please save me.

05:13:19.740 --> 05:13:24.240
Chapter 18.

05:13:24.599 --> 05:13:28.439
When cricket opened her eyes again, a

05:13:28.439 --> 05:13:31.020
long time later, almost midday, she

05:13:31.020 --> 05:13:31.560
sensed.

05:13:31.619 --> 05:13:34.020
There was an entirely new dragon standing

05:13:34.020 --> 05:13:36.599
outside the door of her cell. looking in

05:13:36.599 --> 05:13:37.680
with thoughtful curiosity.

05:13:37.740 --> 05:13:41.159
Seated next to her, with an enormously

05:13:41.159 --> 05:13:43.919
grumpy expression, was Lady Scarab.

05:13:43.979 --> 05:13:47.759
The new dragon was tall and angular, and

05:13:47.759 --> 05:13:49.680
her scales were a bright golden color

05:13:49.680 --> 05:13:52.500
that almost looked green in the low flame

05:13:52.500 --> 05:13:53.159
silk light.

05:13:53.279 --> 05:13:56.400
Thin lines of black scales outlined her

05:13:56.400 --> 05:13:58.919
iridescent green eyes, and dotted her

05:13:58.919 --> 05:13:59.520
cheekbones.

05:13:59.580 --> 05:14:02.520
More black lines traced the veins in her

05:14:02.520 --> 05:14:03.000
wings.

05:14:03.060 --> 05:14:06.119
Gold earrings shaped like beetles hung

05:14:06.119 --> 05:14:06.840
from her ears.

05:14:06.900 --> 05:14:10.139
A necklace of onyx stingers rested on her

05:14:10.139 --> 05:14:12.360
collarbone, and her claws were each

05:14:12.360 --> 05:14:14.939
painted with perfect lines of black and

05:14:14.939 --> 05:14:15.119
gold.

05:14:15.180 --> 05:14:18.479
Cricket had only seen her once before

05:14:18.479 --> 05:14:21.599
across a crowded ballroom, but it was not

05:14:21.599 --> 05:14:24.180
hard to guess that this was Lady Jewel

05:14:24.180 --> 05:14:27.060
ruler of Jewel Hive, daughter of Lady

05:14:27.060 --> 05:14:29.819
Scarab, and cousin to Queen Wasp.

05:14:29.880 --> 05:14:32.819
The way she held herself was all regal

05:14:32.819 --> 05:14:35.220
elegance, as if she were being painted.

05:14:35.279 --> 05:14:38.939
The only crack in her facade was that she

05:14:38.939 --> 05:14:40.619
winced a little every time her mother

05:14:40.619 --> 05:14:43.380
moved, and she seemed to be keeping half

05:14:43.380 --> 05:14:45.299
an eye on Lady Scarab at all times.

05:14:45.360 --> 05:14:48.779
Hmm, said Lady Jewel.

05:14:48.840 --> 05:14:51.419
So this is the dragon who's thrown my

05:14:51.419 --> 05:14:52.680
hive into such a tizzy.

05:14:52.740 --> 05:14:55.560
She tapped her chin with one long

05:14:55.560 --> 05:14:56.700
glittering claw.

05:14:56.759 --> 05:14:59.520
You're quite small to cause so much

05:14:59.520 --> 05:14:59.939
trouble.

05:15:00.000 --> 05:15:04.259
Small and brainless, Scarab snapped.

05:15:04.319 --> 05:15:08.520
Mother, Jules said in a warning tone.

05:15:08.639 --> 05:15:11.220
You promised you'd be quiet.

05:15:11.279 --> 05:15:13.619
Scarab growled.

05:15:13.680 --> 05:15:16.799
Cricket tried to sit up and discovered

05:15:16.799 --> 05:15:18.840
that the paralysis had worn off her wings

05:15:18.840 --> 05:15:21.599
and neck, although they still ached, and

05:15:21.599 --> 05:15:22.740
she had to move slowly.

05:15:22.799 --> 05:15:27.479
Lady Jewel, she said in a creaky voice.

05:15:27.540 --> 05:15:31.740
No need to bow, Jules said. waving her

05:15:31.740 --> 05:15:32.099
talons.

05:15:32.159 --> 05:15:35.279
Cricket settled back gratefully.

05:15:35.340 --> 05:15:37.740
Standing would have been a challenge, to

05:15:37.740 --> 05:15:38.459
say the least.

05:15:38.520 --> 05:15:40.860
What are you going to do to me?

05:15:40.860 --> 05:15:42.060
she whispered.

05:15:42.119 --> 05:15:45.959
That's a fine question to ask now.

05:15:46.020 --> 05:15:47.520
Scarab bellowed.

05:15:47.580 --> 05:15:52.139
Mother, Jules said, giving her a quelling

05:15:52.139 --> 05:15:52.380
look.

05:15:52.439 --> 05:15:54.779
Scarab glared at both of them and

05:15:54.779 --> 05:15:56.099
subsided, muttering.

05:15:56.159 --> 05:15:58.439
Jules smiled back at cricket.

05:15:58.500 --> 05:16:02.099
You mean the torture, the experiments, the

05:16:02.099 --> 05:16:02.939
vanishing prisoners?

05:16:03.060 --> 05:16:06.779
Jules sat down, coiling her long, shining

05:16:06.779 --> 05:16:07.680
tail around her legs.

05:16:07.740 --> 05:16:09.659
Not for you.

05:16:09.720 --> 05:16:11.759
The queen wants to handle you herself.

05:16:11.819 --> 05:16:15.060
She shrugged, with a faintly disappointed

05:16:15.060 --> 05:16:15.299
look.

05:16:15.360 --> 05:16:19.560
But if they were real, I would say you

05:16:19.560 --> 05:16:20.279
deserve them.

05:16:20.400 --> 05:16:21.959
Scarab interjected.

05:16:22.020 --> 05:16:23.580
Mother!

05:16:23.700 --> 05:16:26.520
Joel barked, as a prisoner a few doors

05:16:26.520 --> 05:16:28.200
down called, eh?

05:16:28.259 --> 05:16:29.040
Not real?

05:16:29.099 --> 05:16:29.700
What's that?

05:16:29.819 --> 05:16:32.939
Jewel did something carefully to her face

05:16:32.939 --> 05:16:35.639
like smoothing away the cross expression

05:16:35.639 --> 05:16:37.860
and replacing it with everlasting

05:16:37.860 --> 05:16:38.279
patience.

05:16:38.340 --> 05:16:42.959
My mother, she said to Cricket, is not

05:16:42.959 --> 05:16:45.060
normally allowed in my palace, for

05:16:45.060 --> 05:16:47.220
reasons that become clearer each time she

05:16:47.220 --> 05:16:48.060
does visit.

05:16:48.119 --> 05:16:51.419
She has no idea what I actually do with

05:16:51.419 --> 05:16:52.500
dragons in my prison.

05:16:52.560 --> 05:16:56.040
Right, snorted Lady Scarab.

05:16:56.099 --> 05:16:58.860
I'm sure my daughter, who once hid all

05:16:58.860 --> 05:17:01.560
mine knives because they scared her, has

05:17:01.560 --> 05:17:03.959
grown up to become a master torturer.

05:17:04.020 --> 05:17:05.159
What?

05:17:05.220 --> 05:17:06.000
Really?

05:17:06.060 --> 05:17:07.979
Called the nosy prisoner.

05:17:08.040 --> 05:17:11.159
Fain to the side of blood, this one

05:17:11.159 --> 05:17:13.560
Scarab added, jerking her head at her

05:17:13.560 --> 05:17:13.799
daughter.

05:17:13.919 --> 05:17:16.319
I was five.

05:17:16.439 --> 05:17:19.619
Lady Jewel closed her eyes and took a

05:17:19.619 --> 05:17:20.939
deep, calming breath.

05:17:21.000 --> 05:17:25.139
Let's talk about you, she said.

05:17:25.200 --> 05:17:27.180
Opening them again and looking at

05:17:27.180 --> 05:17:27.659
cricket.

05:17:27.720 --> 05:17:30.659
Do you know how hard it is to get paint

05:17:30.659 --> 05:17:31.860
out of tree stuff?

05:17:31.919 --> 05:17:34.560
I'm going to have pink smudges all over

05:17:34.560 --> 05:17:36.119
my hive forever now.

05:17:36.180 --> 05:17:40.919
And you lost my best paint brush, didn't

05:17:40.919 --> 05:17:41.099
you?

05:17:41.159 --> 05:17:43.680
Scarab said, lashing her tail.

05:17:43.740 --> 05:17:47.099
Not that my mother had anything to do

05:17:47.099 --> 05:17:47.459
with this.

05:17:47.580 --> 05:17:49.500
Jewel added quickly.

05:17:49.560 --> 05:17:51.959
Should have given you an old one.

05:17:52.080 --> 05:17:53.700
Scarab growled.

05:17:53.819 --> 05:17:56.520
But you weren't supposed to get caught

05:17:56.520 --> 05:17:57.360
you idiot.

05:17:57.419 --> 05:18:00.000
Oh my gosh, mom, seriously.

05:18:00.060 --> 05:18:02.340
Joel flapped her wings.

05:18:02.400 --> 05:18:04.979
The royal stands entirely collapsing.

05:18:05.099 --> 05:18:08.099
I am trying to be menacing and

05:18:08.099 --> 05:18:08.939
mysterious.

05:18:09.000 --> 05:18:12.000
Could you be quiet for 12nd while I

05:18:12.000 --> 05:18:12.599
handle this?

05:18:12.659 --> 05:18:13.979
With what?

05:18:14.099 --> 05:18:16.560
A new necklace and a party?

05:18:16.619 --> 05:18:17.939
Scarab grumbled.

05:18:18.000 --> 05:18:21.419
You may not have noticed, but somehow I

05:18:21.419 --> 05:18:25.139
managed to be a very good hive ruler, even

05:18:25.139 --> 05:18:28.680
I would say, especially, when you and

05:18:28.680 --> 05:18:30.540
your advice are on the other side of the

05:18:30.540 --> 05:18:31.080
continent.

05:18:31.080 --> 05:18:34.740
Hmm, Scarab said disapprovingly.

05:18:34.799 --> 05:18:37.439
The glitter bazaar would be better if

05:18:37.439 --> 05:18:38.220
you'd listened to me.

05:18:38.340 --> 05:18:41.279
The glitter bazaar is fine.

05:18:41.340 --> 05:18:45.000
And your schools have absolutely rubbish

05:18:45.000 --> 05:18:45.959
history programs.

05:18:46.020 --> 05:18:47.939
That's not up to me.

05:18:48.000 --> 05:18:50.580
Queen Wasp sets the curriculums.

05:18:50.639 --> 05:18:52.979
Why do you think I have a giant library

05:18:52.979 --> 05:18:55.319
full of history books for my subjects?

05:18:55.380 --> 05:18:58.080
And that table in the front hall?

05:18:58.139 --> 05:18:59.580
is still in the wrong place.

05:18:59.700 --> 05:19:01.500
Scarab went on.

05:19:01.560 --> 05:19:04.080
It would be much more useful as a

05:19:04.080 --> 05:19:05.400
sideboard in the dining room.

05:19:05.459 --> 05:19:08.580
Joel pressed her claws to her forehead.

05:19:08.639 --> 05:19:11.279
Mother, she said.

05:19:11.340 --> 05:19:13.979
Maybe you should go visit with your

05:19:13.979 --> 05:19:14.580
grandchildren.

05:19:14.700 --> 05:19:17.099
Not on your life.

05:19:17.159 --> 05:19:19.080
Scarab said promptly.

05:19:19.139 --> 05:19:22.680
Those brats are very loud, and I will not

05:19:22.680 --> 05:19:24.479
be tricked into dragonette sitting.

05:19:24.540 --> 05:19:27.180
Stop distracting me and get on with

05:19:27.180 --> 05:19:28.680
interrogating this nitwit.

05:19:28.799 --> 05:19:31.860
That's what I'm trying to.

05:19:32.159 --> 05:19:34.860
Jules stopped and took another deep

05:19:34.860 --> 05:19:35.459
breath.

05:19:35.520 --> 05:19:38.520
She turned toward Cricket with a

05:19:38.520 --> 05:19:40.319
resolutely serene expression.

05:19:40.380 --> 05:19:41.939
You.

05:19:42.060 --> 05:19:44.159
Cricket, right?

05:19:44.220 --> 05:19:48.540
Yes, that's me, Cricket said.

05:19:48.599 --> 05:19:50.099
Did you read my messages?

05:19:50.159 --> 05:19:51.779
I'm telling the truth.

05:19:51.840 --> 05:19:54.240
Queen Wasp is lying about the book of

05:19:54.240 --> 05:19:54.900
Clearsight.

05:19:54.959 --> 05:19:58.380
I've always suspected that, Jules said.

05:19:58.439 --> 05:20:01.680
Some of our great, great, great, great

05:20:01.680 --> 05:20:04.319
grandmothers were not as quick and clever

05:20:04.319 --> 05:20:06.060
with their lies as WASP has been.

05:20:06.119 --> 05:20:08.880
There were hints in the history books, if

05:20:08.880 --> 05:20:09.840
anyone looked carefully.

05:20:09.900 --> 05:20:11.639
The books?

05:20:11.759 --> 05:20:13.860
I do read.

05:20:13.979 --> 05:20:18.000
Jules smiled, more or less a tiny quirk

05:20:18.000 --> 05:20:20.580
of her mouth, despite the rumors to the

05:20:20.580 --> 05:20:21.000
contrary.

05:20:21.060 --> 05:20:24.000
I'd be quite interested to read the Book

05:20:24.000 --> 05:20:24.720
of Clearsight.

05:20:24.840 --> 05:20:28.500
I don't have it, Cricket confessed.

05:20:28.560 --> 05:20:32.279
Loved it with someone smart enough not to

05:20:32.279 --> 05:20:32.759
get caught.

05:20:32.819 --> 05:20:33.959
I hope.

05:20:34.020 --> 05:20:36.119
Scarab chimed in again.

05:20:36.180 --> 05:20:40.439
She says, there's no line of hive wing

05:20:40.439 --> 05:20:42.360
succession in there, sparkles.

05:20:42.419 --> 05:20:43.740
You know what that means.

05:20:43.860 --> 05:20:48.360
That you could have been queen, Joel said

05:20:48.360 --> 05:20:48.900
with a sigh.

05:20:49.020 --> 05:20:54.000
That you could still be queen, Scarab

05:20:54.000 --> 05:20:54.599
said fiercely.

05:20:54.659 --> 05:20:58.200
With my help, of course, or else you'd

05:20:58.200 --> 05:20:59.040
probably do it all wrong.

05:20:59.099 --> 05:21:02.159
Paint all the hives rainbow colors or

05:21:02.159 --> 05:21:02.400
something.

05:21:02.459 --> 05:21:06.479
Oh, for the mother, you can't say things

05:21:06.479 --> 05:21:06.840
like that.

05:21:06.959 --> 05:21:09.720
Jewel leaned back to check up and down

05:21:09.720 --> 05:21:10.200
the corridor.

05:21:10.319 --> 05:21:13.020
The guards are all the way back of the

05:21:13.020 --> 05:21:15.900
entrance, Scarab said, flipping her tail

05:21:15.900 --> 05:21:17.040
from side to side.

05:21:17.099 --> 05:21:18.840
They can't hear us.

05:21:18.900 --> 05:21:22.319
I can, called the prisoner.

05:21:22.380 --> 05:21:26.279
You're a silkwing, Scarab called back.

05:21:26.340 --> 05:21:28.680
True, he answered.

05:21:28.740 --> 05:21:29.340
True.

05:21:29.459 --> 05:21:31.200
Lady Joel.

05:21:31.259 --> 05:21:33.000
Cricket said hesitantly.

05:21:33.119 --> 05:21:36.720
May I ask, is my sister all right?

05:21:36.779 --> 05:21:40.020
She caught herself, remembering.

05:21:40.080 --> 05:21:43.020
It still felt too strange to call Katy

05:21:43.020 --> 05:21:43.740
did her mother.

05:21:43.799 --> 05:21:45.360
Katie did.

05:21:45.419 --> 05:21:48.000
She was brought in last night before me.

05:21:48.060 --> 05:21:51.959
She'll be fine, Joel said. with

05:21:51.959 --> 05:21:53.220
surprising gentleness.

05:21:53.279 --> 05:21:56.400
The queen is less interested in her now

05:21:56.400 --> 05:21:57.000
that we have you.

05:21:57.060 --> 05:21:59.939
I will find out what she knows, which I

05:21:59.939 --> 05:22:02.159
assume is nothing, and release her before

05:22:02.159 --> 05:22:03.180
Wasp arrives.

05:22:03.240 --> 05:22:06.900
And that will be when, Scarab demanded.

05:22:06.959 --> 05:22:10.979
Very soon, Jewel answered, which, thank

05:22:10.979 --> 05:22:12.000
you so much for that.

05:22:12.060 --> 05:22:14.880
I was supposed to have another 3 days to

05:22:14.880 --> 05:22:16.979
prepare before her usual nest to visit.

05:22:17.099 --> 05:22:19.619
She...

05:22:19.619 --> 05:22:23.459
She said she's coming to fix me, Cricket

05:22:23.459 --> 05:22:25.979
said, to make me like everyone else.

05:22:26.040 --> 05:22:27.299
Can she do that?

05:22:27.360 --> 05:22:30.900
Joel glanced at her mother, pausing for a

05:22:30.900 --> 05:22:31.080
moment.

05:22:31.139 --> 05:22:32.520
Yes.

05:22:32.580 --> 05:22:34.139
She's done it before.

05:22:34.200 --> 05:22:35.639
What?

05:22:35.700 --> 05:22:37.439
Lady Scarab spat.

05:22:37.500 --> 05:22:38.880
You never told me that.

05:22:39.000 --> 05:22:43.860
It doesn't always work, Jules said, and I

05:22:43.860 --> 05:22:44.880
don't know how she does it.

05:22:45.000 --> 05:22:47.220
But we had a pair of dragons in here a

05:22:47.220 --> 05:22:49.500
few years ago, who'd been preparing a

05:22:49.500 --> 05:22:51.060
case for flame silk rights.

05:22:51.119 --> 05:22:54.299
They were pretty old, nearly as old as

05:22:54.299 --> 05:22:54.720
you mother.

05:22:54.840 --> 05:22:59.279
So, perhaps not total idiots then, Scarab

05:22:59.279 --> 05:22:59.759
snapped.

05:22:59.819 --> 05:23:02.279
Sure, Jules said.

05:23:02.340 --> 05:23:04.680
They said they remembered a time when

05:23:04.680 --> 05:23:06.720
flame silks were treated like normal

05:23:06.720 --> 05:23:09.240
members of the community, selling their

05:23:09.240 --> 05:23:11.279
flame silk and living like anyone else.

05:23:11.340 --> 05:23:14.939
Anyway, Wasp didn't like that very much.

05:23:15.000 --> 05:23:18.540
So she made my guard to drag them in, and

05:23:18.540 --> 05:23:20.159
she came by and took them into a closed

05:23:20.159 --> 05:23:21.119
room for a while.

05:23:21.180 --> 05:23:24.000
And when they came back out, their eyes

05:23:24.000 --> 05:23:24.419
were white.

05:23:24.479 --> 05:23:27.540
And they never argued against the queen

05:23:27.540 --> 05:23:27.779
again.

05:23:27.900 --> 05:23:29.939
I take it back.

05:23:30.000 --> 05:23:31.560
Scarab huffed.

05:23:31.619 --> 05:23:33.479
Total idiots after all.

05:23:33.540 --> 05:23:37.439
So, every time she threatens to add you

05:23:37.439 --> 05:23:39.060
to her hive mind.

05:23:39.119 --> 05:23:42.180
She might actually be able to.

05:23:42.299 --> 05:23:43.439
Jules said.

05:23:43.500 --> 05:23:47.459
But you don't know how, Cricket said, or

05:23:47.459 --> 05:23:48.240
what she does to them.

05:23:48.299 --> 05:23:50.520
Jewel shook her head.

05:23:50.639 --> 05:23:53.400
I know it doesn't work if they have

05:23:53.400 --> 05:23:55.380
silkwing ancestors in the last 3

05:23:55.380 --> 05:23:56.279
generations though.

05:23:56.340 --> 05:23:59.459
She keeps all those old dragons penned up

05:23:59.459 --> 05:24:00.659
together in Setsy Hive.

05:24:00.720 --> 05:24:04.319
You didn't tell me that either, Scara

05:24:04.319 --> 05:24:04.860
barked.

05:24:04.919 --> 05:24:08.819
Of course I didn't, Jules said, flicking

05:24:08.819 --> 05:24:09.720
her wings at her mother.

05:24:09.779 --> 05:24:12.479
I was afraid you'd go over there and

05:24:12.479 --> 05:24:15.240
storm around with a protest sign and get

05:24:15.240 --> 05:24:16.380
yourself thrown in with them.

05:24:16.439 --> 05:24:20.159
To right, said Scarab.

05:24:20.220 --> 05:24:22.680
Someone needs to give my niece a good

05:24:22.680 --> 05:24:23.279
thumping.

05:24:23.340 --> 05:24:27.060
Well, I would like you to stay in control

05:24:27.060 --> 05:24:28.200
of your own brain.

05:24:28.259 --> 05:24:31.979
As annoying as that brain is, mother, so

05:24:31.979 --> 05:24:34.439
I would appreciate it if you could not go

05:24:34.439 --> 05:24:36.540
thumping the queen of our tribe anytime

05:24:36.540 --> 05:24:36.720
soon.

05:24:36.779 --> 05:24:39.900
If someone doesn't thump her soon.

05:24:39.959 --> 05:24:42.779
We won't have any dragons left who can.

05:24:42.900 --> 05:24:46.380
Scarab growled softly to herself, and

05:24:46.380 --> 05:24:48.000
paced off down the corridor.

05:24:48.060 --> 05:24:51.000
Cricket tried to stretch the pain out of

05:24:51.000 --> 05:24:52.919
her wings and neck as she thought.

05:24:52.979 --> 05:24:55.979
The queen could do something to dragons

05:24:55.979 --> 05:24:58.560
behind closed doors to make them part of

05:24:58.560 --> 05:24:59.580
her hive mind.

05:24:59.639 --> 05:25:01.799
But surely she hadn't gone to every

05:25:01.799 --> 05:25:05.040
dragon in every hive to do it, one at a

05:25:05.040 --> 05:25:07.919
time, 1000s of dragons over 50 years.

05:25:07.979 --> 05:25:10.740
For one thing, dragons would remember

05:25:10.740 --> 05:25:12.959
that happening, so everyone would know

05:25:12.959 --> 05:25:13.619
how she did it.

05:25:13.740 --> 05:25:16.380
Katydid would have remembered surely.

05:25:16.500 --> 05:25:19.020
And dragons would slip through the cracks

05:25:19.020 --> 05:25:21.479
and Queen Wasp just couldn't possibly

05:25:21.479 --> 05:25:23.639
have time to get to every hive wing that

05:25:23.639 --> 05:25:23.819
way.

05:25:23.880 --> 05:25:25.560
Wait.

05:25:25.619 --> 05:25:28.439
Lady Jewel, Cricket said.

05:25:28.500 --> 05:25:30.779
Did you say something about the queen

05:25:30.779 --> 05:25:33.419
coming for a nest visit?

05:25:33.479 --> 05:25:34.799
Yes.

05:25:34.860 --> 05:25:38.159
Jewel tipped her head, studying cricket.

05:25:38.220 --> 05:25:41.040
She visits the hive nests twice a year.

05:25:41.159 --> 05:25:44.279
Once in the dry season, once in the rainy

05:25:44.279 --> 05:25:44.639
season.

05:25:44.700 --> 05:25:47.520
To ensure that they're clean and safe and

05:25:47.520 --> 05:25:49.799
full of eggs, according to her rules.

05:25:49.860 --> 05:25:52.740
Do you go into the nest with her?

05:25:52.799 --> 05:25:53.939
Cricket asked.

05:25:54.000 --> 05:25:55.200
No.

05:25:55.259 --> 05:25:57.479
She always goes alone.

05:25:57.540 --> 05:26:00.840
Jewel tapped her claws on the floor.

05:26:00.900 --> 05:26:02.099
Hmm.

05:26:02.220 --> 05:26:04.919
Scarab reappeared at the bars.

05:26:04.979 --> 05:26:08.040
I'm sensing the development of another

05:26:08.040 --> 05:26:09.479
completely stupid plan.

05:26:09.540 --> 05:26:13.139
Cricket got herself to stand. and stepped

05:26:13.139 --> 05:26:14.279
toward the leader of the hive.

05:26:14.340 --> 05:26:18.540
Lady Jewel, she said, please let me out

05:26:18.540 --> 05:26:21.180
of here, and I promise I'll find out what

05:26:21.180 --> 05:26:22.439
she does in the nests.

05:26:22.560 --> 05:26:25.560
If I'm right, and it has something to do

05:26:25.560 --> 05:26:28.020
with the mind control, maybe we can

05:26:28.020 --> 05:26:29.099
figure out a way to stop her.

05:26:29.159 --> 05:26:32.880
I can't let you out, little Dragonette

05:26:32.880 --> 05:26:33.840
Jules said.

05:26:33.900 --> 05:26:36.299
As much as I might be tempted to.

05:26:36.360 --> 05:26:39.419
Queen Wasp would punish my guards most

05:26:39.419 --> 05:26:41.700
severely, and they are loyal to me when

05:26:41.700 --> 05:26:42.779
their minds are their own.

05:26:42.779 --> 05:26:44.400
They don't deserve that.

05:26:44.459 --> 05:26:48.060
So put those 2 you don't like on duty

05:26:48.060 --> 05:26:49.619
Scarab suggested.

05:26:49.680 --> 05:26:53.279
The oily ones, who are probably spying on

05:26:53.279 --> 05:26:54.119
you for the queen.

05:26:54.180 --> 05:26:57.360
Joel narrowed her eyes at her mother for

05:26:57.360 --> 05:26:58.139
a long moment.

05:26:58.200 --> 05:27:01.259
Hmm, she said at length.

05:27:01.380 --> 05:27:03.540
That might actually work.

05:27:03.599 --> 05:27:05.580
See?

05:27:05.700 --> 05:27:07.500
Scarab said triumphantly.

05:27:07.560 --> 05:27:10.860
I am full of good advice, if you actually

05:27:10.860 --> 05:27:11.279
listen.

05:27:11.340 --> 05:27:13.680
By the book, mother.

05:27:13.799 --> 05:27:15.180
I listen to you all the time.

05:27:15.240 --> 05:27:18.659
Not about those dragonettes of yours, you

05:27:18.659 --> 05:27:19.020
don't.

05:27:19.080 --> 05:27:21.779
Oof, they are a disaster.

05:27:21.840 --> 05:27:23.880
They are not.

05:27:24.119 --> 05:27:26.400
This is not productive.

05:27:26.459 --> 05:27:29.759
Jewel closed her eyes and robbed her

05:27:29.759 --> 05:27:30.540
temples for a moment.

05:27:30.599 --> 05:27:33.299
You can only control yourself.

05:27:33.360 --> 05:27:35.819
You can only control yourself.

05:27:35.880 --> 05:27:37.439
She murmured.

05:27:37.500 --> 05:27:38.700
All right.

05:27:38.759 --> 05:27:42.180
Let's say I do put those sneaks on guard

05:27:42.180 --> 05:27:42.540
duty.

05:27:42.599 --> 05:27:44.700
How would we get her past them?

05:27:44.759 --> 05:27:46.740
Cricket glanced around her cell.

05:27:46.799 --> 05:27:50.819
Could I go out another way instead of

05:27:50.819 --> 05:27:52.319
through the prison gate?

05:27:52.319 --> 05:27:53.279
Up or down maybe?

05:27:53.340 --> 05:27:56.220
She scratched the tree stuff below her.

05:27:56.279 --> 05:27:59.580
Down would drop you into root worms

05:27:59.580 --> 05:28:02.099
ballroom, and she would not be pleased

05:28:02.099 --> 05:28:02.520
about that.

05:28:02.580 --> 05:28:06.119
Lady Jewel looked up at the ceiling, her

05:28:06.119 --> 05:28:08.220
eyes darting around as though she was

05:28:08.220 --> 05:28:09.479
measuring the space in her head.

05:28:09.540 --> 05:28:13.919
Up. I think you'd end up in my kitchens

05:28:13.919 --> 05:28:15.419
or close to them.

05:28:15.479 --> 05:28:18.240
I don't really want a hole in my kitchen

05:28:18.240 --> 05:28:20.400
floor that looks down into a prison cell

05:28:20.400 --> 05:28:22.619
but I suppose there are dragons up there

05:28:22.619 --> 05:28:24.000
who could help you get out of the

05:28:24.000 --> 05:28:24.419
palace.

05:28:24.540 --> 05:28:26.939
She tapped her claws again.

05:28:27.000 --> 05:28:30.240
How can I make a hole in tree stuff?

05:28:30.360 --> 05:28:32.159
Cricket said thoughtfully.

05:28:32.220 --> 05:28:35.580
A hammer, or something heavy would do it

05:28:35.580 --> 05:28:38.159
but it would take a while, and the noise

05:28:38.159 --> 05:28:39.060
would bring the guards.

05:28:39.119 --> 05:28:42.959
She studied the walls, the bars, the

05:28:42.959 --> 05:28:43.740
corridor outside.

05:28:43.799 --> 05:28:47.580
Flame silk, flame silk might work.

05:28:47.639 --> 05:28:51.419
Or it might burn down my palace, Joel

05:28:51.419 --> 05:28:52.080
pointed out.

05:28:52.139 --> 05:28:55.380
I'd be careful, Cricket promised.

05:28:55.439 --> 05:28:59.099
And, Scarab observed, with unusual

05:28:59.099 --> 05:29:02.159
cheerfulness, then Wasp would think her

05:29:02.159 --> 05:29:03.900
flame silk friend broke in to get her

05:29:03.900 --> 05:29:04.139
out.

05:29:04.200 --> 05:29:06.360
Can't hardly blame you for that.

05:29:06.419 --> 05:29:09.000
After she lost them twice in her own

05:29:09.000 --> 05:29:09.360
hive.

05:29:09.419 --> 05:29:12.959
I suspect Wasp can find a way to blame me

05:29:12.959 --> 05:29:14.819
no matter what, Jules said.

05:29:14.880 --> 05:29:18.900
Isn't this why you act like such a vapid

05:29:18.900 --> 05:29:20.340
banana slog around her?

05:29:20.400 --> 05:29:23.580
Scarab asked, flapping her wings, so

05:29:23.580 --> 05:29:25.619
she'll think you're a harmless idiot, and

05:29:25.619 --> 05:29:26.340
leave you in peace.

05:29:26.400 --> 05:29:29.580
I do not, Joel protested.

05:29:29.639 --> 05:29:32.400
Ah said Scarab.

05:29:32.459 --> 05:29:35.159
So you actually are a harmless idiot.

05:29:35.220 --> 05:29:37.740
Joel shot her mother a cross look.

05:29:37.799 --> 05:29:40.200
The point is, yes.

05:29:40.319 --> 05:29:43.080
Wasp would not be at all surprised if I

05:29:43.080 --> 05:29:45.360
lost a dragon from my prisons, because

05:29:45.360 --> 05:29:47.159
she thinks I have nothing but pollen

05:29:47.159 --> 05:29:47.819
between my ears.

05:29:47.880 --> 05:29:50.459
That doesn't mean she won't be furious

05:29:50.459 --> 05:29:52.380
and perfectly nasty to me.

05:29:52.439 --> 05:29:56.279
Perfectly nasty, is Wasp's natural

05:29:56.279 --> 05:29:59.099
resting state, Scarab observed.

05:29:59.159 --> 05:30:00.479
You'll survive it.

05:30:00.599 --> 05:30:03.540
I say it's worth it to keep one more hive

05:30:03.540 --> 05:30:04.139
wing free.

05:30:04.200 --> 05:30:06.540
She nodded at cricket.

05:30:06.599 --> 05:30:09.900
Sneaking into the nest and spying on the

05:30:09.900 --> 05:30:12.360
queen, on the other talon, sounds like

05:30:12.360 --> 05:30:13.319
the height of stupid.

05:30:13.380 --> 05:30:16.740
That's the deal, Jules said firmly.

05:30:16.860 --> 05:30:19.740
I want to follow this theory, and I can't

05:30:19.740 --> 05:30:20.340
do it myself.

05:30:20.400 --> 05:30:22.200
She'll have eyes on me.

05:30:22.259 --> 05:30:25.439
I want to know the truth too, Cricket

05:30:25.439 --> 05:30:27.659
said, wrapping her talons around the

05:30:27.659 --> 05:30:28.020
bars.

05:30:28.080 --> 05:30:30.540
It's all right, Lady Scarab.

05:30:30.599 --> 05:30:31.560
I want to do this.

05:30:31.619 --> 05:30:33.779
I think we'll find answers in there.

05:30:33.840 --> 05:30:34.799
I really do.

05:30:34.860 --> 05:30:37.860
Scarab looked from her daughter to

05:30:37.860 --> 05:30:40.680
cricket and back, then flung her wings up

05:30:40.680 --> 05:30:41.459
with a snort.

05:30:41.520 --> 05:30:42.779
Fine.

05:30:42.840 --> 05:30:45.540
Let's get this daft dragonette, some

05:30:45.540 --> 05:30:46.200
flame silk.

05:30:46.319 --> 05:30:50.639
Chapter 19.

05:30:50.880 --> 05:30:55.139
Cricket waited, as she'd been instructed

05:30:55.139 --> 05:30:57.479
until Lady Jewel and Scarab were long

05:30:57.479 --> 05:30:57.840
gone.

05:30:57.900 --> 05:31:00.360
Long enough for Jewel to have replaced

05:31:00.360 --> 05:31:01.979
the guards at the front entrance of the

05:31:01.979 --> 05:31:02.279
prison.

05:31:02.400 --> 05:31:05.220
Then she took out the little stone pot of

05:31:05.220 --> 05:31:06.779
flame silk that Jewel had left with her.

05:31:06.900 --> 05:31:09.900
The golden thread inside glowed bright

05:31:09.900 --> 05:31:10.439
and hot.

05:31:10.500 --> 05:31:12.240
She guessed it was very new.

05:31:12.299 --> 05:31:15.900
Maybe it's even blues, she thought.

05:31:15.959 --> 05:31:18.599
Maybe one of the dragons in the market

05:31:18.599 --> 05:31:20.880
traded it up through the hive yesterday

05:31:20.880 --> 05:31:23.700
so it wound up here in Jules' palace.

05:31:23.759 --> 05:31:27.000
She liked that thought, that maybe a

05:31:27.000 --> 05:31:28.380
little piece of blue was going to help

05:31:28.380 --> 05:31:28.860
her escape.

05:31:28.919 --> 05:31:32.220
She still had the flame silk tweezers

05:31:32.220 --> 05:31:34.560
she'd taken from her school library the

05:31:34.560 --> 05:31:35.819
night she ran away with Blue.

05:31:35.880 --> 05:31:37.200
Carefully.

05:31:37.259 --> 05:31:39.540
She used them to twist the thread of

05:31:39.540 --> 05:31:42.119
flame silk until it was straight and taut

05:31:42.119 --> 05:31:44.700
like a wire, and then she lifted the

05:31:44.700 --> 05:31:46.919
thread out, and flew up to the ceiling.

05:31:46.979 --> 05:31:50.159
It was very awkward, trying to keep

05:31:50.159 --> 05:31:52.799
herself in the air, nearly upside down

05:31:52.799 --> 05:31:54.900
and work on the ceiling without dropping

05:31:54.900 --> 05:31:55.860
the flame silk thread.

05:31:55.979 --> 05:31:58.560
She traced out a circle big enough for

05:31:58.560 --> 05:32:00.479
her to fit through, leaving a black

05:32:00.479 --> 05:32:03.180
smoking line, with small flickers of

05:32:03.180 --> 05:32:05.819
flame curling from a few of the edges.

05:32:05.880 --> 05:32:08.159
Then she traced it again, and again

05:32:08.159 --> 05:32:10.860
pressing the flame silk farther into the

05:32:10.860 --> 05:32:11.459
tree stuff.

05:32:11.520 --> 05:32:14.700
She knew tree stuff was made of bits of

05:32:14.700 --> 05:32:17.700
wood pulp, silk, and clay, and she

05:32:17.700 --> 05:32:19.860
guessed that how quickly it burned would

05:32:19.860 --> 05:32:21.720
depend on how much of each was in this

05:32:21.720 --> 05:32:22.799
section of the ceiling.

05:32:22.919 --> 05:32:26.099
Tracing the lines seemed to take forever

05:32:26.099 --> 05:32:29.520
around and around, over and over again.

05:32:29.580 --> 05:32:33.119
Her wings started to ache, and she had to

05:32:33.119 --> 05:32:34.740
land back on the floor for a little while

05:32:34.740 --> 05:32:35.459
to rest them.

05:32:35.520 --> 05:32:39.000
Psst, called a voice from the hallway.

05:32:39.060 --> 05:32:41.759
Cricket edged over to the bars and tried

05:32:41.759 --> 05:32:42.540
to peer out.

05:32:42.599 --> 05:32:45.540
She could see light purple talons waving

05:32:45.540 --> 05:32:46.919
from a cell a few doors away.

05:32:46.979 --> 05:32:49.919
Yes, she whispered back.

05:32:49.979 --> 05:32:53.040
I didn't catch all that, said the

05:32:53.040 --> 05:32:55.439
prisoner, but if I want to stay on Lady

05:32:55.439 --> 05:32:59.580
Jules good side, and I fervently do, what

05:32:59.580 --> 05:33:01.200
should I say to the queen when she asks

05:33:01.200 --> 05:33:02.159
me how you escaped?

05:33:02.220 --> 05:33:04.860
Cricket was silent for a moment

05:33:04.860 --> 05:33:05.759
worrying.

05:33:05.819 --> 05:33:08.939
Why wouldn't you tell the queen what you

05:33:08.939 --> 05:33:09.360
heard?

05:33:09.360 --> 05:33:10.200
she asked.

05:33:10.259 --> 05:33:13.799
Because Lady Jewel is the only ruler in

05:33:13.799 --> 05:33:16.020
the hives who can be trusted, the

05:33:16.020 --> 05:33:17.159
Silkwing whispered back.

05:33:17.220 --> 05:33:20.279
Queen Wasp has no sense of mercy or

05:33:20.279 --> 05:33:20.880
justice.

05:33:20.939 --> 05:33:24.060
I'm due to be released tomorrow, and I

05:33:24.060 --> 05:33:25.619
think Lady Jewel will be fair with me.

05:33:25.680 --> 05:33:28.799
I think so too, Cricket said.

05:33:28.919 --> 05:33:31.560
Wondering now about the stories of Jules

05:33:31.560 --> 05:33:32.099
prison.

05:33:32.159 --> 05:33:34.560
What if the dragons who disappeared in

05:33:34.560 --> 05:33:36.840
here were actually spirited away to

05:33:36.840 --> 05:33:39.360
safety by Jewel, to keep them out of the

05:33:39.360 --> 05:33:40.380
queen's talons?

05:33:40.439 --> 05:33:43.259
She led the queen and everyone else think

05:33:43.259 --> 05:33:45.299
that cruel, secretive things went on

05:33:45.299 --> 05:33:47.939
behind the prison doors, but perhaps that

05:33:47.939 --> 05:33:49.860
was a clever way to conceal what she

05:33:49.860 --> 05:33:51.419
really did for dragons in trouble.

05:33:51.479 --> 05:33:53.700
What are you in here for?

05:33:53.759 --> 05:33:54.900
Cricket asked.

05:33:55.020 --> 05:33:59.340
Not paying my library fines, the dragon

05:33:59.340 --> 05:34:00.240
answered ruefully.

05:34:00.360 --> 05:34:02.880
Cricket wished he could see her smile.

05:34:02.939 --> 05:34:06.299
If you could tell the queen, she said

05:34:06.299 --> 05:34:09.119
that you think you heard a dragon burn a

05:34:09.119 --> 05:34:10.919
hole in my ceiling from the other side

05:34:10.919 --> 05:34:12.840
that would be very helpful.

05:34:12.900 --> 05:34:15.540
I could do that, he said.

05:34:15.599 --> 05:34:18.599
And when you saw this dragon, you shouted

05:34:18.599 --> 05:34:21.000
Blue, Cricket said.

05:34:21.060 --> 05:34:22.740
She'll expect it was him.

05:34:22.799 --> 05:34:27.119
Good luck, the prisoner said, waving his

05:34:27.119 --> 05:34:28.319
talent through the bars again.

05:34:28.439 --> 05:34:31.919
Cricket returned to the scorched line in

05:34:31.919 --> 05:34:34.139
the ceiling, burning it again and again.

05:34:34.200 --> 05:34:36.779
She didn't know how long it took to fly

05:34:36.779 --> 05:34:39.659
from Wasp Hive to Jewel Hive, but she

05:34:39.659 --> 05:34:41.279
felt the queen drawing closer with every

05:34:41.279 --> 05:34:41.880
heartbeat.

05:34:41.939 --> 05:34:43.380
She had to hurry.

05:34:43.439 --> 05:34:46.319
Finally, she felt that thread

05:34:46.319 --> 05:34:48.180
breakthrough into open space on the other

05:34:48.180 --> 05:34:49.020
side of the ceiling.

05:34:49.139 --> 05:34:51.959
The circle of tree stuff trembled above

05:34:51.959 --> 05:34:54.900
her, barely hanging in place, and she

05:34:54.900 --> 05:34:56.099
shoved it hard with her shoulder.

05:34:56.159 --> 05:34:59.880
Stand back, someone called from above.

05:34:59.939 --> 05:35:01.799
Startled.

05:35:01.860 --> 05:35:03.240
Cricket flew to the side.

05:35:03.299 --> 05:35:05.639
She heard a thump, and then another.

05:35:05.700 --> 05:35:07.860
And then the circle fell out of the

05:35:07.860 --> 05:35:10.319
ceiling in a crash of tree stuffed dust.

05:35:10.380 --> 05:35:13.380
That'll bring the guards, the other

05:35:13.380 --> 05:35:14.220
prisoner called.

05:35:14.279 --> 05:35:15.599
Better hurry and go.

05:35:15.720 --> 05:35:18.900
Come on. cried the voice from the next

05:35:18.900 --> 05:35:19.560
level up.

05:35:19.619 --> 05:35:22.919
Cricket saw dark orange claws beckoning

05:35:22.919 --> 05:35:23.880
through the hole in the ceiling.

05:35:23.939 --> 05:35:26.520
She darted over, and squeezed herself

05:35:26.520 --> 05:35:29.220
through, folding her wings in as tight as

05:35:29.220 --> 05:35:31.380
they'd go, and losing a few scarves in

05:35:31.380 --> 05:35:31.860
the process.

05:35:31.860 --> 05:35:35.340
Talons reached for her, tugging her

05:35:35.340 --> 05:35:37.319
upward until she tumbled free onto the

05:35:37.319 --> 05:35:39.000
floor of Jewel's palace kitchen.

05:35:39.060 --> 05:35:42.419
Five silk wing servants were scattered

05:35:42.419 --> 05:35:44.759
around the room, staring at her with wide

05:35:44.759 --> 05:35:47.639
eyes, frozen in the middle of chopping, or

05:35:47.639 --> 05:35:49.799
stirring, or roasting, or whatever they'd

05:35:49.799 --> 05:35:52.500
been doing, but standing by the hole were

05:35:52.500 --> 05:35:55.139
cinnabar and tow, the silk wings from the

05:35:55.139 --> 05:35:57.360
chrysalis, they were the ones who'd

05:35:57.360 --> 05:35:58.139
helped her climb through.

05:35:58.200 --> 05:36:01.560
You're all right, Cricket gasped.

05:36:01.619 --> 05:36:03.900
I thought Lady Jewel was going to punish

05:36:03.900 --> 05:36:04.020
you.

05:36:04.080 --> 05:36:06.599
Not much, Tao said.

05:36:06.659 --> 05:36:07.740
She likes me.

05:36:07.799 --> 05:36:11.700
She likes me too, Cinnabar huffed. taking

05:36:11.700 --> 05:36:12.959
the stone jar from cricket.

05:36:13.020 --> 05:36:15.720
Cricket dropped the flame silk into it

05:36:15.720 --> 05:36:18.180
and Cinnabar neatly capped the jar and

05:36:18.180 --> 05:36:20.459
slotted it onto a high shelf between

05:36:20.459 --> 05:36:23.340
glass jars labeled basil and ginger.

05:36:23.400 --> 05:36:25.860
Not as much as she likes me.

05:36:25.919 --> 05:36:27.599
Tao said serenely.

05:36:27.659 --> 05:36:30.540
Also, whenever the queen says to punish

05:36:30.540 --> 05:36:32.819
us severely, Jewel gives us a medal.

05:36:32.939 --> 05:36:35.639
She clapped at a few of the watching silk

05:36:35.639 --> 05:36:36.060
wings.

05:36:36.119 --> 05:36:38.580
Pour some water over this hole to make

05:36:38.580 --> 05:36:40.619
sure it doesn't burn further, and you

05:36:40.619 --> 05:36:42.540
were all in the pantry and saw nothing.

05:36:42.659 --> 05:36:45.900
Yes, Tao, one of them answered.

05:36:45.959 --> 05:36:47.700
The others bowed their heads in

05:36:47.700 --> 05:36:48.119
agreement.

05:36:48.180 --> 05:36:51.840
Follow us, Cinnabar said to Cricket

05:36:51.840 --> 05:36:53.400
turning and sprinting out of the

05:36:53.400 --> 05:36:53.880
kitchen.

05:36:53.939 --> 05:36:56.340
Cricket followed, with Tao at her side.

05:36:56.400 --> 05:36:58.740
They ran through the winding back

05:36:58.740 --> 05:37:01.799
passages of the palace, narrow halls that

05:37:01.799 --> 05:37:03.540
cricket guests were intended for servants

05:37:03.540 --> 05:37:06.060
to keep them out of sight of Jules' hive

05:37:06.060 --> 05:37:06.659
wing guests.

05:37:06.720 --> 05:37:09.360
She caught glimpses of jeweled toned

05:37:09.360 --> 05:37:12.299
ballrooms as they flew by, ruby red walls

05:37:12.299 --> 05:37:14.880
and yellow silk banners, and emerald

05:37:14.880 --> 05:37:15.900
patterns in the floors.

05:37:15.959 --> 05:37:18.720
She could still hear the rain and feel

05:37:18.720 --> 05:37:20.880
the breeze from outside in almost every

05:37:20.880 --> 05:37:21.060
room.

05:37:21.119 --> 05:37:24.900
At last they came to a small nondescript

05:37:24.900 --> 05:37:25.139
door.

05:37:25.200 --> 05:37:28.080
Cinnabar opened it and peeked outside.

05:37:28.439 --> 05:37:31.439
A gust of wind came through, carrying the

05:37:31.439 --> 05:37:33.779
savannah ascents of sunlight and rain and

05:37:33.779 --> 05:37:34.080
grass.

05:37:34.139 --> 05:37:36.840
She closed it again quickly, and looked

05:37:36.840 --> 05:37:37.619
back at Tao.

05:37:37.740 --> 05:37:41.279
Tree hoppers out there, she said softly.

05:37:41.340 --> 05:37:44.040
Cricket wondered if Blue could have read

05:37:44.040 --> 05:37:46.380
Tao's expression, because she couldn't at

05:37:46.380 --> 05:37:46.560
all.

05:37:46.680 --> 05:37:48.840
The gentle silk wing was either

05:37:48.840 --> 05:37:51.479
smothering a smile, or trying not to bite

05:37:51.479 --> 05:37:51.720
something.

05:37:51.779 --> 05:37:54.720
Is he himself?

05:37:54.840 --> 05:37:55.619
She asked.

05:37:55.680 --> 05:37:58.619
I couldn't tell, Cinnabar said.

05:37:58.680 --> 05:37:59.880
His back is to the door.

05:37:59.939 --> 05:38:01.919
I'll talk to him.

05:38:01.979 --> 05:38:05.099
Tal stepped forward, brushing past

05:38:05.099 --> 05:38:06.599
cricket in the dim hallway.

05:38:06.659 --> 05:38:08.279
Is that a good idea?

05:38:08.340 --> 05:38:11.340
Cinnabar asked, with the queen so close?

05:38:11.459 --> 05:38:15.659
I am Lady Jules, chief steward, Tao said

05:38:15.659 --> 05:38:18.419
austerely, and he is her treasurer.

05:38:18.479 --> 05:38:20.700
We are allowed to have an ordinary

05:38:20.700 --> 05:38:22.020
everyday conversation.

05:38:22.139 --> 05:38:24.720
Cinnabar querked an eyebrow at her.

05:38:24.779 --> 05:38:29.040
I promise we won't be obvious, Tao said

05:38:29.040 --> 05:38:31.740
in her normal voice, really, Cinnabar.

05:38:31.799 --> 05:38:35.220
You're obvious, every time you even look

05:38:35.220 --> 05:38:37.740
at each other, Cinnabar grumbled.

05:38:37.799 --> 05:38:40.200
Just get away from him quick, if his eyes

05:38:40.200 --> 05:38:40.799
go white.

05:38:40.860 --> 05:38:42.659
Tao shuddered.

05:38:42.720 --> 05:38:44.099
I always do.

05:38:44.159 --> 05:38:47.279
She slipped out through the door, and

05:38:47.279 --> 05:38:49.020
Cricket nudged up to peek through the

05:38:49.020 --> 05:38:49.979
crack with cinnabar.

05:38:50.099 --> 05:38:54.060
Outside, a wide balcony garden overlooked

05:38:54.060 --> 05:38:56.400
the savannah covered in plants of all

05:38:56.400 --> 05:38:57.360
shapes and sizes.

05:38:57.419 --> 05:39:00.840
Raspberry bushes lined the paths, and

05:39:00.840 --> 05:39:03.180
white honeysuckle climbed the gazebos.

05:39:03.240 --> 05:39:06.659
Cricket spotted pale pink lotus flowers

05:39:06.659 --> 05:39:09.360
drifting across the ponds, and clusters

05:39:09.360 --> 05:39:10.740
of forget me nots everywhere.

05:39:10.799 --> 05:39:13.799
The way most of the plans spilled over

05:39:13.799 --> 05:39:16.020
their borders made her miss her little

05:39:16.020 --> 05:39:18.479
terrarium back at school, even though

05:39:18.479 --> 05:39:20.459
she'd always found the endless botany

05:39:20.459 --> 05:39:21.360
classes rather boring.

05:39:21.479 --> 05:39:25.919
It was raining, a quiet, gentle rainfall

05:39:25.919 --> 05:39:28.139
but a roof extended over part of the

05:39:28.139 --> 05:39:31.259
gardens, and underneath it, a plump

05:39:31.259 --> 05:39:33.180
worried looking hive wing sat by one of

05:39:33.180 --> 05:39:36.240
the pools, reading, his scales were a

05:39:36.240 --> 05:39:38.459
dark greenish black, with pale orange

05:39:38.459 --> 05:39:41.220
stripes along his wings, tail, and face.

05:39:41.279 --> 05:39:44.099
He turned to look up as Tao approached

05:39:44.099 --> 05:39:46.560
and Cricket saw what Cinnabar meant.

05:39:46.619 --> 05:39:49.200
His whole face lit up, as though he'd

05:39:49.200 --> 05:39:50.700
just discovered sunshine.

05:39:50.819 --> 05:39:54.599
By the hive, Cinnabar muttered.

05:39:54.659 --> 05:39:56.159
They're terrible at this.

05:39:56.220 --> 05:40:00.240
He's a hive wing, Cricket whispered, and

05:40:00.240 --> 05:40:01.380
she's a silk wing.

05:40:01.439 --> 05:40:04.259
Yep, said Cinnabar.

05:40:04.319 --> 05:40:06.180
Extra very forbidden.

05:40:06.240 --> 05:40:08.459
It's a problem, and we all know it.

05:40:08.520 --> 05:40:11.340
Even Lady Jewel, but no one can do

05:40:11.340 --> 05:40:11.880
anything about it.

05:40:11.939 --> 05:40:15.599
Seeing the 2 dragons laughing, their

05:40:15.599 --> 05:40:18.240
wings brushing accidentally, Cricket knew

05:40:18.240 --> 05:40:19.439
she wouldn't have been able to do

05:40:19.439 --> 05:40:20.580
anything about it either.

05:40:20.580 --> 05:40:23.700
Even if she were their queen, she'd never

05:40:23.700 --> 05:40:25.979
be able to separate 2 dragons who looked

05:40:25.979 --> 05:40:26.759
so happy together.

05:40:26.880 --> 05:40:29.099
Oh, right.

05:40:29.159 --> 05:40:31.500
Stop being cute and get him out of there

05:40:31.500 --> 05:40:33.779
Cinnabar grumbled between her teeth.

05:40:33.900 --> 05:40:37.020
Tal gestured toward a door on the other

05:40:37.020 --> 05:40:39.180
side of the garden, and they both started

05:40:39.180 --> 05:40:40.439
walking in that direction.

05:40:40.500 --> 05:40:42.720
Cinnabar poked her nose out a little

05:40:42.720 --> 05:40:44.340
farther, watching them go.

05:40:44.400 --> 05:40:48.060
And then, Tree Hopper froze in place for

05:40:48.060 --> 05:40:48.240
a moment.

05:40:48.299 --> 05:40:52.200
Tao stumbled beside him, glanced at him

05:40:52.200 --> 05:40:54.659
quickly, and ducked her head, her whole

05:40:54.659 --> 05:40:56.759
posture changing instantly into that of a

05:40:56.759 --> 05:40:57.540
dutiful servant.

05:40:57.599 --> 05:41:01.680
The hive wing turned his head in a slow

05:41:01.680 --> 05:41:03.540
eerie twist to scan the garden.

05:41:03.599 --> 05:41:06.119
Cricket and cinnabar jumped back behind

05:41:06.119 --> 05:41:08.279
the door before the wide eyes got to

05:41:08.279 --> 05:41:08.520
them.

05:41:08.580 --> 05:41:12.900
I have arrived, said the queen's chilly

05:41:12.900 --> 05:41:13.080
voice.

05:41:13.200 --> 05:41:15.900
Cricket felt a spasm of fear shoot

05:41:15.900 --> 05:41:17.340
through her from snout to tail.

05:41:17.459 --> 05:41:20.639
Jewel, meet me in the prison.

05:41:20.759 --> 05:41:24.360
There was a pause, and then Tree Hoppers

05:41:24.360 --> 05:41:25.380
shook himself with a hiss.

05:41:25.439 --> 05:41:30.419
Sorry, he said, in a low voice to Tao

05:41:30.419 --> 05:41:32.880
looking down at his talons, as though he

05:41:32.880 --> 05:41:34.139
couldn't bear to meet her eyes.

05:41:34.200 --> 05:41:38.159
It's not your fault, she said softly.

05:41:38.220 --> 05:41:40.860
Cricket's heart was thundering in her

05:41:40.860 --> 05:41:41.220
ears.

05:41:41.279 --> 05:41:43.740
She was sure she could hear talon steps

05:41:43.740 --> 05:41:45.659
coming along the corridor.

05:41:45.720 --> 05:41:47.759
Any moment, the queen would step into the

05:41:47.759 --> 05:41:50.700
prison and see her empty cell, unless she

05:41:50.700 --> 05:41:51.240
knew already.

05:41:51.299 --> 05:41:54.240
Maybe she'd seen it through her spies.

05:41:54.299 --> 05:41:57.240
Any moment, the queen would take over the

05:41:57.240 --> 05:41:59.639
entire hive again, and cricket would be

05:41:59.639 --> 05:42:00.599
surrounded by her.

05:42:00.599 --> 05:42:03.540
The 2 dragons in the garden went through

05:42:03.540 --> 05:42:04.860
the far door at last.

05:42:04.919 --> 05:42:07.200
Cinnabar and Cricket leaped out of their

05:42:07.200 --> 05:42:08.880
hiding spot and ran for the edge.

05:42:09.000 --> 05:42:12.479
If you were smart, Cinnabar said.

05:42:12.540 --> 05:42:14.520
You'd fly out that way and never stop.

05:42:14.580 --> 05:42:17.400
She pointed out at the ocean beyond

05:42:17.400 --> 05:42:18.599
Dragonfly Bay.

05:42:18.659 --> 05:42:20.639
I wish I could.

05:42:20.700 --> 05:42:23.040
Cricket thought of her dream of the

05:42:23.040 --> 05:42:25.500
distant kingdoms, where Clearsight had

05:42:25.500 --> 05:42:25.799
come from.

05:42:25.860 --> 05:42:29.520
She and Blue could be safe over there, out

05:42:29.520 --> 05:42:31.740
of reach of Queen Wasp's claws.

05:42:31.799 --> 05:42:34.680
I promised Lady Jewel I'd find some

05:42:34.680 --> 05:42:36.540
answers for her first, she told

05:42:36.540 --> 05:42:37.319
Cinnabar.

05:42:37.380 --> 05:42:38.759
Thank you for your help.

05:42:38.819 --> 05:42:41.759
The dark orange dragon waved.

05:42:41.819 --> 05:42:44.459
As Cricket dove into the air and twisted

05:42:44.459 --> 05:42:46.560
her wings to spiral down the side of the

05:42:46.560 --> 05:42:47.159
hive.

05:42:47.220 --> 05:42:49.680
Other dragons were out despite the rain

05:42:49.680 --> 05:42:52.200
flitting from one ledge to another, or

05:42:52.200 --> 05:42:54.599
venturing into the wet savannah for prey

05:42:54.599 --> 05:42:57.479
she wove through them, keeping an eye on

05:42:57.479 --> 05:42:59.759
the hive wings, until she found an open

05:42:59.759 --> 05:43:02.099
ledge on the nest level and could duck

05:43:02.099 --> 05:43:02.520
inside.

05:43:02.580 --> 05:43:05.459
The walkways around the nest were little

05:43:05.459 --> 05:43:08.520
pebbled paths, dotted with benches, where

05:43:08.520 --> 05:43:10.619
dragons could meet and make plans for

05:43:10.619 --> 05:43:11.639
their future offspring.

05:43:11.700 --> 05:43:15.240
The paths circled the giant dome, which

05:43:15.240 --> 05:43:17.400
was painted smooth and white, like an

05:43:17.400 --> 05:43:18.000
eggshell.

05:43:18.060 --> 05:43:20.880
Cricket had visited the cicada hive nest

05:43:20.880 --> 05:43:22.740
once, and it looked a lot like this.

05:43:22.799 --> 05:43:25.080
She'd seen parents meeting with

05:43:25.080 --> 05:43:27.119
administrators to decide what schools

05:43:27.119 --> 05:43:28.439
their dragonettes would attend.

05:43:28.500 --> 05:43:31.919
She'd even seen some discussing arranged

05:43:31.919 --> 05:43:33.180
marriage plans.

05:43:33.240 --> 05:43:35.819
But the walkways around the Jewel Hive

05:43:35.819 --> 05:43:36.659
Nest were empty.

05:43:36.720 --> 05:43:39.599
She crept up to the snowy walls of the

05:43:39.599 --> 05:43:42.000
dome and around to the main door, which

05:43:42.000 --> 05:43:43.680
was opposite the entrance to the ramps.

05:43:43.740 --> 05:43:46.560
A sign was posted on the door of the dome

05:43:46.560 --> 05:43:49.080
closed for inspection by the queen.

05:43:49.139 --> 05:43:52.500
Oh, moons, Cricket thought.

05:43:52.560 --> 05:43:54.000
Please don't be in there already.

05:43:54.060 --> 05:43:58.200
She glanced around, and spotted 2 guards

05:43:58.200 --> 05:44:00.060
pacing up and down the ramps.

05:44:00.119 --> 05:44:02.580
Quickly, she dove behind a bench and

05:44:02.580 --> 05:44:04.080
peered at them through the slats.

05:44:04.139 --> 05:44:06.720
Their attention was focused outward

05:44:06.720 --> 05:44:08.939
staring dragons away from the nest.

05:44:09.060 --> 05:44:10.979
They didn't look back at the dome.

05:44:11.040 --> 05:44:13.080
They could, any second.

05:44:13.139 --> 05:44:15.900
But while she was watching, they didn't

05:44:15.900 --> 05:44:18.060
and she had to hope she'd be lucky.

05:44:18.119 --> 05:44:21.540
Taking a deep breath, she darted to the

05:44:21.540 --> 05:44:23.939
door, pulled it open. and ducked inside.

05:44:24.060 --> 05:44:27.299
It swung shut behind her, and she caught

05:44:27.299 --> 05:44:28.919
it with her tail so it wouldn't thud.

05:44:28.979 --> 05:44:32.040
The inside of the dome was very dark.

05:44:32.099 --> 05:44:35.099
For a moment, Cricket was afraid that

05:44:35.099 --> 05:44:37.259
there was no light in there at all, and

05:44:37.259 --> 05:44:40.200
for a moment, with a shiver of fear, she

05:44:40.200 --> 05:44:42.360
wondered whether Queen Wasp could see in

05:44:42.360 --> 05:44:42.659
the dark.

05:44:42.720 --> 05:44:46.919
She could be in here, watching me right

05:44:46.919 --> 05:44:47.279
now.

05:44:47.340 --> 05:44:51.000
Cricket stood petrified by the door

05:44:51.000 --> 05:44:54.599
trying to breathe quietly, and slowly she

05:44:54.599 --> 05:44:57.299
realized that her eyes were adjusting, and

05:44:57.299 --> 05:44:58.919
the nest was not completely dark after

05:44:58.919 --> 05:44:59.159
all.

05:44:59.220 --> 05:45:02.639
It was not lit by flame silk, though.

05:45:02.700 --> 05:45:05.400
The glowing green light came from small

05:45:05.400 --> 05:45:07.860
clouds of bioluminescent mushrooms

05:45:07.860 --> 05:45:11.040
gathered in clumps all around the room, at

05:45:11.040 --> 05:45:13.500
the base of the walls and along the paths

05:45:13.500 --> 05:45:14.099
between the eggs.

05:45:14.159 --> 05:45:18.119
There was something weird and haunted and

05:45:18.119 --> 05:45:20.520
beautiful about the scene, as though

05:45:20.520 --> 05:45:22.439
cricket had wandered onto the surface of

05:45:22.439 --> 05:45:23.220
one of the moons.

05:45:23.340 --> 05:45:27.060
The nest was full of eggs, cradled in

05:45:27.060 --> 05:45:29.580
small hollows in the floor, 10 apiece.

05:45:29.700 --> 05:45:32.939
Cricket shivered again, thinking of all

05:45:32.939 --> 05:45:35.700
the tiny heartbeats under the shells, all

05:45:35.700 --> 05:45:37.439
the little dragons waiting to hatch.

05:45:37.500 --> 05:45:40.680
She stepped onto one of the paths and

05:45:40.680 --> 05:45:41.939
studied the closest egg.

05:45:42.000 --> 05:45:45.360
A name was written on the shell in ink

05:45:45.360 --> 05:45:48.299
the mother's name cricket guest, and

05:45:48.299 --> 05:45:50.580
below that, scored into the shell.

05:45:50.639 --> 05:45:52.979
There was something else, some kind of

05:45:52.979 --> 05:45:53.459
symbol.

05:45:53.520 --> 05:45:55.619
Cricket bent closer.

05:45:55.680 --> 05:45:59.400
It looked like a pair of stingers, arcing

05:45:59.400 --> 05:46:01.560
sharply away from each other, like the

05:46:01.560 --> 05:46:02.939
antennae of a wasp.

05:46:03.000 --> 05:46:05.700
She checked the next egg and the next.

05:46:05.759 --> 05:46:08.939
They all bore the same marking, until she

05:46:08.939 --> 05:46:10.740
came around to a group of newer eggs.

05:46:10.799 --> 05:46:13.740
These had only half the marking, one

05:46:13.740 --> 05:46:16.139
sharp line, traced ominously along the

05:46:16.139 --> 05:46:17.099
curve of the shells.

05:46:17.220 --> 05:46:21.000
The very newest ones had no marks on them

05:46:21.000 --> 05:46:21.360
at all.

05:46:21.419 --> 05:46:24.779
Cricket's mind was buzzing with questions

05:46:24.779 --> 05:46:27.299
but she knew she'd already spent too long

05:46:27.299 --> 05:46:28.319
gazing at the eggs.

05:46:28.380 --> 05:46:31.619
She needed to find a place to hide, which

05:46:31.619 --> 05:46:33.479
would be nearly impossible in a room that

05:46:33.479 --> 05:46:35.400
contained nothing but eggs and glowing

05:46:35.400 --> 05:46:36.180
toadstools.

05:46:36.240 --> 05:46:40.139
She turned, searching the shadows, and

05:46:40.139 --> 05:46:42.180
her tail bumped one of the larger eggs in

05:46:42.180 --> 05:46:42.959
the last hollow.

05:46:43.020 --> 05:46:46.200
It rocked slightly in its crevice, and

05:46:46.200 --> 05:46:47.400
she jumped forward to catch it.

05:46:47.459 --> 05:46:49.979
She could feel the vibrations of the

05:46:49.979 --> 05:46:51.599
dragonette moving under the shell.

05:46:51.659 --> 05:46:56.040
This egg had only one mark on it, and

05:46:56.040 --> 05:46:58.560
instead of a name, the word written on

05:46:58.560 --> 05:47:00.900
the shell was Orphanage.

05:47:01.020 --> 05:47:04.380
Poor little dragonette, crooked thought.

05:47:04.439 --> 05:47:07.319
He or she won't even have a katydid.

05:47:07.439 --> 05:47:10.259
Yesterday, I thought for a while that I'd

05:47:10.259 --> 05:47:11.279
never known my parents.

05:47:11.340 --> 05:47:14.880
But this one really never will, and Queen

05:47:14.880 --> 05:47:16.860
Wasp will be able to control this

05:47:16.860 --> 05:47:18.419
dragonette whenever she wants.

05:47:18.479 --> 05:47:20.880
They'll never have a chance to be free.

05:47:20.939 --> 05:47:25.139
A strange instinct seized her, and she

05:47:25.139 --> 05:47:27.419
wrapped the egg in one of her scarves

05:47:27.419 --> 05:47:28.319
tying it to her chest.

05:47:28.380 --> 05:47:31.560
Then she looked up, blinking back tears

05:47:31.560 --> 05:47:32.759
and saw the rafters.

05:47:32.819 --> 05:47:35.700
The nest was not a perfect dome.

05:47:35.759 --> 05:47:38.159
It had cracked and shifted over the years

05:47:38.159 --> 05:47:39.240
since it was built.

05:47:39.299 --> 05:47:41.700
Four tall columns and a pair of

05:47:41.700 --> 05:47:43.380
crossbeams had been added at some point

05:47:43.380 --> 05:47:45.060
to keep the structure stable.

05:47:45.119 --> 05:47:48.479
Up there, in the shadow where the support

05:47:48.479 --> 05:47:50.880
beams met, maybe she could hide up

05:47:50.880 --> 05:47:51.119
there.

05:47:51.180 --> 05:47:54.180
Cricket spread her wings and flew up to

05:47:54.180 --> 05:47:54.959
the crossbeams.

05:47:55.020 --> 05:47:58.259
She crept cautiously along them, finally

05:47:58.259 --> 05:48:00.419
settling in what seemed to be the darkest

05:48:00.419 --> 05:48:02.220
corner, right above the door.

05:48:02.279 --> 05:48:04.799
She might kill me for this.

05:48:04.919 --> 05:48:07.919
Cricket didn't know where the line of

05:48:07.919 --> 05:48:09.479
treason was for the queen.

05:48:09.540 --> 05:48:12.119
Would she be content to take cricket's

05:48:12.119 --> 05:48:13.200
brain and freedom from her?

05:48:13.259 --> 05:48:15.779
Or would spying on her secrets mean

05:48:15.779 --> 05:48:16.439
certain death?

05:48:16.500 --> 05:48:19.740
If so, knowing about the book was cause

05:48:19.740 --> 05:48:21.419
enough to kill her, surely.

05:48:21.479 --> 05:48:24.779
I think it's safe to say that if the

05:48:24.779 --> 05:48:27.360
queen catches me, I'm in enormous trouble

05:48:27.360 --> 05:48:29.159
no matter what she decides to do.

05:48:29.279 --> 05:48:32.700
Cricket wrapped her wings around the egg

05:48:32.700 --> 05:48:34.619
and curled into the smallest ball she

05:48:34.619 --> 05:48:37.439
could make, she thought about blue, and

05:48:37.439 --> 05:48:40.200
sundew, and sore tail, hiding somewhere

05:48:40.200 --> 05:48:42.419
there was still time before sunset.

05:48:42.479 --> 05:48:44.819
If the answer to the mind control

05:48:44.819 --> 05:48:48.599
question was here, She had to hope Sundu

05:48:48.599 --> 05:48:49.740
could get the message to her parents

05:48:49.740 --> 05:48:52.380
before they did something terrible and

05:48:52.380 --> 05:48:53.279
irreversible.

05:48:53.340 --> 05:48:57.779
But sunset crept closer and closer, and

05:48:57.779 --> 05:48:58.919
nobody came into the dome.

05:48:59.040 --> 05:49:01.919
Cricket began to worry that the queen

05:49:01.919 --> 05:49:02.520
wasn't coming.

05:49:02.580 --> 05:49:05.099
What if she was so furious about cricket

05:49:05.099 --> 05:49:07.919
escaping, that she'd decided to skip the

05:49:07.919 --> 05:49:10.500
nest visit in favor of taking over the

05:49:10.500 --> 05:49:12.000
whole tribe to search for her.

05:49:12.060 --> 05:49:15.119
Or what if she was busy punishing the

05:49:15.119 --> 05:49:16.799
dragons in Jules' palace for letting

05:49:16.799 --> 05:49:17.520
cricket escape?

05:49:17.580 --> 05:49:20.400
I hope Lady Jewel is all right.

05:49:20.459 --> 05:49:24.540
And Cinnabar, and Tao, and Lady Scarab.

05:49:24.659 --> 05:49:28.259
She hoped Jewel had had time to free Katy

05:49:28.259 --> 05:49:30.840
did, as she'd promised before the queen

05:49:30.840 --> 05:49:31.200
arrived.

05:49:31.319 --> 05:49:34.619
She could feel the sun sinking down the

05:49:34.619 --> 05:49:37.200
sky, and she was beginning to imagine the

05:49:37.200 --> 05:49:39.000
most terrible scenes happening back of

05:49:39.000 --> 05:49:39.540
the palace.

05:49:39.599 --> 05:49:43.860
When suddenly, she heard a soft creak, and

05:49:43.860 --> 05:49:46.139
a bar of light lanced across the eggs.

05:49:46.200 --> 05:49:50.040
It was Queen Wasp, at last.

05:49:50.099 --> 05:49:54.540
Chapter 20.

05:49:54.900 --> 05:49:58.439
The queen stalked forward into the nest

05:49:58.439 --> 05:50:01.020
on soundless talons.

05:50:01.080 --> 05:50:03.720
The door snicked shut behind her, and

05:50:03.720 --> 05:50:06.419
cricket watched the queen pause, surveying

05:50:06.419 --> 05:50:06.900
the eggs.

05:50:06.959 --> 05:50:10.799
Or letting her eyes adjust, Cricket

05:50:10.799 --> 05:50:11.220
thought.

05:50:11.279 --> 05:50:13.799
Maybe she can't see in the dark after

05:50:13.799 --> 05:50:14.040
all.

05:50:14.099 --> 05:50:17.279
That thought did not make the queen any

05:50:17.279 --> 05:50:18.119
less terrifying.

05:50:18.180 --> 05:50:22.080
Queen Wasp was enormous, even from

05:50:22.080 --> 05:50:24.119
Cricket's vantage point up by the dome

05:50:24.119 --> 05:50:24.479
ceiling.

05:50:24.540 --> 05:50:28.080
Cricket knew, logically, that Wasp was

05:50:28.080 --> 05:50:30.419
probably smaller than Lady Scarab, as

05:50:30.419 --> 05:50:33.060
Scarab was older than her, but there was

05:50:33.060 --> 05:50:35.220
something about the way Queen Wasp stood

05:50:35.220 --> 05:50:38.159
and held her wings and radiated menace

05:50:38.159 --> 05:50:40.979
that made her seem quite possibly the

05:50:40.979 --> 05:50:43.259
largest dragon in the entire world.

05:50:43.319 --> 05:50:45.840
Her name was well chosen too.

05:50:45.959 --> 05:50:49.319
From above, cricket had a perfect view of

05:50:49.319 --> 05:50:51.240
the yellow and black stripes and black

05:50:51.240 --> 05:50:54.119
horns that made the queen look so much

05:50:54.119 --> 05:50:57.000
like one of the Pantalan wasps that could

05:50:57.000 --> 05:50:58.799
kill an elephant with its venom.

05:50:58.919 --> 05:51:02.639
Cricket breathed as lightly, softly as

05:51:02.639 --> 05:51:05.580
she could, trying not to move, or shift

05:51:05.580 --> 05:51:06.360
or twitch.

05:51:06.419 --> 05:51:09.000
The queen stepped between the eggs.

05:51:09.060 --> 05:51:11.939
Her head twisting abruptly to one side

05:51:11.939 --> 05:51:14.880
then to the other, her tongue flicking in

05:51:14.880 --> 05:51:15.240
and out.

05:51:15.299 --> 05:51:18.360
She passed the hollows of eggs with the

05:51:18.360 --> 05:51:19.020
double marks.

05:51:19.080 --> 05:51:22.200
Her tail slid behind her, like a cobra

05:51:22.200 --> 05:51:23.099
stalking its prey.

05:51:23.159 --> 05:51:26.939
She reached the 1st group of newer eggs

05:51:26.939 --> 05:51:29.459
those with only one stinger marked on

05:51:29.459 --> 05:51:29.580
them.

05:51:29.639 --> 05:51:33.240
Here she stopped, hissing for a long

05:51:33.240 --> 05:51:34.020
terrifying moment.

05:51:34.080 --> 05:51:37.439
Queen Wasp picked up one of the eggs.

05:51:37.500 --> 05:51:40.979
Her tail rose behind her, and a long

05:51:40.979 --> 05:51:42.900
needle sharp stinger slid out of the

05:51:42.900 --> 05:51:43.139
tip.

05:51:43.200 --> 05:51:45.599
Cricket fought back a gasp.

05:51:45.659 --> 05:51:48.299
Everyone knew about the stingers and

05:51:48.299 --> 05:51:51.119
queen wasp's claws and how much pain they

05:51:51.119 --> 05:51:51.779
could inject.

05:51:51.779 --> 05:51:54.299
She'd never heard anyone mention a

05:51:54.299 --> 05:51:56.340
stinger in the queen's tail as well.

05:51:56.400 --> 05:51:59.700
In a move like a flash of lightning, the

05:51:59.700 --> 05:52:02.220
queen struck, plunging her tail stinger

05:52:02.220 --> 05:52:03.060
into the eggshell.

05:52:03.119 --> 05:52:06.360
A pulse of something bright green seemed

05:52:06.360 --> 05:52:08.459
to move through the stinger into the egg

05:52:08.520 --> 05:52:12.599
into the dragonette inside, Cricket

05:52:12.599 --> 05:52:14.220
thought, with mute horror.

05:52:14.340 --> 05:52:16.860
And then the queen drew her stinger out

05:52:16.860 --> 05:52:19.259
and dropped the egg back into place.

05:52:19.319 --> 05:52:22.560
With one claw, she sketched the 2nd half

05:52:22.560 --> 05:52:25.080
of the marking on the shell, and then she

05:52:25.080 --> 05:52:26.099
picked up the next egg.

05:52:26.159 --> 05:52:28.979
Cricket could only watch a few more

05:52:28.979 --> 05:52:32.279
before she had to close her eyes and bury

05:52:32.279 --> 05:52:33.720
her face in the egg she held.

05:52:33.840 --> 05:52:37.200
The queen moved quickly, efficiently

05:52:37.200 --> 05:52:40.619
ruthlessly, and Cricket knew what she was

05:52:40.619 --> 05:52:40.799
saying.

05:52:40.860 --> 05:52:43.500
This is how she does it.

05:52:43.560 --> 05:52:46.439
She poisons her dragons before they're

05:52:46.439 --> 05:52:46.979
even hatched.

05:52:47.040 --> 05:52:49.740
They come into the world already linked

05:52:49.740 --> 05:52:52.020
to her by whatever that is she's

05:52:52.020 --> 05:52:54.840
injecting into the eggs, the moment they

05:52:54.840 --> 05:52:55.500
open their eyes.

05:52:55.560 --> 05:52:58.319
She can be there, inside their heads.

05:52:58.380 --> 05:53:01.680
Does it take 2 injections to work?

05:53:01.740 --> 05:53:03.360
Or is one for backup?

05:53:03.479 --> 05:53:07.319
She glanced down at the orphaned egg she

05:53:07.319 --> 05:53:09.180
was cradling in the scarf.

05:53:09.240 --> 05:53:11.040
Would this dragon belong to the queen

05:53:11.040 --> 05:53:11.459
already?

05:53:11.520 --> 05:53:14.279
Or could it be free if the queen never

05:53:14.279 --> 05:53:15.419
stabbed it a 2nd time?

05:53:15.479 --> 05:53:18.360
I came from a nest too.

05:53:18.419 --> 05:53:20.099
So why not me?

05:53:20.159 --> 05:53:23.880
She thought for a while, trying to ignore

05:53:23.880 --> 05:53:25.799
the soft, chilling noises from below

05:53:25.799 --> 05:53:25.979
her.

05:53:26.040 --> 05:53:29.639
Scarab said Katy did was trying to hide

05:53:29.639 --> 05:53:30.659
my egg at first.

05:53:30.720 --> 05:53:34.259
She smuggled me into a nest later, after

05:53:34.259 --> 05:53:35.759
I'd been an egg for a while.

05:53:35.819 --> 05:53:39.479
She must have seen the marks too, and not

05:53:39.479 --> 05:53:40.319
known what they meant.

05:53:40.380 --> 05:53:44.459
I bet she marked my egg herself, so later

05:53:44.459 --> 05:53:46.259
the queen thought she'd already stabbed

05:53:46.259 --> 05:53:46.439
me.

05:53:46.560 --> 05:53:48.840
That's how I escaped.

05:53:48.959 --> 05:53:52.200
She brushed her talons gently over the

05:53:52.200 --> 05:53:53.220
single mark on the egg.

05:53:53.340 --> 05:53:56.279
Which marking had Katy did put on the

05:53:56.279 --> 05:53:56.580
egg?

05:53:56.639 --> 05:54:00.000
Maybe cricket had been injected, but only

05:54:00.000 --> 05:54:01.139
once instead of twice.

05:54:01.200 --> 05:54:03.959
She tightened her grip on the scarf.

05:54:04.020 --> 05:54:06.540
It was nauseating to think of the queen

05:54:06.540 --> 05:54:08.580
plunging her poison into cricket.

05:54:08.639 --> 05:54:11.340
Still worse to know she was doing it now

05:54:11.340 --> 05:54:13.139
to all these baby dragons.

05:54:13.259 --> 05:54:15.540
I wish I could stop her.

05:54:15.599 --> 05:54:18.840
I wish I could fly down there, and drop a

05:54:18.840 --> 05:54:21.360
deadly centipede on her head, or drown

05:54:21.360 --> 05:54:22.500
her inflame silk.

05:54:22.560 --> 05:54:25.979
I wish I were brave or fierce or

05:54:25.979 --> 05:54:26.400
dangerous.

05:54:26.459 --> 05:54:28.560
But she couldn't do anything.

05:54:28.619 --> 05:54:31.139
Not here, not now.

05:54:31.200 --> 05:54:33.419
She had only one weapon.

05:54:33.479 --> 05:54:35.580
She knew the truth about the queen.

05:54:35.639 --> 05:54:38.700
And right now, she was the only one who

05:54:38.700 --> 05:54:39.000
knew.

05:54:39.060 --> 05:54:42.479
She had to stay safe to make sure she

05:54:42.479 --> 05:54:44.340
could get that information to Lady Jewel

05:54:44.340 --> 05:54:47.220
and maybe to the whole tribe, if she

05:54:47.220 --> 05:54:47.400
could.

05:54:47.459 --> 05:54:51.659
So she stayed in the rafters, as still as

05:54:51.659 --> 05:54:54.240
a mouse with hawks overhead while the

05:54:54.240 --> 05:54:55.740
queen finished her gruesome work.

05:54:55.799 --> 05:54:59.939
The last egg was set down, the last shell

05:54:59.939 --> 05:55:02.819
marked, and Queen Wasp slithered out the

05:55:02.819 --> 05:55:04.919
door, as silently as she'd arrived.

05:55:04.979 --> 05:55:07.979
Cricket checked her internal sense of

05:55:07.979 --> 05:55:10.139
time, and felt a spasm of panic.

05:55:10.200 --> 05:55:12.180
It was almost sunset.

05:55:12.240 --> 05:55:15.180
She wanted to leap off her perch and race

05:55:15.180 --> 05:55:17.459
down to the glitter bazaar, but she

05:55:17.459 --> 05:55:19.139
needed to wait long enough for the queen

05:55:19.139 --> 05:55:20.159
to be definitely gone.

05:55:20.220 --> 05:55:21.959
Now?

05:55:21.959 --> 05:55:22.979
Now?

05:55:23.099 --> 05:55:23.939
Is it safe?

05:55:24.000 --> 05:55:25.439
Can I go now?

05:55:25.500 --> 05:55:28.259
She wondered if something about her

05:55:28.259 --> 05:55:30.779
humming anxiety, translated through the

05:55:30.779 --> 05:55:33.299
eggshell in her arms, because she felt

05:55:33.299 --> 05:55:36.240
the dragonette inside move again, rolling

05:55:36.240 --> 05:55:37.319
and scrunching around.

05:55:37.380 --> 05:55:40.200
Finally, she'd waited as long as she

05:55:40.200 --> 05:55:42.180
could, and she flew back down to the

05:55:42.180 --> 05:55:42.779
ground.

05:55:42.840 --> 05:55:45.599
She glanced around to the eggs, feeling

05:55:45.599 --> 05:55:47.520
her wings droop to either side of her.

05:55:47.580 --> 05:55:50.819
I'm sorry, little dragons, she

05:55:50.819 --> 05:55:51.299
whispered.

05:55:51.360 --> 05:55:53.279
I wish I could save you all.

05:55:53.340 --> 05:55:56.700
Cricket pressed her ear to the door, and

05:55:56.700 --> 05:55:59.040
listened for a long time, but heard

05:55:59.040 --> 05:56:01.619
nothing outside, pulling her scarves

05:56:01.619 --> 05:56:02.159
closer.

05:56:02.220 --> 05:56:04.380
She opened the door a crack and peeked

05:56:04.380 --> 05:56:04.560
out.

05:56:04.619 --> 05:56:06.540
The guards were gone.

05:56:06.599 --> 05:56:09.299
She could see dragons moving up and down

05:56:09.299 --> 05:56:11.400
the ramps, but she couldn't tell if they

05:56:11.400 --> 05:56:12.720
were mind controlled or not.

05:56:12.720 --> 05:56:15.900
It felt horribly likely that the queen

05:56:15.900 --> 05:56:17.520
would have the whole hive on alert

05:56:17.520 --> 05:56:18.479
looking for her.

05:56:18.599 --> 05:56:21.720
She slipped out and around the curve of

05:56:21.720 --> 05:56:23.939
the dome, back toward the sky ledge.

05:56:24.060 --> 05:56:26.580
It would be safer to fly than to try

05:56:26.580 --> 05:56:28.560
creeping down all the levels inside the

05:56:28.560 --> 05:56:31.500
hive, past the 100s of eyes that could be

05:56:31.500 --> 05:56:32.700
looking for her.

05:56:32.759 --> 05:56:34.200
Or perhaps not.

05:56:34.259 --> 05:56:37.020
Cricket hesitated on the ledge.

05:56:37.080 --> 05:56:39.540
The light drizzle from earlier had

05:56:39.540 --> 05:56:41.099
strengthened into a driving storm.

05:56:41.159 --> 05:56:44.400
Rain poured down with a vengeance.

05:56:44.459 --> 05:56:47.220
Lightning crackled on the horizon, and

05:56:47.220 --> 05:56:48.659
the wind was strong enough to shake the

05:56:48.659 --> 05:56:48.959
hive.

05:56:49.080 --> 05:56:51.900
Even standing inside the hive.

05:56:51.959 --> 05:56:54.119
Cricket felt the spray of raindrops on

05:56:54.119 --> 05:56:56.580
her face, as though the entire sea was

05:56:56.580 --> 05:56:58.200
throwing itself around in fury.

05:56:58.259 --> 05:57:02.340
Still safer than the zombie eyes, Cricket

05:57:02.340 --> 05:57:03.180
told herself.

05:57:03.240 --> 05:57:05.099
She didn't want to get caught again.

05:57:05.159 --> 05:57:08.880
She would not get caught again, especially

05:57:08.880 --> 05:57:11.459
with this egg, and a dragonette inside

05:57:11.459 --> 05:57:13.799
who had a chance to be free, like her.

05:57:13.860 --> 05:57:17.040
She took a deep breath and plunged into

05:57:17.040 --> 05:57:17.520
the storm.

05:57:17.580 --> 05:57:21.000
The wind howled furiously and tried to

05:57:21.000 --> 05:57:23.819
smash her against the hive walls, but she

05:57:23.819 --> 05:57:26.220
folded her wings and dropped, plummeting

05:57:26.220 --> 05:57:26.759
toward the earth.

05:57:26.819 --> 05:57:30.060
Rain battered her face, nearly blinding

05:57:30.060 --> 05:57:32.580
her, but she managed to pull up just

05:57:32.580 --> 05:57:34.680
before she hit the outer glitter bazaar

05:57:34.680 --> 05:57:35.159
canopy.

05:57:35.220 --> 05:57:37.680
Below it, she could see the shapes of

05:57:37.680 --> 05:57:39.779
dragons rushing to fix the leaks and

05:57:39.779 --> 05:57:40.680
protect their wares.

05:57:40.799 --> 05:57:44.099
Her scarves felt like wet seaweed

05:57:44.099 --> 05:57:45.840
clinging to her neck and legs.

05:57:45.900 --> 05:57:48.479
She landed in a mud puddle outside the

05:57:48.479 --> 05:57:50.819
market, and squelched toward the end of

05:57:50.819 --> 05:57:51.299
the stalls.

05:57:51.360 --> 05:57:54.479
The egg vibrated in its soaking wet

05:57:54.479 --> 05:57:57.180
makeshift sling, nearly slipping away

05:57:57.180 --> 05:57:58.020
from her a couple of times.

05:57:58.080 --> 05:58:01.560
She had her head down and eyes nearly

05:58:01.560 --> 05:58:02.939
closed against the downpour.

05:58:03.000 --> 05:58:05.580
So when a dragon ducked under the canopy

05:58:05.580 --> 05:58:07.619
and stepped in front of her, she almost

05:58:07.619 --> 05:58:08.819
ran straight into him.

05:58:08.880 --> 05:58:12.419
Cricket, he yelled over the rush of the

05:58:12.419 --> 05:58:12.720
wind.

05:58:12.779 --> 05:58:16.380
Blue, she cried joyfully, you're all

05:58:16.380 --> 05:58:16.619
right.

05:58:16.680 --> 05:58:19.740
You're all right, he shouted back

05:58:19.740 --> 05:58:20.520
beaming.

05:58:20.580 --> 05:58:22.380
He swept her up in his wings.

05:58:22.439 --> 05:58:25.259
As your warmth surrounding her, she felt

05:58:25.259 --> 05:58:27.000
safe for the 1st time all day.

05:58:27.000 --> 05:58:29.700
I worried about you so much.

05:58:29.759 --> 05:58:32.880
Any luck searching for Luna?

05:58:33.000 --> 05:58:33.540
she asked.

05:58:33.599 --> 05:58:37.560
No, he said, into her shoulder with a

05:58:37.560 --> 05:58:37.860
sigh.

05:58:37.919 --> 05:58:40.860
Sundu thinks we should ask the leaf wings

05:58:40.860 --> 05:58:41.639
if they've seen her.

05:58:41.700 --> 05:58:45.540
Whoa, why do you have an egg with you?

05:58:45.599 --> 05:58:49.380
I saved it from the queen, Cricket said

05:58:49.380 --> 05:58:51.599
pulling back a little so he could see the

05:58:51.599 --> 05:58:52.680
smooth white shell.

05:58:52.740 --> 05:58:54.779
Where's sundew?

05:58:54.840 --> 05:58:57.060
Has she sent a message to the other leaf

05:58:57.060 --> 05:58:57.540
wings yet?

05:58:57.599 --> 05:58:59.400
I don't think so.

05:58:59.459 --> 05:59:02.340
They both glanced up at the dark clouds

05:59:02.340 --> 05:59:02.759
overhead.

05:59:02.819 --> 05:59:05.880
Raindrops cascaded down Blue's face like

05:59:05.880 --> 05:59:06.959
tiny sapphires.

05:59:07.080 --> 05:59:09.900
It was impossible to see the sun, but

05:59:09.900 --> 05:59:11.159
Cricket knew it was sinking.

05:59:11.220 --> 05:59:13.200
Am I too late?

05:59:13.259 --> 05:59:15.299
What are the leaf wings planning?

05:59:15.360 --> 05:59:16.979
Can I still stop them?

05:59:17.099 --> 05:59:20.939
I have to talk to her, quickly, Cricket

05:59:20.939 --> 05:59:21.360
said.

05:59:21.419 --> 05:59:22.500
This way.

05:59:22.560 --> 05:59:25.799
Blue guided her to the canopy and lifted

05:59:25.799 --> 05:59:27.659
an edge so she could slide underneath.

05:59:27.720 --> 05:59:31.259
Cricket found herself in a small, rickety

05:59:31.259 --> 05:59:33.659
looking stall, with rain dripping through

05:59:33.659 --> 05:59:34.919
a tear in the web overhead.

05:59:34.979 --> 05:59:37.560
A silk wing was hovering by the hole

05:59:37.560 --> 05:59:39.119
trying to patch it with his silk.

05:59:39.240 --> 05:59:41.880
Swordtail was up there too, helping to

05:59:41.880 --> 05:59:42.419
hold it together.

05:59:42.479 --> 05:59:45.959
She couldn't identify right away what was

05:59:45.959 --> 05:59:46.799
for sale in here.

05:59:46.860 --> 05:59:49.740
The shelves seemed to hold a mishmash of

05:59:49.740 --> 05:59:50.099
items.

05:59:50.159 --> 05:59:52.979
From little pots of blackberries to damp

05:59:52.979 --> 05:59:56.459
silk pillows, a few cracked mirrors, a

05:59:56.459 --> 05:59:58.319
very unfortunate smelling pile of

05:59:58.319 --> 06:00:01.020
wildebeest pelts, and a barrel labeled

06:00:01.020 --> 06:00:01.560
seeds.

06:00:01.619 --> 06:00:03.900
There was not much room to maneuver

06:00:03.900 --> 06:00:04.919
between the tent walls.

06:00:04.979 --> 06:00:08.639
Cricket felt oversized and wet and very

06:00:08.639 --> 06:00:09.060
muddy.

06:00:09.119 --> 06:00:12.000
She started unwinding all the wet scarves

06:00:12.000 --> 06:00:12.360
around her.

06:00:12.419 --> 06:00:15.240
Tao appeared from under one of the

06:00:15.240 --> 06:00:15.599
tables.

06:00:15.659 --> 06:00:18.720
I can't believe you made it here, she

06:00:18.720 --> 06:00:19.259
said.

06:00:19.319 --> 06:00:21.240
The queen is livid.

06:00:21.299 --> 06:00:23.459
Everyone in the hive is supposed to be

06:00:23.459 --> 06:00:23.880
looking for you.

06:00:23.939 --> 06:00:27.000
She followed Cricket's glands up to the

06:00:27.000 --> 06:00:27.959
silk wing on the ceiling.

06:00:28.020 --> 06:00:30.060
That's my stepbrother.

06:00:30.119 --> 06:00:32.400
Don't worry, he's in the chrysalis.

06:00:32.459 --> 06:00:35.400
We can trust him Is Lady Jewel all

06:00:35.400 --> 06:00:35.639
right?

06:00:35.700 --> 06:00:36.720
Cricket asked.

06:00:36.779 --> 06:00:38.459
She will be, I think.

06:00:38.520 --> 06:00:41.099
She's made the queen this mad before and

06:00:41.099 --> 06:00:43.740
survived, mostly because the queen thinks

06:00:43.740 --> 06:00:45.720
she's a butterfly brain, who could never

06:00:45.720 --> 06:00:46.860
execute an actual plan.

06:00:46.919 --> 06:00:49.740
Can you take her a message for me?

06:00:49.799 --> 06:00:52.259
I found out what the queen is doing in

06:00:52.259 --> 06:00:52.740
the nest.

06:00:52.799 --> 06:00:55.139
But I have to tell Sundu first.

06:00:55.200 --> 06:00:59.400
I'm here, Sundoo said, pushing her way

06:00:59.400 --> 06:01:00.659
through a curtain from the next room.

06:01:00.720 --> 06:01:03.119
Her silkwing disguise had been

06:01:03.119 --> 06:01:03.599
abandoned.

06:01:03.720 --> 06:01:05.459
She looked like herself again.

06:01:05.520 --> 06:01:08.099
Cricket felt a surge of relief at the

06:01:08.099 --> 06:01:09.479
side of her serious green face.

06:01:09.540 --> 06:01:12.180
Sundew, she cried.

06:01:12.240 --> 06:01:14.700
We can tell your parents I know how the

06:01:14.700 --> 06:01:15.299
queen does it.

06:01:15.360 --> 06:01:17.939
She's poisoning dragons when they're

06:01:17.939 --> 06:01:18.840
still in their eggs.

06:01:18.900 --> 06:01:21.419
I saw her stabbing them with her tail

06:01:21.419 --> 06:01:22.020
stinger.

06:01:22.080 --> 06:01:24.900
She goes to every nest in all the hives

06:01:24.900 --> 06:01:25.500
to do it.

06:01:25.560 --> 06:01:28.380
That way, when they hatch.

06:01:28.439 --> 06:01:29.819
She can mind control them right away.

06:01:29.880 --> 06:01:32.880
Apparently she can inject grown dragons

06:01:32.880 --> 06:01:35.459
too, but it must be faster to do all the

06:01:35.459 --> 06:01:36.180
eggs at once.

06:01:36.240 --> 06:01:38.520
To grown dragons?

06:01:38.580 --> 06:01:39.540
Blue echoed.

06:01:39.599 --> 06:01:42.479
You mean, could she do it to you?

06:01:42.540 --> 06:01:45.659
Cricket tried not to let it show on her

06:01:45.659 --> 06:01:48.360
face how scared she'd been, or how close

06:01:48.360 --> 06:01:50.459
she'd come to that exact fate today.

06:01:50.520 --> 06:01:54.000
Yes, I think so, she said.

06:01:54.060 --> 06:01:56.400
I think she missed stabbing my egg

06:01:56.400 --> 06:01:59.159
because Katie did snuck me into the nest

06:01:59.159 --> 06:02:01.560
late, but if she got her claws on me

06:02:01.560 --> 06:02:01.860
now.

06:02:01.919 --> 06:02:04.380
She could force me into the hive mind.

06:02:04.439 --> 06:02:06.180
No.

06:02:06.240 --> 06:02:08.040
Blue said passionately.

06:02:08.099 --> 06:02:11.279
That is never, never going to happen.

06:02:11.340 --> 06:02:14.520
Cricket brushed his wings with hers.

06:02:14.639 --> 06:02:17.939
We can save other eggs like I was saved.

06:02:18.000 --> 06:02:19.979
Sundo, don't you see?

06:02:20.040 --> 06:02:22.200
What Queen Wasp can do.

06:02:22.259 --> 06:02:23.459
It's not a power.

06:02:23.520 --> 06:02:26.340
I mean, it is, but it doesn't have to

06:02:26.340 --> 06:02:26.520
be.

06:02:26.639 --> 06:02:28.439
Hive wings could be free.

06:02:28.500 --> 06:02:31.020
This one will be free.

06:02:31.080 --> 06:02:34.799
She held out the egg. and Sundew touched

06:02:34.799 --> 06:02:37.200
it lightly, as though she wasn't entirely

06:02:37.200 --> 06:02:38.759
convinced it was safe to have around.

06:02:38.819 --> 06:02:42.240
Wow, said the leaf wing.

06:02:42.299 --> 06:02:45.299
That is a lot of information.

06:02:45.360 --> 06:02:48.479
We have to tell your parents to call off

06:02:48.479 --> 06:02:50.520
their other plan, Cricket said

06:02:50.520 --> 06:02:51.180
breathlessly.

06:02:51.240 --> 06:02:52.860
It's sunset.

06:02:52.919 --> 06:02:53.580
We have to do it now.

06:02:53.639 --> 06:02:54.840
How do we get to them?

06:02:54.900 --> 06:02:57.240
Sundew made a face.

06:02:57.299 --> 06:03:00.360
Her trying not to make a face, face.

06:03:00.599 --> 06:03:01.919
Cricket?

06:03:01.979 --> 06:03:05.639
It's amazing and insane and creepy what

06:03:05.639 --> 06:03:07.500
you found, but it doesn't change

06:03:07.500 --> 06:03:08.220
anything.

06:03:08.279 --> 06:03:10.139
Of course it does.

06:03:10.200 --> 06:03:13.080
Cricket pulled the egg back into her

06:03:13.080 --> 06:03:13.439
chest.

06:03:13.500 --> 06:03:16.139
We can stop her from stabbing any more

06:03:16.139 --> 06:03:16.500
eggs.

06:03:16.560 --> 06:03:19.200
Once I tell Lady Jewel, I know she'll

06:03:19.200 --> 06:03:20.520
come up with some way to protect them.

06:03:20.580 --> 06:03:23.639
Maybe the other hive rulers will too.

06:03:23.700 --> 06:03:27.419
But even if they can, and I don't see how

06:03:27.419 --> 06:03:29.279
with Queen Wasp still in charge.

06:03:29.340 --> 06:03:33.119
But even if we could save the eggs, we

06:03:33.119 --> 06:03:35.340
can't save the dragons who are already in

06:03:35.340 --> 06:03:36.779
her hive mind, can we?

06:03:36.900 --> 06:03:39.900
Sundew asked, we still have an entire

06:03:39.900 --> 06:03:42.599
tribe of wasp brains to deal with, right?

06:03:42.659 --> 06:03:44.639
There's no way to shut it down.

06:03:44.700 --> 06:03:47.939
Cricket glanced around as Blue wove his

06:03:47.939 --> 06:03:48.720
tail through hers.

06:03:48.779 --> 06:03:51.959
There might be, he said.

06:03:52.080 --> 06:03:54.360
Ask your parents for more time.

06:03:54.479 --> 06:03:56.159
Maybe we can find out more.

06:03:56.220 --> 06:03:59.159
They are really not going to like that

06:03:59.159 --> 06:04:00.479
Sundew said.

06:04:00.599 --> 06:04:03.360
Our dragons want vengeance, Hivewing.

06:04:03.419 --> 06:04:06.000
The last time I saw my parents, they

06:04:06.000 --> 06:04:07.680
barely listened to my report at all.

06:04:07.740 --> 06:04:12.180
But nobody wants another war, do they?

06:04:12.240 --> 06:04:15.540
Cricket brushed rain and tears off her

06:04:15.540 --> 06:04:15.900
face.

06:04:15.959 --> 06:04:18.779
Don't they remember how terrible the tree

06:04:18.779 --> 06:04:19.500
wars were?

06:04:19.560 --> 06:04:23.400
Of course they do, said Sundew.

06:04:23.459 --> 06:04:25.439
That's exactly why they're doing this.

06:04:25.500 --> 06:04:27.599
The hive wings started it.

06:04:27.659 --> 06:04:29.700
The leaf wings are going to end it.

06:04:29.759 --> 06:04:34.619
It must be awful, Blue said, thinking

06:04:34.619 --> 06:04:36.720
that war is the only solution.

06:04:36.779 --> 06:04:40.080
He lifted the egg gently out of cricket's

06:04:40.080 --> 06:04:41.880
talons and dried it with his cape.

06:04:41.939 --> 06:04:44.400
Isn't there something we can do?

06:04:44.459 --> 06:04:45.900
Cricket said again.

06:04:45.959 --> 06:04:47.639
There must be something.

06:04:47.759 --> 06:04:50.220
We know Queen Wasp's secrets now.

06:04:50.279 --> 06:04:53.459
If we tell everyone, if dragons knew the

06:04:53.459 --> 06:04:57.720
truth, They still couldn't stop her, Sundu

06:04:57.720 --> 06:04:58.020
said.

06:04:58.080 --> 06:04:59.819
She controls them completely.

06:04:59.880 --> 06:05:03.180
Not the silk wings, Tao said.

06:05:03.240 --> 06:05:05.700
This information could make a big

06:05:05.700 --> 06:05:08.279
difference to the chrysalis, and Lady

06:05:08.279 --> 06:05:08.880
Jewel.

06:05:08.939 --> 06:05:13.380
You should tell them then, Sandu said, but

06:05:13.380 --> 06:05:14.939
I don't think my parents will care.

06:05:15.000 --> 06:05:17.279
Would they listen to us?

06:05:17.400 --> 06:05:18.779
Blue asked.

06:05:18.840 --> 06:05:20.880
Could we try talking to them?

06:05:21.000 --> 06:05:24.419
What if, what if I offered to give them

06:05:24.419 --> 06:05:27.000
some of my flame silk in exchange for

06:05:27.000 --> 06:05:27.360
more time?

06:05:27.419 --> 06:05:28.799
Cricket?

06:05:28.860 --> 06:05:30.720
Maybe we could negotiate with them.

06:05:30.779 --> 06:05:33.540
You don't have to do that.

06:05:33.599 --> 06:05:36.959
Cricket said, taking one of his talons

06:05:36.959 --> 06:05:38.880
and brushing her claws over the glowing

06:05:38.880 --> 06:05:39.240
scales.

06:05:39.299 --> 06:05:41.400
I would though.

06:05:41.459 --> 06:05:42.419
Blue said.

06:05:42.479 --> 06:05:44.639
I want to stop this war too.

06:05:44.700 --> 06:05:46.020
Sundo.

06:05:46.139 --> 06:05:47.459
Can we please try?

06:05:47.580 --> 06:05:50.880
The leaf wings spread her gold dappled

06:05:50.880 --> 06:05:52.259
green wings and sighed.

06:05:52.319 --> 06:05:55.080
We can try, she said.

06:05:55.139 --> 06:05:56.759
I'll take you to them.

06:05:56.880 --> 06:05:58.380
They're waiting for me right now.

06:05:58.439 --> 06:06:02.099
Can we also ask them to leave Jewel Hive

06:06:02.099 --> 06:06:02.580
out of it?

06:06:02.639 --> 06:06:03.779
Cricket asked.

06:06:03.840 --> 06:06:05.819
For as long as possible anyway?

06:06:05.880 --> 06:06:09.180
Lady Jewel would be on your side if you

06:06:09.180 --> 06:06:10.319
don't hurt her dragons.

06:06:10.380 --> 06:06:12.540
I really think she would.

06:06:12.599 --> 06:06:15.119
I agree, Tao said.

06:06:15.180 --> 06:06:20.459
We'll ask, Sundoo said, looking torn, but

06:06:20.459 --> 06:06:23.279
Tao, if you can find a reason to get all

06:06:23.279 --> 06:06:25.560
the silkwing dragonettes out of the hive

06:06:25.560 --> 06:06:28.259
to somewhere safe, that might be a good

06:06:28.259 --> 06:06:29.939
idea is all I can say.

06:06:30.000 --> 06:06:32.340
She looked up at the ceiling.

06:06:32.400 --> 06:06:34.860
Sore tail, we're leaving.

06:06:34.919 --> 06:06:37.799
Sortell hopped down to the ground and

06:06:37.799 --> 06:06:39.060
gave Cricket a nudge.

06:06:39.119 --> 06:06:42.060
Glad you're all right, he said gruffly.

06:06:42.119 --> 06:06:45.299
Cricket told Tao everything she'd seen

06:06:45.299 --> 06:06:47.220
inside the nest while her friends

06:06:47.220 --> 06:06:48.060
gathered their things.

06:06:48.180 --> 06:06:51.540
Tao pressed her talons together, looking

06:06:51.540 --> 06:06:52.020
worried.

06:06:52.080 --> 06:06:55.619
Are you sure that dragonette won't have

06:06:55.619 --> 06:06:56.880
the queen in its head too?

06:06:56.939 --> 06:06:59.400
She asked. nodding at the egg.

06:06:59.459 --> 06:07:01.560
That's what I want to find out.

06:07:01.619 --> 06:07:02.819
Cricket said.

06:07:02.880 --> 06:07:05.159
Seems like a risky experiment.

06:07:05.220 --> 06:07:08.759
I am a scientist, Cricket said.

06:07:08.880 --> 06:07:10.979
Sometimes risks are necessary.

06:07:11.040 --> 06:07:14.759
She'd said those words many times in her

06:07:14.759 --> 06:07:17.220
life, although they had never gotten her

06:07:17.220 --> 06:07:19.200
out of any of the trouble her experiment

06:07:19.200 --> 06:07:21.419
had gotten her into, but it felt

06:07:21.419 --> 06:07:24.180
different now, real and serious.

06:07:24.240 --> 06:07:27.419
She wrung out her scarves and wrapped up

06:07:27.419 --> 06:07:29.880
the egg again, tying it to her even more

06:07:29.880 --> 06:07:30.360
securely.

06:07:30.419 --> 06:07:33.360
She guessed they'd be flying all night in

06:07:33.360 --> 06:07:35.580
a thunderstorm, and she wanted to keep it

06:07:35.580 --> 06:07:36.540
warm and safe.

06:07:36.540 --> 06:07:40.259
The truth was, the dragonette in the egg

06:07:40.259 --> 06:07:41.700
wasn't just an experiment.

06:07:41.759 --> 06:07:44.220
It was someone who could be free of the

06:07:44.220 --> 06:07:44.939
hive mind.

06:07:45.000 --> 06:07:47.939
The 1st dragon she could save from Queen

06:07:47.939 --> 06:07:48.779
Wasp.

06:07:48.840 --> 06:07:51.419
Hopefully, the 1st of many.

06:07:51.479 --> 06:07:55.020
If this works, if we get away from here

06:07:55.020 --> 06:07:56.099
without being caught.

06:07:56.220 --> 06:07:59.099
If we make it to the leaf wings, and

06:07:59.099 --> 06:08:01.560
convince them to give us more time, and

06:08:01.560 --> 06:08:03.659
find a way to stop the mind control.

06:08:03.900 --> 06:08:05.939
If nothing went wrong.

06:08:06.000 --> 06:08:08.880
This dragonette might have a chance at a

06:08:08.880 --> 06:08:12.000
better life, and all the tribes might

06:08:12.000 --> 06:08:13.020
have a chance at peace.

06:08:13.139 --> 06:08:17.759
Chapter 21.

06:08:17.939 --> 06:08:21.840
Cricket woke up the next morning into a

06:08:21.840 --> 06:08:23.279
feeling of lingering dread.

06:08:23.340 --> 06:08:26.040
She had dreamed about losing the orphan

06:08:26.040 --> 06:08:29.340
egg, about Queen Wasp, stabbing her in

06:08:29.340 --> 06:08:31.439
the heart with her mind control poison

06:08:31.439 --> 06:08:35.279
about sundew, opening her palms, and

06:08:35.279 --> 06:08:37.319
unleashing an army of swarming black

06:08:37.319 --> 06:08:40.259
insects that covered Pantala from coast

06:08:40.259 --> 06:08:40.740
to coast.

06:08:40.799 --> 06:08:44.220
She opened her eyes, and found herself

06:08:44.220 --> 06:08:45.779
curled tight around the egg.

06:08:45.779 --> 06:08:49.500
Cool scales rested against her back, and

06:08:49.500 --> 06:08:51.479
when she peeked over her shoulder, she

06:08:51.479 --> 06:08:54.299
found Blue asleep with one wing tented

06:08:54.299 --> 06:08:54.720
over hers.

06:08:54.779 --> 06:08:57.900
Sundew had brought them to a peninsula

06:08:57.900 --> 06:09:00.959
northeast of Jewel Hive, to a cave at the

06:09:00.959 --> 06:09:03.180
bottom of the seaside cliffs, but when

06:09:03.180 --> 06:09:05.520
they arrived late the night before, there

06:09:05.520 --> 06:09:07.619
was no sign of Belladonna or hemlock.

06:09:07.680 --> 06:09:10.020
It had still been raining when they crept

06:09:10.020 --> 06:09:12.299
into the shallow nook and curled up on

06:09:12.299 --> 06:09:14.639
the damp rocks, but sometime in the night

06:09:14.639 --> 06:09:15.959
the rain must have stopped.

06:09:16.020 --> 06:09:18.000
There was no more thunder.

06:09:18.060 --> 06:09:21.180
The howling wind had finally dozed off.

06:09:21.299 --> 06:09:24.540
She could see the waters of Dragonfly Bay

06:09:24.540 --> 06:09:27.599
outside, leaden and gray, like the clouds

06:09:27.599 --> 06:09:28.380
above them.

06:09:28.439 --> 06:09:30.959
Carefully, Cricket slid herself up to

06:09:30.959 --> 06:09:32.520
sitting and checked the egg.

06:09:32.580 --> 06:09:35.759
There was a crack along the top of the

06:09:35.759 --> 06:09:36.180
shell.

06:09:36.240 --> 06:09:39.180
Her heart stopped, and she touched it

06:09:39.180 --> 06:09:41.580
gently with one claw, then held the egg

06:09:41.580 --> 06:09:42.360
up to listen to it.

06:09:42.419 --> 06:09:45.060
Is the dragonnet all right?

06:09:45.119 --> 06:09:46.979
Did I crack the egg?

06:09:47.040 --> 06:09:50.880
As soon as she lifted it, a brisk tapping

06:09:50.880 --> 06:09:52.500
sound came from inside the shell

06:09:52.560 --> 06:09:54.840
something poked to the crack from the

06:09:54.840 --> 06:09:55.319
other side.

06:09:55.380 --> 06:09:57.659
Is it hatching?

06:09:57.779 --> 06:10:00.599
Cricket knew she shouldn't be quite so

06:10:00.599 --> 06:10:01.080
alarmed.

06:10:01.139 --> 06:10:04.200
Hatching was, in fact, what eggs did.

06:10:04.259 --> 06:10:06.720
This one had to hatch at some point.

06:10:06.779 --> 06:10:09.240
But she'd really thought she'd have a few

06:10:09.240 --> 06:10:10.200
more days first.

06:10:10.259 --> 06:10:13.020
How could she possibly have grabbed an

06:10:13.020 --> 06:10:14.759
egg that close to hatching?

06:10:14.819 --> 06:10:17.459
The queen had originally planned to visit

06:10:17.459 --> 06:10:18.479
3 days later.

06:10:18.540 --> 06:10:21.360
Surely she timed her visit to catch all

06:10:21.360 --> 06:10:23.159
the eggs before their hatching times.

06:10:23.279 --> 06:10:27.240
No, Cricket said firmly to the egg.

06:10:27.299 --> 06:10:29.939
It is not time to hatch yet.

06:10:30.000 --> 06:10:33.479
The tapping paused, and then picked up

06:10:33.479 --> 06:10:33.779
speed.

06:10:33.900 --> 06:10:38.040
Stop that, Cricket said. are you doing?

06:10:38.099 --> 06:10:39.659
You're not ready to hatch.

06:10:39.720 --> 06:10:40.919
You can't come out?

06:10:40.979 --> 06:10:44.340
She put one talon over the crack, covering

06:10:44.340 --> 06:10:44.580
it up.

06:10:44.639 --> 06:10:47.819
The dragonette inside jabbed her palm

06:10:47.819 --> 06:10:49.020
with one of its claws.

06:10:49.080 --> 06:10:51.659
Stay, cricket ordered.

06:10:51.720 --> 06:10:53.400
Stay in there.

06:10:53.520 --> 06:10:57.900
That sounds like it's going well, Sundew

06:10:57.900 --> 06:11:00.240
commented from across the cave. opening

06:11:00.240 --> 06:11:02.159
one bleary eye to glare at her.

06:11:02.220 --> 06:11:05.279
It cannot possibly be time for this egg

06:11:05.279 --> 06:11:06.959
to hatch, Cricket said.

06:11:07.020 --> 06:11:10.500
I think it disagrees with you, Sandu

06:11:10.500 --> 06:11:11.040
observed.

06:11:11.099 --> 06:11:14.459
Blue sat up, yawning, and looked over

06:11:14.459 --> 06:11:15.720
Cricket's shoulder.

06:11:15.900 --> 06:11:18.240
Maybe it thinks it's time to hatch

06:11:18.240 --> 06:11:20.040
because it's not in the nest anymore.

06:11:20.099 --> 06:11:23.459
Oh, my stars, cricket said.

06:11:23.580 --> 06:11:24.900
Is that a thing?

06:11:24.959 --> 06:11:26.159
A real thing?

06:11:26.220 --> 06:11:28.740
Can it really tell it's not in the nest?

06:11:28.799 --> 06:11:32.639
Well, the light is different, and the

06:11:32.639 --> 06:11:34.619
noise is outside the shell, and it's

06:11:34.619 --> 06:11:35.759
being moved around a lot more.

06:11:35.819 --> 06:11:39.299
So, maybe, Blue Guest.

06:11:39.360 --> 06:11:41.759
I thought you were the one who knew

06:11:41.759 --> 06:11:42.479
things.

06:11:42.540 --> 06:11:43.919
Sundew said to Cricket.

06:11:43.979 --> 06:11:47.279
Not about eggs and dragonettes and

06:11:47.279 --> 06:11:48.900
hatching, Cricket said.

06:11:48.959 --> 06:11:50.580
I've never studied those.

06:11:50.639 --> 06:11:53.639
I know about seeds, and dirt, and plants

06:11:53.639 --> 06:11:55.979
and oh, no, blue.

06:11:56.040 --> 06:11:59.220
You might be right, are eggs like seeds?

06:11:59.340 --> 06:12:01.139
Like, if you put them in the right

06:12:01.139 --> 06:12:02.580
conditions, they grow.

06:12:02.700 --> 06:12:06.299
He spread his wings with an, I have no

06:12:06.299 --> 06:12:07.799
idea expression.

06:12:07.860 --> 06:12:11.520
Baby, Cricket said to the egg.

06:12:11.580 --> 06:12:14.819
Small dragon, this would be a very silly

06:12:14.819 --> 06:12:16.439
place and time to hatch.

06:12:16.500 --> 06:12:17.639
Do not do it.

06:12:17.700 --> 06:12:20.880
A claw poked straight through the crack

06:12:20.880 --> 06:12:22.319
and wiggled gleefully at her.

06:12:22.380 --> 06:12:25.080
Cricket gave Sun to a helpless look.

06:12:25.139 --> 06:12:27.840
This was your brilliant idea.

06:12:27.900 --> 06:12:30.180
Sundew said, don't look at me.

06:12:30.240 --> 06:12:32.099
I don't want anything to do with any

06:12:32.099 --> 06:12:35.040
dragonettes, especially a hive wing

06:12:35.040 --> 06:12:35.700
dragonette.

06:12:35.759 --> 06:12:37.500
She jumped to her feet.

06:12:37.560 --> 06:12:39.779
I'll go get us something to eat.

06:12:39.900 --> 06:12:41.880
Yes, that's what I should do.

06:12:41.939 --> 06:12:45.419
She hurried out of the cave, casting the

06:12:45.419 --> 06:12:47.159
egg a suspicious look as she went by.

06:12:47.220 --> 06:12:51.180
It's going to be very confused, Blue

06:12:51.180 --> 06:12:51.540
said.

06:12:51.659 --> 06:12:52.680
Don't you think?

06:12:52.740 --> 06:12:54.360
Or maybe not.

06:12:54.419 --> 06:12:56.939
I guess it probably doesn't have any

06:12:56.939 --> 06:12:59.159
expectations about what hatching will be

06:12:59.159 --> 06:12:59.580
like.

06:12:59.639 --> 06:13:01.500
I wonder if it's scared.

06:13:01.619 --> 06:13:04.500
The egg was rocking merrily back and

06:13:04.500 --> 06:13:06.959
forth, emitting tiny squeaks.

06:13:07.319 --> 06:13:10.500
Somehow, I think not, Cricket said.

06:13:10.619 --> 06:13:13.319
More cracks spidered out from the 1st

06:13:13.319 --> 06:13:13.619
one.

06:13:13.680 --> 06:13:16.439
Delighted with its success, the

06:13:16.439 --> 06:13:18.599
dragonette kicked harder, finally sending

06:13:18.599 --> 06:13:21.299
a fragment of eggshell flying off to whap

06:13:21.299 --> 06:13:22.619
into Cricket's nose.

06:13:22.680 --> 06:13:24.360
I'm serious.

06:13:24.419 --> 06:13:27.360
Cricket yelped at it, stop hatching right

06:13:27.360 --> 06:13:27.540
now.

06:13:27.659 --> 06:13:30.659
The eggshell cracked in half in her

06:13:30.659 --> 06:13:31.200
talons.

06:13:31.259 --> 06:13:34.380
The pieces fell away, leaving a small

06:13:34.380 --> 06:13:36.360
black and yellow dragonette sitting

06:13:36.360 --> 06:13:39.240
between her claws, happily shaking bits

06:13:39.240 --> 06:13:41.040
of eggshell and goop off her wings.

06:13:41.099 --> 06:13:43.139
Whoa.

06:13:43.259 --> 06:13:46.080
Blue leaned closer and blinked at it.

06:13:46.200 --> 06:13:49.740
Oh no, said Cricket.

06:13:49.799 --> 06:13:53.759
Yim declared the dragonette. accidentally

06:13:53.759 --> 06:13:55.139
whacking blue in the snout with her

06:13:55.139 --> 06:13:55.380
tail.

06:13:55.500 --> 06:13:59.880
Aw, Swordtail said from across the cave.

06:13:59.939 --> 06:14:01.680
Look how cute she is.

06:14:01.740 --> 06:14:03.599
Ripped?

06:14:03.659 --> 06:14:04.799
the dragonette agreed.

06:14:04.860 --> 06:14:07.080
She seized one of Cricket's claws and

06:14:07.080 --> 06:14:08.700
started chewing on it.

06:14:08.759 --> 06:14:11.819
No, thank you, ow, Cricket said.

06:14:11.880 --> 06:14:14.099
Tugging her off and lifting her up so

06:14:14.099 --> 06:14:15.060
they were eye to eye.

06:14:15.119 --> 06:14:17.099
Ow!

06:14:17.159 --> 06:14:20.099
The dragonette mimicked solemnly.

06:14:20.279 --> 06:14:21.000
Ow.

06:14:21.060 --> 06:14:23.759
She reached for Cricket's ear with a

06:14:23.759 --> 06:14:24.599
hungry expression.

06:14:24.659 --> 06:14:26.700
She is cute.

06:14:26.819 --> 06:14:28.740
Blue said, smiling.

06:14:28.860 --> 06:14:33.360
She is trying to eat me, Cricket pointed

06:14:33.360 --> 06:14:33.599
out.

06:14:33.659 --> 06:14:34.860
Sundo.

06:14:34.919 --> 06:14:36.180
I know you can hear me.

06:14:36.240 --> 06:14:37.439
Did you find any food?

06:14:37.500 --> 06:14:40.380
Sundu poked her head into the cave.

06:14:40.439 --> 06:14:43.439
I perhaps should have mentioned this

06:14:43.439 --> 06:14:46.680
sooner, she said, but I rather intensely

06:14:46.680 --> 06:14:48.180
dislike small dragonettes.

06:14:48.240 --> 06:14:52.020
Gorb, the dragonette said sternly.

06:14:52.080 --> 06:14:53.220
Ow.

06:14:53.279 --> 06:14:57.840
Here, Sundu said, tossing a fish across

06:14:57.840 --> 06:15:00.299
the cave to cricket, Blue jumped forward

06:15:00.299 --> 06:15:01.139
and caught it for her.

06:15:01.200 --> 06:15:03.779
But don't you dare let it think food

06:15:03.779 --> 06:15:04.439
comes from me.

06:15:04.500 --> 06:15:07.860
Cricket gave the fish to the dragonette

06:15:07.860 --> 06:15:10.439
and set her down in a small hollow in the

06:15:10.439 --> 06:15:10.740
rocks.

06:15:10.799 --> 06:15:13.740
The baby stuck the fish in her mouth

06:15:13.740 --> 06:15:16.139
chewed vigorously for a moment, and then

06:15:16.139 --> 06:15:17.819
keeled over and fell asleep.

06:15:17.880 --> 06:15:22.139
So cute, Swordtail said again. inching

06:15:22.139 --> 06:15:23.340
closer to grin at her.

06:15:23.400 --> 06:15:26.520
She needs a name, Blue said.

06:15:26.580 --> 06:15:30.000
They all looked down at her black scales

06:15:30.000 --> 06:15:33.180
striped with wide, fuzzy swaths of bright

06:15:33.180 --> 06:15:33.419
yellow.

06:15:33.540 --> 06:15:36.779
She looks kind of like a bumblebee.

06:15:36.840 --> 06:15:37.919
Cricket said.

06:15:37.979 --> 06:15:41.099
Bumblebee, swordtail echoed.

06:15:41.159 --> 06:15:41.819
I like that.

06:15:41.939 --> 06:15:43.560
Me too.

06:15:43.619 --> 06:15:44.880
Blue agreed.

06:15:44.939 --> 06:15:47.279
I have no opinion.

06:15:47.340 --> 06:15:49.979
Sundu offered, from her spot halfway out

06:15:49.979 --> 06:15:50.340
the door.

06:15:50.400 --> 06:15:53.639
Come peek at her, Swartell said.

06:15:53.700 --> 06:15:55.080
It's safe while she's sleeping.

06:15:55.200 --> 06:16:00.000
Not interested, Sundew said firmly.

06:16:00.060 --> 06:16:02.700
Cricket leaned down and picked up the 2

06:16:02.700 --> 06:16:03.959
halves of the eggshell.

06:16:04.020 --> 06:16:06.540
The dragonette seemed normal, as far as

06:16:06.540 --> 06:16:09.419
she could tell, if perhaps a little noisy

06:16:09.419 --> 06:16:12.900
and hyper, and ravenous, although she

06:16:12.900 --> 06:16:14.400
really had no idea what a normal

06:16:14.400 --> 06:16:15.659
dragonette should be like.

06:16:15.779 --> 06:16:19.259
Bumblebee hadn't gone wide eyed in the 20

06:16:19.259 --> 06:16:20.880
heartbeats she'd been awake anyhow.

06:16:20.939 --> 06:16:23.459
Cricket wasn't quite sure what the next

06:16:23.459 --> 06:16:24.959
step of this experiment was.

06:16:25.020 --> 06:16:28.619
Wait until Queen Wasp did look out of her

06:16:28.619 --> 06:16:28.979
eyes?

06:16:29.040 --> 06:16:31.799
If that happened, what would they do with

06:16:31.799 --> 06:16:32.639
Bumblebee?

06:16:32.700 --> 06:16:34.139
Abandon her somewhere?

06:16:34.200 --> 06:16:36.720
I won't ever do that.

06:16:36.779 --> 06:16:39.180
But it's not going to happen.

06:16:39.240 --> 06:16:41.279
She was only injected once.

06:16:41.340 --> 06:16:43.200
Like me, probably.

06:16:43.259 --> 06:16:44.639
She'll be free.

06:16:44.700 --> 06:16:48.180
Something caught her attention, and she

06:16:48.180 --> 06:16:50.099
squinted at the eggshells for a moment.

06:16:50.159 --> 06:16:52.380
Blue, she said.

06:16:52.439 --> 06:16:53.880
Do you see this?

06:16:53.939 --> 06:16:55.860
He leaned over and looked.

06:16:55.919 --> 06:16:59.400
That's the inside of Bumblebee's shell.

06:16:59.459 --> 06:17:02.700
It looks kind of greenish.

06:17:02.759 --> 06:17:04.680
Let me see.

06:17:04.799 --> 06:17:08.279
Sundew crossed the cave, and Cricket held

06:17:08.279 --> 06:17:09.540
the shells up to the light.

06:17:09.599 --> 06:17:12.419
There was definitely some kind of green

06:17:12.419 --> 06:17:14.819
residue, dusting the inside of the

06:17:14.819 --> 06:17:15.240
shells.

06:17:15.360 --> 06:17:18.959
Sundew took one shell and poked the green

06:17:18.959 --> 06:17:20.880
part, but it didn't brush off.

06:17:20.939 --> 06:17:24.540
It looked like a thin green crust, almost

06:17:24.540 --> 06:17:25.680
baked onto the shell.

06:17:25.740 --> 06:17:28.979
She found at it for a moment, then lifted

06:17:28.979 --> 06:17:30.360
it to her snout and sniffed it.

06:17:30.479 --> 06:17:33.900
Yuck, Swordell declared.

06:17:33.959 --> 06:17:37.680
I know this smell, Sundoo said.

06:17:37.740 --> 06:17:40.200
She stared out at the bay for a moment

06:17:40.200 --> 06:17:41.700
then sniffed it again.

06:17:41.759 --> 06:17:44.880
Cricket sniffed the one she was holding.

06:17:44.939 --> 06:17:48.840
It had a dark, leaf rot scent with

06:17:48.840 --> 06:17:51.000
something unpleasantly peppery lurking

06:17:51.000 --> 06:17:51.540
inside it.

06:17:51.659 --> 06:17:53.939
There was something a little familiar

06:17:53.939 --> 06:17:55.680
about it, but nothing she could

06:17:55.680 --> 06:17:56.099
identify.

06:17:56.159 --> 06:18:00.060
I spent 4 days surrounded by this smell

06:18:00.060 --> 06:18:01.259
Sundew said.

06:18:01.319 --> 06:18:02.580
What?

06:18:02.639 --> 06:18:04.619
Cricket said, startled.

06:18:04.680 --> 06:18:05.639
Where?

06:18:05.759 --> 06:18:09.299
It comes from a plant, sundew said.

06:18:09.360 --> 06:18:12.659
And Queen Wasp's private greenhouse is

06:18:12.659 --> 06:18:13.259
full of it.

06:18:13.319 --> 06:18:17.880
Chapter 22.

06:18:18.180 --> 06:18:20.639
Cricket gasped.

06:18:20.700 --> 06:18:24.419
The greenhouse where we met you, where we

06:18:24.419 --> 06:18:27.000
captured you, Sundu corrected her.

06:18:27.060 --> 06:18:30.659
The one that says, Queen Wasp's top

06:18:30.659 --> 06:18:33.360
secret greenhouse, keep out, or I will

06:18:33.360 --> 06:18:34.979
dismember you, and then kill you some

06:18:34.979 --> 06:18:35.220
more.

06:18:35.340 --> 06:18:36.540
Blue asked.

06:18:36.599 --> 06:18:39.180
That's the one, Sundew said.

06:18:39.240 --> 06:18:41.159
There were other plans in it too.

06:18:41.220 --> 06:18:42.419
But that's the main one.

06:18:42.479 --> 06:18:45.900
It's everywhere in there, and it smells

06:18:45.900 --> 06:18:46.560
terrible.

06:18:46.619 --> 06:18:48.360
Send you.

06:18:48.479 --> 06:18:50.340
Is that what she's using?

06:18:50.400 --> 06:18:51.720
Cricket asked.

06:18:51.779 --> 06:18:54.119
Could a plant give her mind control

06:18:54.119 --> 06:18:54.779
powers?

06:18:54.840 --> 06:18:58.020
Maybe for instance, if she ate a lot of

06:18:58.020 --> 06:18:59.880
it, and then injected it into her

06:18:59.880 --> 06:19:00.599
victims?

06:19:00.659 --> 06:19:03.540
I don't know, Sundew snapped.

06:19:03.599 --> 06:19:06.299
I've never heard of a plant like that, but

06:19:06.299 --> 06:19:08.159
I'd call this a clue, don't you think?

06:19:08.220 --> 06:19:10.380
She waved the eggshell at them.

06:19:10.439 --> 06:19:15.240
Blue said, wrinkling his snout at the

06:19:15.240 --> 06:19:15.959
green stuff.

06:19:16.020 --> 06:19:18.599
I wonder if it tastes as bad as it

06:19:18.599 --> 06:19:19.080
smells.

06:19:19.200 --> 06:19:22.740
I certainly hope so, Swartell said.

06:19:22.799 --> 06:19:25.380
I hope she has to eat hive loads of it.

06:19:25.439 --> 06:19:27.840
This could be the way to save the

06:19:27.840 --> 06:19:30.419
dragonettes, Cricket said, meeting

06:19:30.419 --> 06:19:31.500
sundew's eyes.

06:19:31.560 --> 06:19:32.459
Right?

06:19:32.520 --> 06:19:34.860
Couldn't we destroy her supply?

06:19:34.919 --> 06:19:37.500
And then she won't be able to eat it, or

06:19:37.500 --> 06:19:38.939
inject it into them.

06:19:39.000 --> 06:19:42.299
Or do it to any grown up dragons, like

06:19:42.299 --> 06:19:43.439
Lady Jewel either.

06:19:43.500 --> 06:19:46.799
Like you, Blue said.

06:19:46.860 --> 06:19:49.080
He sat up with an alert expression.

06:19:49.139 --> 06:19:51.240
Then you'd be safe from her.

06:19:51.299 --> 06:19:52.560
Let's do it.

06:19:52.619 --> 06:19:56.400
You had me at Destroy, Sword Tell

06:19:56.400 --> 06:19:56.819
offered.

06:19:56.880 --> 06:20:00.720
I'm up for it, Sundu said, spreading her

06:20:00.720 --> 06:20:02.700
wings, but it's not that easy.

06:20:02.759 --> 06:20:06.299
Wasp Hive is swarming with soldiers since

06:20:06.299 --> 06:20:08.459
we stole the Book of Clearsight and broke

06:20:08.459 --> 06:20:10.139
into the flame silk cavern.

06:20:10.200 --> 06:20:12.180
There are guards patrolling the

06:20:12.180 --> 06:20:13.500
greenhouses all the time.

06:20:13.560 --> 06:20:15.959
Queen Wasp is in their heads more than

06:20:15.959 --> 06:20:17.700
half the day, keeping watch.

06:20:17.759 --> 06:20:20.340
I don't see how we'll get anywhere near

06:20:20.340 --> 06:20:21.299
it without getting caught.

06:20:21.360 --> 06:20:24.000
They sat in silence for a moment.

06:20:24.060 --> 06:20:26.459
Cricket's mind was spinning through

06:20:26.459 --> 06:20:27.180
possibilities.

06:20:27.240 --> 06:20:30.240
If this was the answer, if they could

06:20:30.240 --> 06:20:33.119
take the queen's power away, it was a

06:20:33.119 --> 06:20:35.880
start, at least, it might not stop the

06:20:35.880 --> 06:20:38.580
leaf wing's plans for war, but it would

06:20:38.580 --> 06:20:40.799
give the next generation a chance against

06:20:40.799 --> 06:20:44.279
Queen Wasp, if they survived that war.

06:20:44.340 --> 06:20:47.639
We'll tell my parents, Sundew said.

06:20:47.759 --> 06:20:49.979
Belladonna will know what to do with this

06:20:49.979 --> 06:20:50.520
information.

06:20:50.580 --> 06:20:53.279
Maybe they can take a pot of leaf wings

06:20:53.279 --> 06:20:54.299
to attack the greenhouse.

06:20:54.419 --> 06:20:56.099
Oh, what?

06:20:56.159 --> 06:20:57.060
Cricket asked.

06:20:57.180 --> 06:21:01.740
A pod, Sundu repeated, like a small group

06:21:01.740 --> 06:21:03.360
part of the warrior force.

06:21:03.479 --> 06:21:06.659
Are you part of the warrior force?

06:21:06.720 --> 06:21:08.040
SwordTell asked.

06:21:08.099 --> 06:21:10.619
Sundew made one of her inscrutable

06:21:10.619 --> 06:21:11.159
faces.

06:21:11.220 --> 06:21:12.659
Sort of.

06:21:12.720 --> 06:21:15.299
I'm kind of my own pod.

06:21:15.360 --> 06:21:17.459
Where are your parents?

06:21:17.520 --> 06:21:18.659
Cricket asked.

06:21:18.720 --> 06:21:19.860
Why aren't they here?

06:21:19.919 --> 06:21:22.619
She glanced over to make sure that

06:21:22.619 --> 06:21:24.959
Bumblebee was still sleeping and saw that

06:21:24.959 --> 06:21:27.479
she'd flopped over on her back, with the

06:21:27.479 --> 06:21:29.040
fish still hanging out of her mouth.

06:21:29.099 --> 06:21:32.099
Tiny snores emitted from her snout.

06:21:32.220 --> 06:21:34.139
I don't know.

06:21:34.200 --> 06:21:34.919
They should be.

06:21:35.040 --> 06:21:38.279
Sundew went back to the mouth of the cave

06:21:38.279 --> 06:21:39.419
looking out at the bay.

06:21:39.479 --> 06:21:42.779
I hope nothing went wrong, she said

06:21:42.779 --> 06:21:43.319
quietly.

06:21:43.439 --> 06:21:46.619
Um, what's that?

06:21:46.740 --> 06:21:49.740
Blue asked, pointing south across the

06:21:49.740 --> 06:21:49.979
water.

06:21:50.040 --> 06:21:52.500
Cricket joined them on the edge of the

06:21:52.500 --> 06:21:54.540
rocks, followed by SwordTail.

06:21:54.599 --> 06:21:57.659
All 4 dragons squinted out into the gray

06:21:57.659 --> 06:21:58.020
morning.

06:21:58.080 --> 06:22:01.500
A column of black smoke rose into the sky

06:22:01.500 --> 06:22:02.819
on the southern horizon.

06:22:02.939 --> 06:22:05.220
Her heart pounding.

06:22:05.279 --> 06:22:07.200
Cricket turned to sundew.

06:22:07.259 --> 06:22:08.639
What is that?

06:22:08.639 --> 06:22:09.479
she asked.

06:22:09.540 --> 06:22:11.819
Did the leaf wings do that?

06:22:11.939 --> 06:22:15.659
I don't know, Sundew said.

06:22:15.720 --> 06:22:18.119
And for once her frown looked worried

06:22:18.119 --> 06:22:18.900
instead of angry.

06:22:18.959 --> 06:22:22.619
They didn't tell me they, I mean, they

06:22:22.619 --> 06:22:24.060
weren't supposed to.

06:22:24.119 --> 06:22:26.639
Cricket threw open her wings and flew to

06:22:26.639 --> 06:22:28.619
the top of the cliff, high above the

06:22:28.619 --> 06:22:28.919
sea.

06:22:28.979 --> 06:22:31.979
From here, on a clear day, you could

06:22:31.979 --> 06:22:33.840
almost see to the far end of the

06:22:33.840 --> 06:22:34.259
continent.

06:22:34.319 --> 06:22:38.099
This was not a clear day, but she could

06:22:38.099 --> 06:22:40.200
still see the spire of wasp hive to the

06:22:40.200 --> 06:22:43.259
west and jewel hive in the southwest.

06:22:43.319 --> 06:22:45.479
The column of smoke came from beyond

06:22:45.479 --> 06:22:47.700
Jewel Hive, farther south.

06:22:47.759 --> 06:22:52.080
It's not Jewel Hive, Sundew said, landing

06:22:52.080 --> 06:22:52.619
beside her.

06:22:52.680 --> 06:22:55.680
Bloodworm hive, cricket said.

06:22:55.799 --> 06:22:57.360
Yes.

06:22:57.479 --> 06:23:00.900
The leaf wing stared out at the smoke, as

06:23:00.900 --> 06:23:02.459
though it was something she'd ordered at

06:23:02.459 --> 06:23:04.619
a cafe, but it had come in the wrong

06:23:04.619 --> 06:23:06.659
color, and covered with maggots.

06:23:06.779 --> 06:23:09.119
They went ahead and did it.

06:23:09.180 --> 06:23:11.159
Without waiting for me.

06:23:11.220 --> 06:23:14.279
She blew out a long exhale.

06:23:14.340 --> 06:23:17.819
All those dragonettes, Cricket said

06:23:17.819 --> 06:23:20.159
feeling as if her roots had been sliced

06:23:20.159 --> 06:23:20.459
off.

06:23:20.520 --> 06:23:24.299
The eggs in their nest, the silk wings

06:23:24.299 --> 06:23:25.259
who can't fly.

06:23:25.319 --> 06:23:27.060
She closed her eyes.

06:23:27.180 --> 06:23:29.520
Could I have saved them?

06:23:29.580 --> 06:23:33.180
If I'd been faster and smarter and found

06:23:33.180 --> 06:23:34.139
the answers sooner?

06:23:34.200 --> 06:23:37.500
They said they would wait for my report.

06:23:37.560 --> 06:23:40.439
But I guess they were lying about that.

06:23:40.500 --> 06:23:44.400
Sundu looked sincerely angry in a

06:23:44.400 --> 06:23:45.900
different way than usual, Cricket

06:23:45.900 --> 06:23:46.259
thought.

06:23:46.319 --> 06:23:49.080
Maybe they didn't care what I was doing.

06:23:49.139 --> 06:23:52.560
Maybe they were just planting their seeds

06:23:52.560 --> 06:23:55.259
for the last 6 days, moving all the

06:23:55.259 --> 06:23:56.340
pieces into place.

06:23:56.400 --> 06:23:58.619
Did you know all the pieces?

06:23:58.680 --> 06:24:00.900
Cricket asked numbly.

06:24:00.959 --> 06:24:02.880
Did you know what they were planning?

06:24:02.939 --> 06:24:04.979
Sundew hesitated.

06:24:05.099 --> 06:24:06.720
I knew most of it.

06:24:06.779 --> 06:24:10.080
This plan was in motion before we met you

06:24:10.080 --> 06:24:13.319
but I thought, I really thought they'd

06:24:13.319 --> 06:24:13.799
wait for me.

06:24:13.860 --> 06:24:16.979
She ducked her head to look sideways at

06:24:16.979 --> 06:24:17.400
cricket.

06:24:17.520 --> 06:24:19.860
One thing changed, though.

06:24:19.919 --> 06:24:22.560
Because of you three, we learned about

06:24:22.560 --> 06:24:23.400
the chrysalis.

06:24:23.459 --> 06:24:25.799
I wouldn't have believed they existed

06:24:25.799 --> 06:24:26.939
before.

06:24:27.000 --> 06:24:29.880
I mean, that Silk Wings could even think

06:24:29.880 --> 06:24:30.840
about fighting back.

06:24:30.900 --> 06:24:34.680
We found bloodworm hives chrysalis, and

06:24:34.680 --> 06:24:36.779
gave them a message to evacuate their

06:24:36.779 --> 06:24:39.060
dragonettes from the hive, and to stay

06:24:39.060 --> 06:24:40.200
out of the webs last night.

06:24:40.259 --> 06:24:42.479
Cricket shot her look.

06:24:42.540 --> 06:24:45.540
I'm sure that didn't arouse suspicion at

06:24:45.540 --> 06:24:45.779
all.

06:24:45.840 --> 06:24:48.419
You'd be surprised how little attention

06:24:48.419 --> 06:24:50.700
your tribe pays to what silk wings do

06:24:50.700 --> 06:24:52.500
Sundew said pointedly.

06:24:52.560 --> 06:24:55.080
They were silent for another moment.

06:24:55.139 --> 06:24:58.259
I'm sure they'll get the eggs out too

06:24:58.259 --> 06:24:59.819
Sundew offered.

06:24:59.880 --> 06:25:02.159
Shifting uncomfortably on her talons.

06:25:02.220 --> 06:25:05.040
Once they realize they can't save the

06:25:05.040 --> 06:25:05.520
hive.

06:25:05.580 --> 06:25:07.919
That's the 1st thing the hive wings will

06:25:07.919 --> 06:25:08.099
do.

06:25:08.159 --> 06:25:11.279
I hope you're right, Cricket said.

06:25:11.340 --> 06:25:13.979
I hope someone remembers the silk wings

06:25:13.979 --> 06:25:14.939
in their cocoons too.

06:25:15.000 --> 06:25:18.299
Something swooped across the sky to her

06:25:18.299 --> 06:25:20.700
right, and Sundew tugged her down

06:25:20.700 --> 06:25:23.279
throwing her wing over Cricket's back, so

06:25:23.279 --> 06:25:25.380
they were both flat to the earth, and

06:25:25.380 --> 06:25:27.599
partly camouflaged by sundew's green

06:25:27.599 --> 06:25:28.319
scales.

06:25:28.380 --> 06:25:31.740
Hive wings were swarming toward bloodworm

06:25:31.740 --> 06:25:35.159
hive, 100s of them rising from wasp hive

06:25:35.159 --> 06:25:37.500
and jewel hive, and somewhere farther

06:25:37.500 --> 06:25:40.020
north, Yellow Jacket hive, cricket

06:25:40.020 --> 06:25:40.560
guest.

06:25:40.619 --> 06:25:43.560
They flew like a cloud of bats across the

06:25:43.560 --> 06:25:45.840
sky, south to the burning city.

06:25:45.900 --> 06:25:49.319
Queen Wasp was sending her hive mind to

06:25:49.319 --> 06:25:50.040
try to save it.

06:25:50.099 --> 06:25:53.099
Cricket clutched Sundu's arm.

06:25:53.159 --> 06:25:55.799
Right now, she said.

06:25:55.860 --> 06:25:57.479
Right now what?

06:25:57.540 --> 06:26:00.540
Now is the time to burn her greenhouse.

06:26:00.659 --> 06:26:03.000
Cricket pointed at the dragons

06:26:03.000 --> 06:26:04.259
disappearing into the distance.

06:26:04.319 --> 06:26:07.200
Everyone's flying to bloodworm hive.

06:26:07.259 --> 06:26:09.000
It's the perfect distraction.

06:26:09.060 --> 06:26:13.500
It's not a distraction, Sandu objected.

06:26:13.560 --> 06:26:15.180
It's a blow for justice.

06:26:15.299 --> 06:26:18.779
Well, we can use it as a distraction

06:26:18.779 --> 06:26:21.599
Cricket said, to do something that might

06:26:21.599 --> 06:26:23.520
actually help dragons instead of hurting

06:26:23.520 --> 06:26:26.099
anyone if we go right now.

06:26:26.159 --> 06:26:30.240
My parents, Sundew said, glancing at the

06:26:30.240 --> 06:26:30.659
smoke again.

06:26:30.720 --> 06:26:32.819
I'm supposed to wait for them.

06:26:32.880 --> 06:26:35.400
I'm not authorized for another mission.

06:26:35.520 --> 06:26:37.500
Seriously?

06:26:37.560 --> 06:26:40.080
Cricket arched her eyebrows at the leaf

06:26:40.080 --> 06:26:40.500
wing.

06:26:40.560 --> 06:26:43.560
You need to wait for permission?

06:26:43.619 --> 06:26:45.180
You?

06:26:45.299 --> 06:26:48.000
No, Sundew barked.

06:26:48.060 --> 06:26:49.919
I'm just wondering where they are, that's

06:26:49.919 --> 06:26:50.099
all.

06:26:50.159 --> 06:26:51.479
I don't need them.

06:26:51.540 --> 06:26:53.459
Let's go kill some plants.

06:26:53.580 --> 06:26:55.139
Oof.

06:26:55.200 --> 06:26:57.000
No, I don't like the sound of that at

06:26:57.000 --> 06:26:57.180
all.

06:26:57.240 --> 06:27:00.000
Let's go destroy some hive wing stuff.

06:27:00.060 --> 06:27:01.380
That's much better.

06:27:01.439 --> 06:27:04.740
Bumblebee did not wake up as Cricket

06:27:04.740 --> 06:27:06.840
wrapped her in her scarf sling and tucked

06:27:06.840 --> 06:27:07.680
her into her chest.

06:27:07.740 --> 06:27:11.279
She snorted and gruffled, and stuck sharp

06:27:11.279 --> 06:27:13.740
little claws into her, but Cricket poked

06:27:13.740 --> 06:27:15.540
the fish back into her mouth, and

06:27:15.540 --> 06:27:16.860
bumblebee dozed off again.

06:27:16.919 --> 06:27:20.040
They flew along the south coast of the

06:27:20.040 --> 06:27:22.500
peninsula, staying below the level of the

06:27:22.500 --> 06:27:24.180
cliffs to avoid being spotted.

06:27:24.240 --> 06:27:27.060
Cricket noticed that Swordell couldn't

06:27:27.060 --> 06:27:27.959
keep his eyes off the bay.

06:27:28.020 --> 06:27:30.720
He kept turning to search the beach below

06:27:30.720 --> 06:27:31.259
them.

06:27:31.319 --> 06:27:34.020
The 5th time he crashed into sundew by

06:27:34.020 --> 06:27:36.060
accident, she nearly threw him into the

06:27:36.060 --> 06:27:36.299
ocean.

06:27:36.419 --> 06:27:40.200
She glanced at Blue, and saw him turning

06:27:40.200 --> 06:27:41.459
to look out at the islands too.

06:27:41.520 --> 06:27:45.840
Oh, she realized, they're looking for

06:27:45.840 --> 06:27:46.439
Luna.

06:27:46.500 --> 06:27:48.119
I hope she's all right.

06:27:48.180 --> 06:27:50.759
I hope her flame silk is helping to keep

06:27:50.759 --> 06:27:51.119
her safe.

06:27:51.180 --> 06:27:54.419
There were no more hive wings in the sky

06:27:54.419 --> 06:27:56.520
when they reached the grassland on the

06:27:56.520 --> 06:27:58.139
outskirts of wasp hives.

06:27:58.200 --> 06:28:00.840
They landed and slipped into the shadow

06:28:00.840 --> 06:28:02.159
of one of the greenhouses.

06:28:02.220 --> 06:28:04.860
Cricket could still see the smoke in the

06:28:04.860 --> 06:28:05.340
distance.

06:28:05.400 --> 06:28:08.040
Now, with small figures wheeling around

06:28:08.040 --> 06:28:08.279
it.

06:28:08.340 --> 06:28:12.479
If bloodworm high falls, Blue said

06:28:12.479 --> 06:28:13.919
leaning against her side.

06:28:13.979 --> 06:28:17.819
So do the webs between it and Mantis Hive

06:28:17.819 --> 06:28:18.659
and Jewel Hive.

06:28:18.720 --> 06:28:21.299
That's a lot of silkwing homes.

06:28:21.360 --> 06:28:24.779
Sundew hunched her shoulders and dug her

06:28:24.779 --> 06:28:25.619
claws into the ground.

06:28:25.680 --> 06:28:27.900
I'll go scout ahead.

06:28:27.959 --> 06:28:30.540
She hurried off between the glass walls.

06:28:30.659 --> 06:28:35.099
It's weird, Blue said, watching her go.

06:28:35.159 --> 06:28:38.639
The posters always said, the leaf wings

06:28:38.639 --> 06:28:40.080
were going to do something terrible to

06:28:40.080 --> 06:28:43.619
the hives, and I always believed it, until

06:28:43.619 --> 06:28:44.639
we met Sundew.

06:28:44.700 --> 06:28:47.099
And then the more I knew her.

06:28:47.159 --> 06:28:50.159
I guess I started thinking the leaf wings

06:28:50.159 --> 06:28:51.060
would all be like her.

06:28:51.119 --> 06:28:54.360
Mad on the outside, but kind on the

06:28:54.360 --> 06:28:55.740
inside, right?

06:28:55.799 --> 06:28:59.220
Like, of course, she could blow up the

06:28:59.220 --> 06:29:01.560
whole hive, and maybe she'd even want to

06:29:01.560 --> 06:29:03.540
but she wouldn't actually do it.

06:29:03.599 --> 06:29:06.119
So I thought none of them would actually

06:29:06.119 --> 06:29:06.599
do it.

06:29:06.659 --> 06:29:08.520
But now they have.

06:29:08.580 --> 06:29:11.700
So with Queen Wasp right and I was

06:29:11.700 --> 06:29:11.939
wrong.

06:29:12.000 --> 06:29:14.099
I don't know what to think.

06:29:14.159 --> 06:29:17.279
I think you're still right, Cricket

06:29:17.279 --> 06:29:17.639
said.

06:29:17.700 --> 06:29:20.700
I mean, that Sundew wouldn't have done it

06:29:20.700 --> 06:29:21.119
herself.

06:29:21.180 --> 06:29:23.580
And I hope there are other leaf wings

06:29:23.580 --> 06:29:24.000
like her.

06:29:24.060 --> 06:29:28.139
She looked south again at the smoke that

06:29:28.139 --> 06:29:29.939
seemed to be painted onto the clouds

06:29:29.939 --> 06:29:30.599
forever now.

06:29:30.659 --> 06:29:33.840
Did this mean the hive wings and leaf

06:29:33.840 --> 06:29:34.860
wings were at war again?

06:29:34.919 --> 06:29:37.200
It felt so clear to her that they

06:29:37.200 --> 06:29:37.740
shouldn't be.

06:29:37.740 --> 06:29:41.340
They all had one enemy, the same enemy.

06:29:41.400 --> 06:29:42.840
Queen Wasp.

06:29:42.900 --> 06:29:45.659
If only she could get them to see that.

06:29:45.720 --> 06:29:48.240
But she was just one little dragon.

06:29:48.299 --> 06:29:50.520
How could she get anyone to listen to

06:29:50.520 --> 06:29:50.700
her?

06:29:50.819 --> 06:29:53.880
Sundu appeared around a corner of a

06:29:53.880 --> 06:29:55.380
greenhouse and beckoned to them.

06:29:55.439 --> 06:29:58.799
They hurried to her on silent talons

06:29:58.799 --> 06:29:59.700
through the wet grass.

06:29:59.819 --> 06:30:03.599
Just 2 guards patrolling the greenhouses

06:30:03.599 --> 06:30:06.540
as far as I can see, she said in a low

06:30:06.540 --> 06:30:09.720
voice, hard to tell from a distance, but

06:30:09.720 --> 06:30:10.979
they seem to have their own eyes.

06:30:11.040 --> 06:30:13.979
If we keep quiet, I think we can sneak

06:30:13.979 --> 06:30:14.520
past them.

06:30:14.580 --> 06:30:19.020
Florable, announced Bumblebee, popping

06:30:19.020 --> 06:30:20.880
her head out of the sling around cricket

06:30:20.880 --> 06:30:23.040
Sundew gave her a steely look.

06:30:23.159 --> 06:30:26.520
Don't even think about it, Dragonette.

06:30:26.580 --> 06:30:28.500
Blean Mark!

06:30:28.619 --> 06:30:31.680
Bumblebee retorted at top volume.

06:30:31.740 --> 06:30:34.259
She squirmed around in the sling, pulled

06:30:34.259 --> 06:30:36.659
out the fish, which had not improved in

06:30:36.659 --> 06:30:39.000
smell over the course of the morning, and

06:30:39.000 --> 06:30:40.560
flung it at sundew's head.

06:30:40.619 --> 06:30:45.299
I beg your pardon, Sundu said, catching

06:30:45.299 --> 06:30:47.340
the fish and waving it at bumblebee.

06:30:47.400 --> 06:30:50.340
This was a perfectly good breakfast, and

06:30:50.340 --> 06:30:52.080
at your own fault you're hungry if you

06:30:52.080 --> 06:30:52.740
don't want to eat it.

06:30:52.799 --> 06:30:57.599
It's mebo, smebo, smebo, bumblebee said

06:30:57.599 --> 06:30:59.939
in the same tone, wagging her claw at

06:30:59.939 --> 06:31:00.479
sundew.

06:31:00.540 --> 06:31:04.139
Listen here, Sundew said with a scowl.

06:31:04.200 --> 06:31:07.380
We are on a stealth horticultural mission

06:31:07.380 --> 06:31:10.259
and you are going to be absolutely silent

06:31:10.259 --> 06:31:11.459
until we are done.

06:31:11.520 --> 06:31:12.840
Do you understand?

06:31:12.900 --> 06:31:15.720
Looble, fooble, gooble.

06:31:15.840 --> 06:31:17.580
Bumblebee burbled.

06:31:17.639 --> 06:31:19.380
Reaching towards sundew with her front

06:31:19.380 --> 06:31:20.040
talons.

06:31:20.099 --> 06:31:22.380
Herkle, turkle, miss you.

06:31:22.500 --> 06:31:25.560
Nope, no, no, sir.

06:31:25.619 --> 06:31:27.659
Cricket, control your tiny monster.

06:31:27.720 --> 06:31:31.979
I think she wants you, Cricket admitted.

06:31:32.040 --> 06:31:34.380
The dragonette was vigorously wiggling

06:31:34.380 --> 06:31:36.419
her way out of the sling, no matter how

06:31:36.419 --> 06:31:37.860
cricket tried to pin her down.

06:31:37.919 --> 06:31:39.779
Well, too bad.

06:31:39.840 --> 06:31:41.580
Sundew snapped.

06:31:41.700 --> 06:31:43.319
Boo bah.

06:31:43.380 --> 06:31:45.720
Bumblebee shouted enthusiastically.

06:31:45.779 --> 06:31:47.159
Shh.

06:31:47.279 --> 06:31:49.740
Swordell tried, flapping his wings at

06:31:49.740 --> 06:31:49.979
her.

06:31:50.040 --> 06:31:53.040
Cricket hadn't realized a dragonette that

06:31:53.040 --> 06:31:54.119
small could laugh already.

06:31:54.180 --> 06:31:57.419
Bumblebee's whole face wrinkled up, and

06:31:57.419 --> 06:31:59.639
she fell back into the sling, giggling

06:31:59.639 --> 06:32:00.419
hysterically.

06:32:00.479 --> 06:32:05.099
So, Sundew said to Cricket, this is

06:32:05.099 --> 06:32:07.139
officially the worst idea you've ever

06:32:07.139 --> 06:32:07.439
had.

06:32:07.500 --> 06:32:10.919
She might be quieter if you take her

06:32:10.919 --> 06:32:12.299
Cricket suggested.

06:32:12.360 --> 06:32:15.479
I'm not sure, Blue said.

06:32:15.540 --> 06:32:17.459
I think she likes it when you yell at

06:32:17.459 --> 06:32:17.700
her.

06:32:17.759 --> 06:32:21.779
Here, Sundew said, digging into one of

06:32:21.779 --> 06:32:23.099
her pouches.

06:32:23.159 --> 06:32:23.700
Give her this.

06:32:23.759 --> 06:32:27.299
I'm not sticking a sleep flower up a baby

06:32:27.299 --> 06:32:29.700
dragonette's nose, cricket said

06:32:29.700 --> 06:32:32.459
protectively, or a centipede, or a

06:32:32.459 --> 06:32:34.619
paralysis dart, or whatever else you have

06:32:34.619 --> 06:32:34.860
in there.

06:32:34.919 --> 06:32:37.680
It's just dried mango.

06:32:37.740 --> 06:32:39.060
Sundew said.

06:32:39.119 --> 06:32:42.659
Even I have yet to use a paralysis toxin

06:32:42.659 --> 06:32:43.740
on a baby dragonette.

06:32:43.799 --> 06:32:46.080
She scowled at Bumblebee.

06:32:46.139 --> 06:32:49.500
The key word there is yet, howler

06:32:49.500 --> 06:32:49.979
monkey.

06:32:50.040 --> 06:32:52.020
Yum, yum, yum.

06:32:52.080 --> 06:32:55.319
Bumblebee agreed cheerfully, snatching

06:32:55.319 --> 06:32:57.779
the mango out of sundew's talons and

06:32:57.779 --> 06:32:58.680
stuffing it in her mouth.

06:32:58.740 --> 06:33:02.819
Her eyes went wide, and she gave Sundew a

06:33:02.819 --> 06:33:03.659
worshipful look.

06:33:03.720 --> 06:33:05.939
Yum.

06:33:06.000 --> 06:33:09.779
What is this feeling of doom that just

06:33:09.779 --> 06:33:10.680
settled on me?

06:33:10.799 --> 06:33:13.080
sundew asked the sky.

06:33:13.139 --> 06:33:15.419
You did have mango.

06:33:15.479 --> 06:33:18.000
Swordtel said to her accusingly.

06:33:18.060 --> 06:33:21.180
Can we please get on with bringing down

06:33:21.180 --> 06:33:22.680
the hive wing queen now?

06:33:22.740 --> 06:33:24.840
Sundu said to Bumblebee.

06:33:24.900 --> 06:33:27.720
The dragonette ignored her, snuggled into

06:33:27.720 --> 06:33:29.639
cricket. and went to work on the mango.

06:33:29.700 --> 06:33:33.659
Sortail and Sundew went first, padding

06:33:33.659 --> 06:33:34.680
swiftly through the aisles.

06:33:34.740 --> 06:33:38.279
Cricket felt a weird shiver of déjà vu

06:33:38.279 --> 06:33:40.200
remembering the last time they were

06:33:40.200 --> 06:33:42.180
sneaking through these same greenhouses

06:33:42.180 --> 06:33:43.740
early in the morning.

06:33:43.799 --> 06:33:46.560
That was before the queen knew cricket

06:33:46.560 --> 06:33:49.200
secret, when cricket still had the option

06:33:49.200 --> 06:33:49.799
of going home.

06:33:49.860 --> 06:33:53.459
That was before I knew her secrets too

06:33:53.459 --> 06:33:55.020
but now I do.

06:33:55.080 --> 06:33:58.080
I have the truth in my talons, and I'm

06:33:58.080 --> 06:33:59.220
going to do something with it.

06:33:59.279 --> 06:34:02.279
The Queen's greenhouse loomed up before

06:34:02.279 --> 06:34:05.939
them. crowded with dark green leaves that

06:34:05.939 --> 06:34:07.380
pressed against the glass windows.

06:34:07.439 --> 06:34:09.900
Cricket couldn't believe they'd been here

06:34:09.900 --> 06:34:12.240
before, standing in the middle of the

06:34:12.240 --> 06:34:14.580
queen's secret and hadn't even realized

06:34:14.580 --> 06:34:14.819
it.

06:34:14.880 --> 06:34:17.580
One guard stood outside the door.

06:34:17.639 --> 06:34:19.860
Idly reading the warning sign.

06:34:19.919 --> 06:34:22.560
His tail flicked back and forth across

06:34:22.560 --> 06:34:24.959
the grass, leaving a silvery trail

06:34:24.959 --> 06:34:26.159
through the wet blades.

06:34:26.220 --> 06:34:28.380
He didn't look very worried about anyone

06:34:28.380 --> 06:34:30.060
coming to do battle with the plants.

06:34:30.119 --> 06:34:33.240
Sunder reached into one of her pouches

06:34:33.299 --> 06:34:35.819
and softly drew out a tiny hollow tube.

06:34:35.880 --> 06:34:38.759
She slipped something sharp into one end

06:34:38.759 --> 06:34:41.819
raised the other to her mouth, and blew

06:34:41.819 --> 06:34:42.720
the dart at the guard.

06:34:42.779 --> 06:34:45.599
His tail went still on the grass.

06:34:45.720 --> 06:34:48.240
His wings stopped mid flutter.

06:34:48.299 --> 06:34:50.459
His whole body was frozen in place.

06:34:50.520 --> 06:34:52.680
Florb.

06:34:52.799 --> 06:34:55.259
Bumblebee said approvingly around the

06:34:55.259 --> 06:34:55.740
mango.

06:34:55.799 --> 06:34:59.580
Drag him away from the greenhouse, sundew

06:34:59.580 --> 06:35:00.840
said to sore tell.

06:35:00.900 --> 06:35:02.639
He doesn't need to go up in flames with

06:35:02.639 --> 06:35:02.819
it.

06:35:02.880 --> 06:35:06.060
Cricket and Blue exchanged glances.

06:35:06.119 --> 06:35:09.240
She's saving a random hive wing.

06:35:09.299 --> 06:35:11.639
She's making sure he doesn't die.

06:35:11.759 --> 06:35:14.520
Cricket didn't think Sundew would have

06:35:14.520 --> 06:35:15.900
done that before she knew them.

06:35:15.959 --> 06:35:18.060
If we could change her mind.

06:35:18.119 --> 06:35:19.979
Maybe we can change others.

06:35:20.040 --> 06:35:23.939
Thortell grappled with a paralyzed dragon

06:35:23.939 --> 06:35:25.860
while the other 3 sliced away the webs

06:35:25.860 --> 06:35:28.020
covering the greenhouse door and stepped

06:35:28.020 --> 06:35:28.319
inside.

06:35:28.380 --> 06:35:31.799
The heat and humidity swamped cricket

06:35:31.799 --> 06:35:32.939
just as it had before.

06:35:33.000 --> 06:35:36.060
And now she recognized the smell too.

06:35:36.119 --> 06:35:39.180
Sharp and unpleasant amid the other

06:35:39.180 --> 06:35:40.500
scents of the plants around them.

06:35:40.560 --> 06:35:45.240
It's this one, Sundew said, lifting a

06:35:45.240 --> 06:35:47.099
leaf on one of the vines that thronged

06:35:47.099 --> 06:35:49.680
the greenhouse, circling and choking the

06:35:49.680 --> 06:35:50.459
other plants.

06:35:50.520 --> 06:35:53.639
The stem of the vine was dark red, with

06:35:53.639 --> 06:35:55.919
veins of bright green, and the leaves

06:35:55.919 --> 06:35:58.680
were the same in reverse, bright green

06:35:58.680 --> 06:36:00.959
with veins of red, like streams of

06:36:00.959 --> 06:36:01.560
blood.

06:36:01.560 --> 06:36:04.740
Each was the size of a dragon talon with

06:36:04.740 --> 06:36:06.060
jagged tough edges.

06:36:06.119 --> 06:36:08.459
It would have been perfectly

06:36:08.459 --> 06:36:10.919
appropriately creepy, if it weren't for

06:36:10.919 --> 06:36:12.659
the clusters of tiny white flowers

06:36:12.659 --> 06:36:14.040
nestled between the leaves.

06:36:14.099 --> 06:36:17.520
Sundew rubbed the leaf between her claws

06:36:17.520 --> 06:36:19.200
for a moment, frowning at it.

06:36:19.259 --> 06:36:22.680
I don't know what it is, she said at

06:36:22.680 --> 06:36:23.040
length.

06:36:23.099 --> 06:36:25.979
Me neither, Cricket offered.

06:36:26.040 --> 06:36:28.259
I don't remember seeing it in any of my

06:36:28.259 --> 06:36:30.180
botany books, and I think I would.

06:36:30.240 --> 06:36:32.939
I know someone who might know.

06:36:33.000 --> 06:36:36.360
Sundew used her claws to slice through

06:36:36.360 --> 06:36:39.119
the vine in 2 spots, making a cutting as

06:36:39.119 --> 06:36:40.020
long as her arm.

06:36:40.439 --> 06:36:42.419
She rolled it into a loose ball, and

06:36:42.419 --> 06:36:43.860
tucked it into an empty pouch.

06:36:43.919 --> 06:36:46.139
Is that a good idea?

06:36:46.259 --> 06:36:47.639
Blue asked.

06:36:47.700 --> 06:36:50.580
Shouldn't we destroy all of it so it can

06:36:50.580 --> 06:36:52.740
never grow again, and no one can ever use

06:36:52.740 --> 06:36:53.520
it like she has.

06:36:53.580 --> 06:36:58.020
I think we need to know what it is, Sundew

06:36:58.020 --> 06:36:58.500
said to him.

06:36:58.560 --> 06:37:02.520
Me too, Cricket agreed, and maybe.

06:37:02.639 --> 06:37:05.700
She hesitated, afraid to say it out

06:37:05.700 --> 06:37:06.000
loud.

06:37:06.060 --> 06:37:08.400
Maybe there's an antidote.

06:37:08.459 --> 06:37:10.200
Sundew finished for her.

06:37:10.259 --> 06:37:12.419
Blue's eyes widened.

06:37:12.540 --> 06:37:17.459
Smorg Bamfibo, Bumblebee declared, in

06:37:17.459 --> 06:37:19.200
Sundoo's solemnest voice.

06:37:19.259 --> 06:37:23.099
I feel like you're mocking me, Sundu said

06:37:23.099 --> 06:37:23.939
to the dragonette.

06:37:24.000 --> 06:37:26.700
Smink smock smackie fee.

06:37:26.759 --> 06:37:29.220
The dragonhead answered with enormous

06:37:29.220 --> 06:37:31.619
gravity, copying sundew's frown.

06:37:31.740 --> 06:37:34.500
Sundew raised one eyebrow at cricket.

06:37:34.560 --> 06:37:37.680
I swear I did not teach her to do that.

06:37:37.740 --> 06:37:39.060
Cricket promised.

06:37:39.119 --> 06:37:43.439
All right, Sundew said, turning to sweep

06:37:43.439 --> 06:37:44.639
the greenhouse with her gaze.

06:37:44.759 --> 06:37:47.279
Who wants to burn it all down?

06:37:47.340 --> 06:37:51.240
There was a pause before she turned and

06:37:51.240 --> 06:37:52.619
leveled her gaze on Blue.

06:37:52.740 --> 06:37:56.700
Oh, right, me, Blue said.

06:37:56.759 --> 06:37:59.040
He stepped to the nearest cluster of

06:37:59.040 --> 06:38:01.319
vines and set his front talons on them.

06:38:01.380 --> 06:38:04.860
Fiery silk erupted from his wrists

06:38:04.860 --> 06:38:06.180
catching and tangling through the

06:38:06.180 --> 06:38:06.599
leaves.

06:38:06.659 --> 06:38:09.659
Everywhere it touched, blades of flame

06:38:09.659 --> 06:38:13.020
flickered, smoked, curled into black ash

06:38:13.020 --> 06:38:15.479
or brightened into orange blossoms of

06:38:15.479 --> 06:38:15.959
fire.

06:38:16.380 --> 06:38:19.500
Heavy, reddish green smoke rose from the

06:38:19.500 --> 06:38:21.900
vines, and Cricket covered her snout with

06:38:21.900 --> 06:38:22.740
one of her scarves.

06:38:22.799 --> 06:38:26.099
Don't breathe it in, she shouted at the

06:38:26.099 --> 06:38:26.400
others.

06:38:26.459 --> 06:38:28.560
She wrapped another scarf around

06:38:28.560 --> 06:38:30.240
bumblebee's indignant face.

06:38:30.299 --> 06:38:32.159
Blue, let's go.

06:38:32.279 --> 06:38:35.400
She tugged on his arm, and turned to run

06:38:35.400 --> 06:38:36.540
to the door with Sundew.

06:38:36.599 --> 06:38:40.139
Blue followed them, pausing every few

06:38:40.139 --> 06:38:42.180
steps to shoot more fountains of flame

06:38:42.180 --> 06:38:43.259
over the vines.

06:38:43.319 --> 06:38:45.599
Cricket could hear the crackling fire

06:38:45.599 --> 06:38:47.220
building and spreading.

06:38:47.279 --> 06:38:50.580
The heat shot past tolerable and pressed

06:38:50.580 --> 06:38:51.360
against her scales.

06:38:51.419 --> 06:38:53.759
And she thought of the dragons and

06:38:53.759 --> 06:38:56.220
bloodworm hive, and wondered if this was

06:38:56.220 --> 06:38:58.319
what they'd felt as they fled their

06:38:58.319 --> 06:38:58.919
burning city.

06:38:58.979 --> 06:39:02.159
They threw open the door, and tumbled

06:39:02.159 --> 06:39:03.479
onto the wet grass outside.

06:39:03.540 --> 06:39:06.599
Blue leaped out after them, and slammed

06:39:06.599 --> 06:39:07.319
the door behind him.

06:39:07.380 --> 06:39:09.900
But it splintered into a 1000000 pieces

06:39:09.900 --> 06:39:10.860
as it hit the frame.

06:39:10.919 --> 06:39:14.580
Glass fragments exploded outward, along

06:39:14.580 --> 06:39:17.400
with tongues of fire, roaring like angry

06:39:17.400 --> 06:39:18.180
dragons.

06:39:18.240 --> 06:39:21.779
Cricket curled her body around bumblebee

06:39:21.779 --> 06:39:24.000
and ran to escape the flames and smoke.

06:39:24.060 --> 06:39:27.119
She nearly collided head on with a 2nd

06:39:27.119 --> 06:39:29.520
hive wing guard, who started to grab her

06:39:29.520 --> 06:39:32.400
and then froze, staring open mouthed at

06:39:32.400 --> 06:39:33.419
the burning greenhouse.

06:39:33.479 --> 06:39:37.380
That one is lost, Cricket said. shaking

06:39:37.380 --> 06:39:37.619
her.

06:39:37.680 --> 06:39:40.860
Get water, and you can save the others.

06:39:40.919 --> 06:39:42.240
Make sure your friend is safe too.

06:39:42.360 --> 06:39:45.779
She turned to look around and saw the

06:39:45.779 --> 06:39:48.060
paralyzed guard lying a few greenhouses

06:39:48.060 --> 06:39:48.540
away.

06:39:48.599 --> 06:39:51.000
Sortail was still trying to drag him a

06:39:51.000 --> 06:39:51.540
little farther.

06:39:51.599 --> 06:39:54.240
The grass was wet enough that cricket

06:39:54.240 --> 06:39:56.040
hoped the fire wouldn't spread.

06:39:56.099 --> 06:39:57.119
But she wasn't sure.

06:39:57.180 --> 06:40:00.060
She didn't want the other greenhouses to

06:40:00.060 --> 06:40:00.240
burn.

06:40:00.299 --> 06:40:02.819
They held the food and other resources

06:40:02.819 --> 06:40:04.259
for 100s of dragons.

06:40:04.319 --> 06:40:06.900
Sundew's parents might have been willing

06:40:06.900 --> 06:40:09.060
to burn them, but she thought sundew

06:40:09.060 --> 06:40:09.419
wouldn't.

06:40:09.540 --> 06:40:12.180
The guard pointed at the greenhouse.

06:40:12.240 --> 06:40:15.419
The queen, she stammered.

06:40:15.479 --> 06:40:17.340
She, that's her.

06:40:17.459 --> 06:40:19.979
Cricket gripped her shoulders to get her

06:40:19.979 --> 06:40:20.340
attention.

06:40:20.400 --> 06:40:23.759
That is where she kept the plant that

06:40:23.759 --> 06:40:25.860
lets her control us, she said.

06:40:25.919 --> 06:40:29.279
I saw her stabbing eggs in the jewel hive

06:40:29.279 --> 06:40:29.700
nest.

06:40:29.759 --> 06:40:32.400
She injects us before we've even

06:40:32.400 --> 06:40:33.060
hatched.

06:40:33.119 --> 06:40:34.380
Do you understand?

06:40:34.439 --> 06:40:37.619
That plant gave her the hive mind power.

06:40:37.740 --> 06:40:40.080
And we burned it to take it away from

06:40:40.080 --> 06:40:40.259
her.

06:40:40.319 --> 06:40:42.299
What?

06:40:42.360 --> 06:40:44.639
The guard shook her head, confused.

06:40:44.700 --> 06:40:48.779
No, the queen, she has that power because

06:40:48.779 --> 06:40:49.979
she's our queen.

06:40:50.040 --> 06:40:53.400
She had it because of a plant, Cricket

06:40:53.400 --> 06:40:53.880
said.

06:40:53.939 --> 06:40:57.659
She's been poisoning us, our whole tribe

06:40:57.659 --> 06:40:59.700
ever since the tree wars, maybe longer.

06:40:59.759 --> 06:41:01.560
You have to tell everyone.

06:41:01.619 --> 06:41:03.779
The guard looked terrified.

06:41:03.840 --> 06:41:05.400
Me?

06:41:05.459 --> 06:41:07.680
Yes, Cricket said.

06:41:07.740 --> 06:41:10.139
Knowing the truth isn't enough if you

06:41:10.139 --> 06:41:13.020
don't share it, everyone needs to know.

06:41:13.080 --> 06:41:17.819
I have to save the greenhouses, the guard

06:41:17.819 --> 06:41:20.040
said, pulling out of cricket's grip.

06:41:20.159 --> 06:41:22.319
She turned and ran toward the hive.

06:41:22.380 --> 06:41:24.720
She will be back with help soon.

06:41:24.840 --> 06:41:27.000
Blue said at Cricket's shoulder.

06:41:27.060 --> 06:41:29.880
Sortell, are you napping?

06:41:29.939 --> 06:41:31.200
Sundew shouted.

06:41:31.259 --> 06:41:32.220
Let's go.

06:41:32.340 --> 06:41:35.159
Sortell leaped away from the guard and

06:41:35.159 --> 06:41:36.060
into the sky.

06:41:36.119 --> 06:41:38.340
The others spread their wings and joined

06:41:38.340 --> 06:41:41.099
him, and Cricket swerved around a plume

06:41:41.099 --> 06:41:43.200
of smoke as it erupted from the

06:41:43.200 --> 06:41:44.040
greenhouse roof.

06:41:44.099 --> 06:41:47.939
They soared away, toward a looming bank

06:41:47.939 --> 06:41:49.380
of dark clouds in the north.

06:41:49.439 --> 06:41:52.319
Cricket beat her wings as hard as she

06:41:52.319 --> 06:41:55.619
could, and glanced down at Bumblebee, who

06:41:55.619 --> 06:41:57.900
had somehow managed to fall asleep again

06:41:57.900 --> 06:41:59.520
despite all the commotion.

06:41:59.580 --> 06:42:03.720
They flew and flew, following sundew

06:42:03.720 --> 06:42:06.779
until Wasp Hive was far behind them.

06:42:06.840 --> 06:42:08.580
There was no sign of any pursuers.

06:42:08.639 --> 06:42:12.000
Cricket hoped that all of Queen Wasp's

06:42:12.000 --> 06:42:14.520
attention was on Bloodworm Hive, and that

06:42:14.520 --> 06:42:16.259
she wouldn't even discover the fire in

06:42:16.259 --> 06:42:18.299
her greenhouse until she returned home.

06:42:18.360 --> 06:42:19.799
Home.

06:42:19.860 --> 06:42:22.259
There's a thing I don't have anymore.

06:42:22.319 --> 06:42:25.020
Send do, she called.

06:42:25.080 --> 06:42:26.279
Where are we going?

06:42:26.340 --> 06:42:28.500
Shouldn't we go back to the cave to find

06:42:28.500 --> 06:42:29.040
your parents?

06:42:29.099 --> 06:42:31.799
Sundew glanced over her shoulder.

06:42:31.919 --> 06:42:35.040
Her green and gold scales somehow still

06:42:35.040 --> 06:42:37.500
shining even in the grayest sky.

06:42:37.560 --> 06:42:40.080
I'm not waiting around for them, she

06:42:40.080 --> 06:42:40.560
called back.

06:42:40.619 --> 06:42:42.479
They'll expect to meet me back home.

06:42:42.540 --> 06:42:44.279
Where's that?

06:42:44.340 --> 06:42:46.740
Cricket asked, catching up to her.

06:42:46.799 --> 06:42:49.200
Are we going to where the other leaf

06:42:49.200 --> 06:42:49.619
wings are?

06:42:49.740 --> 06:42:51.720
Her pulse sped up.

06:42:51.779 --> 06:42:54.540
Despite her worries and her sadness over

06:42:54.540 --> 06:42:55.619
bloodworm hive.

06:42:55.680 --> 06:42:59.040
At last, she was going to find out how

06:42:59.040 --> 06:43:01.500
the leaf wings had survived the tree wars

06:43:01.500 --> 06:43:04.380
and where they'd been hiding all this

06:43:04.380 --> 06:43:04.500
time.

06:43:04.619 --> 06:43:08.400
Has anyone ever told you that you ask a

06:43:08.400 --> 06:43:09.240
lot of questions?

06:43:09.240 --> 06:43:11.159
Sundew said wryly.

06:43:11.220 --> 06:43:14.639
All the time, cricket said, smiling

06:43:14.639 --> 06:43:14.939
back.

06:43:15.000 --> 06:43:18.299
Well, I'm surprised you haven't guessed

06:43:18.299 --> 06:43:19.380
this answer by now.

06:43:19.439 --> 06:43:23.159
Sundew pointed her snout north, closing

06:43:23.159 --> 06:43:25.020
her eyes as a gust of wind and rain

06:43:25.020 --> 06:43:26.459
rippled over their scales.

06:43:26.580 --> 06:43:28.139
That way?

06:43:28.560 --> 06:43:29.099
Cricket said.

06:43:29.159 --> 06:43:31.979
You mean, all the way that way?

06:43:32.099 --> 06:43:35.459
Are you saying the leaf wings are in?

06:43:36.419 --> 06:43:38.939
She trailed off, remembering the stories

06:43:38.939 --> 06:43:41.759
she'd read about carnivorous plants, 10

06:43:41.759 --> 06:43:45.479
times the size of a dragon, of toxins, and

06:43:45.479 --> 06:43:48.959
snakes, and quicksand, and deadly vines

06:43:48.959 --> 06:43:52.020
and venomous wasps, and all the many, many

06:43:52.020 --> 06:43:53.939
ways a dragon could die up there.

06:43:53.939 --> 06:43:58.619
Yes, said sundew, smiling a real smile

06:43:58.619 --> 06:43:58.979
now.

06:43:59.040 --> 06:44:02.759
We're going home to the poison jungle.

06:44:02.819 --> 06:44:07.200
Epilogue.

06:44:07.319 --> 06:44:11.939
I'm not sure this was a good idea, Tsunami

06:44:11.939 --> 06:44:13.500
said to Turtle.

06:44:13.560 --> 06:44:15.419
She wasn't sure why she was whispering.

06:44:15.479 --> 06:44:18.000
They appeared to be alone in the jungle

06:44:18.000 --> 06:44:20.580
and yet it also felt as if there were

06:44:20.580 --> 06:44:22.680
100s of eyes watching their every move.

06:44:22.740 --> 06:44:26.639
The tangled trees seemed to be reaching

06:44:26.639 --> 06:44:30.060
for them, with long trailing roots and

06:44:30.060 --> 06:44:32.939
branches, like skeletal fingers slid into

06:44:32.939 --> 06:44:33.240
the water.

06:44:33.299 --> 06:44:37.200
The sand under them had become oozing mud

06:44:37.200 --> 06:44:39.479
and she couldn't see anything through the

06:44:39.479 --> 06:44:41.880
silt and foggy green haze in the river.

06:44:41.939 --> 06:44:46.439
At least, she'd thought it was a river, a

06:44:46.439 --> 06:44:48.360
river they could follow into the interior

06:44:48.360 --> 06:44:49.080
of the continent.

06:44:49.139 --> 06:44:51.299
But as the banks closed in.

06:44:51.360 --> 06:44:53.580
And the jutting rocks got sharper.

06:44:53.639 --> 06:44:56.220
She was getting the distinct sensation of

06:44:56.220 --> 06:44:58.740
swimming into a very large shark like

06:44:58.740 --> 06:44:59.340
mouth.

06:44:59.340 --> 06:45:03.419
She paused, treading water for a moment

06:45:03.419 --> 06:45:04.259
and turning in a circle.

06:45:04.319 --> 06:45:08.099
Something enormously long and scaly broke

06:45:08.099 --> 06:45:10.680
the surface of the river for a moment, and

06:45:10.680 --> 06:45:12.180
tsunami readied her claws.

06:45:12.240 --> 06:45:14.939
But the snake only lifted its head to

06:45:14.939 --> 06:45:17.580
study them with cold eyes, then rippled

06:45:17.580 --> 06:45:17.819
away.

06:45:17.880 --> 06:45:21.240
Turtle, luckily had not seen it.

06:45:21.299 --> 06:45:23.819
He had found a boulder to clutch

06:45:23.819 --> 06:45:24.479
panting.

06:45:24.540 --> 06:45:27.060
She kept forgetting to set her pace

06:45:27.060 --> 06:45:29.580
slower for him, although she'd been doing

06:45:29.580 --> 06:45:30.360
it for days.

06:45:30.419 --> 06:45:32.819
Somewhere in the middle of the vast

06:45:32.819 --> 06:45:33.299
ocean.

06:45:33.360 --> 06:45:35.639
They'd both had a small panic attack

06:45:35.639 --> 06:45:37.979
wondering if there was really anything

06:45:37.979 --> 06:45:40.979
out there, or whether they'd missed it, or

06:45:40.979 --> 06:45:42.180
whether they were going in the wrong

06:45:42.180 --> 06:45:44.700
direction, and would end up swimming for

06:45:44.700 --> 06:45:47.400
a 1000 years without ever seeing land

06:45:47.400 --> 06:45:47.700
again.

06:45:47.759 --> 06:45:51.240
That was when tsunami had realized why

06:45:51.240 --> 06:45:53.040
Sea Wings had never made this journey

06:45:53.040 --> 06:45:53.400
before.

06:45:53.459 --> 06:45:56.759
They might be creatures of the sea, but

06:45:56.759 --> 06:45:57.779
they needed land too.

06:45:57.840 --> 06:46:01.200
They would not swim for days with no end

06:46:01.200 --> 06:46:03.540
in sight, with no certainty that they

06:46:03.540 --> 06:46:04.860
would ever find anything.

06:46:04.919 --> 06:46:06.659
Let's go back.

06:46:06.720 --> 06:46:08.700
Tsunami said to her brother.

06:46:08.759 --> 06:46:11.939
Let's find another place to land, more

06:46:11.939 --> 06:46:13.259
like what Luna described.

06:46:13.319 --> 06:46:15.659
Yeah, he gasped.

06:46:15.720 --> 06:46:17.880
I thought she said there weren't any

06:46:17.880 --> 06:46:18.180
trees.

06:46:18.299 --> 06:46:22.919
Maybe she meant only terrifying trees

06:46:22.919 --> 06:46:25.740
tsunami said, looking up at the vines

06:46:25.740 --> 06:46:27.900
oozing off the branches overhead.

06:46:27.959 --> 06:46:29.939
Don't move.

06:46:30.000 --> 06:46:33.119
The voice that suddenly spoke from the

06:46:33.119 --> 06:46:36.119
bank had an odd accent, and a note of

06:46:36.119 --> 06:46:37.979
authority that made tsunami freeze

06:46:37.979 --> 06:46:40.200
obediently before her ears had even

06:46:40.200 --> 06:46:41.400
caught up to the instructions.

06:46:41.459 --> 06:46:44.580
Um, turtles started.

06:46:44.639 --> 06:46:48.299
Don't speak either, said the voice.

06:46:48.360 --> 06:46:51.000
One, two.

06:46:51.119 --> 06:46:54.959
A dark green shape hurdled past tsunami's

06:46:54.959 --> 06:46:57.659
head and smashed into the snake as it

06:46:57.659 --> 06:46:59.040
lunged out of the water at them.

06:46:59.099 --> 06:47:02.639
All tsunami could see for a moment, was a

06:47:02.639 --> 06:47:04.799
blur of claws and fangs and scales

06:47:04.799 --> 06:47:06.299
thrashing.

06:47:06.360 --> 06:47:07.860
She had to close her eyes against the

06:47:07.860 --> 06:47:10.139
waves kicked violently into her face.

06:47:10.200 --> 06:47:14.220
Finally, the river went still, and she

06:47:14.220 --> 06:47:15.419
dared to open her eyes again.

06:47:15.540 --> 06:47:19.080
A green dragon with brown eyes hovered

06:47:19.080 --> 06:47:21.779
overhead, clutching the dead snake in her

06:47:21.779 --> 06:47:22.139
talons.

06:47:22.200 --> 06:47:25.319
Her wings were paler green that her body

06:47:25.319 --> 06:47:28.259
and shaped like leaves, and her under

06:47:28.259 --> 06:47:30.779
scales were dappled with dark green leaf

06:47:30.779 --> 06:47:32.459
shapes, like shadows.

06:47:32.520 --> 06:47:35.939
Three moons, Turtle said.

06:47:36.000 --> 06:47:37.020
Thank you.

06:47:37.080 --> 06:47:41.099
Really, really, really, thank you, tsunami

06:47:41.099 --> 06:47:41.580
echoed.

06:47:41.639 --> 06:47:44.580
Almost too bewildered to speak.

06:47:44.700 --> 06:47:46.799
What kind of dragons are you?

06:47:46.860 --> 06:47:49.740
The stranger asked, flinging the snake

06:47:49.740 --> 06:47:50.459
back into the river.

06:47:50.520 --> 06:47:54.540
We are sea wings, tsunami answered, trying

06:47:54.540 --> 06:47:56.279
to recover her equilibrium.

06:47:56.340 --> 06:47:58.680
I'm tsunami, and this is turtle.

06:47:58.740 --> 06:48:00.659
We're from the other side of the ocean.

06:48:00.720 --> 06:48:03.959
I'm Willow, said the green dragon.

06:48:04.020 --> 06:48:06.540
And if you want to live, you should turn

06:48:06.540 --> 06:48:08.279
around and go back there right now.

06:48:08.340 --> 06:48:12.720
Moon found Luna sitting on the farthest

06:48:12.720 --> 06:48:15.180
edge of the beach again, staring out

06:48:15.180 --> 06:48:17.759
toward Pantala, with the ocean whispering

06:48:17.759 --> 06:48:18.840
over her claws.

06:48:19.319 --> 06:48:21.240
Luna twisted toward the little black

06:48:21.240 --> 06:48:23.520
dragon as she approached, and was

06:48:23.520 --> 06:48:25.319
startled by the grim look on Moon's

06:48:25.319 --> 06:48:25.500
face.

06:48:25.560 --> 06:48:28.680
She'd started to think Moon only ever

06:48:28.680 --> 06:48:31.619
looked either perfectly serene or mildly

06:48:31.619 --> 06:48:32.040
concerned.

06:48:32.099 --> 06:48:34.619
What is it?

06:48:34.680 --> 06:48:35.220
Luna asked.

06:48:35.340 --> 06:48:36.299
A vision?

06:48:36.360 --> 06:48:37.619
Yes.

06:48:37.680 --> 06:48:40.799
Moon said, her gaze shifting toward the

06:48:40.799 --> 06:48:41.279
horizon.

06:48:41.340 --> 06:48:42.840
A vision.

06:48:42.900 --> 06:48:46.259
Cities burning, dragons hurting one

06:48:46.259 --> 06:48:46.500
another.

06:48:46.560 --> 06:48:49.380
More dragons being terrible just because

06:48:49.380 --> 06:48:51.180
other dragons are different from them.

06:48:51.240 --> 06:48:53.939
Just like all my visions.

06:48:54.060 --> 06:48:56.819
She stopped for a moment and rubbed her

06:48:56.819 --> 06:48:57.180
forehead.

06:48:57.240 --> 06:48:59.279
Does that mean we're going there?

06:48:59.340 --> 06:49:01.619
You've thought of a way to get to

06:49:01.619 --> 06:49:02.220
Pantala?

06:49:02.279 --> 06:49:03.959
Moon shook her head.

06:49:04.020 --> 06:49:05.520
No.

06:49:05.580 --> 06:49:08.340
She looked out at Luna's distant home

06:49:08.340 --> 06:49:08.759
again.

06:49:08.819 --> 06:49:11.819
And Luna imagined she could almost see

06:49:11.819 --> 06:49:14.580
the flames and screaming dragons

06:49:14.580 --> 06:49:16.979
reflected in moon's dark green eyes.

06:49:17.099 --> 06:49:20.099
We don't need to, Moon said.

06:49:20.159 --> 06:49:22.139
They're coming to us.

06:49:22.200 --> 06:49:28.619
A guide to the dragons of Pentala.

06:49:28.680 --> 06:49:30.840
Hive wings.

06:49:30.900 --> 06:49:36.119
Description, red, yellow, and or orange

06:49:36.119 --> 06:49:39.180
but always mixed with some black scales, 4

06:49:39.180 --> 06:49:43.080
wings, abilities, vary from dragon to

06:49:43.080 --> 06:49:43.680
dragon.

06:49:43.740 --> 06:49:46.740
Examples include deadly stingers that can

06:49:46.740 --> 06:49:48.959
extend from their wrists to stab their

06:49:48.959 --> 06:49:53.099
enemies, venom in their teeth or claws, a

06:49:53.099 --> 06:49:55.560
paralyzing toxin that can immobilize

06:49:55.560 --> 06:49:55.979
their prey.

06:49:56.040 --> 06:50:00.299
Or boiling acid, sprayed from a stinger

06:50:00.299 --> 06:50:01.020
on their tails.

06:50:01.080 --> 06:50:04.380
Queen, queen wasp.

06:50:04.500 --> 06:50:08.580
Silk wings, description.

06:50:08.639 --> 06:50:11.700
Silkwing dragonettes are born wingless

06:50:11.700 --> 06:50:14.759
but go through a metamorphosis at age 6

06:50:14.759 --> 06:50:18.000
when they develop 4 huge wings and silk

06:50:18.000 --> 06:50:20.520
spinning abilities, as beautiful and

06:50:20.520 --> 06:50:23.639
gentle as butterflies, with scales in any

06:50:23.639 --> 06:50:26.279
color under the sun, except black.

06:50:26.400 --> 06:50:30.840
Abilities, can spin silk from glands on

06:50:30.840 --> 06:50:33.299
their wrists to create webs or other

06:50:33.299 --> 06:50:36.240
woven articles, can detect vibrations

06:50:36.240 --> 06:50:38.159
with their antennae to assess threats.

06:50:38.220 --> 06:50:41.759
Queen, Queen Wasp.

06:50:41.880 --> 06:50:45.299
The last Silkwing Queen, before the tree

06:50:45.299 --> 06:50:47.400
wars, was Queen Monarch.

06:50:47.459 --> 06:50:49.979
Leaf wings.

06:50:50.040 --> 06:50:51.419
Description.

06:50:51.479 --> 06:50:54.180
Wiped out during the tree wars with the

06:50:54.180 --> 06:50:56.939
hive wings, but while they lived, this

06:50:56.939 --> 06:50:59.220
tribe had green and brown scales, and

06:50:59.220 --> 06:51:00.840
wings shaped like leaves.

06:51:00.900 --> 06:51:04.619
Abilities, could absorb energy from

06:51:04.619 --> 06:51:06.419
sunlight and were accomplished

06:51:06.419 --> 06:51:07.020
gardeners.

06:51:07.080 --> 06:51:10.560
Some were rumored to have unusual control

06:51:10.560 --> 06:51:11.880
over plants.

06:51:11.939 --> 06:51:13.380
Queen.

06:51:13.439 --> 06:51:16.560
Last known queen of the leaf wings was

06:51:16.560 --> 06:51:20.459
Queen Sequoia, about 50 years ago, at the

06:51:20.459 --> 06:51:21.599
time of the tree wars.

06:51:39.720 --> 06:51:46.619
This is Shannon McManus.

